VALUES
  (22213, 28, 8, 10, 'Yea, though they have hired among the nations, now will I gather them, and they shall sorrow a little for the burden of the king of princes.', '4~08566~ 7~01471~, 11~06908~ 16~02490~ 18~04592~ 21~04853~ 24~04428~ 26~08269~.'),
  (26614, 43, 12, 19, 'The Pharisees therefore said among themselves, Perceive ye how ye prevail nothing? behold, the world is gone after him.', '1~5330~ 2~3767~ 3~2036~ 4~4314~ 5~1438~, 7~2334~ 8~3754~ 10~5623~ 11~3762~ 12~3756?~* 13~2396~, 15~2889~ 17~565~ 18~3694~ 19~846~.'),
  (507, 1, 20, 8, 'Therefore Abimelech rose early in the morning, and called all his servants, and told all these things in their ears: and the men were sore afraid.', '&para; 1~040~ 3~07925~ 6~01242~, 8~07121~ 11~05650~, 13~01696~ 16~01697~ 19~0241~: 22~0582~ 24~03966~ 25~03372~.'),
  (10520, 13, 6, 58, 'And Hilen with her suburbs, Debir with her suburbs,', '1~02432~ 4~04054~, 5~01688~ 8~04054~,'),
  (23358, 40, 8, 3, 'And Jesus put forth his hand, and touched him, saying, I will; be thou clean. And immediately his leprosy was cleansed.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 3~1614~ [4] 5~5495~, 7~680~ 8~846~, 9~3004~, 11~2309~; 14~2511~. 15~2532~ 16~2112~ 17~846~ 18~3014~ 20~2511~.'),
  (11313, 14, 6, 23, 'Then hear thou from heaven, and do, and judge thy servants, by requiting the wicked, by recompensing his way upon his own head; and by justifying the righteous, by giving him according to his righteousness.', '1~08085~ 4~08064~, 6~06213~, 8~08199~ 10~05650~, 12~07725~ 14~07563~, 16~05414~ 18~01870~ 22~07218~; 25~06663~ 27~06662~, 29~05414~ 34~06666~.'),
  (4073, 4, 12, 9, 'And the anger of the LORD was kindled against them; and he departed.', '2~0639~ 5~03068~ 7~02734~ 12~03212~.'),
  (20439, 25, 4, 10, 'The hands of the pitiful women have sodden their own children: they were their meat in the destruction of the daughter of my people.', '1~03027~ 4~07362~ 5~0802~ 7~01310~ 10~03206~: 14~01262~ 17~07667~ 20~01323~ 23~05971~.'),
  (17690, 23, 1, 27, 'Zion shall be redeemed with judgment, and her converts with righteousness.', '0~06726~ 3~06299~ 5~04941~, 8~07725~ 10~06666~.'),
  (26836, 43, 18, 36, 'Jesus answered, My kingdom is not of this world: if my kingdom were of this world, then would my servants fight, that I should not be delivered to the Jews: but now is my kingdom not from hence.', '0~2424~ 1~611~, 2~1699~ 3~932~ 4~2076~ 5~3756~ 6~1537~ 7~5127~ 8~2889~: 9~1487~ 10~1699~ 11~932~ 12~2258~ 13~1537~ 14~5127~ 15~2889~, 17~302~ 18~1699~ 19~5257~ 20~75~, 21~3363~ 23~3860~ 24~3363~ 26~3860~ 29~2453~: 30~1161~ 31~3568~ 32~2076~ 33~1699~ 34~932~ 35~3756~ 37~1782~.'),
  (29004, 47, 10, 17, 'But he that glorieth, let him glory in the Lord.', '0~1161~ 3~2744~, 6~2744~ 7~1722~ 9~2962~.'),
  (8469, 10, 17, 13, 'Moreover, if he be gotten into a city, then shall all Israel bring ropes to that city, and we will draw it into the river, until there be not one small stone found there.', '1~0518~ 4~0622~ 7~05892~, 11~03478~ 12~05375~ 13~02256~ 16~05892~, 20~05498~ 24~05158~, 29~01571~ 31~06872~ 32~04672~'),
  (22247, 28, 10, 13, 'Ye have plowed wickedness, ye have reaped iniquity; ye have eaten the fruit of lies: because thou didst trust in thy way, in the multitude of thy mighty men.', '2~02790~ 3~07562~, 6~07114~ 7~05766~; 10~0398~ 12~06529~ 14~03585~: 18~0982~ 21~01870~, 24~07230~ 28~01368~.'),
  (7113, 7, 21, 4, 'And it came to pass on the morrow, that the people rose early, and built there an altar, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings.', '7~04283~, 10~05971~ 12~07925~, 14~01129~ 17~04196~, 19~05927~ 21~05930~ 24~08002~.'),
  (15246, 19, 82, 4, 'Deliver the poor and needy: rid them out of the hand of the wicked.', '0~06403~ 2~01800~ 4~034~: 5~05337~ [6] 10~03027~ 13~07563~.'),
  (17056, 20, 23, 3, 'Be not desirous of his dainties: for they are deceitful meat.', '2~0183~ 5~04303~: [8] 9~03577~ 10~03899~.'),
  (12339, 16, 3, 3, 'But the fish gate did the sons of Hassenaah build, who also laid the beams thereof, and set up the doors thereof, the locks thereof, and the bars thereof.', '2~01709~ 3~08179~ 6~01121~ 8~05570~ 9~01129~, [11] 14~07136~ 18~05975~ 20~01817~ 23~04514~ 27~01280~'),
  (24568, 41, 9, 19, 'He answereth him, and saith, O faithless generation, how long shall I be with you? how long shall I suffer you? bring him unto me.', '1~611~ 2~846~, 3~1161~ 4~3004~, 5~5599~ 6~571~ 7~1074~, 9~4219~ 10~2193~ 12~2071~ 13~4314~ 14~5209~? 16~4219~ 17~2193~ 19~430~ 20~5216~? 21~5342~ 22~846~ 23~4314~ 24~3165~.'),
  (1838, 2, 12, 17, 'And ye shall observe the feast of unleavened bread; for in this selfsame day have I brought your armies out of the land of Egypt: therefore shall ye observe this day in your generations by an ordinance for ever.', '3~08104~ [4 6] 8~04682~; 12~06106~ 13~03117~ 16~03318~ 18~06635~ 22~0776~ 24~04714~: 28~08104~ 30~03117~ 33~01755~ 36~02708~ 38~05769~.'),
  (18680, 23, 50, 9, 'Behold, the Lord GOD will help me; who is he that shall condemn me? lo, they all shall wax old as a garment; the moth shall eat them up.', '2~0136~ 3~03069~ 5~05826~ [8] [10] 12~07561~ 19~01086~ 22~0899~; 24~06211~ 28~0398~.'),
  (5604, 5, 27, 13, 'And these shall stand upon mount Ebal to curse; Reuben, Gad, and Asher, and Zebulun, Dan, and Naphtali.', '3~05975~ 5~02022~ 6~05858~ 8~07045~; 9~07205~, 10~01410~, 12~0836~, 14~02074~, 15~01835~, 17~05321~.'),
  (6227, 6, 15, 18, 'And it came to pass, as she came unto him, that she moved him to ask of her father a field: and she lighted off her ass; and Caleb said unto her, What wouldest thou?', '7~0935~ [8 9] 12~05496~ 15~07592~ 18~01~ 20~07704~: 24~06795~ [25] 26~02543~; 28~03612~ 29~0559~'),
  (25472, 42, 11, 54, 'Laying wait for him, and seeking to catch something out of his mouth, that they might accuse him.', '2~1748~ 3~846~, 4~2532~ 5~2212~ 7~2340~ 8~5100~ 10~1537~ 11~846~ 12~4750~, 13~2443~ 16~2723~ 17~846~.'),
  (3423, 3, 23, 16, 'Even unto the morrow after the seventh sabbath shall ye number fifty days; and ye shall offer a new meat offering unto the LORD.', '1~05704~ 3~04283~ 6~07637~ 7~07676~ 10~05608~ 11~02572~ 12~03117~; 16~07126~ 18~02319~ 20~04503~ 23~03068~.'),
  (22472, 30, 6, 13, 'Ye which rejoice in a thing of nought, which say, Have we not taken to us horns by our own strength?', '2~08056~ 5~01697~ 7~03808~, 9~0559~, 13~03947~ 16~07161~ 20~02392~?'),
  (9094, 11, 10, 7, 'Howbeit I believed not the words, until I came, and mine eyes had seen it: and, behold, the half was not told me: thy wisdom and prosperity exceedeth the fame which I heard.', '2~0539~ 5~01697~, 8~0935~, 11~05869~ 13~07200~ [14] 18~02677~ 21~05046~ 24~02451~ 26~02896~ 27~03254~ 29~08052~ 32~08085~.'),
  (13757, 18, 36, 12, 'But if they obey not, they shall perish by the sword, and they shall die without knowledge.', '3~08085~ 7~05674~ 10~07973~, 14~01478~ 16~01847~.'),
  (3767, 4, 4, 19, 'But thus do unto them, that they may live, and not die, when they approach unto the most holy things: Aaron and his sons shall go in, and appoint them every one to his service and to his burden:', '2~06213~ 8~02421~, 11~04191~, 14~05066~ 17~06944~ 19~06944~: 20~0175~ 23~01121~ 26~0935~, 28~07760~ 30~0376~ 31~0376~ 34~05656~ 38~04853~:'),
  (8889, 11, 5, 3, 'Thou knowest how that David my father could not build an house unto the name of the LORD his God for the wars which were about him on every side, until the LORD put them under the soles of his feet.', '1~03045~ 4~01732~ 6~01~ 7~03201~ 9~01129~ 11~01004~ 14~08034~ 17~03068~ 19~0430~ 20~06440~ 22~04421~ 29~05437~, 32~03068~ 33~05414~ 37~03709~ 40~07272~.'),
  (7119, 7, 21, 10, 'And the congregation sent thither twelve thousand men of the valiantest, and commanded them, saying, Go and smite the inhabitants of Jabeshgilead with the edge of the sword, with the women and the children.', '2~05712~ 3~07971~ 5~06240~ 6~08147~* 7~0505~ 8~0376~ 11~02428~ 12~01121~,* 14~06680~ 16~0559~, 17~03212~ 19~05221~ 21~03427~ 23~01568~ 24~03003~ 26~06310~ 29~02719~, 32~0802~ 35~02945~.'),
  (6544, 7, 1, 28, 'And it came to pass, when Israel was strong, that they put the Canaanites to tribute, and did not utterly drive them out.', '6~03478~ 8~02388~, 11~07760~ 13~03669~ 15~04522~, 19~03423~ 22~03423~.'),
  (15984, 19, 119, 77, 'Let thy tender mercies come unto me, that I may live: for thy law is my delight.', '3~07356~ 4~0935~ 10~02421~: 13~08451~ [14] 16~08191~.'),
  (24378, 41, 5, 4, 'Because that he had been often bound with fetters and chains, and the chains had been plucked asunder by him, and the fetters broken in pieces: neither could any man tame him.', '0~1223~ 2~846~ 5~4178~ 6~1210~ 8~3976~ 9~2532~ 10~254~, 11~2532~ 13~254~ 17~1288~ 18~5259~ 19~846~, 20~2532~ 22~3976~ 25~4937~: 26~2532~ 27~2480~ [29] 30~1150~ 31~3762~ 32~846~.*'),
  (29249, 49, 2, 4, 'But God, who is rich in mercy, for his great love wherewith he loved us,', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~2316~, 3~5607~ 4~4145~ 5~1722~ 6~1656~, 7~1223~ 8~846~ 9~4183~ 10~26~ 11~3739~ 13~25~ 14~2248~,'),
  (22320, 29, 1, 20, 'The beasts of the field cry also unto thee: for the rivers of waters are dried up, and the fire hath devoured the pastures of the wilderness.', '1~0929~ 4~07704~ 5~06165~ 11~0650~ 13~04325~ 16~03001~, 19~0784~ 21~0398~ 23~04999~ 26~04057~.'),
  (5951, 6, 5, 11, 'And they did eat of the old corn of the land on the morrow after the passover, unleavened cakes, and parched corn in the selfsame day.', '3~0398~ 7~05669~ 10~0776~ 13~04283~ 16~06453~, 18~04682~, 20~07033~ [21] 24~06106~ 25~03117~.'),
  (2972, 3, 9, 14, 'And he did wash the inwards and the legs, and burnt them upon the burnt offering on the altar.', '3~07364~ 5~07130~ 8~03767~, 10~06999~ [11] 15~05930~ 18~04196~.'),
  (18414, 23, 38, 15, 'What shall I say? he hath both spoken unto me, and himself hath done it: I shall go softly all my years in the bitterness of my soul.', '3~01696~? 7~0559~ 13~06213~ [14] 18~01718~ 21~08141~ 24~04751~ 27~05315~.'),
  (13561, 18, 29, 20, 'My glory was fresh in me, and my bow was renewed in my hand.', '1~03519~ [2] 3~02319~ 5~05978~, 8~07198~ 10~02498~ 13~03027~.'),
  (29435, 50, 2, 28, 'I sent him therefore the more carefully, that, when ye see him again, ye may rejoice, and that I may be the less sorrowful.', '1~3992~ 2~846~ 3~3767~ 6~4708~, 7~2443~, 10~1492~ 11~846~ 12~3825~, 15~5463~, 18~2504~ 20~5600~ 23~253~.'),
  (15986, 19, 119, 79, 'Let those that fear thee turn unto me, and those that have known thy testimonies.', '3~03373~ 5~07725~ 12~03045~ 14~05713~.'),
  (20396, 25, 3, 33, 'For he doth not afflict willingly nor grieve the children of men.', '4~06031~ 5~03820~ 7~03013~ 9~01121~ 11~0376~.'),
  (25263, 42, 8, 6, 'And some fell upon a rock; and as soon as it was sprung up, it withered away, because it lacked moisture.', '0~2532~ 1~2087~ 2~4098~ 3~1909~ 5~4073~; 6~2532~ 13~5453~, 16~3583~, 17~1223~ 19~2192~ 20~3361~* 21~2429~.'),
  (17987, 23, 16, 9, 'Therefore I will bewail with the weeping of Jazer the vine of Sibmah: I will water thee with my tears, O Heshbon, and Elealeh: for the shouting for thy summer fruits and for thy harvest is fallen.', '3~01058~ 6~01065~ 8~03270~ 10~01612~ 12~07643~: 15~07301~ 19~01832~, 21~02809~, 23~0500~: 26~01959~ 30~07019~ 34~07105~ 36~05307~.'),
  (18578, 23, 45, 8, 'Drop down, ye heavens, from above, and let the skies pour down righteousness: let the earth open, and let them bring forth salvation, and let righteousness spring up together; I the LORD have created it.', '1~07491~, 3~08064~, 5~04605~, 9~07834~ 11~05140~ 12~06664~: 15~0776~ 16~06605~, 21~06509~ 22~03468~, 25~06666~ 27~06779~ 28~03162~; 31~03068~ 33~01254~'),
  (15089, 19, 75, 9, 'But I will declare for ever; I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.', '3~05046~ 5~05769~; 9~02167~ 12~0430~ 14~03290~.'),
  (20427, 25, 3, 64, 'Render unto them a recompense, O LORD, according to the work of their hands.', '0~07725~ 4~01576~, 6~03068~, 10~04639~ 13~03027~.'),
  (19808, 24, 33, 24, 'Considerest thou not what this people have spoken, saying, The two families which the LORD hath chosen, he hath even cast them off? thus they have despised my people, that they should be no more a nation before them.', '0~07200~ 5~05971~ 7~01696~, 8~0559~, 10~08147~ 11~04940~ 14~03068~ 16~0977~, 22~03988~? 26~05006~ 28~05971~, 36~01471~ 37~06440~'),
  (16416, 20, 1, 7, 'The fear of the LORD is the beginning of knowledge: but fools despise wisdom and instruction.', '&para; 1~03374~ 4~03068~ [5] 7~07225~ 9~01847~: [10] 11~0191~ 12~0936~ 13~02451~ 15~04148~.'),
  (30477, 60, 4, 15, 'But let none of you suffer as a murderer, or as a thief, or as an evildoer, or as a busybody in other men''s matters.', '0~1063~ 1~3958~ 2~5100~ 3~3361~ 4~5216~ 5~3958~ 6~5613~ 8~5406~, 9~2228~ [10] 12~2812~, 13~2228~ [14] 16~2555~, 17~2228~ 18~5613~ 24~244~.'),
  (27032, 44, 3, 20, 'And he shall send Jesus Christ, which before was preached unto you:', '0~2532~ 3~649~ 4~2424~ 5~5547~, 9~4296~ 11~5213~:'),
  (29110, 48, 2, 13, 'And the other Jews dissembled likewise with him; insomuch that Barnabas also was carried away with their dissimulation.', '0~2532~ 2~3062~ 3~2453~ 4~4942~ 5~2532~ 7~846~; 8~5620~ 10~921~ 11~2532~ 14~4879~ 16~846~ 17~5272~.'),
  (7991, 9, 30, 6, 'And David was greatly distressed; for the people spake of stoning him, because the soul of all the people was grieved, every man for his sons and for his daughters: but David encouraged himself in the LORD his God.', '1~01732~ 3~03966~ 4~03334~; 7~05971~ 8~0559~ 10~05619~ 14~05315~ 18~05971~ 20~04843~, 22~0376~ 25~01121~ 29~01323~: 31~01732~ 32~02388~ 36~03068~ 38~0430~.'),
  (6599, 7, 3, 24, 'When he was gone out, his servants came; and when they saw that, behold, the doors of the parlour were locked, they said, Surely he covereth his feet in his summer chamber.', '4~03318~, 6~05650~ 7~0935~; 11~07200~ 15~01817~ 18~05944~ [19] 20~05274~, 22~0559~, 25~05526~ 27~07272~ 30~04747~ 31~02315~.'),
  (21887, 27, 5, 4, 'They drank wine, and praised the gods of gold, and of silver, of brass, of iron, of wood, and of stone.', '1~08355~ 2~02562~, 4~07624~ 6~0426~ 8~01722~, 11~03702~, 13~05174~, 15~06523~, 17~0636~, 20~069~.'),
  (5064, 5, 5, 5, '(I stood between the LORD and you at that time, to shew you the word of the LORD: for ye were afraid by reason of the fire, and went not up into the mount;) saying,', '1~05975~ 4~03068~ 9~06256~, 11~05046~ 14~01697~ 17~03068~: 21~03372~ 23~06440~ 26~0784~, 30~05927~ 33~02022~;) 34~0559~,'),
  (7596, 9, 15, 29, 'And also the Strength of Israel will not lie nor repent: for he is not a man, that he should repent.', '3~05331~ 5~03478~ 8~08266~ 10~05162~: [13] 16~0120~, 20~05162~.'),
  (10255, 12, 25, 25, 'But it came to pass in the seventh month, that Ishmael the son of Nethaniah, the son of Elishama, of the seed royal, came, and ten men with him, and smote Gedaliah, that he died, and the Jews and the Chaldees that were with him at Mizpah.', '7~07637~ 8~02320~, 10~03458~ 12~01121~ 14~05418~, 16~01121~ 18~0476~, 21~02233~ 22~04410~, 23~0935~, 25~06235~ 26~0582~ 30~05221~ 31~01436~, 34~04191~, 37~03064~ 40~03778~ 46~04709~.'),
  (2837, 3, 5, 2, 'Or if a soul touch any unclean thing, whether it be a carcase of an unclean beast, or a carcase of unclean cattle, or the carcase of unclean creeping things, and if it be hidden from him; he also shall be unclean, and guilty.', '3~05315~ 4~05060~ 6~02931~ 7~01697~, [9 10] 12~05038~ 15~02931~ 16~02416~, 19~05038~ 21~02931~ 22~0929~, 25~05038~ 27~02931~ 29~08318~, [31] 34~05956~ 41~02931~, 43~0816~.'),
  (5556, 5, 25, 3, 'Forty stripes he may give him, and not exceed: lest, if he should exceed, and beat him above these with many stripes, then thy brother should seem vile unto thee.', '0~0705~ 1~05221~ [6] 8~03254~: [10] 13~03254~, 15~05221~ 20~07227~ 21~04347~, 24~0251~ 27~07034~ 28~05869~*'),
  (3123, 3, 14, 7, 'And he shall sprinkle upon him that is to be cleansed from the leprosy seven times, and shall pronounce him clean, and shall let the living bird loose into the open field.', '3~05137~ 10~02891~ 13~06883~ 14~07651~ 15~06471~, 20~02891~, 25~02416~ 26~06833~ 27~07971~ 30~06440~ 31~07704~.'),
  (26746, 43, 16, 5, 'But now I go my way to him that sent me; and none of you asketh me, Whither goest thou?', '0~1161~ 1~3568~ 5~5217~ 6~4314~ 9~3992~ 10~3165~; 11~2532~ 12~3762~ 13~1537~ 14~5216~ 15~2065~ 16~3165~, 17~4226~ 19~5217~?'),
  (402, 1, 17, 1, 'And when Abram was ninety years old and nine, the LORD appeared to Abram, and said unto him, I am the Almighty God; walk before me, and be thou perfect.', '&para; 2~087~ 4~08141~ 5~08673~* 6~08141~ 7~01121~ 9~08672~, 11~03068~ 12~07200~ 14~087~, 16~0559~ [20] 22~07706~ 23~0410~; 24~01980~ 26~06440~, 30~08549~.'),
  (25467, 42, 11, 49, 'Therefore also said the wisdom of God, I will send them prophets and apostles, and some of them they shall slay and persecute:', '0~5124~ 1~1223~* 2~2532~ 3~2036~ 5~4678~ 7~2316~, 10~649~ 11~1519~* 12~846~ 13~4396~ 14~2532~ 15~652~, 16~2532~ [17] 18~1537~ 19~846~ 22~615~ 23~2532~ 24~1559~:'),
  (28352, 45, 15, 33, 'Now the God of peace be with you all. Amen.', '0~1161~ 2~2316~ 4~1515~ [5] 6~3326~ 7~5216~ 8~3956~. 9~281~.'),
  (10556, 13, 7, 13, 'The sons of Naphtali; Jahziel, and Guni, and Jezer, and Shallum, the sons of Bilhah.', '1~01121~ 3~05321~; 4~03185~, 6~01476~, 8~03337~, 10~07967~, 12~01121~ 14~01090~.'),
  (3612, 4, 1, 3, 'From twenty years old and upward, all that are able to go forth to war in Israel: thou and Aaron shall number them by their armies.', '1~06242~ 2~08141~ 3~01121~ 5~04605~, 12~03318~ 14~06635~ 16~03478~: 19~0175~ 21~06485~ 25~06635~.'),
  (3690, 4, 2, 27, 'And those that encamp by him shall be the tribe of Asher: and the captain of the children of Asher shall be Pagiel the son of Ocran.', '3~02583~ [6 7] 9~04294~ 11~0836~: 14~05387~ 17~01121~ 19~0836~ [20 21] 22~06295~ 24~01121~ 26~05918~.'),
  (6365, 6, 19, 37, 'And Kedesh, and Edrei, and Enhazor,', '1~06943~, 3~0154~, 5~05877~,'),
  (29940, 56, 3, 1, 'Put them in mind to be subject to principalities and powers, to obey magistrates, to be ready to every good work,', '&para; 0~5279~ 1~846~ 3~5279~ 6~5293~ 8~746~ 9~2532~ 10~1849~, 13~3980~, 15~1511~ 16~2092~ 17~4314~ 18~3956~ 19~18~ 20~2041~,'),
  (16366, 19, 147, 6, 'The LORD lifteth up the meek: he casteth the wicked down to the ground.', '1~03068~ 3~05749~ 5~06035~: 7~08213~ 9~07563~ 10~08213~ 13~0776~.'),
  (20928, 26, 20, 24, 'Because they had not executed my judgments, but had despised my statutes, and had polluted my sabbaths, and their eyes were after their fathers'' idols.', '4~06213~ 6~04941~, 9~03988~ 11~02708~, 14~02490~ 16~07676~, 19~05869~ 21~0310~ 23~01~ 24~01544~.'),
  (4041, 4, 11, 12, 'Have I conceived all this people? have I begotten them, that thou shouldest say unto me, Carry them in thy bosom, as a nursing father beareth the sucking child, unto the land which thou swarest unto their fathers?', '2~02029~ 5~05971~? 8~03205~ 13~0559~ 16~05375~ 20~02436~, 24~0539~ 25~05375~ 28~03243~, 31~0127~ 34~07650~ 37~01~?'),
  (11768, 14, 27, 4, 'Moreover he built cities in the mountains of Judah, and in the forests he built castles and towers.', '2~01129~ 3~05892~ 6~02022~ 8~03063~, 12~02793~ 14~01129~ 15~01003~ 17~04026~.'),
  (16432, 20, 1, 23, 'Turn you at my reproof: behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you, I will make known my words unto you.', '0~07725~ 4~08433~: 9~05042~ 11~07307~ 17~03045~ 19~01697~'),
  (11923, 14, 33, 6, 'And he caused his children to pass through the fire in the valley of the son of Hinnom: also he observed times, and used enchantments, and used witchcraft, and dealt with a familiar spirit, and with wizards: he wrought much evil in the sight of the LORD, to provoke him to anger.', '2~05674~ 4~01121~ 7~05674~ 9~0784~ 12~01516~ 15~01121~ 17~02011~: 21~06049~, 24~05172~, 27~03784~, 29~06213~ 33~0178~, 36~03049~: 38~06213~ 39~07235~ 40~07451~ 43~05869~ 46~03068~, 51~03707~.'),
  (27746, 44, 22, 26, 'When the centurion heard that, he went and told the chief captain, saying, Take heed what thou doest: for this man is a Roman.', '0~1161~ 2~1543~ 3~191~ [4] 6~4334~ 8~518~ 11~5506~, 12~3004~, 14~3708~ 15~5101~ 17~3195~ 18~4160~:* 19~1063~ 20~3778~ 21~444~ 22~2076~ 24~4514~.'),
  (5234, 5, 11, 20, 'And thou shalt write them upon the door posts of thine house, and upon thy gates:', '3~03789~ 8~04201~ 11~01004~, 15~08179~:'),
  (18149, 23, 26, 10, 'Let favour be shewed to the wicked, yet will he not learn righteousness: in the land of uprightness will he deal unjustly, and will not behold the majesty of the LORD.', '3~02603~ 6~07563~, [7] 10~01077~ 11~03925~ 12~06664~: 15~0776~ 17~05229~ 21~05765~, 24~01077~ 25~07200~ 27~01348~ 30~03068~.'),
  (6996, 7, 17, 9, 'And Micah said unto him, Whence comest thou? And he said unto him, I am a Levite of Bethlehemjudah, and I go to sojourn where I may find a place.', '1~04318~ 2~0559~ 5~0370~ 6~0935~ 10~0559~ [14] 16~03881~ 18~03063~ 19~01035~,* 22~01980~ 24~01481~ 28~04672~ [29 30]'),
  (15374, 19, 89, 39, 'Thou hast made void the covenant of thy servant: thou hast profaned his crown by casting it to the ground.', '3~05010~ 5~01285~ 8~05650~: 11~02490~ 13~05145~ [14 16] 19~0776~.'),
  (18380, 23, 37, 19, 'And have cast their gods into the fire: for they were no gods, but the work of men''s hands, wood and stone: therefore they have destroyed them.', '2~05414~ 4~0430~ 7~0784~: [10] 12~0430~, 15~04639~ 17~0120~ 18~03027~, 19~06086~ 21~068~: 25~06~'),
  (20832, 26, 16, 61, 'Then thou shalt remember thy ways, and be ashamed, when thou shalt receive thy sisters, thine elder and thy younger: and I will give them unto thee for daughters, but not by thy covenant.', '3~02142~ 5~01870~, 8~03637~, 12~03947~ 14~0269~, 16~01419~ 19~06996~: 23~05414~ 28~01323~, 33~01285~.'),
  (821, 1, 29, 22, 'And Laban gathered together all the men of the place, and made a feast.', '1~03837~ 3~0622~ 6~0582~ 9~04725~, 11~06213~ 13~04960~.'),
  (3953, 4, 8, 9, 'And thou shalt bring the Levites before the tabernacle of the congregation: and thou shalt gather the whole assembly of the children of Israel together:', '3~07126~ 5~03881~ 6~06440~ 8~0168~ 11~04150~: 15~06950~ 18~05712~ 21~01121~ 23~03478~ 24~06950~:'),
  (25391, 42, 10, 16, 'He that heareth you heareth me; and he that despiseth you despiseth me; and he that despiseth me despiseth him that sent me.', '2~191~ 3~5216~ 4~191~ 5~1700~; 6~2532~ 9~114~ 10~5209~ 11~114~ 12~1691~; 13~1161~ 16~114~ 17~1691~ 18~114~ 21~649~ 22~3165~.'),
  (18932, 23, 66, 1, 'Thus saith the LORD, The heaven is my throne, and the earth is my footstool: where is the house that ye build unto me? and where is the place of my rest?', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~, 5~08064~ [6] 8~03678~, 11~0776~ [12] 14~01916~ 15~07272~:* [17] 19~01004~ 22~01129~ [27] 29~04725~ 32~04496~?'),
  (3083, 3, 13, 26, 'But if the priest look on it, and, behold, there be no white hair in the bright spot, and it be no lower than the other skin, but be somewhat dark; then the priest shall shut him up seven days:', '3~03548~ 4~07200~ [9 10] 12~03836~ 13~08181~ 17~0934~, [20] 22~08217~ [25] 26~05785~, [28] 30~03544~; 33~03548~ 35~05462~ 38~07651~ 39~03117~:'),
  (9988, 12, 16, 17, 'And king Ahaz cut off the borders of the bases, and removed the laver from off them; and took down the sea from off the brazen oxen that were under it, and put it upon a pavement of stones.', '&para; 1~04428~ 2~0271~ 4~07112~ 6~04526~ 9~04350~, 11~05493~ 13~03595~ 19~03381~ 21~03220~ 25~05178~ 26~01241~ [28] 32~05414~ 36~04837~ 38~068~.'),
  (3016, 3, 11, 14, 'And the vulture, and the kite after his kind;', '2~01676~, 5~0344~ 8~04327~;'),
  (19244, 24, 11, 9, 'And the LORD said unto me, A conspiracy is found among the men of Judah, and among the inhabitants of Jerusalem.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 7~07195~ 9~04672~ 12~0376~ 14~03063~, 18~03427~ 20~03389~.'),
  (4789, 4, 33, 23, 'And they went from Kehelathah, and pitched in mount Shapher.', '2~05265~ 4~06954~, 6~02583~ 8~02022~ 9~08234~.'),
  (5896, 6, 2, 21, 'And she said, According unto your words, so be it. And she sent them away, and they departed: and she bound the scarlet line in the window.', '2~0559~, 6~01697~, [8] 14~07971~, 17~03212~: 20~07194~ 22~08144~ 23~08615~ 26~02474~.'),
  (15362, 19, 89, 27, 'Also I will make him my firstborn, higher than the kings of the earth.', '3~05414~ [5] 6~01060~, 7~05945~ 10~04428~ 13~0776~.'),
  (30445, 60, 3, 5, 'For after this manner in the old time the holy women also, who trusted in God, adorned themselves, being in subjection unto their own husbands:', '0~1063~ 3~3779~ 7~4218~ 9~40~ 10~1135~ 11~2532~, 12~3588~ 13~1679~ 14~1909~ 15~2316~, 16~2885~ 17~1438~, 20~5293~ 23~2398~ 24~435~:'),
  (25081, 42, 4, 6, 'And the devil said unto him, All this power will I give thee, and the glory of them: for that is delivered unto me; and to whomsoever I will I give it.', '0~2532~ 2~1228~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 6~537~ 7~5026~ 8~1849~ 11~1325~ 12~4671~, 13~2532~ 15~1391~ 17~846~: 18~3754~ 21~3860~ 23~1698~; 24~2532~ 25~3739~ 26~1437~ 28~2309~ 30~1325~ 31~846~.'),
  (8782, 11, 2, 4, 'That the LORD may continue his word which he spake concerning me, saying, If thy children take heed to their way, to walk before me in truth with all their heart and with all their soul, there shall not fail thee (said he) a man on the throne of Israel.', '2~03068~ 4~06965~ 6~01697~ 9~01696~ 12~0559~, 15~01121~ 17~08104~ 20~01870~, 22~03212~ 23~06440~ 26~0571~ 30~03824~ 35~05315~, 39~03772~ 40~0559~ 44~0376~ 47~03678~ 49~03478~.'),
  (23435, 40, 10, 8, 'Heal the sick, cleanse the lepers, raise the dead, cast out devils: freely ye have received, freely give.', '0~2323~ 2~770~, 3~2511~ 5~3015~, 6~1453~ 8~3498~, 10~1544~ 11~1140~: 12~1432~ 15~2983~, 16~1432~ 17~1325~.'),
  (24717, 41, 12, 33, 'And to love him with all the heart, and with all the understanding, and with all the soul, and with all the strength, and to love his neighbour as himself, is more than all whole burnt offerings and sacrifices.', '0~2532~ 2~25~ 3~846~ 4~1537~ 5~3650~ 7~2588~, 8~2532~ 9~1537~ 10~3650~ 12~4907~, 13~2532~ 14~1537~ 15~3650~ 17~5590~, 18~2532~ 19~1537~ 20~3650~ 22~2479~, 23~2532~ 25~25~ [26] 27~4139~ 28~5613~ 29~1438~, 30~2076~ 31~4119~ 33~3956~ 36~3646~ 37~2532~ 38~2378~.'),
