VALUES
  (6516, 6, 24, 33, 'And Eleazar the son of Aaron died; and they buried him in a hill that pertained to Phinehas his son, which was given him in mount Ephraim.', '1~0499~ 3~01121~ 5~0175~ 6~04191~; 9~06912~ 13~01389~ [14 16] 17~06372~ 19~01121~, 22~05414~ 25~02022~ 26~0669~.'),
  (29083, 48, 1, 10, 'For do I now persuade men, or God? or do I seek to please men? for if I yet pleased men, I should not be the servant of Christ.', '&para; 0~1063~ 2~3982~ 3~737~ 4~3982~ 5~444~, 6~2228~ 7~2316~? 8~2228~ 11~2212~ 13~700~ 14~444~? 15~1063~ 16~1487~ 17~700~ 18~2089~ 19~700~ 20~444~, 22~302~ 23~3756~ 24~2252~ 26~1401~ 28~5547~.'),
  (2223, 2, 25, 23, 'Thou shalt also make a table of shittim wood: two cubits shall be the length thereof, and a cubit the breadth thereof, and a cubit and a half the height thereof.', '&para; 3~06213~ 5~07979~ [6] 7~07848~ 8~06086~: 10~0520~ [11 12] 14~0753~ 18~0520~ 20~07341~ 24~0520~ 27~02677~ 29~06967~'),
  (21894, 27, 5, 11, 'There is a man in thy kingdom, in whom is the spirit of the holy gods; and in the days of thy father light and understanding and wisdom, like the wisdom of the gods, was found in him; whom the king Nebuchadnezzar thy father, the king, I say, thy father, made master of the magicians, astrologers, Chaldeans, and soothsayers;', '1~0383~ 3~01400~ 6~04437~, [9] 11~07308~ 14~06922~ 15~0426~; 19~03118~ 22~02~ 23~05094~ 25~07924~ 27~02452~, 30~02452~ 33~0426~, 35~07912~ 40~04430~ 41~05020~ 43~02~, 45~04430~, [46 47] 49~02~, 50~06966~ 51~07229~ 54~02749~, 55~0826~, 56~03779~, [57] 58~01505~;'),
  (12986, 18, 5, 26, 'Thou shalt come to thy grave in a full age, like as a shock of corn cometh in in his season.', '2~0935~ [4] 5~06913~ 9~03624~, 15~01430~ 17~05927~ 20~06256~.'),
  (28024, 45, 3, 17, 'And the way of peace have they not known:', '0~2532~ 2~3598~ 4~1515~ 5~1097~ 7~3756~ 8~1097~:'),
  (19137, 24, 7, 9, 'Will ye steal, murder, and commit adultery, and swear falsely, and burn incense unto Baal, and walk after other gods whom ye know not;', '2~01589~, 3~07523~, 6~05003~, 8~07650~ 9~08267~, 12~06999~ 14~01168~, 16~01980~ 17~0310~ 18~0312~ 19~0430~ 22~03045~'),
  (9081, 11, 9, 22, 'But of the children of Israel did Solomon make no bondmen: but they were men of war, and his servants, and his princes, and his captains, and rulers of his chariots, and his horsemen.', '3~01121~ 5~03478~ 7~08010~ 8~05414~ 10~05650~: [13] 14~0582~ 16~04421~, 19~05650~, 22~08269~, 25~07991~, 27~08269~ 30~07393~, 33~06571~.'),
  (25285, 42, 8, 28, 'When he saw Jesus, he cried out, and fell down before him, and with a loud voice said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus, thou Son of God most high? I beseech thee, torment me not.', '0~1161~ 2~1492~ 3~2424~, 6~349~, 7~2532~ 10~4363~ 11~846~, 12~2532~ 15~3173~ 16~5456~ 17~2036~, 18~5101~ 20~1698~ 23~2532~ 24~4671~, 25~2424~, [26] 27~5207~ 29~2316~ 31~5310~? 33~1189~ 34~4675~, 35~928~ 36~3165~ 37~3361~.'),
  (13483, 18, 26, 7, 'He stretcheth out the north over the empty place, and hangeth the earth upon nothing.', '2~05186~ 4~06828~ 8~08414~, [9] 10~08518~ 12~0776~ 14~01099~.'),
  (20176, 24, 50, 1, 'The word that the LORD spake against Babylon and against the land of the Chaldeans by Jeremiah the prophet.', '&para; 1~01697~ 4~03068~ 5~01696~ 7~0894~ [8] 11~0776~ 14~03778~ 15~03027~ 16~03414~ 18~05030~.'),
  (14738, 19, 54, 4, 'Behold, God is mine helper: the Lord is with them that uphold my soul.', '&para; 1~0430~ [2] 4~05826~: 6~0136~ [7] 11~05564~ 13~05315~.'),
  (9998, 12, 17, 7, 'For so it was, that the children of Israel had sinned against the LORD their God, which had brought them up out of the land of Egypt, from under the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt, and had feared other gods,', '&para; [1] 6~01121~ 8~03478~ 10~02398~ 13~03068~ 15~0430~, 20~05927~ 24~0776~ 26~04714~, 30~03027~ 32~06547~ 33~04428~ 35~04714~, 38~03372~ 39~0312~ 40~0430~,'),
  (18034, 23, 19, 21, 'And the LORD shall be known to Egypt, and the Egyptians shall know the LORD in that day, and shall do sacrifice and oblation; yea, they shall vow a vow unto the LORD, and perform it.', '2~03068~ 5~03045~ 7~04714~, 10~04714~ 12~03045~ 14~03068~ 17~03117~, 20~05647~ 21~02077~ 23~04503~; 27~05087~ 29~05088~ 32~03068~, 34~07999~ [35]'),
  (20375, 25, 3, 12, 'He hath bent his bow, and set me as a mark for the arrow.', '2~01869~ 4~07198~, 6~05324~ 10~04307~ 13~02671~.'),
  (4713, 4, 31, 43, '(Now the half that pertained unto the congregation was three hundred thousand and thirty thousand and seven thousand and five hundred sheep,', '2~04275~ [3 5] 7~05712~ 9~07969~ 10~03967~ 11~0505~ 13~07970~ 14~0505~ [15] 16~07651~ 17~0505~ 19~02568~ 20~03967~ 21~06629~ 22~04480~,*'),
  (9291, 11, 15, 34, 'And he did evil in the sight of the LORD, and walked in the way of Jeroboam, and in his sin wherewith he made Israel to sin.', '2~06213~ 3~07451~ 6~05869~ 9~03068~, 11~03212~ 14~01870~ 16~03379~, 20~02403~ 24~03478~ 26~02398~.'),
  (13928, 18, 41, 31, 'He maketh the deep to boil like a pot: he maketh the sea like a pot of ointment.', '3~04688~ 5~07570~ 8~05518~: 10~07760~ 12~03220~ 17~04841~.'),
  (24076, 40, 26, 12, 'For in that she hath poured this ointment on my body, she did it for my burial.', '2~1063~ 3~3778~ 4~846~* 6~906~ 7~5124~ 8~3464~ 9~1909~ 10~3450~ 11~4983~, 13~4160~ [14] 15~4314~ 16~3165~ 17~1779~.'),
  (30918, 66, 12, 11, 'And they overcame him by the blood of the Lamb, and by the word of their testimony; and they loved not their lives unto the death.', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~3528~ 3~846~ 4~1223~ 6~129~ 9~721~, 10~2532~ 11~1223~ 13~3056~ 15~846~ 16~3141~; 17~2532~ 19~25~ 20~3756~ 21~846~ 22~5590~ 23~891~ 25~2288~.'),
  (22215, 28, 8, 12, 'I have written to him the great things of my law, but they were counted as a strange thing.', '2~03789~ 7~07230~ 8~07239~* 11~08451~, [12] 15~02803~ 19~02114~.'),
  (15919, 19, 119, 12, 'Blessed art thou, O LORD: teach me thy statutes.', '&para; 0~01288~ [1] 4~03068~: 5~03925~ 8~02706~.'),
  (31007, 66, 17, 16, 'And the ten horns which thou sawest upon the beast, these shall hate the whore, and shall make her desolate and naked, and shall eat her flesh, and burn her with fire.', '0~2532~ 2~1176~ 3~2768~ 4~3739~ 6~1492~ 7~1909~ 9~2342~, 10~3778~ 12~3404~ 14~4204~, 15~2532~ 17~4160~ 18~846~ 19~2049~ 20~2532~ 21~1131~, 22~2532~ 24~5315~ 25~846~ 26~4561~, 27~2532~ 28~2618~ 29~846~ 30~1722~ 31~4442~.'),
  (25173, 42, 6, 15, 'Matthew and Thomas, James the son of Alphaeus, and Simon called Zelotes,', '0~3156~ 1~2532~ 2~2381~, 3~2385~ 4~3588~ [5] 7~256~, 8~2532~ 9~4613~ 10~2564~ 11~2208~,'),
  (29560, 51, 4, 2, 'Continue in prayer, and watch in the same with thanksgiving;', '&para; 0~4342~ 2~4335~, 4~1127~ 5~1722~ 7~846~ 8~1722~ 9~2169~;'),
  (9976, 12, 16, 5, 'Then Rezin king of Syria and Pekah son of Remaliah king of Israel came up to Jerusalem to war: and they besieged Ahaz, but could not overcome him.', '&para; 1~07526~ 2~04428~ 4~0758~ 6~06492~ 7~01121~ 9~07425~ 10~04428~ 12~03478~ 14~05927~ 16~03389~ 18~04421~: 21~06696~ 22~0271~, 24~03201~ 26~03898~ [27]'),
  (12307, 16, 1, 2, 'That Hanani, one of my brethren, came, he and certain men of Judah; and I asked them concerning the Jews that had escaped, which were left of the captivity, and concerning Jerusalem.', '1~02607~, 2~0259~ 5~0251~, 6~0935~, [9] 10~0582~ 12~03063~; 15~07592~ 19~03064~ 22~06413~, 25~07604~ 28~07628~, 31~03389~.'),
  (21614, 26, 44, 6, 'And thou shalt say to the rebellious, even to the house of Israel, Thus saith the Lord GOD; O ye house of Israel, let it suffice you of all your abominations,', '3~0559~ 6~04805~, [7] 10~01004~ 12~03478~, 14~0559~ 16~0136~ 17~03069~; 20~01004~ 22~03478~, 25~07227~ 30~08441~,'),
  (4743, 4, 32, 19, 'For we will not inherit with them on yonder side Jordan, or forward; because our inheritance is fallen to us on this side Jordan eastward.', '4~05157~ 9~05676~ 10~03383~, 12~01973~; 15~05159~ 17~0935~ 22~05676~ 23~03383~ 24~04217~.'),
  (19533, 24, 23, 40, 'And I will bring an everlasting reproach upon you, and a perpetual shame, which shall not be forgotten.', '3~05414~ 5~05769~ 6~02781~ 11~05769~ 12~03640~, 17~07911~.'),
  (28799, 46, 16, 7, 'For I will not see you now by the way; but I trust to tarry a while with you, if the Lord permit.', '0~1063~ 2~2309~ 3~3756~ 4~1492~ 5~5209~ 6~737~ 7~1722~ 9~3938~; 10~1161~ 12~1679~ 14~1961~ 16~5550~ 17~5100~* 18~4314~ 19~5209~, 20~1437~ 22~2962~ 23~2010~.'),
  (25294, 42, 8, 37, 'Then the whole multitude of the country of the Gadarenes round about besought him to depart from them; for they were taken with great fear: and he went up into the ship, and returned back again.', '0~2532~ 2~537~ 3~4128~ 6~4066~ 9~1046~ 11~4066~ 12~2065~ 13~846~ 15~565~ 16~575~ 17~846~; 18~3754~ 21~4912~ 23~3173~ 24~5401~: 25~1161~ 26~846~ 28~1684~ 29~1519~ 31~4143~, 35~5290~.'),
  (6422, 6, 21, 34, 'And unto the families of the children of Merari, the rest of the Levites, out of the tribe of Zebulun, Jokneam with her suburbs, and Kartah with her suburbs,', '3~04940~ 6~01121~ 8~04847~, 10~03498~ 13~03881~, 17~04294~ 19~02074~, 20~03362~ 23~04054~, 25~07177~ 28~04054~,'),
  (13667, 18, 33, 8, 'Surely thou hast spoken in mine hearing, and I have heard the voice of thy words, saying,', '&para; 3~0559~ 6~0241~, 10~08085~ 12~06963~ [14] 15~04405~, [16]'),
  (28690, 46, 13, 9, 'For we know in part, and we prophesy in part.', '0~1063~ 2~1097~ 3~1537~ 4~3313~, 5~2532~ 7~4395~ 8~1537~ 9~3313~.'),
  (19753, 24, 32, 13, 'And I charged Baruch before them, saying,', '2~06680~ 3~01263~ 4~05869~ 6~0559~,'),
  (19072, 24, 5, 5, 'I will get me unto the great men, and will speak unto them; for they have known the way of the LORD, and the judgment of their God: but these have altogether broken the yoke, and burst the bonds.', '2~03212~ 7~01419~, 10~01696~ 16~03045~ 18~01870~ 21~03068~, [22] 24~04941~ 27~0430~: 31~03162~ 32~07665~ 34~05923~, [35] 36~05423~ 38~04147~.'),
  (8534, 10, 19, 15, 'So the king returned, and came to Jordan. And Judah came to Gilgal, to go to meet the king, to conduct the king over Jordan.', '2~04428~ 3~07725~, 5~0935~ 7~03383~. 9~03063~ 10~0935~ 12~01537~, 14~03212~ 16~07125~ 18~04428~, 20~05674~ 22~04428~ 23~05674~ 24~03383~.'),
  (14556, 19, 41, 5, 'Mine enemies speak evil of me, When shall he die, and his name perish?', '&para; 1~0341~ 2~0559~ 3~07451~ 9~04191~, 12~08034~ 13~06~?'),
  (4976, 5, 2, 32, 'Then Sihon came out against us, he and all his people, to fight at Jahaz.', '1~05511~ 3~03318~ 4~07125~ 10~05971~, 12~04421~ 14~03096~.'),
  (23120, 39, 2, 8, 'But ye are departed out of the way; ye have caused many to stumble at the law; ye have corrupted the covenant of Levi, saith the LORD of hosts.', '3~05493~ 7~01870~; 11~07227~ 13~03782~ 16~08451~; 19~07843~ 21~01285~ 23~03878~, 24~0559~ 26~03068~ 28~06635~.'),
  (26189, 43, 4, 18, 'For thou hast had five husbands; and he whom thou now hast is not thy husband: in that saidst thou truly.', '0~1063~ 3~2192~ 4~4002~ 5~435~; 6~2532~ 8~3739~ 9~2192~ 10~3568~ 11~2192~ 12~2076~ 13~3756~ 14~4675~ 15~435~: 17~5124~ 19~2046~ 20~227~.'),
  (14817, 19, 60, 1, 'To the chief Musician upon Shushaneduth, Michtam of David, to teach; when he strove with Aramnaharaim and with Aramzobah, when Joab returned, and smote of Edom in the valley of salt twelve thousand. O God, thou hast cast us off, thou hast scattered us, thou hast been displeased; O turn thyself to us again.', '&para; [0 3~05329~ 5~07802~, 6~04387~ 8~01732~, 10~03925~; 13~05327~ 15~05104~ 16~0763~ 18~0760~, 20~03097~ 21~07725~, 23~05221~ 25~0123~ 28~01516~ 30~04417~ 31~06240~ 32~08147~* 33] 33~0505~ 35~0430~, 40~02186~, 43~06555~ 48~0599~; 54~07725~.'),
  (16389, 19, 148, 9, 'Mountains, and all hills; fruitful trees, and all cedars:', '0~02022~, 3~01389~; 4~06529~ 5~06086~, 8~0730~:'),
  (17029, 20, 22, 5, 'Thorns and snares are in the way of the froward: he that doth keep his soul shall be far from them.', '&para; 0~06791~ [1] 2~06341~ [3] 6~01870~ 9~06141~: 13~08104~ 15~05315~ 18~07368~'),
  (26682, 43, 13, 37, 'Peter said unto him, Lord, why cannot I follow thee now? I will lay down my life for thy sake.', '0~4074~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~2962~, 5~1302~ 6~1410~ 7~3756~* 9~190~ 10~4671~ 11~737~? 15~5087~ 16~3450~ 17~5590~ 18~5228~ 20~4675~.'),
  (31100, 66, 22, 4, 'And they shall see his face; and his name shall be in their foreheads.', '0~2532~ 3~3700~ 4~846~ 5~4383~; 6~2532~ 7~846~ 8~3686~ [9 10] 11~1909~ 12~846~ 13~3359~.'),
  (4860, 4, 35, 9, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (12086, 15, 2, 50, 'The children of Asnah, the children of Mehunim, the children of Nephusim,', '1~01121~ 3~0619~, 5~01121~ 7~04586~, 9~01121~ 11~05300~ 12~05304~,*'),
  (7039, 7, 19, 8, 'And he arose early in the morning on the fifth day to depart: and the damsel''s father said, Comfort thine heart, I pray thee. And they tarried until afternoon, and they did eat both of them.', '3~07925~ 6~01242~ 9~02549~ 10~03117~ 12~03212~: 15~05291~ 16~01~ 17~0559~, 18~05582~ 20~03824~, 26~04102~ 28~05186~ 29~03117~,* 33~0398~ 34~08147~'),
  (30133, 58, 9, 12, 'Neither by the blood of goats and calves, but by his own blood he entered in once into the holy place, having obtained eternal redemption for us.', '0~3761~ 1~1223~ 3~129~ 5~5131~ 6~2532~ 7~3448~, 8~1161~ 9~1223~ 11~2398~ 12~129~ 15~1525~ 16~2178~ 17~1519~ 20~39~, 22~2147~ 23~166~ 24~3085~ [25 26]'),
  (19481, 24, 22, 18, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD concerning Jehoiakim the son of Josiah king of Judah; They shall not lament for him, saying, Ah my brother! or, Ah sister! they shall not lament for him, saying, Ah lord! or, Ah his glory!', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 6~03079~ 8~01121~ 10~02977~ 11~04428~ 13~03063~; 17~05594~ [20] 21~01945~ 23~0251~! 25~01945~ 26~0269~! 30~05594~ [33] 34~01945~ 35~0113~! 37~01945~ 39~01935~!'),
  (11744, 14, 26, 3, 'Sixteen years old was Uzziah when he began to reign, and he reigned fifty and two years in Jerusalem. His mother''s name also was Jecoliah of Jerusalem.', '0~06240~ 1~08337~* 2~08141~ 3~01121~ [4] 5~05818~ 10~04427~, 13~04427~ 14~02572~ 16~08147~ 17~08141~ 19~03389~. 21~0517~ 22~08034~ [24] 25~03203~ 27~03389~.'),
  (28474, 46, 5, 4, 'In the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, when ye are gathered together, and my spirit, with the power of our Lord Jesus Christ,', '0~1722~ 2~3686~ 4~2257~ 5~2962~ 6~2424~ 7~5547~, 9~5216~ 12~4863~, 13~2532~ 14~1699~ 15~4151~, 16~4862~ 18~1411~ 20~2257~ 21~2962~ 22~2424~ 23~5547~,'),
  (3114, 3, 13, 57, 'And if it appear still in the garment, either in the warp, or in the woof, or in any thing of skin; it is a spreading plague: thou shalt burn that wherein the plague is with fire.', '3~07200~ 4~05750~ 7~0899~, 11~08359~, 15~06154~, 19~03627~ 21~05785~; [23] 25~06524~ [26] 29~08313~ 33~05061~ [34] 36~0784~.'),
  (11776, 14, 28, 3, 'Moreover he burnt incense in the valley of the son of Hinnom, and burnt his children in the fire, after the abominations of the heathen whom the LORD had cast out before the children of Israel.', '3~06999~ 6~01516~ 9~01121~ 11~02011~, 13~01197~ 15~01121~ 18~0784~, 21~08441~ 24~01471~ 27~03068~ 30~03423~ 31~06440~ 33~01121~ 35~03478~.'),
  (9853, 12, 11, 16, 'And they laid hands on her; and she went by the way by the which the horses came into the king''s house: and there was she slain.', '2~07760~ 3~03027~ 8~0935~ 11~01870~ 16~05483~ 17~03996~ 20~04428~ 21~01004~: 26~04191~.'),
  (1516, 1, 50, 5, 'My father made me swear, saying, Lo, I die: in my grave which I have digged for me in the land of Canaan, there shalt thou bury me. Now therefore let me go up, I pray thee, and bury my father, and I will come again.', '1~01~ 4~07650~, 5~0559~, 6~02009~, 8~04191~: 11~06913~ 15~03738~ 20~0776~ 22~03667~, 27~06912~. 33~05927~, 38~06912~ 40~01~, 45~07725~.'),
  (25568, 42, 14, 2, 'And, behold, there was a certain man before him which had the dropsy.', '0~2532~, 1~2400~, 3~2258~ 5~5100~ 6~444~ 7~1715~ 8~846~ 12~5203~.'),
  (19083, 24, 5, 16, 'Their quiver is as an open sepulchre, they are all mighty men.', '1~0827~ [2] 5~06605~ 6~06913~, [8] 11~01368~.'),
  (535, 1, 21, 18, 'Arise, lift up the lad, and hold him in thine hand; for I will make him a great nation.', '0~06965~, 2~05375~ 4~05288~, 6~02388~ 10~03027~; 14~07760~ 17~01419~ 18~01471~.'),
  (19824, 24, 34, 14, 'At the end of seven years let ye go every man his brother an Hebrew, which hath been sold unto thee; and when he hath served thee six years, thou shalt let him go free from thee: but your fathers hearkened not unto me, neither inclined their ear.', '2~07093~ 4~07651~ 5~08141~ 8~07971~ 10~0376~ 12~0251~ 14~05680~, 18~04376~ 25~05647~ 27~08337~ 28~08141~, 33~07971~ 34~02670~ 39~01~ 40~08085~ 45~05186~ 47~0241~.'),
  (2437, 2, 31, 12, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (15127, 19, 78, 5, 'For he established a testimony in Jacob, and appointed a law in Israel, which he commanded our fathers, that they should make them known to their children:', '2~06965~ 4~05715~ 6~03290~, 8~07760~ 10~08451~ 12~03478~, 15~06680~ 17~01~, 23~03045~ 26~01121~:'),
  (7746, 9, 20, 9, 'And Jonathan said, Far be it from thee: for if I knew certainly that evil were determined by my father to come upon thee, then would not I tell it thee?', '&para; 1~03083~ 2~0559~, 7~02486~: 11~03045~ 12~03045~ 14~07451~ 16~03615~ 19~01~ 21~0935~ 28~05046~'),
  (21919, 27, 6, 5, 'Then said these men, We shall not find any occasion against this Daniel, except we find it against him concerning the law of his God.', '0~0116~ 1~0560~ 2~0479~ 3~01400~, 6~03809~ 7~07912~ 8~03606~ 9~05931~ 10~05922~ 11~01836~ 12~01841~, 13~03861~ 15~07912~ [16] 21~01882~ 24~0426~.'),
  (4099, 4, 13, 19, 'And what the land is that they dwell in, whether it be good or bad; and what cities they be that they dwell in, whether in tents, or in strong holds;', '3~0776~ [4] 8~03427~, [11] 12~02896~ 14~07451~; 17~05892~ [18 19] 22~03427~ 23~02007~, 26~04264~, 30~04013~;'),
  (17375, 21, 3, 7, 'A time to rend, and a time to sew; a time to keep silence, and a time to speak;', '1~06256~ 3~07167~, 6~06256~ 8~08609~; 10~06256~ 13~02814~, 16~06256~ 18~01696~;'),
  (5869, 6, 1, 12, 'And to the Reubenites, and to the Gadites, and to half the tribe of Manasseh, spake Joshua, saying,', '3~07206~, 7~01425~, 10~02677~ 12~07626~ 14~04519~, 15~0559~ 16~03091~, 17~0559~,'),
  (20119, 24, 48, 30, 'I know his wrath, saith the LORD; but it shall not be so; his lies shall not so effect it.', '1~03045~ 3~05678~, 4~05002~ 6~03068~; [8 9] [11] 14~0907~ 18~06213~ [19]'),
  (11929, 14, 33, 12, 'And when he was in affliction, he besought the LORD his God, and humbled himself greatly before the God of his fathers,', '5~06887~, 7~02470~ 9~03068~ 11~0430~, 13~03665~ 15~03966~ 16~06440~ 18~0430~ 21~01~,'),
  (17401, 21, 4, 11, 'Again, if two lie together, then they have heat: but how can one be warm alone?', '0~01571~, 2~08147~ 4~07901~, 8~02552~: 12~0259~ 14~03179~ [15]'),
  (4842, 4, 34, 20, 'And of the tribe of the children of Simeon, Shemuel the son of Ammihud.', '3~04294~ 6~01121~ 8~08095~, 9~08050~ 11~01121~ 13~05989~.'),
  (27221, 44, 8, 29, 'Then the Spirit said unto Philip, Go near, and join thyself to this chariot.', '0~1161~ 2~4151~ 3~2036~ 5~5376~, 7~4334~, 8~2532~ 11~2853~ 12~5129~ 13~716~.'),
  (11393, 14, 9, 21, 'For the king''s ships went to Tarshish with the servants of Huram: every three years once came the ships of Tarshish bringing gold, and silver, ivory, and apes, and peacocks.', '2~04428~ 3~0591~ 4~01980~ 6~08659~ 9~05650~ 11~02361~: 13~07969~ 14~08141~ 15~0259~ 16~0935~ 18~0591~ 20~08659~ 21~05375~ 22~02091~, 24~03701~, 25~08143~, 27~06971~, 29~08500~.'),
  (2054, 2, 19, 23, 'And Moses said unto the LORD, The people cannot come up to mount Sinai: for thou chargedst us, saying, Set bounds about the mount, and sanctify it.', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 5~03068~, 7~05971~ 8~03201~ 10~05927~ 12~02022~ 13~05514~: 16~05749~ 18~0559~, 20~01379~ 23~02022~, 25~06942~'),
  (23985, 40, 24, 18, 'Neither let him which is in the field return back to take his clothes.', '0~2532~* 1~3361~ 6~1722~ 8~68~ 9~1994~ 10~3694~ 12~142~ 13~846~ 14~2440~.'),
  (7866, 9, 24, 20, 'And now, behold, I know well that thou shalt surely be king, and that the kingdom of Israel shall be established in thine hand.', '5~03045~ 9~04427~ 11~04427~, 15~04467~ 17~03478~ 20~06965~ 23~03027~.'),
  (26802, 43, 18, 2, 'And Judas also, which betrayed him, knew the place: for Jesus ofttimes resorted thither with his disciples.', '0~1161~ 1~2455~ 2~2532~, 3~3588~ 4~3860~ 5~846~, 6~1492~ 8~5117~: 9~3754~ 10~2424~ 11~4178~ 12~4863~ 13~1563~ 14~3326~ 15~846~ 16~3101~.'),
  (3446, 3, 23, 39, 'Also in the fifteenth day of the seventh month, when ye have gathered in the fruit of the land, ye shall keep a feast unto the LORD seven days: on the first day shall be a sabbath, and on the eighth day shall be a sabbath.', '3~06240~ 4~02568~* 5~03117~ 8~07637~ 9~02320~, 13~0622~ 16~08393~ 19~0776~, 22~02287~ 24~02282~ 27~03068~ 28~07651~ 29~03117~: 32~07223~ 33~03117~ [34 35] 37~07677~, 41~08066~ 42~03117~ [43 44] 46~07677~.'),
  (27995, 45, 2, 17, 'Behold, thou art called a Jew, and restest in the law, and makest thy boast of God,', '&para; 0~2396~, 1~4771~ 3~2028~ 5~2453~, 6~2532~ 7~1879~ 10~3551~, 11~2532~ 14~2744~ 15~1722~ 16~2316~,'),
  (23987, 40, 24, 20, 'But pray ye that your flight be not in the winter, neither on the sabbath day:', '0~1161~ 2~4336~ 3~3363~ 4~5216~ 5~5437~ 6~1096~ 7~3363~ 10~5494~, 11~3366~ 12~1722~ 15~4521~:'),
  (29455, 50, 3, 18, '(For many walk, of whom I have told you often, and now tell you even weeping, that they are the enemies of the cross of Christ:', '0~(1063~ 1~4183~ 2~4043~, 4~3739~ 7~3004~ 8~5213~ 9~4178~, 10~1161~ 11~3568~ 12~3004~ 14~2532~ 15~2799~, [16 18] 20~2190~ 23~4716~ 25~5547~:'),
  (3165, 3, 14, 49, 'And he shall take to cleanse the house two birds, and cedar wood, and scarlet, and hyssop:', '3~03947~ 5~02398~ 7~01004~ 8~08147~ 9~06833~, 11~0730~ 12~06086~, 14~08438~ 15~08144~,* 17~0231~:'),
  (18428, 23, 39, 7, 'And of thy sons that shall issue from thee, which thou shalt beget, shall they take away; and they shall be eunuchs in the palace of the king of Babylon.', '3~01121~ 6~03318~ 12~03205~, 16~03947~; 21~05631~ 24~01964~ 27~04428~ 29~0894~.'),
  (22858, 37, 1, 9, 'Ye looked for much, and, lo, it came to little; and when ye brought it home, I did blow upon it. Why? saith the LORD of hosts. Because of mine house that is waste, and ye run every man unto his own house.', '1~06437~ 3~07235~, [6 7] 9~04592~; 13~0935~ [14] 15~01004~, 18~05301~ 22~05002~ 24~03068~ 26~06635~. 27~03282~ 30~01004~ [32] 33~02720~, 36~07323~ 38~0376~ 42~01004~.'),
  (27253, 44, 9, 21, 'But all that heard him were amazed, and said; Is not this he that destroyed them which called on this name in Jerusalem, and came hither for that intent, that he might bring them bound unto the chief priests?', '0~1161~ 1~3956~ 3~191~ [4] 6~1839~, 7~2532~ 8~3004~; 9~2076~ 10~3756~ 11~3778~ 14~4199~ 16~3588~ 18~1941~ 19~5124~ 20~3686~ 21~1722~ 22~2419~, 23~2532~ 24~2064~ 25~5602~ 26~1519~ 27~5124~ 28~1519~, 29~2443~ 32~71~ 33~846~ 34~1210~ 35~1909~ 38~749~?'),
  (6589, 7, 3, 14, 'So the children of Israel served Eglon the king of Moab eighteen years.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~05647~ 6~05700~ 8~04428~ 10~04124~ 11~06240~ 12~08083~* 13~08141~.'),
  (14294, 19, 26, 12, 'My foot standeth in an even place: in the congregations will I bless the LORD.', '1~07272~ 2~05975~ 6~04334~: 9~04721~ 12~01288~ 14~03068~.'),
  (2825, 3, 4, 25, 'And the priest shall take of the blood of the sin offering with his finger, and put it upon the horns of the altar of burnt offering, and shall pour out his blood at the bottom of the altar of burnt offering.', '2~03548~ 4~03947~ 7~01818~ 11~02403~ 14~0676~, 16~05414~ [17] 20~07161~ 23~04196~ 26~05930~, 30~08210~ 32~01818~ 35~03247~ 38~04196~ 41~05930~.'),
  (28605, 46, 10, 22, 'Do we provoke the Lord to jealousy? are we stronger than he?', '2~3863~ 3~2228~* 5~2962~ 7~3863~? 9~2070~ 11~2478~ 12~3361~* 13~846~?'),
  (10345, 13, 2, 31, 'And the sons of Appaim; Ishi. And the sons of Ishi; Sheshan. And the children of Sheshan; Ahlai.', '2~01121~ 4~0649~; 5~03469~. 8~01121~ 10~03469~; 11~08348~. 14~01121~ 16~08348~; 17~0304~.'),
  (8557, 10, 19, 38, 'And the king answered, Chimham shall go over with me, and I will do to him that which shall seem good unto thee: and whatsoever thou shalt require of me, that will I do for thee.', '2~04428~ 3~0559~, 4~03643~ 6~05674~ 13~06213~ 20~05869~ 21~02896~ 27~0977~ [30] 33~06213~'),
  (10228, 12, 24, 18, 'Zedekiah was twenty and one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. And his mother''s name was Hamutal, the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah.', '0~06667~ [1] 2~06242~ 4~0259~ 5~08141~ 6~01121~ 11~04427~, 14~04427~ 15~06240~ 16~0259~* 17~08141~ 19~03389~. 22~0517~ 23~08034~ [24] 25~02537~, 27~01323~ 29~03414~ 31~03841~.'),
  (20789, 26, 16, 18, 'And tookest thy broidered garments, and coveredst them: and thou hast set mine oil and mine incense before them.', '1~03947~ 3~07553~ 4~0899~, 6~03680~ 11~05414~ 13~08081~ 16~07004~ 17~06440~'),
  (2702, 2, 39, 33, 'And they brought the tabernacle unto Moses, the tent, and all his furniture, his taches, his boards, his bars, and his pillars, and his sockets,', '2~0935~ 4~04908~ 6~04872~, 8~0168~, 12~03627~, 14~07165~, 16~07175~, 18~01280~, 21~05982~, 24~0134~,'),
  (918, 1, 31, 41, 'Thus have I been twenty years in thy house; I served thee fourteen years for thy two daughters, and six years for thy cattle: and thou hast changed my wages ten times.', '4~06242~ 5~08141~ 8~01004~; 11~05647~ 12~06240~ 13~0702~* 14~08141~ 17~08147~ 18~01323~, 20~08337~ 21~08141~ 24~06629~: 28~02498~ 30~04909~ 31~06235~ 32~04489~.'),
  (12107, 15, 3, 1, 'And when the seventh month was come, and the children of Israel were in the cities, the people gathered themselves together as one man to Jerusalem.', '&para; 3~07637~ 4~02320~ 6~05060~, 9~01121~ 11~03478~ [12] 15~05892~, 17~05971~ 20~0622~ 22~0259~ 23~0376~ 25~03389~.'),
  (12759, 17, 3, 3, 'Then the king''s servants, which were in the king''s gate, said unto Mordecai, Why transgressest thou the king''s commandment?', '2~04428~ 3~05650~, [5] 8~04428~ 9~08179~, 10~0559~ 12~04782~, 14~05674~ 17~04428~ 18~04687~?'),
  (7114, 7, 21, 5, 'And the children of Israel said, Who is there among all the tribes of Israel that came not up with the congregation unto the LORD? For they had made a great oath concerning him that came not up to the LORD to Mizpeh, saying, He shall surely be put to death.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~0559~, [7 8] 12~07626~ 14~03478~ 15~0834~ 16~05927~ 21~06951~ 24~03068~? 30~01419~ 31~07621~ 37~05927~ 40~03068~ 42~04709~, 43~0559~, 46~04191~ 50~04191~.');
