  (21744, 26, 48, 33, 'And at the south side four thousand and five hundred measures: and three gates; one gate of Simeon, one gate of Issachar, one gate of Zebulun.', '3~05045~ 4~06285~ 5~0702~ 6~0505~ 8~02568~ 9~03967~ 10~04060~: 12~07969~ 13~08179~; 14~0259~ 15~08179~ 17~08095~, 18~0259~ 19~08179~ 21~03485~, 22~0259~ 23~08179~ 25~02074~.'),
  (5337, 5, 15, 12, 'And if thy brother, an Hebrew man, or an Hebrew woman, be sold unto thee, and serve thee six years; then in the seventh year thou shalt let him go free from thee.', '&para; [0] 3~0251~, 6~05680~, 10~05680~, 12~04376~ 16~05647~ 18~08337~ 19~08141~; 23~07637~ 24~08141~ 29~07971~ 30~02670~'),
  (11602, 14, 20, 6, 'And said, O LORD God of our fathers, art not thou God in heaven? and rulest not thou over all the kingdoms of the heathen? and in thine hand is there not power and might, so that none is able to withstand thee?', '1~0559~, 3~03068~ 4~0430~ 7~01~, [8] 11~0430~ 13~08064~? 15~04910~ [16] 21~04467~ 24~01471~? 28~03027~ [29 31] 32~03581~ 34~01369~, 41~03320~'),
  (5671, 5, 28, 54, 'So that the man that is tender among you, and very delicate, his eye shall be evil toward his brother, and toward the wife of his bosom, and toward the remnant of his children which he shall leave:', '[0 1] 3~0376~ [4 5] 6~07390~ 10~03966~ 11~06028~, 13~05869~ 16~03415~ 19~0251~, 23~0802~ 26~02436~, 30~03499~ 33~01121~ 37~03498~:'),
  (19964, 24, 40, 14, 'And said unto him, Dost thou certainly know that Baalis the king of the Ammonites hath sent Ishmael the son of Nethaniah to slay thee? But Gedaliah the son of Ahikam believed them not.', '1~0559~ 6~03045~ 7~03045~ 9~01185~ 11~04428~ 14~05983~ 15~01121~ 16~07971~ 17~03458~ 19~01121~ 21~05418~ 23~05221~ 24~05315~* 27~01436~ 29~01121~ 31~0296~ 32~0539~'),
  (1790, 2, 10, 8, 'And Moses and Aaron were brought again unto Pharaoh: and he said unto them, Go, serve the LORD your God: but who are they that shall go?', '1~04872~ 3~0175~ 6~07725~ 8~06547~: 11~0559~ 14~03212~, 15~05647~ 17~03068~ 19~0430~: [20] [22] 26~01980~?'),
  (24209, 40, 28, 4, 'And for fear of him the keepers did shake, and became as dead men.', '0~1161~ 1~575~ 2~5401~ 4~846~ 6~5083~ 8~4579~, 9~2532~ 10~1096~ 11~5616~ 12~3498~ [13]'),
  (31082, 66, 21, 13, 'On the east three gates; on the north three gates; on the south three gates; and on the west three gates.', '0~575~ 2~395~ 3~5140~ 4~4440~; 5~575~ 7~1005~ 8~5140~ 9~4440~; 10~575~ 12~3558~ 13~5140~ 14~4440~; 15~2532~ 16~575~ 18~1424~ 19~5140~ 20~4440~.'),
  (10338, 13, 2, 24, 'And after that Hezron was dead in Calebephratah, then Abiah Hezron''s wife bare him Ashur the father of Tekoa.', '1~0310~ 3~02696~ 5~04194~ 7~03613~, 9~029~ 10~02696~ 11~0802~ 12~03205~ 14~0806~ 16~01~ 18~08620~.'),
  (25197, 42, 6, 39, 'And he spake a parable unto them, Can the blind lead the blind? shall they not both fall into the ditch?', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~3850~ 6~846~ 7~3385~,* 8~1410~ 10~5185~ 11~3594~ 13~5185~? 15~297~ 16~3780~ 17~297~ 18~4098~ 19~1519~ 21~999~?'),
  (16456, 20, 2, 14, 'Who rejoice to do evil, and delight in the frowardness of the wicked;', '1~08056~ 3~06213~ 4~07451~, [5] 6~01523~ 9~08419~ 12~07451~;'),
  (7351, 9, 6, 13, 'And they of Bethshemesh were reaping their wheat harvest in the valley: and they lifted up their eyes, and saw the ark, and rejoiced to see it.', '[1 2] 3~01053~ [4] 5~07114~ 7~02406~ 8~07105~ 11~06010~: 15~05375~ 17~05869~, 19~07200~ 21~0727~, 23~08055~ 25~07200~ [26]'),
  (21490, 26, 40, 4, 'And the man said unto me, Son of man, behold with thine eyes, and hear with thine ears, and set thine heart upon all that I shall shew thee; for to the intent that I might shew them unto thee art thou brought hither: declare all that thou seest to the house of Israel.', '2~0376~ 3~01696~ 6~01121~ 8~0120~, 9~07200~ 12~05869~, 14~08085~ 17~0241~, 19~07760~ 21~03820~ 27~07200~ 32~04616~ 36~07200~ [37] [40] 42~0935~ 44~05046~ 48~07200~ 51~01004~ 53~03478~.'),
  (10369, 13, 2, 55, 'And the families of the scribes which dwelt at Jabez; the Tirathites, the Shimeathites, and Suchathites. These are the Kenites that came of Hemath, the father of the house of Rechab.', '2~04940~ 5~05608~ 7~03427~ 9~03258~; 11~08654~, 13~08101~, [14] 15~07756~. 16~01992~ [17] 19~07017~ 21~0935~ 23~02574~, 25~01~ 28~01004~ 30~07394~.'),
  (17080, 20, 23, 27, 'For a whore is a deep ditch; and a strange woman is a narrow pit.', '2~02181~ [3] 5~06013~ 6~07745~; 10~05237~ [11] 13~06862~ 14~0875~.'),
  (6778, 7, 9, 17, '(For my father fought for you, and adventured his life far, and delivered you out of the hand of Midian:', '2~01~ 3~03898~ 7~07993~ 9~05315~ 10~05048~, 12~05337~ 17~03027~ 19~04080~:'),
  (6083, 6, 10, 13, 'And the sun stood still, and the moon stayed, until the people had avenged themselves upon their enemies. Is not this written in the book of Jasher? So the sun stood still in the midst of heaven, and hasted not to go down about a whole day.', '2~08121~ 4~01826~, 7~03394~ 8~05975~, 11~01471~ 13~05358~ 17~0341~. [18] 20~01931~ 21~03789~ 24~05612~ 26~03477~? 29~08121~ 31~05975~ 34~02677~ 36~08064~, 38~0213~ 42~0935~ 45~08549~ 46~03117~.'),
  (10575, 13, 7, 32, 'And Heber begat Japhlet, and Shomer, and Hotham, and Shua their sister.', '1~02268~ 2~03205~ 3~03310~, 5~07763~, 7~02369~, 9~07774~ 11~0269~.'),
  (16799, 20, 14, 18, 'The simple inherit folly: but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.', '&para; 1~06612~ 2~05157~ 3~0200~: 6~06175~ 8~03803~ 10~01847~.'),
  (1268, 1, 42, 11, 'We are all one man''s sons; we are true men, thy servants are no spies.', '0~05168~ [1] 3~0259~ 4~0376~ 5~01121~; [7] 8~03651~ [9] 11~05650~ 14~07270~.'),
  (4908, 5, 1, 10, 'The LORD your God hath multiplied you, and, behold, ye are this day as the stars of heaven for multitude.', '1~03068~ 3~0430~ 5~07235~ [10] 12~03117~ 15~03556~ 17~08064~ 19~07230~.'),
  (10832, 13, 16, 4, 'And he appointed certain of the Levites to minister before the ark of the LORD, and to record, and to thank and praise the LORD God of Israel:', '2~05414~ [3] 6~03881~ 8~08334~ 9~06440~ 11~0727~ 14~03068~, 17~02142~, 20~03034~ 22~01984~ 24~03068~ 25~0430~ 27~03478~:'),
  (20207, 24, 50, 32, 'And the most proud shall stumble and fall, and none shall raise him up: and I will kindle a fire in his cities, and it shall devour all round about him.', '3~02087~ 5~03782~ 7~05307~, 13~06965~: 17~03341~ 19~0784~ 22~05892~, 26~0398~ 29~05439~'),
  (27171, 44, 7, 39, 'To whom our fathers would not obey, but thrust him from them, and in their hearts turned back again into Egypt,', '1~3739~ 2~2257~ 3~3962~ 4~2309~ 5~3756~ 6~1096~ 7~5255~,* 8~235~ [10] 12~683~, 13~2532~ 15~846~ 16~2588~ 19~4762~ 20~1519~ 21~125~,'),
  (15784, 19, 109, 20, 'Let this be the reward of mine adversaries from the LORD, and of them that speak evil against my soul.', '[0] [2] 4~06468~ 7~07853~ 10~03068~, 15~01696~ 16~07451~ 19~05315~.'),
  (11074, 13, 25, 20, 'The thirteenth to Shubael, he, his sons, and his brethren, were twelve:', '1~06240~ 2~07969~ 3~07619~, [4] 6~01121~, 9~0251~, [10] 11~06240~ 12~08147~:*'),
  (20039, 24, 44, 20, 'Then Jeremiah said unto all the people, to the men, and to the women, and to all the people which had given him that answer, saying,', '&para; 1~03414~ 2~0559~ 6~05971~, 9~01397~, 13~0802~, 18~05971~ [23] 24~06030~ 25~01697~,* 26~0559~,'),
  (2378, 2, 29, 37, 'Seven days thou shalt make an atonement for the altar, and sanctify it; and it shall be an altar most holy: whatsoever toucheth the altar shall be holy.', '0~07651~ 1~03117~ 6~03722~ 9~04196~, 11~06942~ 18~04196~ 20~06944~ 21~06944~:* 23~05060~ 25~04196~ 28~06942~.'),
  (22466, 30, 6, 7, 'Therefore now shall they go captive with the first that go captive, and the banquet of them that stretched themselves shall be removed.', '5~01540~ 8~07218~ 11~01540~, 14~04797~ 18~05628~ 22~05493~.'),
  (1202, 1, 41, 2, 'And, behold, there came up out of the river seven well favoured kine and fatfleshed; and they fed in a meadow.', '4~05927~ 8~02975~ 9~07651~ 10~03303~ 11~04758~ 12~06510~ 14~01320~ 15~01277~;* 18~07462~ 21~0260~.'),
  (6223, 6, 15, 14, 'And Caleb drove thence the three sons of Anak, Sheshai, and Ahiman, and Talmai, the children of Anak.', '1~03612~ 2~03423~ 5~07969~ 6~01121~ 8~06061~, 9~08344~, 11~0289~, 13~08526~, 15~03211~ 17~06061~.'),
  (14354, 19, 31, 14, 'But I trusted in thee, O LORD: I said, Thou art my God.', '2~0982~ 6~03068~: 8~0559~, [10] 12~0430~.'),
  (12847, 17, 9, 4, 'For Mordecai was great in the king''s house, and his fame went out throughout all the provinces: for this man Mordecai waxed greater and greater.', '1~04782~ [2] 3~01419~ 6~04428~ 7~01004~, 10~08089~ 12~01980~ 16~04082~: 19~0376~ 20~04782~ 21~01980~ 24~01419~.'),
  (14243, 19, 22, 30, 'A seed shall serve him; it shall be accounted to the Lord for a generation.', '1~02233~ 3~05647~ 8~05608~ 11~0136~ 14~01755~.'),
  (26838, 43, 18, 38, 'Pilate saith unto him, What is truth? And when he had said this, he went out again unto the Jews, and saith unto them, I find in him no fault at all.', '0~4091~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~5101~ 5~2076~ 6~225~? 7~2532~ 11~2036~ 12~5124~, 15~1831~ 16~3825~ 17~4314~ 19~2453~, 20~2532~ 21~3004~ 23~846~, 24~1473~ 25~2147~ 26~1722~ 27~846~ 28~3762~ 29~156~ [30 31]'),
  (20297, 24, 52, 12, 'Now in the fifth month, in the tenth day of the month, which was the nineteenth year of Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon, came Nebuzaradan, captain of the guard, which served the king of Babylon, into Jerusalem,', '&para; 3~02549~ 4~02320~, 7~06218~ [8] 11~02320~, [13] 15~08141~ 16~08672~* 17~06240~* 18~08141~ 20~05019~ 21~04428~ 23~0894~, 24~0935~ 25~05018~, 26~07227~ 29~02876~, [30] 31~05975~ 32~06440~* 34~04428~ 36~0894~, 38~03389~,'),
  (1134, 1, 38, 10, 'And the thing which he did displeased the LORD: wherefore he slew him also.', '3~0834~ 5~06213~ 6~03415~ 7~05869~* 9~03068~: 12~04191~'),
  (10555, 13, 7, 12, 'Shuppim also, and Huppim, the children of Ir, and Hushim, the sons of Aher.', '0~08206~ 3~02650~, 5~01121~ 7~05893~, [8] 9~02366~, 11~01121~ 13~0313~.'),
  (22053, 27, 11, 8, 'And shall also carry captives into Egypt their gods, with their princes, and with their precious vessels of silver and of gold; and he shall continue more years than the king of the north.', '3~0935~ 4~07628~ 6~04714~ 8~0430~, 11~05257~, [12] 15~02532~ 16~03627~ 18~03701~ 21~02091~; 25~05975~ [26] 27~08141~ 30~04428~ 33~06828~.'),
  (16993, 20, 20, 30, 'The blueness of a wound cleanseth away evil: so do stripes the inward parts of the belly.', '&para; 1~02250~ 4~06482~ 5~08562~ 7~07451~: [9] 10~04347~ 13~02315~ 16~0990~.'),
  (4145, 4, 14, 32, 'But as for you, your carcases, they shall fall in this wilderness.', '[1 2] 5~06297~, 8~05307~ 11~04057~.'),
  (12283, 15, 10, 22, 'And of the sons of Pashur; Elioenai, Maaseiah, Ishmael, Nethaneel, Jozabad, and Elasah.', '3~01121~ 5~06583~; 6~0454~, 7~04641~, 8~03458~, 9~05417~, 10~03107~, 12~0501~.'),
  (1029, 1, 35, 13, 'And God went up from him in the place where he talked with him.', '1~0430~ 3~05927~ 8~04725~ 11~01696~'),
  (17478, 21, 8, 11, 'Because sentence against an evil work is not executed speedily, therefore the heart of the sons of men is fully set in them to do evil.', '1~06599~ 4~07451~ 5~04639~ 8~06213~ 9~04120~, 12~03820~ 15~01121~ 17~0120~ 20~04390~ 24~06213~ 25~07451~.'),
  (21503, 26, 40, 17, 'Then brought he me into the outward court, and, lo, there were chambers, and a pavement made for the court round about: thirty chambers were upon the pavement.', '1~0935~ 6~02435~ 7~02691~, [10 11] 12~03957~, 15~07531~ 16~06213~ 19~02691~ 21~05439~: 22~07970~ 23~03957~ [24] 27~07531~.'),
  (10842, 13, 16, 14, 'He is the LORD our God; his judgments are in all the earth.', '[1] 3~03068~ 5~0430~; 7~04941~ [8] 12~0776~.'),
  (10674, 13, 10, 7, 'And when all the men of Israel that were in the valley saw that they fled, and that Saul and his sons were dead, then they forsook their cities, and fled: and the Philistines came and dwelt in them.', '4~0376~ 6~03478~ [8] 11~06010~ 12~07200~ 15~05127~, 18~07586~ 21~01121~ 23~04191~, 26~05800~ 28~05892~, 30~05127~: 33~06430~ 34~0935~ 36~03427~'),
  (12527, 16, 9, 7, 'Thou art the LORD the God, who didst choose Abram, and broughtest him forth out of Ur of the Chaldees, and gavest him the name of Abraham;', '[1] 3~03068~ 5~0430~, 8~0977~ 9~087~, 13~03318~ 16~0218~ 19~03778~, 21~07760~ 24~08034~ 26~085~;'),
  (28500, 46, 6, 17, 'But he that is joined unto the Lord is one spirit.', '0~1161~ 4~2853~ 7~2962~ 8~2076~ 9~1520~ 10~4151~.'),
  (21562, 26, 42, 1, 'Then he brought me forth into the utter court, the way toward the north: and he brought me into the chamber that was over against the separate place, and which was before the building toward the north.', '&para; 4~03318~ 7~02435~ 8~02691~, 11~01870~ 13~06828~: 16~0935~ 20~03957~ [22] 27~01508~, [30] 33~01146~ 36~06828~.'),
  (30243, 58, 12, 15, 'Looking diligently lest any man fail of the grace of God; lest any root of bitterness springing up trouble you, and thereby many be defiled;', '1~1983~ 2~3361~ 4~5100~ 5~5302~ 6~575~ 8~5485~ 10~2316~; 11~3361~ 12~5100~ 13~4491~ 15~4088~ 16~5453~ 17~507~ 18~1776~ [19] 20~2532~ 21~5026~ 22~1223~* 23~4183~ 25~3392~;'),
  (26627, 43, 12, 32, 'And I, if I be lifted up from the earth, will draw all men unto me.', '1~2504~, 2~1437~ 6~5312~ 7~1537~ 9~1093~, 11~1670~ 12~3956~ [13] 14~4314~ 15~1683~.'),
  (6458, 6, 22, 25, 'For the LORD hath made Jordan a border between us and you, ye children of Reuben and children of Gad; ye have no part in the LORD: so shall your children make our children cease from fearing the LORD.', '2~03068~ 4~05414~ 5~03383~ 7~01366~ 13~01121~ 15~07205~ 17~01121~ 19~01410~; 23~02506~ 26~03068~: 30~01121~ 31~07673~ 33~01121~ 34~07673~ 35~01115~ 36~03372~ 38~03068~.'),
  (10590, 13, 8, 7, 'And Naaman, and Ahiah, and Gera, he removed them, and begat Uzza, and Ahihud.', '1~05283~, 3~0281~, 5~01617~, 7~01540~ 10~03205~ 11~05798~, 13~0284~.'),
  (2778, 3, 2, 11, 'No meat offering, which ye shall bring unto the LORD, shall be made with leaven: for ye shall burn no leaven, nor any honey, in any offering of the LORD made by fire.', '&para; 2~04503~, 6~07126~ 9~03068~, 12~06213~ 14~02557~: 18~06999~ 20~07603~, 23~01706~, 26~0801~ 29~03068~ 32~0801~.'),
  (4422, 4, 23, 1, 'And Balaam said unto Balak, Build me here seven altars, and prepare me here seven oxen and seven rams.', '&para; 1~01109~ 2~0559~ 4~01111~, 5~01129~ 8~07651~ 9~04196~, 11~03559~ 14~07651~ 15~06499~ 17~07651~ 18~0352~.'),
  (25186, 42, 6, 28, 'Bless them that curse you, and pray for them which despitefully use you.', '0~2127~ 3~2672~ 4~5213~, 5~2532~ 6~4336~ 7~5228~ 11~1908~ 12~5209~.'),
  (1880, 2, 13, 8, 'And thou shalt shew thy son in that day, saying, This is done because of that which the LORD did unto me when I came forth out of Egypt.', '3~05046~ 5~01121~ 8~03117~, 9~0559~, [10 12] 14~05668~ 15~02088~ [16] 18~03068~ 19~06213~ 25~03318~ 28~04714~.'),
  (1750, 2, 9, 3, 'Behold, the hand of the LORD is upon thy cattle which is in the field, upon the horses, upon the asses, upon the camels, upon the oxen, and upon the sheep: there shall be a very grievous murrain.', '2~03027~ 5~03068~ 6~01961~ 9~04735~ [11] 14~07704~, 17~05483~, 20~02543~, 23~01581~, 26~01241~, 30~06629~: [31 33] 35~03966~ 36~03515~ 37~01698~.'),
  (17069, 20, 23, 16, 'Yea, my reins shall rejoice, when thy lips speak right things.', '2~03629~ 4~05937~, 7~08193~ 8~01696~ 10~04339~.'),
  (8004, 9, 30, 19, 'And there was nothing lacking to them, neither small nor great, neither sons nor daughters, neither spoil, nor any thing that they had taken to them: David recovered all.', '4~05737~ 7~04480~ 8~06996~ 10~01419~, 12~01121~ 14~01323~, 16~07998~, [19] 23~03947~ 26~01732~ 27~07725~'),
  (18963, 24, 1, 8, 'Be not afraid of their faces: for I am with thee to deliver thee, saith the LORD.', '2~03372~ 5~06440~: [8] 12~05337~ 14~05002~ 16~03068~.'),
  (15151, 19, 78, 29, 'So they did eat, and were well filled: for he gave them their own desire;', '3~0398~, 6~03966~ 7~07646~: 10~0935~ 14~08378~;'),
  (26905, 43, 20, 22, 'And when he had said this, he breathed on them, and saith unto them, Receive ye the Holy Ghost:', '0~2532~ 4~2036~ 5~5124~, 8~1720~ [9] 10~2532~ 11~3004~ 13~846~, 15~2983~ 17~40~ 18~4151~:'),
  (15524, 19, 101, 2, 'I will behave myself wisely in a perfect way. O when wilt thou come unto me? I will walk within my house with a perfect heart.', '4~07919~ 7~08549~ 8~01870~. 13~0935~ 18~01980~ 19~07130~ 21~01004~ 24~08537~ 25~03824~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (3, 1, 1, 3, 'And God said, Let there be light: and there was light.', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~0559~, 5~01961~ 6~0216~: 10~0216~.'),
  (18543, 23, 44, 1, 'Yet now hear, O Jacob my servant; and Israel, whom I have chosen:', '&para; 2~08085~, 4~03290~ 6~05650~; 8~03478~, 12~0977~:'),
  (12238, 15, 8, 28, 'And I said unto them, Ye are holy unto the LORD; the vessels are holy also; and the silver and the gold are a freewill offering unto the LORD God of your fathers.', '2~0559~ [6] 7~06944~ 10~03068~; 12~03627~ [13] 14~06944~ 18~03701~ 21~02091~ [22] 25~05071~ 28~03068~ 29~0430~ 32~01~.'),
  (14731, 19, 53, 3, 'Every one of them is gone back: they are altogether become filthy; there is none that doeth good, no, not one.', '6~05472~: 9~03162~ 11~0444~; [12 13] 16~06213~ 17~02896~, 20~0259~.'),
  (5610, 5, 27, 19, 'Cursed be he that perverteth the judgment of the stranger, fatherless, and widow. And all the people shall say, Amen.', '0~0779~ [1] 4~05186~ 6~04941~ 9~01616~, 10~03490~, 12~0490~. 16~05971~ 18~0559~, 19~0543~.'),
  (19520, 24, 23, 27, 'Which think to cause my people to forget my name by their dreams which they tell every man to his neighbour, as their fathers have forgotten my name for Baal.', '1~02803~ 5~05971~ 7~07911~ 9~08034~ 12~02472~ 15~05608~ 17~0376~ 20~07453~, 23~01~ 25~07911~ 27~08034~ 29~01168~.'),
  (22572, 32, 3, 5, 'So the people of Nineveh believed God, and proclaimed a fast, and put on sackcloth, from the greatest of them even to the least of them.', '&para; 2~0582~ 4~05210~ 5~0539~ 6~0430~, 8~07121~ 10~06685~, 12~03847~ 14~08242~, 17~01419~ 23~06996~'),
  (3159, 3, 14, 43, 'And if the plague come again, and break out in the house, after that he hath taken away the stones, and after he hath scraped the house, and after it is plastered;', '3~05061~ 5~07725~, 7~06524~ 11~01004~, 12~0310~ 16~02502~ 19~068~, 21~0310~ 24~07096~ 26~01004~, 28~0310~ 31~02902~;'),
  (16520, 20, 4, 21, 'Let them not depart from thine eyes; keep them in the midst of thine heart.', '3~03868~ 6~05869~; 7~08104~ 11~08432~ 14~03824~.'),
  (4461, 4, 24, 10, 'And Balak''s anger was kindled against Balaam, and he smote his hands together: and Balak said unto Balaam, I called thee to curse mine enemies, and, behold, thou hast altogether blessed them these three times.', '&para; 1~01111~ 2~0639~ 4~02734~ 6~01109~, 9~05606~ 11~03709~ 12~05606~: 14~01111~ 15~0559~ 17~01109~, 19~07121~ 22~06895~ 24~0341~, 29~01288~ 30~01288~ [31] 33~07969~ 34~06471~.'),
  (12626, 16, 11, 29, 'And at Enrimmon, and at Zareah, and at Jarmuth,', '2~05884~, 5~06881~, 8~03412~,'),
  (271, 1, 11, 4, 'And they said, Go to, let us build us a city and a tower, whose top may reach unto heaven; and let us make us a name, lest we be scattered abroad upon the face of the whole earth.', '2~0559~, 4~03051~, 7~01129~ 10~05892~ 13~04026~, 15~07218~ [16 17] 19~08064~; 23~06213~ 26~08034~, 31~06327~ 34~06440~ 38~0776~.'),
  (21662, 26, 45, 23, 'And seven days of the feast he shall prepare a burnt offering to the LORD, seven bullocks and seven rams without blemish daily the seven days; and a kid of the goats daily for a sin offering.', '1~07651~ 2~03117~ 5~02282~ 8~06213~ 11~05930~ 14~03068~, 15~07651~ 16~06499~ 18~07651~ 19~0352~ 21~08549~ 22~03117~ 24~07651~ 25~03117~; 28~08163~ 31~05795~ 32~03117~ [33] 36~02403~.'),
  (9664, 12, 5, 9, 'So Naaman came with his horses and with his chariot, and stood at the door of the house of Elisha.', '&para; 1~05283~ 2~0935~ 5~05483~ 9~07393~, 11~05975~ 14~06607~ 17~01004~ 19~0477~.'),
