VALUES
  (1740, 2, 8, 25, 'And Pharaoh called for Moses and for Aaron, and said, Go ye, sacrifice to your God in the land.', '1~06547~ 2~07121~ 3~0413~ 4~04872~ 7~0175~, 9~0559~, 10~03212~ 12~02076~ 15~0430~ 18~0776~.'),
  (12911, 18, 2, 11, 'Now when Job''s three friends heard of all this evil that was come upon him, they came every one from his own place; Eliphaz the Temanite, and Bildad the Shuhite, and Zophar the Naamathite: for they had made an appointment together to come to mourn with him and to comfort him.', '&para; 2~0347~ 3~07969~ 4~07453~ 5~08085~ 9~07451~ 12~0935~ 16~0935~ 18~0376~ 22~04725~; 23~0464~ 25~08489~, 27~01085~ 29~07747~, 31~06691~ 33~05284~: 39~03259~ 40~03162~ 42~0935~ 44~05110~ 49~05162~'),
  (22195, 28, 7, 8, 'Ephraim, he hath mixed himself among the people; Ephraim is a cake not turned.', '&para; 0~0669~, 3~01101~ 7~05971~; 8~0669~ 11~05692~ 13~02015~.'),
  (400, 1, 16, 15, 'And Hagar bare Abram a son: and Abram called his son''s name, which Hagar bare, Ishmael.', '&para; 1~01904~ 2~03205~ 3~087~ 5~01121~: 7~087~ 8~07121~ 10~01121~ 11~08034~, 13~01904~ 14~03205~, 15~03458~.'),
  (3801, 4, 5, 4, 'And the children of Israel did so, and put them out without the camp: as the LORD spake unto Moses, so did the children of Israel.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 6~06213~, 10~07971~ 11~02351~ 13~04264~: 16~03068~ 17~01696~ 19~04872~, 21~06213~ 23~01121~ 25~03478~.'),
  (21883, 27, 4, 37, 'Now I Nebuchadnezzar praise and extol and honour the King of heaven, all whose works are truth, and his ways judgment: and those that walk in pride he is able to abase.', '0~03705~ 1~0576~ 2~05020~ 3~07624~ 5~07313~ 7~01922~ 9~04430~ 11~08065~, 12~03606~ 14~04567~ [15] 16~07187~, 19~0735~ 20~01780~: 24~01981~ 26~01467~ 29~03202~ 31~08214~.'),
  (16499, 20, 3, 35, 'The wise shall inherit glory: but shame shall be the promotion of fools.', '1~02450~ 3~05157~ 4~03519~: 6~07036~ 10~07311~ 12~03684~.'),
  (22730, 34, 3, 9, 'Ethiopia and Egypt were her strength, and it was infinite; Put and Lubim were thy helpers.', '0~03568~ 2~04714~ [3] 5~06109~, [7 8] 9~07097~ 10~0369~;* 11~06316~ 13~03864~ 16~05833~.'),
  (19572, 24, 25, 29, 'For, lo, I begin to bring evil on the city which is called by my name, and should ye be utterly unpunished? Ye shall not be unpunished: for I will call for a sword upon all the inhabitants of the earth, saith the LORD of hosts.', '3~02490~ 6~07489~ 9~05892~ 12~07121~ 15~08034~, 20~05352~ 21~05352~? 26~05352~: 30~07121~ 33~02719~ 37~03427~ 40~0776~, 41~05002~ 43~03068~ 45~06635~.'),
  (3326, 3, 20, 3, 'And I will set my face against that man, and will cut him off from among his people; because he hath given of his seed unto Molech, to defile my sanctuary, and to profane my holy name.', '3~05414~ 5~06440~ 8~0376~, 13~03772~ 15~07130~ 17~05971~; 21~05414~ 24~02233~ 26~04432~, 28~02930~ 30~04720~, 33~02490~ 35~06944~ 36~08034~.'),
  (7122, 7, 21, 13, 'And the whole congregation sent some to speak to the children of Benjamin that were in the rock Rimmon, and to call peaceably unto them.', '3~05712~ 4~07971~ [5] 7~01696~ 10~01121~ 12~01144~ [14] 17~05553~ 18~07417~, 21~07121~ 22~07965~'),
  (6070, 6, 9, 27, 'And Joshua made them that day hewers of wood and drawers of water for the congregation, and for the altar of the LORD, even unto this day, in the place which he should choose.', '1~03091~ 2~05414~ 5~03117~ 6~02404~ 8~06086~ 10~07579~ 12~04325~ 15~05712~, 19~04196~ 22~03068~, 26~03117~, 29~04725~ 33~0977~.'),
  (29601, 52, 2, 15, 'Who both killed the Lord Jesus, and their own prophets, and have persecuted us; and they please not God, and are contrary to all men:', '1~2532~ 2~615~ 4~2962~ 5~2424~, 6~2532~ 8~2398~ 9~4396~, 10~2532~ 12~1559~ 13~2248~; 14~2532~ 16~700~ 17~3361~ 18~2316~, 19~2532~ 21~1727~ 23~3956~ 24~444~:'),
  (12349, 16, 3, 13, 'The valley gate repaired Hanun, and the inhabitants of Zanoah; they built it, and set up the doors thereof, the locks thereof, and the bars thereof, and a thousand cubits on the wall unto the dung gate.', '1~01516~ 2~08179~ 3~02388~ 4~02586~, 7~03427~ 9~02182~; 11~01129~ 15~05975~ 17~01817~ 20~04514~ 24~01280~ 28~0505~ 29~0520~ 32~02346~ 35~0830~ 36~08179~.'),
  (29194, 48, 5, 16, 'This I say then, Walk in the Spirit, and ye shall not fulfil the lust of the flesh.', '[0] 2~3004~ 3~1161~, 4~4043~ 7~4151~, 8~2532~ 10~5055~ 11~3364~ 12~5055~ 14~1939~ 17~4561~.'),
  (3081, 3, 13, 24, 'Or if there be any flesh, in the skin whereof there is a hot burning, and the quick flesh that burneth have a white bright spot, somewhat reddish, or white;', '[4] 5~01320~, 8~05785~ [10 11] 13~0784~ 14~04348~, 17~04241~ [18] 20~04348~ 23~03836~ 25~0934~, 27~0125~, 29~03836~;'),
  (19862, 24, 36, 11, 'When Michaiah the son of Gemariah, the son of Shaphan, had heard out of the book all the words of the LORD,', '1~04321~ 3~01121~ 5~01587~, 7~01121~ 9~08227~, 11~08085~ 15~05612~ 18~01697~ 21~03068~,'),
  (8062, 10, 2, 6, 'And now the LORD shew kindness and truth unto you: and I also will requite you this kindness, because ye have done this thing.', '3~03068~ 4~06213~ 5~02617~ 7~0571~ 14~06213~ 17~02896~, 21~06213~ 23~01697~.'),
  (13888, 18, 40, 15, 'Behold now behemoth, which I made with thee; he eateth grass as an ox.', '&para; 2~0930~, 5~06213~ 9~0398~ 10~02682~ 13~01241~.'),
  (12712, 17, 1, 1, 'Now it came to pass in the days of Ahasuerus, (this is Ahasuerus which reigned, from India even unto Ethiopia, over an hundred and seven and twenty provinces:)', '&para; 7~03117~ 9~0325~, [11] 12~0325~ 14~04427~, 16~01912~ 19~03568~, [20] 22~03967~ 24~07651~ 26~06242~ 27~04082~:)'),
  (27959, 45, 1, 13, 'Now I would not have you ignorant, brethren, that oftentimes I purposed to come unto you, (but was let hitherto,) that I might have some fruit among you also, even as among other Gentiles.', '0~1161~ 2~2309~ 3~3756~ 4~50~ 5~5209~ 6~50~, 7~80~, 8~3754~ 9~4178~ 11~4388~ 13~2064~ 14~4314~ 15~5209~, 16~2532~* 19~2967~ 20~1204~ 21~891~,)* 22~2443~ 25~2192~ 26~5100~ 27~2590~ 28~1722~ 29~5213~ 30~2532~, 32~2532~ 33~2531~* 34~1722~ 35~3062~ 36~1484~.'),
  (650, 1, 24, 55, 'And her brother and her mother said, Let the damsel abide with us a few days, at the least ten; after that she shall go.', '2~0251~ 5~0517~ 6~0559~, 9~05291~ 10~03427~ [13 14] 15~03117~, 18~0176~ 19~06218~; 20~0310~ 24~03212~.'),
  (14648, 19, 48, 5, 'They saw it, and so they marvelled; they were troubled, and hasted away.', '1~07200~ [2 3] 6~08539~; 9~0926~, [10] 12~02648~.'),
  (21227, 26, 30, 14, 'And I will make Pathros desolate, and will set fire in Zoan, and will execute judgments in No.', '4~06624~ 5~08074~, 8~05414~ 9~0784~ 11~06814~, 14~06213~ 15~08201~ 17~04996~.'),
  (11019, 13, 23, 28, 'Because their office was to wait on the sons of Aaron for the service of the house of the LORD, in the courts, and in the chambers, and in the purifying of all holy things, and the work of the service of the house of God;', '2~04612~ [3] 5~03027~ 8~01121~ 10~0175~ 13~05656~ 16~01004~ 19~03068~, 22~02691~, 26~03957~, 30~02893~ 34~06944~, 37~04639~ 40~05656~ 43~01004~ 45~0430~;'),
  (13447, 18, 24, 2, 'Some remove the landmarks; they violently take away flocks, and feed thereof.', '[0] 1~05381~ 3~01367~; 7~01497~ 8~05739~, 10~07462~ [11]'),
  (9689, 12, 6, 7, 'Therefore said he, Take it up to thee. And he put out his hand, and took it.', '1~0559~ [4] 5~07311~ 11~07971~ 13~03027~, 15~03947~'),
  (14704, 19, 51, 4, 'Against thee, thee only, have I sinned, and done this evil in thy sight: that thou mightest be justified when thou speakest, and be clear when thou judgest.', '6~02398~, 8~06213~ [9] 10~07451~ 13~05869~: 18~06663~ 21~01696~, [22] 24~02135~ 27~08199~.'),
  (18848, 23, 60, 18, 'Violence shall no more be heard in thy land, wasting nor destruction within thy borders; but thou shalt call thy walls Salvation, and thy gates Praise.', '0~02555~ 5~08085~ 8~0776~, 9~07701~ 11~07667~ 14~01366~; 18~07121~ 20~02346~ 21~03444~, 24~08179~ 25~08416~.'),
  (17588, 22, 3, 8, 'They all hold swords, being expert in war: every man hath his sword upon his thigh because of fear in the night.', '2~0270~ 3~02719~, [4] 5~03925~ 7~04421~: 9~0376~ [10] 12~02719~ 15~03409~ 18~06343~ 21~03915~.'),
  (1625, 2, 4, 19, 'And the LORD said unto Moses in Midian, Go, return into Egypt: for all the men are dead which sought thy life.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~ 7~04080~, 8~03212~, 9~07725~ 11~04714~: 15~0582~ 17~04191~ 19~01245~ 21~05315~.'),
  (28511, 46, 7, 8, 'I say therefore to the unmarried and widows, It is good for them if they abide even as I.', '1~3004~ 2~1161~ 5~22~ 6~2532~ 7~5503~, 9~2076~ 10~2570~ 12~846~ 13~1437~ 15~3306~ 16~2504~ 17~5613~ 18~2504~.'),
  (30056, 58, 5, 10, 'Called of God an high priest after the order of Melchisedec.', '&para; 0~4316~ 1~5259~ 2~2316~ 5~749~ 6~2596~ 8~5010~ 10~3198~.'),
  (8667, 10, 23, 6, 'But the sons of Belial shall be all of them as thorns thrust away, because they cannot be taken with hands:', '[1 2] 4~01100~ [5 6] 11~06975~ 13~05074~, 18~03947~ 20~03027~:'),
  (20316, 24, 52, 31, 'And it came to pass in the seven and thirtieth year of the captivity of Jehoiachin king of Judah, in the twelfth month, in the five and twentieth day of the month, that Evilmerodach king of Babylon in the first year of his reign lifted up the head of Jehoiachin king of Judah, and brought him forth out of prison,', '&para; 7~07651~ 9~07970~ 10~08141~ 13~01546~ 15~03078~ 16~04428~ 18~03063~, 21~06240~ 22~08147~* 23~02320~, 26~02568~ 28~06242~ [29] 32~02320~, [33] 34~0192~ 35~04428~ 37~0894~ [40] 41~08141~ 44~04438~ 46~05375~ 48~07218~ 50~03078~ 51~04428~ 53~03063~, 57~03318~ 60~03628~ 61~01004~,*'),
  (15290, 19, 85, 10, 'Mercy and truth are met together; righteousness and peace have kissed each other.', '0~02617~ 2~0571~ 5~06298~; 6~06664~ 8~07965~ 10~05401~ [11 12]'),
  (29479, 50, 4, 21, 'Salute every saint in Christ Jesus. The brethren which are with me greet you.', '0~782~ 1~3956~ 2~40~ 3~1722~ 4~5547~ 5~2424~. 7~80~ 10~4862~ 11~1698~ 12~782~ 13~5209~.'),
  (4555, 4, 26, 60, 'And unto Aaron was born Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.', '2~0175~ 4~03205~ 5~05070~, 7~030~, 8~0499~, 10~0385~.'),
  (28938, 47, 7, 6, 'Nevertheless God, that comforteth those that are cast down, comforted us by the coming of Titus;', '0~235~ 1~2316~, 3~3870~ 8~5011~, 9~3870~ 10~2248~ 11~1722~ 13~3952~ 15~5103~;'),
  (24922, 42, 1, 18, 'And Zacharias said unto the angel, Whereby shall I know this? for I am an old man, and my wife well stricken in years.', '0~2532~ 1~2197~ 2~2036~ 3~4314~ 5~32~, 6~5101~ 7~2596~ 9~1097~ 10~5124~? 11~1063~ 12~1473~ 13~1510~ 16~4246~, 17~2532~ 18~3450~ 19~1135~ 21~4260~ 22~1722~ 23~846~ 24~2250~.*'),
  (18883, 23, 63, 8, 'For he said, Surely they are my people, children that will not lie: so he was their Saviour.', '2~0559~, [5] 7~05971~, 8~01121~ [9] 12~08266~: 17~03467~.'),
  (25745, 42, 18, 43, 'And immediately he received his sight, and followed him, glorifying God: and all the people, when they saw it, gave praise unto God.', '0~2532~ 1~3916~ 5~308~, 6~2532~ 7~190~ 8~846~, 9~1392~ 10~2316~: 11~2532~ 12~3956~ 14~2992~, 17~1492~ [18] 19~1325~ 20~136~ 22~2316~.'),
  (13310, 18, 19, 4, 'And be it indeed that I have erred, mine error remaineth with myself.', '3~0551~ [4] 7~07686~, 9~04879~ 10~03885~'),
  (22128, 28, 2, 14, 'Therefore, behold, I will allure her, and bring her into the wilderness, and speak comfortably unto her.', '&para; 4~06601~ 7~03212~ 11~04057~, 13~01696~ 14~03820~'),
  (25667, 42, 17, 2, 'It were better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and he cast into the sea, than that he should offend one of these little ones.', '2~3081~ 4~846~ 5~1487~ 7~3684~ 8~3458~ 9~4029~ 10~4012~ 11~846~ 12~5137~, 13~2532~ 15~4496~ 16~1519~ 18~2281~, 19~2228~ 20~2443~ 23~4624~ 24~1520~ 26~5130~ 28~3398~.'),
  (30917, 66, 12, 10, 'And I heard a loud voice saying in heaven, Now is come salvation, and strength, and the kingdom of our God, and the power of his Christ: for the accuser of our brethren is cast down, which accused them before our God day and night.', '0~2532~ 2~191~ 4~3173~ 5~5456~ 6~3004~ 7~1722~ 8~3772~, 9~737~ 11~1096~ 12~4991~, 13~2532~ 14~1411~, 15~2532~ 17~932~ 19~2257~ 20~2316~, 21~2532~ 23~1849~ 25~846~ 26~5547~: 27~3754~ 29~2723~ 31~2257~ 32~80~ 35~2598~, 36~3588~ 37~2725~ 38~846~ 39~1799~ 40~2257~ 41~2316~ 42~2250~ 43~2532~ 44~3571~.'),
  (20106, 24, 48, 17, 'All ye that are about him, bemoan him; and all ye that know his name, say, How is the strong staff broken, and the beautiful rod!', '4~05439~ 6~05110~ 12~03045~ 14~08034~, 15~0559~, 19~05797~ 20~04294~ 21~07665~, [22] 24~08597~ 25~04731~!'),
  (20996, 26, 22, 11, 'And one hath committed abomination with his neighbour''s wife; and another hath lewdly defiled his daughter in law; and another in thee hath humbled his sister, his father''s daughter.', '1~0376~ 3~06213~ 4~08441~ 7~07453~ 8~0802~; 10~0376~ 12~02154~ 13~02930~ 17~03618~; 19~0376~ 23~06031~ 25~0269~, 27~01~ 28~01323~.'),
  (4590, 4, 28, 7, 'And the drink offering thereof shall be the fourth part of an hin for the one lamb: in the holy place shalt thou cause the strong wine to be poured unto the LORD for a drink offering.', '3~05262~ [5 6] 8~07243~ [9] 12~01969~ 15~0259~ 16~03532~: 19~06944~ [20] 26~07941~ 29~05258~ 32~03068~ [33] 36~05262~.'),
  (1307, 1, 43, 12, 'And take double money in your hand; and the money that was brought again in the mouth of your sacks, carry it again in your hand; peradventure it was an oversight:', '1~03947~ 2~04932~ 3~03701~ 6~03027~; 9~03701~ 13~07725~ 16~06310~ 19~0572~, [21] 22~07725~ 25~03027~; [28] 30~04870~:'),
  (16740, 20, 12, 12, 'The wicked desireth the net of evil men: but the root of the righteous yieldeth fruit.', '&para; 1~07563~ 2~02530~ 4~04685~ 6~07451~ [7] 10~08328~ 13~06662~ 14~05414~ [15]'),
  (18858, 23, 61, 6, 'But ye shall be named the Priests of the LORD: men shall call you the Ministers of our God: ye shall eat the riches of the Gentiles, and in their glory shall ye boast yourselves.', '4~07121~ 6~03548~ 9~03068~: [10] 12~0559~ 15~08334~ 18~0430~: 21~0398~ 23~02428~ 26~01471~, 30~03519~ 33~03235~'),
  (6618, 7, 4, 12, 'And they shewed Sisera that Barak the son of Abinoam was gone up to mount Tabor.', '2~05046~ 3~05516~ 5~01301~ 7~01121~ 9~042~ 12~05927~ 14~02022~ 15~08396~.'),
  (20409, 25, 3, 46, 'All our enemies have opened their mouths against us.', '2~0341~ 4~06475~ 6~06310~'),
  (8198, 10, 7, 11, 'And as since the time that I commanded judges to be over my people Israel, and have caused thee to rest from all thine enemies. Also the LORD telleth thee that he will make thee an house.', '4~03117~ 7~06680~ 8~08199~ [9 10] 13~05971~ 14~03478~, 20~05117~ 24~0341~. 27~03068~ 28~05046~ 33~06213~ 36~01004~.'),
  (7140, 8, 1, 6, 'Then she arose with her daughters in law, that she might return from the country of Moab: for she had heard in the country of Moab how that the Lord had visited his people in giving them bread.', '&para; 2~06965~ 7~03618~, 11~07725~ 14~07704~ 16~04124~: 20~08085~ 23~07704~ 25~04124~ 29~03068~ 31~06485~ 33~05971~ 35~05414~ 37~03899~.'),
  (11644, 14, 21, 11, 'Moreover he made high places in the mountains of Judah, and caused the inhabitants of Jerusalem to commit fornication, and compelled Judah thereto.', '2~06213~ 4~01116~ 7~02022~ 9~03063~, 13~03427~ 15~03389~ 18~02181~, 20~05080~ 21~03063~ [22]'),
  (10553, 13, 7, 10, 'The sons also of Jediael; Bilhan: and the sons of Bilhan; Jeush, and Benjamin, and Ehud, and Chenaanah, and Zethan, and Tharshish, and Ahishahar.', '1~01121~ 4~03043~; 5~01092~: 8~01121~ 10~01092~; 11~03274~, 13~01144~, 15~0164~, 17~03668~, 19~02133~, 21~08659~, 23~0300~.'),
  (13402, 18, 22, 4, 'Will he reprove thee for fear of thee? will he enter with thee into judgment?', '2~03198~ 5~03374~ 10~0935~ 14~04941~?'),
  (29792, 54, 5, 13, 'And withal they learn to be idle, wandering about from house to house; and not only idle, but tattlers also and busybodies, speaking things which they ought not.', '0~2532~ 1~1161~* 2~260~ 4~3129~ [5 6] 7~692~, 9~4022~ 13~3614~; 14~1161~ 15~3756~ 16~3440~ 17~692~, 18~235~ 19~5397~ 20~2532~ 21~2532~ 22~4021~, 23~2980~ 25~3588~ 27~1163~ 28~3361~.'),
  (17242, 20, 29, 9, 'If a wise man contendeth with a foolish man, whether he rage or laugh, there is no rest.', '&para; [0] 2~02450~ 3~0376~ 4~08199~ 7~0191~ 8~0376~, 11~07264~ 13~07832~, [14 15] 17~05183~.'),
  (5603, 5, 27, 12, 'These shall stand upon mount Gerizim to bless the people, when ye are come over Jordan; Simeon, and Levi, and Judah, and Issachar, and Joseph, and Benjamin:', '2~05975~ 4~02022~ 5~01630~ 7~01288~ 9~05971~, 14~05674~ 15~03383~; 16~08095~, 18~03878~, 20~03063~, 22~03485~, 24~03130~, 26~01144~:'),
  (13288, 18, 18, 3, 'Wherefore are we counted as beasts, and reputed vile in your sight?', '3~02803~ 5~0929~, [6] 8~02933~ 11~05869~?'),
  (25014, 42, 2, 29, 'Lord, now lettest thou thy servant depart in peace, according to thy word:', '0~1203~, 1~3568~ 3~630~ 4~4675~ 5~1401~ 6~630~ 7~1722~ 8~1515~, 9~2596~ 11~4675~ 12~4487~:'),
  (6568, 7, 2, 16, 'Nevertheless the LORD raised up judges, which delivered them out of the hand of those that spoiled them.', '2~03068~ 4~06965~ 5~08199~, 7~03467~ 12~03027~ 16~08154~'),
  (19598, 24, 26, 17, 'Then rose up certain of the elders of the land, and spake to all the assembly of the people, saying,', '2~06965~ 3~0582~ 6~02205~ 9~0776~, 11~0559~ 15~06951~ 18~05971~, 19~0559~,'),
  (13112, 18, 10, 17, 'Thou renewest thy witnesses against me, and increasest thine indignation upon me; changes and war are against me.', '1~02318~ 3~05707~ 7~07235~ 9~03708~ 11~05978~; 12~02487~ 14~06635~ [15]'),
  (16655, 20, 9, 8, 'Reprove not a scorner, lest he hate thee: rebuke a wise man, and he will love thee.', '0~03198~ 3~03887~, 6~08130~ 8~03198~ 11~02450~, 15~0157~'),
  (7419, 9, 9, 21, 'And Saul answered and said, Am not I a Benjamite, of the smallest of the tribes of Israel? and my family the least of all the families of the tribe of Benjamin? wherefore then speakest thou so to me?', '1~07586~ 2~06030~ 4~0559~, [5] 9~01145~, 12~06996~ 15~07626~ 17~03478~? 20~04940~ 22~06810~ 26~04940~ 29~07626~ 31~01144~? 34~01696~ 36~01697~'),
  (25845, 42, 21, 5, 'And as some spake of the temple, how it was adorned with goodly stones and gifts, he said,', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~5100~ 3~3004~ 4~4012~ 6~2411~, 7~3754~ 10~2885~ 12~2570~ 13~3037~ 14~2532~ 15~334~, 17~2036~,'),
  (4693, 4, 31, 23, 'Every thing that may abide the fire, ye shall make it go through the fire, and it shall be clean: nevertheless it shall be purified with the water of separation: and all that abideth not the fire ye shall make go through the water.', '1~01697~ 4~0935~ 6~0784~, [10] 12~05674~ 14~0784~, 19~02891~: 24~02398~ 27~04325~ 29~05079~: 33~0935~ 36~0784~ 41~05674~ 43~04325~.'),
  (19446, 24, 20, 15, 'Cursed be the man who brought tidings to my father, saying, A man child is born unto thee; making him very glad.', '0~0779~ [1] 3~0376~ 6~01319~ 9~01~, 10~0559~, 12~02145~ 13~01121~ 15~03205~ 20~08055~ 21~08055~.'),
  (16780, 20, 13, 24, 'He that spareth his rod hateth his son: but he that loveth him chasteneth him betimes.', '&para; 2~02820~ 4~07626~ 5~08130~ 7~01121~: 11~0157~ 13~04148~ 15~07836~.'),
  (17882, 23, 10, 23, 'For the Lord GOD of hosts shall make a consumption, even determined, in the midst of all the land.', '2~0136~ 3~03069~ 5~06635~ 7~06213~ 9~03617~, 11~02782~, 14~07130~ 18~0776~.'),
  (6204, 6, 14, 10, 'And now, behold, the LORD hath kept me alive, as he said, these forty and five years, even since the LORD spake this word unto Moses, while the children of Israel wandered in the wilderness: and now, lo, I am this day fourscore and five years old.', '4~03068~ 8~02421~, 11~01696~, 13~0705~ 15~02568~ 16~08141~, 18~0227~ 20~03068~ 21~01696~ 23~01697~ 25~04872~, [27 29] 30~03478~ 31~01980~ 34~04057~: [39] 41~03117~ 42~08084~ 44~02568~ 45~08141~ 46~01121~.'),
  (30102, 58, 7, 22, 'By so much was Jesus made a surety of a better testament.', '0~2596~ 2~5118~ 3~1096~ 4~2424~ 5~1096~ 7~1450~ 10~2909~ 11~1242~.'),
  (24546, 41, 8, 35, 'For whosoever will save his life shall lose it; but whosoever shall lose his life for my sake and the gospel''s, the same shall save it.', '0~1063~ 1~302~ 2~3739~* 3~2309~ 4~4982~ 5~846~ 6~5590~ 8~622~ 9~846~; 10~1161~ 11~302~ 12~3739~ 13~622~ 14~846~ 15~5590~ 16~1752~ 18~1700~ 19~2532~ 21~2098~, 23~3778~ 25~4982~ 26~846~.'),
  (3635, 4, 1, 26, 'Of the children of Judah, by their generations, after their families, by the house of their fathers, according to the number of the names, from twenty years old and upward, all that were able to go forth to war;', '2~01121~ 4~03063~, 7~08435~, 10~04940~, 13~01004~ 16~01~, 20~04557~ 23~08034~, 25~06242~ 26~08141~ 27~01121~ 29~04605~, 36~03318~ 38~06635~;'),
  (19759, 24, 32, 19, 'Great in counsel, and mighty in work: for thine eyes are open upon all the ways of the sons of men: to give every one according to his ways, and according to the fruit of his doings:', '0~01419~ 2~06098~, 4~07227~ 6~05950~: 9~05869~ [10] 11~06491~ 15~01870~ 18~01121~ 20~0120~: 22~05414~ 24~0376~ 28~01870~, 33~06529~ 36~04611~:'),
  (22419, 30, 3, 15, 'And I will smite the winter house with the summer house; and the houses of ivory shall perish, and the great houses shall have an end, saith the LORD.', '3~05221~ 5~02779~ 6~01004~ 9~07019~ 10~01004~; 13~01004~ 15~08127~ 17~06~, 20~07227~ 21~01004~ 25~05486~, 26~05002~ 28~03068~.'),
  (27350, 44, 11, 27, 'And in these days came prophets from Jerusalem unto Antioch.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~1722~ 2~5025~ 3~2250~ 4~2718~ 5~4396~ 6~575~ 7~2414~ 8~1519~ 9~490~.'),
  (19635, 24, 28, 8, 'The prophets that have been before me and before thee of old prophesied both against many countries, and against great kingdoms, of war, and of evil, and of pestilence.', '1~05030~ 5~06440~ 8~06440~ 11~05769~ 12~05012~ 15~07227~ 16~0776~, 19~01419~ 20~04467~, 22~04421~, 25~07451~, 28~01698~.'),
  (13793, 18, 37, 15, 'Dost thou know when God disposed them, and caused the light of his cloud to shine?', '2~03045~ 4~0433~ 5~07760~ 10~0216~ 13~06051~ 15~03313~?'),
  (3739, 4, 3, 42, 'And Moses numbered, as the LORD commanded him, all the firstborn among the children of Israel.', '1~04872~ 2~06485~, 5~03068~ 6~06680~ 10~01060~ 13~01121~ 15~03478~.'),
  (2250, 2, 26, 10, 'And thou shalt make fifty loops on the edge of the one curtain that is outmost in the coupling, and fifty loops in the edge of the curtain which coupleth the second.', '3~06213~ 4~02572~ 5~03924~ 8~08193~ 11~0259~ 12~03407~ [13 14] 15~07020~ 18~02279~, 20~02572~ 21~03924~ 24~08193~ 27~03407~ 29~02279~ 31~08145~.'),
  (863, 1, 30, 29, 'And he said unto him, Thou knowest how I have served thee, and how thy cattle was with me.', '2~0559~ 6~03045~ 7~0834~ 10~05647~ 13~0834~ 15~04735~'),
  (21224, 26, 30, 11, 'He and his people with him, the terrible of the nations, shall be brought to destroy the land: and they shall draw their swords against Egypt, and fill the land with the slain.', '3~05971~ 7~06184~ 10~01471~, 13~0935~ 15~07843~ 17~0776~: 21~07324~ 23~02719~ 25~04714~, 27~04390~ 29~0776~ 32~02491~.'),
  (1394, 1, 46, 3, 'And he said, I am God, the God of thy father: fear not to go down into Egypt; for I will there make of thee a great nation:', '2~0559~, [4] 5~0410~, 7~0430~ 10~01~: 11~03372~ 15~03381~ 17~04714~; 22~07760~ 26~01419~ 27~01471~:'),
  (29224, 49, 1, 2, 'Grace be to you, and peace, from God our Father, and from the Lord Jesus Christ.', '0~5485~ [1] 3~5213~, 4~2532~ 5~1515~, 6~575~ 7~2316~ 8~2257~ 9~3962~, 10~2532~ [11] 13~2962~ 14~2424~ 15~5547~.'),
  (27408, 44, 13, 30, 'But God raised him from the dead:', '0~1161~ 1~2316~ 2~1453~ 3~846~ 4~1537~ 6~3498~:'),
  (10244, 12, 25, 14, 'And the pots, and the shovels, and the snuffers, and the spoons, and all the vessels of brass wherewith they ministered, took they away.', '2~05518~, 5~03257~, 8~04212~, 11~03709~, 15~03627~ 17~05178~ 20~08334~, 23~03947~.'),
  (15772, 19, 109, 8, 'Let his days be few; and let another take his office.', '2~03117~ 4~04592~; [5] 7~0312~ 8~03947~ 10~06486~.'),
  (27496, 44, 15, 38, 'But Paul thought not good to take him with them, who departed from them from Pamphylia, and went not with them to the work.', '0~1161~ 1~3972~ 2~515~ 3~3361~ 4~515~ 6~4838~ 7~5126~ 9~4838~, 10~3588~ 11~868~ 12~575~ 13~846~ 14~575~ 15~3828~, 16~2532~ 17~4905~ 18~3361~ 20~846~ 21~1519~ 23~2041~.'),
  (5559, 5, 25, 6, 'And it shall be, that the firstborn which she beareth shall succeed in the name of his brother which is dead, that his name be not put out of Israel.', '[4] 6~01060~ 9~03205~ 11~06965~ 14~08034~ 17~0251~ [18 19] 20~04191~, 23~08034~ 27~04229~ 29~03478~.'),
  (24122, 40, 26, 58, 'But Peter followed him afar off unto the high priest''s palace, and went in, and sat with the servants, to see the end.', '0~1161~ 1~4074~ 2~190~ 3~846~ 5~3113~ 6~575~* 7~2193~ 10~749~ 11~833~, 12~2532~ 13~1525~ 14~2080~, 16~2521~ 17~3326~ 19~5257~, 21~1492~ 23~5056~.'),
  (27217, 44, 8, 25, 'And they, when they had testified and preached the word of the Lord, returned to Jerusalem, and preached the gospel in many villages of the Samaritans.', '2~3767~ 3~3303~ 5~1263~ 6~2532~ 7~2980~ 9~3056~ 12~2962~, 13~5290~ 14~1519~ 15~2419~, 16~5037~ 19~2097~ 21~4183~ 22~2968~ 25~4541~.'),
  (29392, 50, 1, 15, 'Some indeed preach Christ even of envy and strife; and some also of good will:', '0~5100~ 1~3303~ 2~2784~ 3~5547~ 4~2532~ 5~1223~ 6~5355~ 7~2532~ 8~2054~; 9~1161~ 10~5100~ 11~2532~ 12~1223~ 14~2107~:'),
  (23349, 40, 7, 23, 'And then will I profess unto them, I never knew you: depart from me, ye that work iniquity.', '0~2532~ 1~5119~ 4~3670~ 6~846~ 7~3754~,* 9~3763~ 10~1097~ 11~5209~: 12~672~ 13~575~ 14~1700~, 17~2038~ 18~458~.'),
  (2790, 3, 3, 7, 'If he offer a lamb for his offering, then shall he offer it before the LORD.', '2~07126~ 4~03775~ 7~07133~, 11~07126~ 13~06440~ 15~03068~.'),
  (30794, 66, 4, 10, 'The four and twenty elders fall down before him that sat on the throne, and worship him that liveth for ever and ever, and cast their crowns before the throne, saying,', '1~5064~ 2~2532~ 3~1501~ 4~4245~ 6~4098~ 7~1799~ 10~2521~ 11~1909~ 13~2362~, 14~2532~ 15~4352~ 18~2198~ 19~1519~ 20~165~ 22~165~, 23~2532~ 24~906~ 25~846~ 26~4735~ 27~1799~ 29~2362~, 30~3004~,');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (14371, 19, 32, 7, 'Thou art my hiding place; thou shalt preserve me from trouble; thou shalt compass me about with songs of deliverance. Selah.', '&para; [1] 4~05643~; 7~05341~ 10~06862~; 13~05437~ 17~07438~ 19~06405~. 20~05542~.'),
  (12268, 15, 10, 7, 'And they made proclamation throughout Judah and Jerusalem unto all the children of the captivity, that they should gather themselves together unto Jerusalem;', '3~05674~ 4~06963~* 6~03063~ 8~03389~ 12~01121~ 15~01473~, 21~06908~ 23~03389~;'),
  (13865, 18, 39, 22, 'He mocketh at fear, and is not affrighted; neither turneth he back from the sword.', '1~07832~ 3~06343~, 7~02865~; 11~07725~ 12~06440~ 14~02719~.'),
  (23608, 40, 14, 1, 'At that time Herod the tetrarch heard of the fame of Jesus,', '&para; 0~1722~ 1~1565~ 2~2540~ 3~2264~ 5~5076~ 6~191~ 9~189~ 11~2424~,'),
  (348, 1, 14, 8, 'And there went out the king of Sodom, and the king of Gomorrah, and the king of Admah, and the king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (the same is Zoar;) and they joined battle with them in the vale of Siddim;', '3~03318~ 5~04428~ 7~05467~, 10~04428~ 12~06017~, 15~04428~ 17~0126~, 20~04428~ 22~06636~, 25~04428~ 27~01106~ 29~01931~ [30] 31~06820~;) 34~06186~ 35~04421~ 40~06010~ 42~07708~;'),
  (30198, 58, 11, 10, 'For he looked for a city which hath foundations, whose builder and maker is God.', '0~1063~ 3~1551~ 5~4172~ 7~2192~ 8~2310~, 9~3739~ 10~5079~ 11~2532~ 12~1217~ [13] 14~2316~.'),
  (10601, 13, 8, 18, 'Ishmerai also, and Jezliah, and Jobab, the sons of Elpaal;', '0~03461~ 3~03152~, 5~03103~, 7~01121~ 9~0508~;'),
  (17323, 20, 31, 30, 'Favour is deceitful, and beauty is vain: but a woman that feareth the LORD, she shall be praised.', '0~02580~ [1] 2~08267~, 4~03308~ [5] 6~01892~: [7] 9~0802~ [10] 11~03373~ 13~03068~, 17~01984~.'),
  (10516, 13, 6, 54, 'Now these are their dwelling places throughout their castles in their coasts, of the sons of Aaron, of the families of the Kohathites: for theirs was the lot.', '&para; [2] 5~04186~ 8~02918~ 11~01366~, 14~01121~ 16~0175~, 19~04940~ 22~06956~: 27~01486~.'),
  (658, 1, 24, 63, 'And Isaac went out to meditate in the field at the eventide: and he lifted up his eyes, and saw, and, behold, the camels were coming.', '1~03327~ 3~03318~ 5~07742~ 8~07704~ 9~06437~ 11~06153~: 15~05375~ 17~05869~, 19~07200~, 23~01581~ [24] 25~0935~.'),
  (6245, 6, 15, 36, 'And Sharaim, and Adithaim, and Gederah, and Gederothaim; fourteen cities with their villages:', '1~08189~, 3~05723~, 5~01449~, 7~01453~; 8~06240~ 9~0702~* 10~05892~ 13~02691~:'),
  (15239, 19, 81, 13, 'Oh that my people had hearkened unto me, and Israel had walked in my ways!', '0~03863~ 3~05971~ 5~08085~ [8] 9~03478~ 11~01980~ 14~01870~!'),
  (26205, 43, 4, 34, 'Jesus saith unto them, My meat is to do the will of him that sent me, and to finish his work.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 4~1699~ 5~1033~ 6~2076~ 7~2443~ 8~4160~ 10~2307~ 14~3992~ 15~3165~, 16~2532~ 18~5048~ 19~846~ 20~2041~.'),
  (4136, 4, 14, 23, 'Surely they shall not see the land which I sware unto their fathers, neither shall any of them that provoked me see it:', '3~0518~ 4~07200~ 6~0776~ 9~07650~ 12~01~, 19~05006~ 21~07200~'),
  (8732, 11, 1, 7, 'And he conferred with Joab the son of Zeruiah, and with Abiathar the priest: and they following Adonijah helped him.', '2~01697~ 4~03097~ 6~01121~ 8~06870~, 11~054~ 13~03548~: 16~0310~ 17~0138~ 18~05826~ [19]'),
  (2824, 3, 4, 24, 'And he shall lay his hand upon the head of the goat, and kill it in the place where they kill the burnt offering before the LORD: it is a sin offering.', '3~05564~ 5~03027~ 8~07218~ 11~08163~, 13~07819~ 17~04725~ 20~07819~ 23~05930~ 24~06440~ 26~03068~: [28] 31~02403~.'),
  (2520, 2, 34, 19, 'All that openeth the matrix is mine; and every firstling among thy cattle, whether ox or sheep, that is male.', '2~06363~ 4~07358~ [5] 9~06363~ 12~04735~, [13] 14~07794~ 16~07716~, [17 19] 19~02142~.'),
  (16865, 20, 16, 16, 'How much better is it to get wisdom than gold! and to get understanding rather to be chosen than silver!', '&para; 2~02896~ [3 4] 6~07069~ 7~02451~ 9~02742~! 12~07069~ 13~0998~ 17~0977~ 19~03701~!'),
  (11791, 14, 28, 18, 'The Philistines also had invaded the cities of the low country, and of the south of Judah, and had taken Bethshemesh, and Ajalon, and Gederoth, and Shocho with the villages thereof, and Timnah with the villages thereof, Gimzo also and the villages thereof: and they dwelt there.', '1~06430~ 4~06584~ 6~05892~ 10~08219~, 14~05045~ 16~03063~, 19~03920~ 20~01053~, 22~0357~, 24~01450~, 26~07755~ 29~01323~ 32~08553~ 35~01323~ 37~01579~ 41~01323~ 45~03427~'),
  (28229, 45, 11, 4, 'But what saith the answer of God unto him? I have reserved to myself seven thousand men, who have not bowed the knee to the image of Baal.', '0~235~ 1~5101~ 2~3004~ 6~5538~ 8~846~? 11~2641~ 13~1683~ 15~2035~ 16~435~, 17~3748~ 18~2578~ 19~3756~ 20~2578~ 22~1119~ [24 26] 27~896~.'),
  (30205, 58, 11, 17, 'By faith Abraham, when he was tried, offered up Isaac: and he that had received the promises offered up his only begotten son.', '1~4102~ 2~11~, 6~3985~, 8~4374~ 9~2464~: 10~2532~ 14~324~ 16~1860~ 18~4374~ 21~3439~ [22]'),
  (20236, 24, 51, 15, 'He hath made the earth by his power, he hath established the world by his wisdom, and hath stretched out the heaven by his understanding.', '2~06213~ 4~0776~ 7~03581~, 10~03559~ 12~08398~ 15~02451~, 19~05186~ 21~08064~ 24~08394~.'),
  (2701, 2, 39, 32, 'Thus was all the work of the tabernacle of the tent of the congregation finished: and the children of Israel did according to all that the LORD commanded Moses, so did they.', '&para; 4~05656~ 7~04908~ 10~0168~ 13~04150~ 14~03615~: 17~01121~ 19~03478~ 20~06213~ 26~03068~ 27~06680~ 28~04872~, 30~06213~'),
  (20879, 26, 18, 21, 'But if the wicked will turn from all his sins that he hath committed, and keep all my statutes, and do that which is lawful and right, he shall surely live, he shall not die.', '&para; 3~07563~ 5~07725~ 9~02403~ 13~06213~, 15~08104~ 18~02708~, 20~06213~ 24~04941~ 26~06666~, 29~02421~ 30~02421~, 34~04191~.'),
  (19925, 24, 38, 21, 'But if thou refuse to go forth, this is the word that the LORD hath shewed me:', '3~03986~ 6~03318~, [8] 10~01697~ 13~03068~ 15~07200~'),
  (25067, 42, 3, 30, 'Which was the son of Simeon, which was the son of Juda, which was the son of Joseph, which was the son of Jonan, which was the son of Eliakim,', '[2 3] 5~4826~, [8 9] 11~2455~, [14 15] 17~2501~, [20 21] 23~2494~, [26 27] 29~1662~,'),
  (20941, 26, 20, 37, 'And I will cause you to pass under the rod, and I will bring you into the bond of the covenant:', '6~05674~ 9~07626~, 13~0935~ 17~04562~ 20~01285~:'),
  (25870, 42, 21, 30, 'When they now shoot forth, ye see and know of your own selves that summer is now nigh at hand.', '0~3752~ 2~2235~ 4~4261~, 6~991~ 8~1097~ 9~575~ 12~1438~ 13~3754~ 14~2330~ 15~2076~ 16~2235~ 19~1451~.'),
  (10921, 13, 19, 6, 'And when the children of Ammon saw that they had made themselves odious to David, Hanun and the children of Ammon sent a thousand talents of silver to hire them chariots and horsemen out of Mesopotamia, and out of Syriamaachah, and out of Zobah.', '&para; 3~01121~ 5~05983~ 6~07200~ 12~0887~ 14~01732~, 15~02586~ 18~01121~ 20~05983~ 21~07971~ 23~0505~ 24~03603~ 26~03701~ 28~07936~ 30~07393~ 32~06571~ 35~0763~, 39~04601~ 40~0758~,* 44~06678~.'),
  (29153, 48, 4, 6, 'And because ye are sons, God hath sent forth the Spirit of his Son into your hearts, crying, Abba, Father.', '0~1161~ 1~3754~ 3~2075~ 4~5207~, 5~2316~ 8~1821~ 10~4151~ 12~846~ 13~5207~ 14~1519~ 15~5216~ 16~2588~, 17~2896~, 18~5~, 19~3962~.'),
  (17445, 21, 7, 7, 'Surely oppression maketh a wise man mad; and a gift destroyeth the heart.', '&para; 1~06233~ 5~02450~ 6~01984~; 9~04979~ 10~06~ 12~03820~.'),
  (24400, 41, 5, 26, 'And had suffered many things of many physicians, and had spent all that she had, and was nothing bettered, but rather grew worse,', '0~2532~ 2~3958~ 4~4183~ 5~5259~ 6~4183~ 7~2395~, 8~2532~ 10~1159~ 11~3956~ 13~1438~ 14~3844~, 15~2532~ 16~5623~ 17~3367~ 18~5623~, 19~235~ 20~3123~ 21~2064~ 22~5501~ 23~1519~,*'),
  (4596, 4, 28, 13, 'And a several tenth deal of flour mingled with oil for a meat offering unto one lamb; for a burnt offering of a sweet savour, a sacrifice made by fire unto the LORD.', '4~06241~ 6~05560~ 7~01101~ 9~08081~ [10] 13~04503~ 15~0259~ 16~03532~; [17] 20~05930~ 23~05207~ 24~07381~, 29~0801~ 32~03068~.'),
  (16276, 19, 140, 4, 'Keep me, O LORD, from the hands of the wicked; preserve me from the violent man; who have purposed to overthrow my goings.', '0~08104~ 3~03068~, 6~03027~ 9~07563~; 10~05341~ 14~02555~ 15~0376~; 18~02803~ 20~01760~ 22~06471~.'),
  (397, 1, 16, 12, 'And he will be a wild man; his hand will be against every man, and every man''s hand against him; and he shall dwell in the presence of all his brethren.', '5~06501~ 6~0120~; 8~03027~ [9 10] 17~03027~ 23~07931~ 26~06440~ 30~0251~.'),
  (27344, 44, 11, 21, 'And the hand of the Lord was with them: and a great number believed, and turned unto the Lord.', '0~2532~ 2~5495~ 5~2962~ 6~2258~ 7~3326~ 8~846~: 9~5037~ 11~4183~ 12~706~ 13~4100~, 15~1994~ 16~1909~ 18~2962~.'),
  (29963, 57, 1, 9, 'Yet for love''s sake I rather beseech thee, being such an one as Paul the aged, and now also a prisoner of Jesus Christ.', '1~1223~ 2~26~ 4~3870~ 5~3123~ 6~3870~ [7] 8~5607~ 11~5108~ 12~5613~ 13~3972~ 15~4246~, 16~1161~ 17~3570~ 18~2532~ 20~1198~ 22~2424~ 23~5547~.'),
  (17849, 23, 9, 11, 'Therefore the LORD shall set up the adversaries of Rezin against him, and join his enemies together;', '2~03068~ 5~07682~ 7~06862~ 9~07526~ 13~05526~ 15~0341~ 16~05526~;'),
  (19414, 24, 18, 21, 'Therefore deliver up their children to the famine, and pour out their blood by the force of the sword; and let their wives be bereaved of their children, and be widows; and let their men be put to death; let their young men be slain by the sword in battle.', '2~05414~ 4~01121~ 7~07458~, 10~05064~ [12] 15~03027~ 18~02719~; 22~0802~ 24~07909~ [29] 30~0490~; 34~0582~ 36~02026~ 38~04194~; [39] 42~0970~ [43] 44~05221~ 47~02719~ 49~04421~.'),
  (7968, 9, 28, 19, 'Moreover the LORD will also deliver Israel with thee into the hand of the Philistines: and to morrow shalt thou and thy sons be with me: the LORD also shall deliver the host of Israel into the hand of the Philistines.', '2~03068~ 5~05414~ 6~03478~ 11~03027~ 14~06430~: 17~04279~ [18] 22~01121~ [23] 27~03068~ 30~05414~ 32~04264~ 34~03478~ 37~03027~ 40~06430~.'),
  (17449, 21, 7, 11, 'Wisdom is good with an inheritance: and by it there is profit to them that see the sun.', '&para; 0~02451~ [1] 2~02896~ 5~05159~: [7 10] 11~03148~ 15~07200~ 17~08121~.'),
  (29626, 52, 4, 7, 'For God hath not called us unto uncleanness, but unto holiness.', '0~1063~ 1~2316~ 2~2564~ 3~3756~ 4~2564~ 5~2248~ 6~1909~ 7~167~, 8~235~ 9~1722~ 10~38~.'),
  (1708, 2, 7, 18, 'And the fish that is in the river shall die, and the river shall stink; and the Egyptians shall loathe to drink of the water of the river.', '2~01710~ [4] 7~02975~ 9~04191~, 12~02975~ 14~0887~; 17~04714~ 19~03811~ 21~08354~ 24~04325~ 27~02975~.'),
  (17607, 22, 4, 16, 'Awake, O north wind; and come, thou south; blow upon my garden, that the spices thereof may flow out. Let my beloved come into his garden, and eat his pleasant fruits.', '0~05782~, 3~06828~; 5~0935~, 7~08486~; 8~06315~ 11~01588~, [12] 14~01314~ 18~05140~. 21~01730~ 22~0935~ 25~01588~, 27~0398~ 29~04022~ 30~06529~.'),
  (13912, 18, 41, 15, 'His scales are his pride, shut up together as with a close seal.', '[0] 1~0650~ [2 2~04043~ 3] 4~01346~, 7~05462~ [8 9] 11~06862~ 12~02368~.'),
  (1318, 1, 43, 23, 'And he said, Peace be to you, fear not: your God, and the God of your father, hath given you treasure in your sacks: I had your money. And he brought Simeon out unto them.', '2~0559~, 3~07965~ [4] 7~03372~ 10~0430~, 13~0430~ 16~01~, 18~05414~ 20~04301~ 23~0572~: 25~0935~ 27~03701~. 30~03318~ 31~08095~'),
  (18201, 23, 28, 28, 'Bread corn is bruised; because he will not ever be threshing it, nor break it with the wheel of his cart, nor bruise it with his horsemen.', '0~03899~ [1] 3~01854~; 8~05331~ 10~0156~ 11~01758~* 14~02000~ [15 16] 18~01536~ 21~05699~, 23~01854~ [25] 27~06571~.'),
  (8390, 10, 14, 27, 'And unto Absalom there were born three sons, and one daughter, whose name was Tamar: she was a woman of a fair countenance.', '2~053~ 5~03205~ 6~07969~ 7~01121~, 9~0259~ 10~01323~, 12~08034~ [13] 14~08559~: 18~0802~ 21~03303~ 22~04758~.'),
  (12203, 15, 7, 21, 'And I, even I Artaxerxes the king, do make a decree to all the treasurers which are beyond the river, that whatsoever Ezra the priest, the scribe of the law of the God of heaven, shall require of you, it be done speedily,', '1~04481~, [2] 3~0576~ 4~0783~ 6~04430~, 8~07761~ 10~02942~ 12~03606~ 14~01490~ [16] 17~05675~ 19~05103~, 22~05831~ 24~03549~, 26~05613~ 29~01882~ 32~0426~ 34~08065~, 36~07593~ 41~05648~ 42~0629~,'),
  (8955, 11, 7, 13, 'And king Solomon sent and fetched Hiram out of Tyre.', '&para; 1~04428~ 2~08010~ 3~07971~ 5~03947~ 6~02438~ 9~06865~.'),
  (11951, 14, 34, 9, 'And when they came to Hilkiah the high priest, they delivered the money that was brought into the house of God, which the Levites that kept the doors had gathered of the hand of Manasseh and Ephraim, and of all the remnant of Israel, and of all Judah and Benjamin; and they returned to Jerusalem.', '3~0935~ 5~02518~ 7~01419~ 8~03548~, 10~05414~ 12~03701~ 15~0935~ 18~01004~ 20~0430~, 23~03881~ 25~08104~ 27~05592~ 29~0622~ 32~03027~ 34~04519~ 36~0669~, 41~07611~ 43~03478~, 47~03063~ 49~01144~; 52~07725~ 54~03389~.'),
  (20772, 26, 16, 1, 'Again the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (375, 1, 15, 11, 'And when the fowls came down upon the carcases, Abram drove them away.', '3~05861~ 5~03381~ 8~06297~, 9~087~ 12~05380~.'),
  (15068, 19, 74, 11, 'Why withdrawest thou thy hand, even thy right hand? pluck it out of thy bosom.', '1~07725~ 4~03027~, 8~03225~? 9~03615~ [10] 12~07130~ 14~02436~ 15~02436~.*'),
  (10125, 12, 20, 19, 'Then said Hezekiah unto Isaiah, Good is the word of the LORD which thou hast spoken. And he said, Is it not good, if peace and truth be in my days?', '1~0559~ 2~02396~ 4~03470~, 5~02896~ [6] 8~01697~ 11~03068~ 15~01696~. 18~0559~, [19 20] [22] 24~07965~ 26~0571~ 30~03117~?'),
  (8983, 11, 7, 41, 'The two pillars, and the two bowls of the chapiters that were on the top of the two pillars; and the two networks, to cover the two bowls of the chapiters which were upon the top of the pillars;', '1~08147~ 2~05982~, [5] 6~01543~ 9~03805~ [11] 14~07218~ 17~08147~ 18~05982~; 21~08147~ 22~07639~, 24~03680~ 26~08147~ 27~01543~ 30~03805~ [32] 35~07218~ 38~05982~;'),
  (7848, 9, 24, 2, 'Then Saul took three thousand chosen men out of all Israel, and went to seek David and his men upon the rocks of the wild goats.', '1~07586~ 2~03947~ 3~07969~ 4~0505~ 5~0977~ 6~0376~ 10~03478~, 12~03212~ 14~01245~ 15~01732~ 18~0582~ 19~06440~ 21~06697~ 25~03277~.'),
  (24939, 42, 1, 35, 'And the angel answered and said unto her, The Holy Ghost shall come upon thee, and the power of the Highest shall overshadow thee: therefore also that holy thing which shall be born of thee shall be called the Son of God.', '0~2532~ 2~32~ 3~611~ 5~2036~ 7~846~, 9~40~ 10~4151~ 12~1904~ 13~1909~ 14~4571~, 15~2532~ 17~1411~ 20~5310~ 22~1982~ 23~4671~: 24~1352~ 25~2532~ 28~40~ 32~1080~ 33~1537~ 34~4675~ 37~2564~ 39~5207~ 41~2316~.'),
  (87, 1, 4, 7, 'If thou doest well, shalt thou not be accepted? and if thou doest not well, sin lieth at the door. And unto thee shall be his desire, and thou shalt rule over him.', '0~0518~ 3~03190~, 8~07613~? 14~03190~, 15~02403~ 16~07257~ 19~06607~. [23 24] 26~08669~, 30~04910~'),
  (10653, 13, 9, 30, 'And some of the sons of the priests made the ointment of the spices.', '[1] 4~01121~ 7~03548~ 8~07543~ 10~04842~ 13~01314~.'),
  (19301, 24, 13, 26, 'Therefore will I discover thy skirts upon thy face, that thy shame may appear.', '3~02834~ 5~07757~ 8~06440~, 11~07036~ 13~07200~.'),
  (7072, 7, 20, 11, 'So all the men of Israel were gathered against the city, knit together as one man.', '3~0376~ 5~03478~ 7~0622~ 10~05892~, 12~02270~ 14~0259~ 15~0376~.'),
  (10794, 13, 14, 12, 'And when they had left their gods there, David gave a commandment, and they were burned with fire.', '4~05800~ 6~0430~ 8~01732~ 11~0559~, 15~08313~ 17~0784~.'),
  (11389, 14, 9, 17, 'Moreover the king made a great throne of ivory, and overlaid it with pure gold.', '2~04428~ 3~06213~ 5~01419~ 6~03678~ 8~08127~, 10~06823~ 13~02889~ 14~02091~.'),
  (16180, 19, 133, 2, 'It is like the precious ointment upon the head, that ran down upon the beard, even Aaron''s beard: that went down to the skirts of his garments;', '[0 1] 4~02896~ 5~08081~ 8~07218~, 11~03381~ 14~02206~, [15] 16~0175~ 17~02206~: 20~03381~ 23~06310~ 26~04060~;'),
  (15047, 19, 73, 18, 'Surely thou didst set them in slippery places: thou castedst them down into destruction.', '3~07896~ 7~02513~: 11~05307~ 13~04876~.'),
  (29256, 49, 2, 11, 'Wherefore remember, that ye being in time past Gentiles in the flesh, who are called Uncircumcision by that which is called the Circumcision in the flesh made by hands;', '&para; 0~1352~ 1~3421~, 2~3754~ 3~5210~ [4] 7~4218~ 8~1484~ 9~1722~ 11~4561~, 12~3588~ 14~3004~ 15~203~ 16~5259~ 18~3588~ 20~3004~ 22~4061~ 23~1722~ 25~4561~ 28~5499~;'),
  (25225, 42, 7, 18, 'And the disciples of John shewed him of all these things.', '0~2532~ 2~3101~ 4~2491~ 5~518~ 6~846~ 7~4012~ 8~3956~ 10~5130~.'),
  (25916, 42, 22, 38, 'And they said, Lord, behold, here are two swords. And he said unto them, It is enough.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~, 3~2962~, 4~2400~, 5~5602~ [6] 7~1417~ 8~3162~. 9~1161~ 11~2036~ 13~846~, 15~2076~ 16~2425~.'),
  (15556, 19, 102, 26, 'They shall perish, but thou shalt endure: yea, all of them shall wax old like a garment; as a vesture shalt thou change them, and they shall be changed:', '2~06~, 6~05975~: 13~01086~ 16~0899~; 19~03830~ 22~02498~ 28~02498~:'),
  (12155, 15, 5, 12, 'But after that our fathers had provoked the God of heaven unto wrath, he gave them into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon, the Chaldean, who destroyed this house, and carried the people away into Babylon.', '0~03861~ 1~04481~ 4~02~ 6~07265~ 8~0426~ 10~08065~ 12~07265~, 14~03052~ 15~01994~ 18~03028~ 20~05020~ 22~04430~ 24~0895~, 26~03679~, 28~05642~ 29~01836~ 30~01005~, 32~01541~ 34~05972~ 35~01541~ 37~0895~.'),
  (20258, 24, 51, 37, 'And Babylon shall become heaps, a dwellingplace for dragons, an astonishment, and an hissing, without an inhabitant.', '1~0894~ 4~01530~, 6~04583~ 8~08577~, 10~08047~, 13~08322~, 16~03427~.'),
  (503, 1, 20, 4, 'But Abimelech had not come near her: and he said, Lord, wilt thou slay also a righteous nation?', '1~040~ 5~07126~ 9~0559~, 10~0136~, 13~02026~ 16~06662~ 17~01471~?'),
  (24304, 41, 3, 6, 'And the Pharisees went forth, and straightway took counsel with the Herodians against him, how they might destroy him.', '0~2532~ 2~5330~ 4~1831~, 6~2112~ 7~4160~ 8~4824~ 9~3326~ 11~2265~ 12~2596~ 13~846~, 14~3704~ 17~622~ 18~846~.'),
  (20373, 25, 3, 10, 'He was unto me as a bear lying in wait, and as a lion in secret places.', '[1] [4] 6~01677~ 9~0693~, [10 11] 13~0738~ 16~04565~.'),
  (13131, 18, 11, 14, 'If iniquity be in thine hand, put it far away, and let not wickedness dwell in thy tabernacles.', '1~0205~ [2] 5~03027~, 9~07368~, 13~05766~ 14~07931~ 17~0168~.'),
  (17173, 20, 26, 23, 'Burning lips and a wicked heart are like a potsherd covered with silver dross.', '&para; 0~01814~ 1~08193~ 4~07451~ 5~03820~ [6 7] 9~02789~ 10~06823~ 12~03701~ 13~05509~.'),
  (25490, 42, 12, 18, 'And he said, This will I do: I will pull down my barns, and build greater; and there will I bestow all my fruits and my goods.', '0~2532~ 2~2036~, 3~5124~ 6~4160~: 10~2507~ 11~3450~ 12~596~, 13~2532~ 14~3618~ 15~3187~; 16~2532~ 17~1563~ 20~4863~ 21~3956~ 22~3450~ 23~1081~ 24~2532~ 25~3450~ 26~18~.'),
  (7898, 9, 25, 30, 'And it shall come to pass, when the LORD shall have done to my lord according to all the good that he hath spoken concerning thee, and shall have appointed thee ruler over Israel;', '8~03068~ 11~06213~ 14~0113~ 19~02896~ 23~01696~ 29~06680~ 31~05057~ 33~03478~;'),
  (16131, 19, 127, 1, 'A Song of degrees for Solomon. Except the LORD build the house, they labour in vain that build it: except the LORD keep the city, the watchman waketh but in vain.', '&para; [0 1~07892~ 3~04609~ 5] 5~08010~ 8~03068~ 9~01129~ 11~01004~, 13~05998~ 15~07723~ 17~01129~ 21~03068~ 22~08104~ 24~05892~, 26~08104~ 27~08245~ [28] 30~07723~.'),
  (21412, 26, 37, 6, 'And I will lay sinews upon you, and will bring up flesh upon you, and cover you with skin, and put breath in you, and ye shall live; and ye shall know that I am the LORD.', '3~05414~ 4~01517~ 10~05927~ 11~01320~ 15~07159~ 18~05785~, 20~05414~ 21~07307~ 27~02421~; 31~03045~ [34] 36~03068~.'),
  (23385, 40, 8, 30, 'And there was a good way off from them an herd of many swine feeding.', '0~1161~ 2~2258~ 6~3112~ 7~575~ 8~846~ 10~34~ 12~4183~ 13~5519~ 14~1006~.'),
  (16215, 19, 136, 10, 'To him that smote Egypt in their firstborn: for his mercy endureth for ever:', '&para; 3~05221~ 4~04714~ 7~01060~: 10~02617~ [11] 13~05769~:'),
  (15946, 19, 119, 39, 'Turn away my reproach which I fear: for thy judgments are good.', '&para; 1~05674~ 3~02781~ 6~03025~: 9~04941~ [10] 11~02896~.'),
  (29264, 49, 2, 19, 'Now therefore ye are no more strangers and foreigners, but fellowcitizens with the saints, and of the household of God;', '0~3767~ 1~686~ 3~2075~ 5~3765~ 6~3581~ 7~2532~ 8~3941~, 9~235~ 10~4847~ 13~40~, 14~2532~ 17~3609~ 19~2316~;'),
  (24756, 41, 13, 28, 'Now learn a parable of the fig tree; When her branch is yet tender, and putteth forth leaves, ye know that summer is near:', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~3129~ 3~3850~ 4~575~ 7~4808~; 8~3752~ 9~846~ 10~2798~ 11~1096~ 12~2235~ 13~527~, 14~2532~ 16~1631~ 17~5444~, 19~1097~ 20~3754~ 21~2330~ 22~2076~ 23~1451~:'),
  (11149, 13, 27, 32, 'Also Jonathan David''s uncle was a counsellor, a wise man, and a scribe: and Jehiel the son of Hachmoni was with the king''s sons:', '1~03083~ 2~01732~ 3~01730~ 6~03289~, 8~0995~ 9~0376~, 12~05608~: 14~03171~ 16~01121~ 18~02453~ [19] 22~04428~ 23~01121~:'),
  (10002, 12, 17, 11, 'And there they burnt incense in all the high places, as did the heathen whom the LORD carried away before them; and wrought wicked things to provoke the LORD to anger:', '4~06999~ 9~01116~, [11] 13~01471~ 16~03068~ 18~01540~ 19~06440~ 22~06213~ 23~07451~ 24~01697~ 28~03068~ 30~03707~:'),
  (2486, 2, 33, 8, 'And it came to pass, when Moses went out unto the tabernacle, that all the people rose up, and stood every man at his tent door, and looked after Moses, until he was gone into the tabernacle.', '6~04872~ 8~03318~ 11~0168~, [12] 15~05971~ 17~06965~, 19~05324~ 21~0376~ [22] 24~0168~ 25~06607~, 27~05027~ 28~0310~ 29~04872~, 33~0935~ 36~0168~.'),
  (14783, 19, 57, 6, 'They have prepared a net for my steps; my soul is bowed down: they have digged a pit before me, into the midst whereof they are fallen themselves. Selah.', '2~03559~ 4~07568~ 7~06471~; 9~05315~ 12~03721~: 15~03738~ 17~07882~ 18~06440~ 22~08432~ 26~05307~ [27] 28~05542~.'),
  (28261, 45, 11, 36, 'For of him, and through him, and to him, are all things: to whom be glory for ever. Amen.', '0~3754~ 1~1537~ 2~846~, 3~2532~ 4~1223~ 5~846~, 6~2532~ 7~1519~ 8~846~, [9] 11~3956~: 13~846~ [14] 15~1391~ 16~1519~ 17~165~. 18~281~.'),
  (30011, 58, 2, 18, 'For in that he himself hath suffered being tempted, he is able to succour them that are tempted.', '0~1063~ 1~1722~ 2~3739~ 3~3958~ 4~846~ 6~3958~ 8~3985~, 11~1410~ 13~997~ 17~3985~.'),
  (6478, 6, 23, 11, 'Take good heed therefore unto yourselves, that ye love the LORD your God.', '&para; 1~03966~ 2~08104~ 5~05315~, 8~0157~ 10~03068~ 12~0430~.'),
  (2962, 3, 9, 4, 'Also a bullock and a ram for peace offerings, to sacrifice before the LORD; and a meat offering mingled with oil: for to day the LORD will appear unto you.', '2~07794~ 5~0352~ 8~08002~, 10~02076~ 11~06440~ 13~03068~; 17~04503~ 18~01101~ 20~08081~: 23~03117~ 25~03068~ 27~07200~'),
  (7630, 9, 17, 5, 'And he had an helmet of brass upon his head, and he was armed with a coat of mail; and the weight of the coat was five thousand shekels of brass.', '[1 2] 4~03553~ 6~05178~ 9~07218~, [12] 13~03847~ 16~08302~ 18~07193~; 21~04948~ 24~08302~ [25] 26~02568~ 27~0505~ 28~08255~ 30~05178~.'),
  (24254, 41, 1, 29, 'And forthwith, when they were come out of the synagogue, they entered into the house of Simon and Andrew, with James and John.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~2112~, 5~1831~ 7~1537~ 9~4864~, 11~2064~ 12~1519~ 14~3614~ 16~4613~ 17~2532~ 18~406~, 19~3326~ 20~2385~ 21~2532~ 22~2491~.'),
  (12461, 16, 7, 32, 'The men of Bethel and Ai, an hundred twenty and three.', '1~0582~ 3~01008~ 5~05857~, 7~03967~ 8~06242~ 10~07969~.'),
  (67, 1, 3, 11, 'And he said, Who told thee that thou wast naked? Hast thou eaten of the tree, whereof I commanded thee that thou shouldest not eat?', '&para; 2~0559~, 3~04310~ 4~05046~ [8] 9~05903~? 12~0398~ 15~06086~, 19~06680~ 23~01115~ 24~0398~?'),
  (6678, 7, 6, 17, 'And he said unto him, If now I have found grace in thy sight, then shew me a sign that thou talkest with me.', '2~0559~ 9~04672~ 10~02580~ 13~05869~, 15~06213~ 18~0226~ 21~01696~'),
  (16112, 19, 124, 1, 'A Song of degrees of David. If it had not been the LORD who was on our side, now may Israel say;', '&para; [0 1~07892~ 3~04609~ 5] 5~01732~ 6~03884~ [7 10] 12~03068~ 20~03478~ 21~0559~;');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (28525, 46, 7, 22, 'For he that is called in the Lord, being a servant, is the Lord''s freeman: likewise also he that is called, being free, is Christ''s servant.', '0~1063~ 4~2564~ 5~1722~ 7~2962~, [8] 10~1401~, 11~2076~ 13~2962~ 14~558~: 15~3668~ 16~2532~ 20~2564~, [21] 22~1658~, 23~2076~ 24~5547~ 25~1401~.'),
  (12002, 14, 35, 27, 'And his deeds, first and last, behold, they are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah.', '2~01697~, 3~07223~ 5~0314~, [8] 9~03789~ 12~05612~ 15~04428~ 17~03478~ 19~03063~.'),
  (7787, 9, 21, 8, 'And David said unto Ahimelech, And is there not here under thine hand spear or sword? for I have neither brought my sword nor my weapons with me, because the king''s business required haste.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~0288~, 7~03426~ 8~0371~ 12~03027~ 13~02595~ 15~02719~? 20~03947~ 22~02719~ 25~03627~ 27~03027~, 30~04428~ 31~01697~ 32~01961~ 33~05169~.'),
  (12373, 16, 4, 5, 'And cover not their iniquity, and let not their sin be blotted out from before thee: for they have provoked thee to anger before the builders.', '1~03680~ 4~05771~, 9~02403~ 12~04229~ 14~06440~ [20] 22~03707~ 25~01129~.'),
  (555, 1, 22, 4, 'Then on the third day Abraham lifted up his eyes, and saw the place afar off.', '3~07992~ 4~03117~ 5~085~ 7~05375~ 9~05869~, 11~07200~ 13~04725~ 15~07350~.'),
  (3458, 3, 24, 7, 'And thou shalt put pure frankincense upon each row, that it may be on the bread for a memorial, even an offering made by fire unto the LORD.', '3~05414~ 4~02134~ 5~03828~ [7] 8~04635~, 15~03899~ 18~0234~, [19] 24~0801~ 27~03068~.'),
  (22503, 30, 8, 13, 'In that day shall the fair virgins and young men faint for thirst.', '2~03117~ 5~03303~ 6~01330~ 9~0970~ 10~05968~ 12~06772~.'),
  (1245, 1, 41, 45, 'And Pharaoh called Joseph''s name Zaphnathpaaneah; and he gave him to wife Asenath the daughter of Potipherah priest of On. And Joseph went out over all the land of Egypt.', '1~06547~ 2~07121~ 3~03130~ 4~08034~ 5~06847~; 8~05414~ 11~0802~ 12~0621~ 14~01323~ 16~06319~ 17~03548~ 19~0204~. 21~03130~ 23~03318~ [25] 27~0776~ 29~04714~.'),
  (6203, 6, 14, 9, 'And Moses sware on that day, saying, Surely the land whereon thy feet have trodden shall be thine inheritance, and thy children''s for ever, because thou hast wholly followed the LORD my God.', '1~04872~ 2~07650~ 5~03117~, 6~0559~, 9~0776~ 12~07272~ 14~01869~ 18~05159~, 21~01121~ 22~05704~ 23~05769~, 27~04390~ 28~0310~ 30~03068~ 32~0430~.'),
  (12028, 15, 1, 3, 'Who is there among you of all his people? his God be with him, and let him go up to Jerusalem, which is in Judah, and build the house of the LORD God of Israel, (he is the God,) which is in Jerusalem.', '[1 2] 8~05971~? 10~0430~ 18~05927~ 20~03389~, [22] 24~03063~, 26~01129~ 28~01004~ 31~03068~ 32~0430~ 34~03478~, [36] 38~0430~,) [40] 42~03389~.'),
  (14871, 19, 65, 2, 'O thou that hearest prayer, unto thee shall all flesh come.', '3~08085~ 4~08605~, 9~01320~ 10~0935~.'),
  (30813, 66, 6, 4, 'And there went out another horse that was red: and power was given to him that sat thereon to take peace from the earth, and that they should kill one another: and there was given unto him a great sword.', '0~2532~ 3~1831~ 4~243~ 5~2462~ [6 7] 8~4450~: 9~2532~ [10] 12~1325~ 14~846~ 16~2521~ 17~846~ 18~1909~ 19~2983~ 20~1515~ 21~575~ 23~1093~, 24~2532~ 25~2443~ 28~4969~ 30~240~: 31~2532~ 34~1325~ 36~846~ 38~3173~ 39~3162~.'),
  (28327, 45, 15, 8, 'Now I say that Jesus Christ was a minister of the circumcision for the truth of God, to confirm the promises made unto the fathers:', '0~1161~ 2~3004~ 4~2424~ 5~5547~ 6~1096~ 8~1249~ 11~4061~ 12~5228~ 14~225~ 16~2316~, 17~1519~ 18~950~ 20~1860~ [21] 24~3962~:'),
  (13208, 18, 14, 18, 'And surely the mountain falling cometh to nought, and the rock is removed out of his place.', '1~0199~ 3~02022~ 4~05307~ 7~05034~, 10~06697~ 12~06275~ 16~04725~.'),
  (16999, 20, 21, 6, 'The getting of treasures by a lying tongue is a vanity tossed to and fro of them that seek death.', '&para; 1~06467~ 3~0214~ 6~08267~ 7~03956~ [8] 10~01892~ 15~05086~ 18~01245~ 19~04194~.'),
  (30021, 58, 3, 10, 'Wherefore I was grieved with that generation, and said, They do alway err in their heart; and they have not known my ways.', '0~1352~ 3~4360~ 5~1565~ 6~1074~, 7~2532~ 8~2036~, 10~4105~ 11~104~ 12~4105~ [14] 15~2588~; 16~1161~ 17~846~ 18~1097~ 19~3756~ 20~1097~ 21~3450~ 22~3598~.'),
  (28472, 46, 5, 2, 'And ye are puffed up, and have not rather mourned, that he that hath done this deed might be taken away from among you.', '0~2532~ 1~5210~ 2~2075~ 4~5448~, 5~2532~ 6~3996~ 7~3780~ 8~3123~ 9~3996~, 10~2443~ 14~4160~ 15~5124~ 16~2041~ 20~1808~ 21~1537~ 22~3319~ 23~5216~.'),
  (484, 1, 19, 23, 'The sun was risen upon the earth when Lot entered into Zoar.', '1~08121~ 3~03318~ 6~0776~ 8~03876~ 9~0935~ 11~06820~.'),
  (21566, 26, 42, 5, 'Now the upper chambers were shorter: for the galleries were higher than these, than the lower, and than the middlemost of the building.', '2~05945~ 3~03957~ [4] 5~07114~: 8~0862~ 10~0398~ 12~02007~, 15~08481~, 19~08484~ 22~01146~.'),
  (4243, 4, 16, 44, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (2878, 3, 6, 24, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (29517, 51, 2, 7, 'Rooted and built up in him, and stablished in the faith, as ye have been taught, abounding therein with thanksgiving.', '0~4492~ 1~2532~ 3~2026~ 4~1722~ 5~846~, 6~2532~ 7~950~ 8~1722~ 10~4102~, 11~2531~ 15~1321~, 16~4052~ 17~846~ 18~1722~* 19~1722~ 20~2169~.'),
  (18843, 23, 60, 13, 'The glory of Lebanon shall come unto thee, the fir tree, the pine tree, and the box together, to beautify the place of my sanctuary; and I will make the place of my feet glorious.', '1~03519~ 3~03844~ 5~0935~ 10~01265~, 13~08410~, 16~08391~ 17~03162~, 19~06286~ 21~04725~ 24~04720~; 30~04725~ 33~07272~ 34~03513~.'),
  (22365, 29, 3, 13, 'Put ye in the sickle, for the harvest is ripe: come, get you down; for the press is full, the vats overflow; for their wickedness is great.', '0~07971~ 4~04038~, 7~07105~ 9~01310~: 10~0935~, 13~03381~; 16~01660~ 18~04390~, 20~03342~ 21~07783~; 24~07451~ [25] 26~07227~.'),
  (19243, 24, 11, 8, 'Yet they obeyed not, nor inclined their ear, but walked every one in the imagination of their evil heart: therefore I will bring upon them all the words of this covenant, which I commanded them to do; but they did them not.', '2~08085~ 5~05186~ 7~0241~, 9~03212~ 11~0376~ 14~08307~ 17~07451~ 18~03820~: 22~0935~ 27~01697~ 30~01285~, 33~06680~ [34] 36~06213~; 39~06213~ [40]'),
  (17071, 20, 23, 18, 'For surely there is an end; and thine expectation shall not be cut off.', '3~03426~ 5~0319~; 8~08615~ 13~03772~.'),
  (6769, 7, 9, 8, 'The trees went forth on a time to anoint a king over them; and they said unto the olive tree, Reign thou over us.', '1~06086~ 3~01980~ [4 6] 8~04886~ 10~04428~ 15~0559~ 19~02132~, 20~04427~'),
  (13154, 18, 12, 17, 'He leadeth counsellors away spoiled, and maketh the judges fools.', '1~03212~ 2~03289~ 4~07758~, 8~08199~ 9~01984~.'),
  (21975, 27, 8, 5, 'And as I was considering, behold, an he goat came from the west on the face of the whole earth, and touched not the ground: and the goat had a notable horn between his eyes.', '4~0995~, 7~05795~ 8~06842~ 9~0935~ 12~04628~ 15~06440~ 19~0776~, 21~05060~ 24~0776~: 27~06842~ [28] 30~02380~ 31~07161~ 34~05869~.'),
  (20, 1, 1, 20, 'And God said, Let the waters bring forth abundantly the moving creature that hath life, and fowl that may fly above the earth in the open firmament of heaven.', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~0559~, 5~04325~ 8~08317~ 11~08318~ 13~05315~ 14~02416~, 16~05775~ [17] 19~05774~ 20~05921~ 22~0776~ 25~06440~ 26~07549~ 28~08064~.'),
  (17617, 22, 5, 10, 'My beloved is white and ruddy, the chiefest among ten thousand.', '1~01730~ [2] 3~06703~ 5~0122~, 7~01713~ 10~07233~.'),
  (25483, 42, 12, 11, 'And when they bring you unto the synagogues, and unto magistrates, and powers, take ye no thought how or what thing ye shall answer, or what ye shall say:', '0~1161~ 1~3752~ 3~4374~ 4~5209~ 5~1909~ 7~4864~, 8~2532~ [9] 10~746~, 11~2532~ 12~1849~, 13~3309~ 15~3361~ 16~3309~ 17~4459~ 18~2228~ 20~5101~ 23~626~, 24~2228~ 25~5101~ 28~2036~:'),
  (25193, 42, 6, 35, 'But love ye your enemies, and do good, and lend, hoping for nothing again; and your reward shall be great, and ye shall be the children of the Highest: for he is kind unto the unthankful and to the evil.', '0~4133~ 2~25~ 3~5216~ 4~2190~, 5~2532~ 7~15~, 8~2532~ 9~1155~, 10~560~ 12~3367~ 13~560~; 14~2532~ 15~5216~ 16~3408~ 18~2071~ 19~4183~, 20~2532~ 23~2071~ 25~5207~ 28~5310~: 29~3754~ 30~846~ 31~2076~ 32~5543~ 33~1909~ 35~884~ 36~2532~ [37] 39~4190~.'),
  (16017, 19, 119, 110, 'The wicked have laid a snare for me: yet I erred not from thy precepts.', '1~07563~ 3~05414~ 5~06341~ 10~08582~ 14~06490~.'),
  (26881, 43, 19, 41, 'Now in the place where he was crucified there was a garden; and in the garden a new sepulchre, wherein was never man yet laid.', '0~1161~ 1~1722~ 3~5117~ 4~3699~ 7~4717~ 9~2258~ 11~2779~; 12~2532~ 13~1722~ 15~2779~ 17~2537~ 18~3419~, 19~3739~ 20~1722~* 21~5087~ 22~3764~ 23~3762~ 24~3764~ 25~5087~.'),
  (29947, 56, 3, 8, 'This is a faithful saying, and these things I will that thou affirm constantly, that they which have believed in God might be careful to maintain good works. These things are good and profitable unto men.', '[0 1] 3~4103~ 4~3056~, 5~2532~ 7~5130~ 8~4012~ 9~1014~ 11~4571~ 13~1226~, 14~2443~ 18~4100~ 20~2316~ 23~5431~ 25~4291~ 26~2570~ 27~2041~. 29~5023~ 30~2076~ 31~2570~ 32~2532~ 33~5624~ 35~444~.'),
  (12095, 15, 2, 59, 'And these were they which went up from Telmelah, Telharsa, Cherub, Addan, and Immer: but they could not shew their father''s house, and their seed, whether they were of Israel:', '[2] 6~05927~ 8~08528~, 9~08521~, 10~03743~, 11~0135~, [12] 13~0564~: 16~03201~ 18~05046~ 20~01~ 21~01004~, 24~02233~, [27] 29~03478~:'),
  (7457, 9, 11, 5, 'And, behold, Saul came after the herd out of the field; and Saul said, What aileth the people that they weep? And they told him the tidings of the men of Jabesh.', '&para; 2~07586~ 3~0935~ 4~0310~ 6~01241~ 10~07704~; 12~07586~ 13~0559~, [15] 17~05971~ 20~01058~? 23~05608~ 26~01697~ 29~0582~ 31~03003~.'),
  (11197, 13, 29, 25, 'And the LORD magnified Solomon exceedingly in the sight of all Israel, and bestowed upon him such royal majesty as had not been on any king before him in Israel.', '2~03068~ 3~01431~ 4~08010~ 5~04605~ 8~05869~ 11~03478~, 13~05414~ [16] 17~04438~ 18~01935~ 25~04428~ 26~06440~ 29~03478~.'),
  (1300, 1, 43, 5, 'But if thou wilt not send him, we will not go down: for the man said unto us, Ye shall not see my face, except your brother be with you.', '5~07971~ [6] 11~03381~: 14~0376~ 15~0559~ 21~07200~ 23~06440~, 26~0251~ [27]'),
  (29142, 48, 3, 24, 'Wherefore the law was our schoolmaster to bring us unto Christ, that we might be justified by faith.', '0~5620~ 2~3551~ 3~1096~ 4~2257~ 5~3807~ [6 8] 9~1519~ 10~5547~, 11~2443~ 15~1344~ 16~1537~ 17~4102~.'),
  (23984, 40, 24, 17, 'Let him which is on the housetop not come down to take any thing out of his house:', '4~1909~ 6~1430~ 7~3361~ 9~2597~ 11~142~ 13~5100~ 15~1537~ 16~846~ 17~3614~:'),
  (3023, 3, 11, 21, 'Yet these may ye eat of every flying creeping thing that goeth upon all four, which have legs above their feet, to leap withal upon the earth;', '4~0398~ 7~05775~ 8~08318~ 11~01980~ [13] 14~0702~, 17~03767~ 18~04605~ 20~07272~, 22~05425~ 23~02004~ 26~0776~;'),
  (14803, 19, 59, 4, 'They run and prepare themselves without my fault: awake to help me, and behold.', '1~07323~ 3~03559~ [6] 7~05771~: 8~05782~ 10~07125~ 13~07200~.'),
  (8252, 10, 10, 5, 'When they told it unto David, he sent to meet them, because the men were greatly ashamed: and the king said, Tarry at Jericho until your beards be grown, and then return.', '2~05046~ [3] 5~01732~, 7~07971~ 9~07125~ 13~0582~ 15~03966~ 16~03637~: 19~04428~ 20~0559~, 21~03427~ 23~03405~ 26~02206~ 28~06779~, [30] 31~07725~.'),
  (1017, 1, 35, 1, 'And God said unto Jacob, Arise, go up to Bethel, and dwell there: and make there an altar unto God, that appeared unto thee when thou fleddest from the face of Esau thy brother.', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~0559~ 4~03290~, 5~06965~, 7~05927~ 9~01008~, 11~03427~ 14~06213~ 17~04196~ 19~0410~, 21~07200~ 26~01272~ 29~06440~ 31~06215~ 33~0251~.'),
  (25141, 42, 5, 22, 'But when Jesus perceived their thoughts, he answering said unto them, What reason ye in your hearts?', '0~1161~ 2~2424~ 3~1921~ 4~846~ 5~1261~, 7~611~ 8~2036~ 9~4314~ 10~846~, 11~5101~ 13~1260~ 14~1722~ 15~5216~ 16~2588~?'),
  (29979, 57, 1, 25, 'The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.', '1~5485~ 3~2257~ 4~2962~ 5~2424~ 6~5547~ [7] 8~3326~ 9~5216~ 10~4151~. 11~281~ 12~1125~.* [13 14~575~ 15~4516~ 16~4314~ 17~5371~, 18~1223~ 19~3682~ 21] 21~3610~'),
  (5994, 6, 7, 12, 'Therefore the children of Israel could not stand before their enemies, but turned their backs before their enemies, because they were accursed: neither will I be with you any more, except ye destroy the accursed from among you.', '2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~03201~ 7~06965~ 8~06440~ 10~0341~, [11] 12~06437~ [13] 14~06203~ 15~06440~ 17~0341~, 21~02764~: 29~03254~, 30~03808~ 32~08045~ 34~02764~ 36~07130~'),
  (17686, 23, 1, 23, 'Thy princes are rebellious, and companions of thieves: every one loveth gifts, and followeth after rewards: they judge not the fatherless, neither doth the cause of the widow come unto them.', '1~08269~ [2] 3~05637~, 5~02270~ 7~01590~: 10~0157~ 11~07810~, 13~07291~ 15~08021~: 17~08199~ 20~03490~, 24~07379~ 27~0490~ 28~0935~'),
  (27694, 44, 21, 14, 'And when he would not be persuaded, we ceased, saying, The will of the Lord be done.', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 3~3982~ 4~3361~ 6~3982~, 8~2270~, 9~2036~, 11~2307~ 14~2962~ 16~1096~.'),
  (1373, 1, 45, 10, 'And thou shalt dwell in the land of Goshen, and thou shalt be near unto me, thou, and thy children, and thy children''s children, and thy flocks, and thy herds, and all that thou hast:', '3~03427~ 6~0776~ 8~01657~, 13~07138~ 19~01121~, 22~01121~ 23~01121~, 26~06629~, 29~01241~,'),
  (3688, 4, 2, 25, 'The standard of the camp of Dan shall be on the north side by their armies: and the captain of the children of Dan shall be Ahiezer the son of Ammishaddai.', '1~01714~ 4~04264~ 6~01835~ [7 8] 12~06828~ 15~06635~: 18~05387~ 21~01121~ 23~01835~ [24 25] 26~0295~ 28~01121~ 30~05996~.'),
  (28458, 46, 4, 9, 'For I think that God hath set forth us the apostles last, as it were appointed to death: for we are made a spectacle unto the world, and to angels, and to men.', '0~1063~ 2~1380~ 3~3754~ 4~2316~ 7~584~ 8~2248~ 10~652~ 11~2078~, 12~5613~ 17~1935~: 18~3754~ 21~1096~ 23~2302~ 26~2889~, 27~2532~ 29~32~, 30~2532~ 32~444~.'),
  (29090, 48, 1, 17, 'Neither went I up to Jerusalem to them which were apostles before me; but I went into Arabia, and returned again unto Damascus.', '0~3761~ 3~424~ 4~1519~ 5~2414~ 6~4314~ 10~652~ 11~4253~ 12~1700~; 13~235~ 15~565~ 16~1519~ 17~688~, 18~2532~ 19~5290~ 20~3825~ 21~1519~ 22~1154~.'),
  (13048, 18, 8, 10, 'Shall not they teach thee, and tell thee, and utter words out of their heart?', '3~03384~ [5] 6~0559~ 9~03318~ 10~04405~ 14~03820~?'),
  (7438, 9, 10, 13, 'And when he had made an end of prophesying, he came to the high place.', '6~03615~ 8~05012~, 10~0935~ 14~01116~.'),
  (22942, 38, 4, 11, 'Then answered I, and said unto him, What are these two olive trees upon the right side of the candlestick and upon the left side thereof?', '&para; 1~06030~ 4~0559~ [8] 10~08147~ 12~02132~ 15~03225~ [16] 19~04501~ 23~08040~ [24]'),
  (20108, 24, 48, 19, 'O inhabitant of Aroer, stand by the way, and espy; ask him that fleeth, and her that escapeth, and say, What is done?', '1~03427~ 3~06177~, 4~05975~ 7~01870~, 9~06822~; 10~07592~ 13~05127~, 17~04422~, [18] 19~0559~, 22~01961~?'),
  (16353, 19, 146, 3, 'Put not your trust in princes, nor in the son of man, in whom there is no help.', '3~0982~ 5~05081~, [6] 9~01121~ 11~0120~, [14 15] 17~08668~.'),
  (1309, 1, 43, 14, 'And God Almighty give you mercy before the man, that he may send away your other brother, and Benjamin. If I be bereaved of my children, I am bereaved.', '1~0410~ 2~07706~ 3~05414~ 5~07356~ 6~06440~ 8~0376~, 13~07971~ 15~0312~ 16~0251~, 18~01144~. 19~0834~ 22~07921~ [23 25] 28~07921~.'),
  (10696, 13, 11, 15, 'Now three of the thirty captains went down to the rock to David, into the cave of Adullam; and the host of the Philistines encamped in the valley of Rephaim.', '1~07969~ 4~07970~ 5~07218~ 7~03381~ 10~06697~ 12~01732~, 15~04631~ 17~05725~; 20~04264~ 23~06430~ 24~02583~ 27~06010~ 29~07497~.'),
  (18372, 23, 37, 11, 'Behold, thou hast heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all lands by destroying them utterly; and shalt thou be delivered?', '3~08085~ 6~04428~ 8~0804~ 10~06213~ 13~0776~ 17~02763~; 22~05337~?'),
  (12787, 17, 4, 16, 'Go, gather together all the Jews that are present in Shushan, and fast ye for me, and neither eat nor drink three days, night or day: I also and my maidens will fast likewise; and so will I go in unto the king, which is not according to the law: and if I perish, I perish.', '0~03212~, 2~03664~ 5~03064~ 8~04672~ 10~07800~, 12~06684~ 18~0398~ 20~08354~ 21~07969~ 22~03117~, 23~03915~ 25~03117~: 30~05291~ 32~06684~ 35~03651~ 38~0935~ 42~04428~, [44] 49~01881~: 53~06~, 55~06~.'),
  (18740, 23, 54, 8, 'In a little wrath I hid my face from thee for a moment; but with everlasting kindness will I have mercy on thee, saith the LORD thy Redeemer.', '2~08241~ 3~07110~ 5~05641~ 7~06440~ 12~07281~; 15~05769~ 16~02617~ 20~07355~ 23~0559~ 25~03068~ 27~01350~.'),
  (7386, 9, 8, 10, 'And Samuel told all the words of the LORD unto the people that asked of him a king.', '1~08050~ 2~0559~ 5~01697~ 8~03068~ 11~05971~ 13~07592~ 17~04428~.'),
  (24957, 42, 1, 52, 'He hath put down the mighty from their seats, and exalted them of low degree.', '3~2507~ 5~1413~ 6~575~ [7] 8~2362~, 9~2532~ 10~5312~ 14~5011~.'),
  (13610, 18, 31, 13, 'If I did despise the cause of my manservant or of my maidservant, when they contended with me;', '3~03988~ 5~04941~ 8~05650~ 12~0519~, 15~07379~'),
  (19101, 24, 6, 3, 'The shepherds with their flocks shall come unto her; they shall pitch their tents against her round about; they shall feed every one in his place.', '1~07462~ 4~05739~ 6~0935~ 11~08628~ [12] 13~0168~ 17~05439~; 20~07462~ 22~0376~ 25~03027~.'),
  (23393, 40, 9, 4, 'And Jesus knowing their thoughts said, Wherefore think ye evil in your hearts?', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~1492~ 3~846~ 4~1761~ 5~2036~, 6~2444~ 7~1760~ 8~5210~ 9~4190~ 10~1722~ 11~5216~ 12~2588~?'),
  (18437, 23, 40, 8, 'The grass withereth, the flower fadeth: but the word of our God shall stand for ever.', '1~02682~ 2~03001~, 4~06731~ 5~05034~: 8~01697~ 11~0430~ 13~06965~ 15~05769~.'),
  (24429, 41, 6, 12, 'And they went out, and preached that men should repent.', '0~2532~ 3~1831~, 5~2784~ 6~2443~ 9~3340~.'),
  (13056, 18, 8, 18, 'If he destroy him from his place, then it shall deny him, saying, I have not seen thee.', '2~01104~ 6~04725~, [8] 10~03584~ [12] 16~07200~'),
  (16305, 19, 143, 3, 'For the enemy hath persecuted my soul; he hath smitten my life down to the ground; he hath made me to dwell in darkness, as those that have been long dead.', '2~0341~ 4~07291~ 6~05315~; 9~01792~ 11~02416~ 12~01792~ 15~0776~; 21~03427~ 23~04285~, 29~05769~ 30~04191~.'),
  (5007, 5, 3, 26, 'But the LORD was wroth with me for your sakes, and would not hear me: and the LORD said unto me, Let it suffice thee; speak no more unto me of this matter.', '2~03068~ 4~05674~ 13~08085~ 17~03068~ 18~0559~ 23~07227~ 25~01696~ 27~03254~ 32~01697~.'),
  (14050, 19, 9, 20, 'Put them in fear, O LORD: that the nations may know themselves to be but men. Selah.', '0~07896~ 3~04172~ 4~04172~,* 6~03068~: [7] 9~01471~ 11~03045~ [13 15] 16~0582~. 17~05542~.'),
  (18076, 23, 22, 15, 'Thus saith the Lord GOD of hosts, Go, get thee unto this treasurer, even unto Shebna, which is over the house, and say,', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~0136~ 4~03069~ 6~06635~, 7~03212~, 8~0935~ 12~05532~, [13] 15~07644~, [17] 20~01004~, [21 22]'),
  (23859, 40, 21, 23, 'And when he was come into the temple, the chief priests and the elders of the people came unto him as he was teaching, and said, By what authority doest thou these things? and who gave thee this authority?', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~846~ 4~2064~ 5~1519~ 7~2411~, 10~749~ 11~2532~ 13~4245~ 16~2992~ 17~4334~ 19~846~ 23~1321~, 25~3004~, 26~1722~ 27~4169~ 28~1849~ 30~4160~ 32~5023~? 33~2532~ 34~5101~ 35~1325~ 36~4671~ 37~5026~ 38~1849~?'),
  (30214, 58, 11, 26, 'Esteeming the reproach of Christ greater riches than the treasures in Egypt: for he had respect unto the recompense of the reward.', '0~2233~ 2~3680~ 4~5547~ 5~3187~ 6~4149~ 7~2233~ 9~2344~ 10~1722~ 11~125~: 12~1063~ 15~578~ 16~1519~ 21~3405~.'),
  (13759, 18, 36, 14, 'They die in youth, and their life is among the unclean.', '0~05315~ 1~04191~ 3~05290~, 6~02416~ [7] 10~06945~.'),
  (10815, 13, 15, 16, 'And David spake to the chief of the Levites to appoint their brethren to be the singers with instruments of music, psalteries and harps and cymbals, sounding, by lifting up the voice with joy.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 5~08269~ 8~03881~ 10~05975~ 12~0251~ [13 14] 16~07891~ 18~03627~ 20~07892~, 21~05035~ 23~03658~ 25~04700~, 26~08085~, 29~07311~ 31~06963~ 33~08057~.'),
  (24320, 41, 3, 22, 'And the scribes which came down from Jerusalem said, He hath Beelzebub, and by the prince of the devils casteth he out devils.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~1122~ 3~3588~ 5~2597~ 6~575~ 7~2414~ 8~3004~ 9~3754~,* 11~2192~ 12~954~ 13~3754~,* 14~2532~ 15~1722~ 17~758~ 20~1140~ 23~1544~ 24~1140~.'),
  (17763, 23, 5, 15, 'And the mean man shall be brought down, and the mighty man shall be humbled, and the eyes of the lofty shall be humbled:', '3~0120~ 7~07817~, 11~0376~ 14~08213~, 17~05869~ 20~01364~ 23~08213~:'),
  (29829, 55, 1, 4, 'Greatly desiring to see thee, being mindful of thy tears, that I may be filled with joy;', '1~1971~ 3~1492~ 4~4571~, 6~3415~ 8~4675~ 9~1144~, 10~2443~ 14~4137~ 16~5479~;'),
  (14726, 19, 52, 7, 'Lo, this is the man that made not God his strength; but trusted in the abundance of his riches, and strengthened himself in his wickedness.', '[1 2] 4~01397~ [5] 6~07760~ 8~0430~ 10~04581~; 12~0982~ 15~07230~ 18~06239~, [19] 20~05810~ 24~01942~.'),
  (12233, 15, 8, 23, 'So we fasted and besought our God for this: and he was entreated of us.', '2~06684~ 4~01245~ 6~0430~ 12~06279~'),
  (1106, 1, 37, 18, 'And when they saw him afar off, even before he came near unto them, they conspired against him to slay him.', '3~07200~ 6~07350~, 11~07126~ 15~05230~ 19~04191~'),
  (21130, 26, 26, 21, 'I will make thee a terror, and thou shalt be no more: though thou be sought for, yet shalt thou never be found again, saith the Lord GOD.', '2~05414~ 5~01091~, [8 9] [11] 16~01245~, 20~05769~ 22~04672~ 24~05002~ 26~0136~ 27~03069~.'),
  (153, 1, 6, 15, 'And this is the fashion which thou shalt make it of: The length of the ark shall be three hundred cubits, the breadth of it fifty cubits, and the height of it thirty cubits.', '[2 4] 8~06213~ [10] 12~0753~ 15~08392~ [16 17] 18~07969~ 19~03967~ 20~0520~, 22~07341~ 25~02572~ 26~0520~, 29~06967~ 32~07970~ 33~0520~.'),
  (570, 1, 22, 19, 'So Abraham returned unto his young men, and they rose up and went together to Beersheba; and Abraham dwelt at Beersheba.', '1~085~ 2~07725~ 6~05288~, 10~06965~ 12~03212~ 13~03162~ 15~0884~; 17~085~ 18~03427~ 20~0884~.'),
  (13794, 18, 37, 16, 'Dost thou know the balancings of the clouds, the wondrous works of him which is perfect in knowledge?', '2~03045~ 4~04657~ 7~05645~, 10~04652~ 15~08549~ 17~01843~?'),
  (4670, 4, 30, 16, 'These are the statutes, which the LORD commanded Moses, between a man and his wife, between the father and his daughter, being yet in her youth in her father''s house.', '[1] 3~02706~, 6~03068~ 7~06680~ 8~04872~, 11~0376~ 14~0802~, 17~01~ 20~01323~, [21 22] 25~05271~ 28~01~ 29~01004~.'),
  (1950, 2, 15, 25, 'And he cried unto the LORD; and the LORD shewed him a tree, which when he had cast into the waters, the waters were made sweet: there he made for them a statute and an ordinance, and there he proved them,', '2~06817~ 5~03068~; 8~03068~ 9~03384~ 12~06086~, [13] 17~07993~ 20~04325~, 22~04325~ 25~04985~: 28~07760~ 32~02706~ 35~04941~, 39~05254~'),
  (1116, 1, 37, 28, 'Then there passed by Midianites merchantmen; and they drew and lifted up Joseph out of the pit, and sold Joseph to the Ishmeelites for twenty pieces of silver: and they brought Joseph into Egypt.', '2~05674~ 4~04084~ 5~05503~ 6~0582~;* 9~04900~ 12~05927~ 13~03130~ 17~0953~, 19~04376~ 20~03130~ 23~03459~ 25~06242~ [26] 28~03701~: 31~0935~ 32~03130~ 34~04714~.'),
  (28989, 47, 10, 2, 'But I beseech you, that I may not be bold when I am present with that confidence, wherewith I think to be bold against some, which think of us as if we walked according to the flesh.', '0~1161~ 2~1189~ [3] 7~3361~ 9~2292~ 13~3918~ 16~4006~, 17~3739~ 19~3049~ 22~5111~ 23~1909~ 24~5100~, 25~3588~ 26~3049~ 28~2248~ 29~5613~ 32~4043~ 33~2596~ 36~4561~.'),
  (15178, 19, 78, 56, 'Yet they tempted and provoked the most high God, and kept not his testimonies:', '2~05254~ 4~04784~ 7~05945~ 8~0430~, 10~08104~ 13~05713~:'),
  (12622, 16, 11, 25, 'And for the villages, with their fields, some of the children of Judah dwelt at Kirjatharba, and in the villages thereof, and at Dibon, and in the villages thereof, and at Jekabzeel, and in the villages thereof,', '3~02691~, 6~07704~, [7] 10~01121~ 12~03063~ 13~03427~ 15~07153~, [17] 19~02691~ 23~01769~, [25] 27~01323~ 31~03343~, [33] 35~01323~'),
  (29945, 56, 3, 6, 'Which he shed on us abundantly through Jesus Christ our Saviour;', '0~3739~ 2~1632~ 3~1909~ 4~2248~ 5~4146~ 6~1223~ 7~2424~ 8~5547~ 9~2257~ 10~4990~;'),
  (9485, 11, 21, 26, 'And he did very abominably in following idols, according to all things as did the Amorites, whom the LORD cast out before the children of Israel.', '3~03966~ 4~08581~ 6~03212~ 7~0310~* 8~01544~, [12] 14~06213~ 16~0567~, 19~03068~ 21~03423~ 22~06440~ 24~01121~ 26~03478~.'),
  (8247, 10, 9, 13, 'So Mephibosheth dwelt in Jerusalem: for he did eat continually at the king''s table; and was lame on both his feet.', '1~04648~ 2~03427~ 4~03389~: 8~0398~ 9~08548~ 12~04428~ 13~07979~; 16~06455~ 18~08147~ 20~07272~.');
