  (30376, 59, 5, 6, 'Ye have condemned and killed the just; and he doth not resist you.', '2~2613~ [3] 4~5407~ 6~1342~; [7] 9~498~ 10~3756~ 11~498~ 12~5213~.'),
  (12997, 18, 6, 10, 'Then should I yet have comfort; yea, I would harden myself in sorrow: let him not spare; for I have not concealed the words of the Holy One.', '5~05165~; 9~05539~ 12~02427~: 16~02550~; 21~03582~ 23~0561~ 27~06918~.'),
  (8561, 10, 19, 42, 'And all the men of Judah answered the men of Israel, Because the king is near of kin to us: wherefore then be ye angry for this matter? have we eaten at all of the king''s cost? or hath he given us any gift?', '3~0376~ 5~03063~ 6~06030~ 8~0376~ 10~03478~, 13~04428~ [14] 17~07138~ 24~02734~ 27~01697~? 30~0398~ 32~0398~ 35~04428~ [36] 40~05375~ 43~05379~?'),
  (7578, 9, 15, 11, 'It repenteth me that I have set up Saul to be king: for he is turned back from following me, and hath not performed my commandments. And it grieved Samuel; and he cried unto the LORD all night.', '1~05162~ 7~04427~ 8~07586~ [9 10] 11~04428~: 16~07725~ 18~0310~ 23~06965~ 25~01697~. 28~02734~ 29~08050~; 32~02199~ 35~03068~ 37~03915~.'),
  (23089, 38, 14, 12, 'And this shall be the plague wherewith the LORD will smite all the people that have fought against Jerusalem; Their flesh shall consume away while they stand upon their feet, and their eyes shall consume away in their holes, and their tongue shall consume away in their mouth.', '5~04046~ 8~03068~ 10~05062~ 13~05971~ 16~06633~ 18~03389~; 20~01320~ 23~04743~ 26~05975~ 29~07272~, 32~05869~ 35~04743~ 38~02356~, 41~03956~ 44~04743~ 47~06310~.'),
  (28583, 46, 9, 27, 'But I keep under my body, and bring it into subjection: lest that by any means, when I have preached to others, I myself should be a castaway.', '0~235~ 3~5299~ 4~3450~ 5~4983~, 6~2532~ [8] 10~1396~: 15~4458~ 16~3381~,* 20~2784~ 22~243~, 24~846~ 26~1096~ 28~96~.'),
  (13908, 18, 41, 11, 'Who hath prevented me, that I should repay him? whatsoever is under the whole heaven is mine.', '&para; 2~06923~ 7~07999~ [8 10] 14~08064~'),
  (22167, 28, 5, 6, 'They shall go with their flocks and with their herds to seek the LORD; but they shall not find him; he hath withdrawn himself from them.', '2~03212~ 5~06629~ 9~01241~ 11~01245~ 13~03068~; 18~04672~ [19] 22~02502~'),
  (11132, 13, 27, 15, 'The twelfth captain for the twelfth month was Heldai the Netophathite, of Othniel: and in his course were twenty and four thousand.', '1~06240~ [2] 2~08147~ 5~06240~ 6~08147~* 7~02320~ [8] 9~02469~ 11~05200~, 13~06274~: 17~04256~ [18] 19~06242~ 21~0702~ 22~0505~.'),
  (27731, 44, 22, 11, 'And when I could not see for the glory of that light, being led by the hand of them that were with me, I came into Damascus.', '0~1161~ 1~5613~ 3~1689~ 4~3756~ 5~1689~ 6~575~ 8~1391~ 10~1565~ 11~5457~, 16~5496~ 17~5259~ 20~4895~ 22~3427~, 24~2064~ 25~1519~ 26~1154~.'),
  (1939, 2, 15, 14, 'The people shall hear, and be afraid: sorrow shall take hold on the inhabitants of Palestina.', '1~05971~ 3~08085~, [4] 6~07264~: 7~02427~ 10~0270~ 13~03427~ 15~06429~.'),
  (22561, 32, 2, 4, 'Then I said, I am cast out of thy sight; yet I will look again toward thy holy temple.', '2~0559~, 6~01644~ 9~05869~; 13~05027~ 14~03254~ 17~06944~ 18~01964~.'),
  (21821, 27, 3, 5, 'That at what time ye hear the sound of the cornet, flute, harp, sackbut, psaltery, dulcimer, and all kinds of music, ye fall down and worship the golden image that Nebuchadnezzar the king hath set up:', '[0] 3~05732~ 5~08086~ 7~07032~ 10~07162~, 11~04953~, 12~07030~ 13~07030~,* 14~05443~, 15~06460~, 16~05481~, 18~03606~ 19~02178~ 21~02170~, 24~05308~ 26~05457~ 28~01722~ 29~06755~ 31~05020~ 33~04430~ 36~06966~:'),
  (26486, 43, 9, 31, 'Now we know that God heareth not sinners: but if any man be a worshipper of God, and doeth his will, him he heareth.', '0~1161~ 2~1492~ 3~3754~ 4~2316~ 5~191~ 6~3756~ 7~268~: 8~235~ 9~1437~ 11~5100~ 12~5600~ 16~2318~, 17~2532~ 18~4160~ 19~846~ 20~2307~, 21~5127~ 23~191~.'),
  (5381, 5, 17, 11, 'According to the sentence of the law which they shall teach thee, and according to the judgment which they shall tell thee, thou shalt do: thou shalt not decline from the sentence which they shall shew thee, to the right hand, nor to the left.', '3~06310~ 6~08451~ 10~03384~ 16~04941~ 20~0559~ 24~06213~: 28~05493~ 31~01697~ 35~05046~ [37] 40~03225~, [42] 44~08040~.'),
  (6486, 6, 24, 3, 'And I took your father Abraham from the other side of the flood, and led him throughout all the land of Canaan, and multiplied his seed, and gave him Isaac.', '2~03947~ 4~01~ 5~085~ 9~05676~ 12~05104~, 14~03212~ 19~0776~ 21~03667~, 23~07235~ 25~02233~, 27~05414~ 29~03327~.'),
  (12795, 17, 5, 7, 'Then answered Esther, and said, My petition and my request is;', '1~06030~ 2~0635~, 4~0559~, 6~07596~ 9~01246~ [10]'),
  (14793, 19, 58, 5, 'Which will not hearken to the voice of charmers, charming never so wisely.', '3~08085~ 6~06963~ 8~03907~, 9~02266~ 10~02267~* 13~02449~.'),
  (4301, 4, 19, 7, 'Then the priest shall wash his clothes, and he shall bathe his flesh in water, and afterward he shall come into the camp, and the priest shall be unclean until the even.', '2~03548~ 4~03526~ 6~0899~, 10~07364~ 12~01320~ 14~04325~, 16~0310~ 19~0935~ 22~04264~, 25~03548~ 28~02930~ 31~06153~.'),
  (20680, 26, 11, 16, 'Therefore say, Thus saith the Lord GOD; Although I have cast them far off among the heathen, and although I have scattered them among the countries, yet will I be to them as a little sanctuary in the countries where they shall come.', '1~0559~, 3~0559~ 5~0136~ 6~03069~; 13~07368~ 16~01471~, 21~06327~ 25~0776~, 34~04592~ 35~04720~ 38~0776~ 42~0935~.'),
  (8747, 11, 1, 22, 'And, lo, while she yet talked with the king, Nathan the prophet also came in.', '5~01696~ 8~04428~, 9~05416~ 11~05030~ 14~0935~.'),
  (28867, 47, 3, 10, 'For even that which was made glorious had no glory in this respect, by reason of the glory that excelleth.', '0~1063~ 1~2532~ 6~1392~ 8~3761~ 9~1392~ 10~1722~ 11~5129~ 12~3313~, 14~1752~ 17~1391~ 19~5235~.'),
  (12588, 16, 10, 30, 'And that we would not give our daughters unto the people of the land, nor take their daughters for our sons:', '5~05414~ 7~01323~ 10~05971~ 13~0776~, 15~03947~ 17~01323~ 20~01121~:'),
  (2355, 2, 29, 14, 'But the flesh of the bullock, and his skin, and his dung, shalt thou burn with fire without the camp: it is a sin offering.', '2~01320~ 5~06499~, 8~05785~, 11~06569~, 14~08313~ 16~0784~ 17~02351~ 19~04264~: [21] 24~02403~.'),
  (12442, 16, 7, 13, 'The children of Zattu, eight hundred forty and five.', '1~01121~ 3~02240~, 4~08083~ 5~03967~ 6~0705~ 8~02568~.'),
  (3367, 3, 21, 17, 'Speak unto Aaron, saying, Whosoever he be of thy seed in their generations that hath any blemish, let him not approach to offer the bread of his God.', '0~01696~ 2~0175~, 3~0559~, 4~0376~ [5 6] 9~02233~ 12~01755~ [15] 16~03971~, 20~07126~ 22~07126~ 24~03899~ 27~0430~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (26221, 43, 4, 50, 'Jesus saith unto him, Go thy way; thy son liveth. And the man believed the word that Jesus had spoken unto him, and he went his way.', '0~2424~ 1~3004~ 3~846~, 6~4198~; 7~4675~ 8~5207~ 9~2198~. 10~2532~ 12~444~ 13~4100~ 15~3056~ 16~3739~ 17~2424~ 19~2036~ 21~846~, 22~2532~ 26~4198~.'),
  (25539, 42, 13, 8, 'And he answering said unto him, Lord, let it alone this year also, till I shall dig about it, and dung it:', '0~1161~ 2~611~ 3~3004~ 5~846~, 6~2962~, 7~863~ 8~846~ 9~863~ 10~5124~ 11~2094~ 12~2532~, 13~3755~ 14~2193~ 16~4626~ 17~4012~ 18~846~, 19~2532~ 20~906~ 21~2874~* [22]'),
  (20251, 24, 51, 30, 'The mighty men of Babylon have forborne to fight, they have remained in their holds: their might hath failed; they became as women: they have burned her dwellingplaces; her bars are broken.', '2~01368~ 4~0894~ 6~02308~ 8~03898~, 11~03427~ [13] 14~04679~: 16~01369~ 18~05405~; 22~0802~: 25~03341~ 27~04908~; 29~01280~ 31~07665~.'),
  (6823, 7, 10, 5, 'And Jair died, and was buried in Camon.', '1~02971~ 2~04191~, 5~06912~ 7~07056~.'),
  (22737, 34, 3, 16, 'Thou hast multiplied thy merchants above the stars of heaven: the cankerworm spoileth, and fleeth away.', '2~07235~ 4~07402~ 7~03556~ 9~08064~: 11~03218~ 12~06584~, 15~05774~.'),
  (23811, 40, 20, 9, 'And when they came that were hired about the eleventh hour, they received every man a penny.', '0~2532~ 3~2064~ [5 6] 7~4012~ 9~1734~ 10~5610~, 12~2983~ 14~303~ 16~1220~.'),
  (1787, 2, 10, 5, 'And they shall cover the face of the earth, that one cannot be able to see the earth: and they shall eat the residue of that which is escaped, which remaineth unto you from the hail, and shall eat every tree which groweth for you out of the field:', '3~03680~ 5~05869~ 8~0776~, 13~03201~ 15~07200~ 17~0776~: 21~0398~ 23~03499~ 28~06413~, 30~07604~ 35~01259~, 38~0398~ 40~06086~ 42~06779~ 48~07704~:'),
  (15718, 19, 107, 10, 'Such as sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, being bound in affliction and iron;', '&para; 2~03427~ 4~02822~ 10~06757~, [11] 12~0615~ 14~06040~ 16~01270~;'),
  (28099, 45, 6, 15, 'What then? shall we sin, because we are not under the law, but under grace? God forbid.', '0~5101~ 1~3767~? 4~264~, 5~3754~ 7~2070~ 8~3756~ 9~5259~ 11~3551~, 12~235~ 13~5259~ 14~5485~? 16~1096~ 17~3361~.*'),
  (13892, 18, 40, 19, 'He is the chief of the ways of God: he that made him can make his sword to approach unto him.', '[1] 3~07225~ 6~01870~ 8~0410~: 11~06213~ 14~05066~ 16~02719~ 18~05066~ [19 20]'),
  (13157, 18, 12, 20, 'He removeth away the speech of the trusty, and taketh away the understanding of the aged.', '2~05493~ 4~08193~ 7~0539~, 10~03947~ 12~02940~ 15~02205~.'),
  (10685, 13, 11, 4, 'And David and all Israel went to Jerusalem, which is Jebus; where the Jebusites were, the inhabitants of the land.', '1~01732~ 4~03478~ 5~03212~ 7~03389~, [9] 10~02982~; 13~02983~ [14] 16~03427~ 19~0776~.'),
  (24218, 40, 28, 13, 'Saying, Say ye, His disciples came by night, and stole him away while we slept.', '0~3004~, 2~2036~ 3~3754~,* 4~846~ 5~3101~ 6~2064~ 8~3571~, 10~2813~ 11~846~ [12] 14~2257~ 15~2837~.'),
  (16372, 19, 147, 12, 'Praise the LORD, O Jerusalem; praise thy God, O Zion.', '&para; 0~07623~ 2~03068~, 4~03389~; 5~01984~ 7~0430~, 9~06726~.'),
  (20061, 24, 46, 7, 'Who is this that cometh up as a flood, whose waters are moved as the rivers?', '[1] [3] 5~05927~ 8~02975~, 10~04325~ 12~01607~ 15~05104~?'),
  (8756, 11, 1, 31, 'Then Bathsheba bowed with her face to the earth, and did reverence to the king, and said, Let my lord king David live for ever.', '1~01339~ 2~06915~ [4] 5~0639~ 8~0776~, 11~07812~ 14~04428~, 16~0559~, 19~0113~ 20~04428~ 21~01732~ 22~02421~ 24~05769~.'),
  (1051, 1, 36, 6, 'And Esau took his wives, and his sons, and his daughters, and all the persons of his house, and his cattle, and all his beasts, and all his substance, which he had got in the land of Canaan; and went into the country from the face of his brother Jacob.', '1~06215~ 2~03947~ 4~0802~, 7~01121~, 10~01323~, 14~05315~ 17~01004~, 20~04735~, 24~0929~, 28~07075~, 32~07408~ 35~0776~ 37~03667~; 39~03212~ 42~0776~ 45~06440~ 48~0251~ 49~03290~.'),
  (9693, 12, 6, 11, 'Therefore the heart of the king of Syria was sore troubled for this thing; and he called his servants, and said unto them, Will ye not shew me which of us is for the king of Israel?', '2~03820~ 5~04428~ 7~0758~ 10~05590~ 13~01697~; 16~07121~ 18~05650~, 20~0559~ 26~05046~ [31] 34~04428~ 36~03478~?'),
  (6722, 7, 7, 21, 'And they stood every man in his place round about the camp: and all the host ran, and cried, and fled.', '2~05975~ 4~0376~ 9~05439~ 11~04264~: 15~04264~ 16~07323~, 18~07321~, 20~05127~'),
  (26419, 43, 8, 23, 'And he said unto them, Ye are from beneath; I am from above: ye are of this world; I am not of this world.', '0~2532~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~5210~ 6~2075~ 7~1537~ 8~2736~; 9~1473~ 10~1510~ 11~1537~ 12~507~: 13~5210~ 14~2075~ 15~1537~ 16~5127~ 17~2889~; 18~1473~ 19~1510~ 20~3756~ 21~1537~ 22~5127~ 23~2889~.'),
  (14177, 19, 18, 50, 'Great deliverance giveth he to his king; and sheweth mercy to his anointed, to David, and to his seed for evermore.', '0~01431~ 1~03444~ 6~04428~; 8~06213~ 9~02617~ 12~04899~, 14~01732~, 18~02233~ 19~05704~ 20~05769~.'),
  (1629, 2, 4, 23, 'And I say unto thee, Let my son go, that he may serve me: and if thou refuse to let him go, behold, I will slay thy son, even thy firstborn.', '2~0559~ 7~01121~ 8~07971~, 12~05647~ 17~03985~ 21~07971~, 25~02026~ 27~01121~, [28] 30~01060~.'),
  (2056, 2, 19, 25, 'So Moses went down unto the people, and spake unto them.', '1~04872~ 3~03381~ 6~05971~, 8~0559~'),
  (28850, 47, 2, 10, 'To whom ye forgive any thing, I forgive also: for if I forgave any thing, to whom I forgave it, for your sakes forgave I it in the person of Christ;', '0~1161~ 1~3739~ 3~5483~ 5~5100~, 6~1473~ [7] 8~2532~: 9~1063~ 10~2532~ 11~1473~ 12~5483~ 14~1536~, 16~3739~ 18~5483~ [19] 22~5209~ [23 23~1223~ 25] 26~1722~ 28~4383~ 30~5547~;'),
  (6163, 6, 13, 3, 'From Sihor, which is before Egypt, even unto the borders of Ekron northward, which is counted to the Canaanite: five lords of the Philistines; the Gazathites, and the Ashdothites, the Eshkalonites, the Gittites, and the Ekronites; also the Avites:', '1~07883~, [3] 4~06440~ 5~04714~, 9~01366~ 11~06138~ 12~06828~, [13] 15~02803~ 18~03669~: 19~02568~ 20~05633~ 23~06430~; 25~05841~, 28~0796~, 30~0832~, 32~01663~, 35~06139~; 38~05761~:'),
  (8909, 11, 6, 5, 'And against the wall of the house he built chambers round about, against the walls of the house round about, both of the temple and of the oracle: and he made chambers round about:', '3~07023~ 6~01004~ 8~01129~ 9~03326~ 10~03326~* 12~05439~, [13] 15~07023~ 18~01004~ 20~05439~, [21] 24~01964~ 28~01687~: 31~06213~ 32~06763~ 34~05439~:'),
  (23558, 40, 13, 9, 'Who hath ears to hear, let him hear.', '0~3588~ 1~2192~ 2~3775~ 4~191~, 7~191~.'),
  (28136, 45, 8, 4, 'That the righteousness of the law might be fulfilled in us, who walk not after the flesh, but after the Spirit.', '0~2443~ 2~1345~ 5~3551~ 8~4137~ 9~1722~ 10~2254~, 12~4043~ 13~3361~ 14~2596~ 16~4561~, 17~235~ 18~2596~ 20~4151~.'),
  (2153, 2, 23, 4, 'If thou meet thine enemy''s ox or his ass going astray, thou shalt surely bring it back to him again.', '2~06293~ 4~0341~ 5~07794~ 8~02543~ 10~08582~, 13~07725~ 16~07725~ 19~07725~.'),
  (11790, 14, 28, 17, 'For again the Edomites had come and smitten Judah, and carried away captives.', '3~0130~ 5~0935~ 7~05221~ 8~03063~, 11~07617~ 12~07628~.'),
  (12633, 16, 11, 36, 'And of the Levites were divisions in Judah, and in Benjamin.', '3~03881~ [4] 5~04256~ [6] 7~03063~, [8] 10~01144~.'),
  (5317, 5, 14, 21, 'Ye shall not eat of any thing that dieth of itself: thou shalt give it unto the stranger that is in thy gates, that he may eat it; or thou mayest sell it unto an alien: for thou art an holy people unto the LORD thy God. Thou shalt not seethe a kid in his mother''s milk.', '3~0398~ [4] 10~05038~: 13~05414~ 17~01616~ [19] 22~08179~, 26~0398~ 31~04376~ 35~05237~: [38] 40~06918~ 41~05971~ 44~03068~ 46~0430~. 50~01310~ 52~01423~ 55~0517~ 56~02461~.'),
  (21641, 26, 45, 2, 'Of this there shall be for the sanctuary five hundred in length, with five hundred in breadth, square round about; and fifty cubits round about for the suburbs thereof.', '7~06944~ 8~02568~ 9~03967~ [10 11] 13~02568~ 14~03967~ [15 16] 17~07251~ 19~05439~; 21~02572~ 22~0520~ 24~05439~ 27~04054~'),
  (19127, 24, 6, 29, 'The bellows are burned, the lead is consumed of the fire; the founder melteth in vain: for the wicked are not plucked away.', '1~04647~ 3~02787~, 5~05777~ 7~08552~ 10~0784~ 11~0800~;* 13~06884~ 14~06884~ 16~07723~: 19~07451~ 23~05423~.'),
  (28374, 45, 16, 22, 'I Tertius, who wrote this epistle, salute you in the Lord.', '0~1473~ 1~5060~, 3~1125~ [4] 5~1992~, 6~782~ 7~5209~ 8~1722~ 10~2962~.'),
  (30347, 59, 3, 12, 'Can the fig tree, my brethren, bear olive berries? either a vine, figs? so can no fountain both yield salt water and fresh.', '0~1410~ 1~3361~* 4~4808~, 5~3450~ 6~80~, 7~4160~ 9~1636~? 10~2228~ 12~288~, 13~4810~? 14~3779~ [15] 16~3762~ 17~4077~ 19~4160~ 20~252~ 21~5204~ 22~2532~ 23~1099~.'),
  (10289, 13, 1, 29, 'These are their generations: The firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth; then Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsam,', '[1] 3~08435~: 5~01060~ 7~03458~, 8~05032~; 10~06938~, 12~0110~, 14~04017~,'),
  (23589, 40, 13, 40, 'As therefore the tares are gathered and burned in the fire; so shall it be in the end of this world.', '0~5618~ 1~3767~ 3~2215~ 5~4816~ 6~2532~ 7~2618~ 10~4442~; 11~3779~ 14~2071~ 15~1722~ 17~4930~ 19~5127~ 20~165~.'),
  (8350, 10, 13, 26, 'Then said Absalom, If not, I pray thee, let my brother Amnon go with us. And the king said unto him, Why should he go with thee?', '1~0559~ 2~053~, 10~0251~ 11~0550~ 12~03212~ 17~04428~ 18~0559~ 24~03212~'),
  (16869, 20, 16, 20, 'He that handleth a matter wisely shall find good: and whoso trusteth in the LORD, happy is he.', '&para; 4~01697~ 5~07919~ 7~04672~ 8~02896~: 11~0982~ 14~03068~, 15~0835~ [16]'),
  (18497, 23, 42, 8, 'I am the LORD: that is my name: and my glory will I not give to another, neither my praise to graven images.', '[1] 3~03068~: [5] 7~08034~: 10~03519~ 14~05414~ 16~0312~, 19~08416~ 22~06456~.'),
  (13753, 18, 36, 8, 'And if they be bound in fetters, and be holden in cords of affliction;', '[2 3] 4~0631~ 6~02131~, [7] 9~03920~ 11~02256~ 13~06040~;'),
  (26348, 43, 7, 5, 'For neither did his brethren believe in him.', '0~1063~ 1~3761~ 2~4100~ 3~846~ 4~80~ 5~4100~ 6~1519~ 7~846~.'),
  (3421, 3, 23, 14, 'And ye shall eat neither bread, nor parched corn, nor green ears, until the selfsame day that ye have brought an offering unto your God: it shall be a statute for ever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.', '3~0398~ 5~03899~, 8~07039~, 11~03759~, 14~02088~ 15~06106~* 16~03117~ 17~05704~ 20~0935~ 22~07133~ 25~0430~: [26 28] 30~02708~ 32~05769~ 35~01755~ 39~04186~.'),
  (19955, 24, 40, 5, 'Now while he was not yet gone back, he said, Go back also to Gedaliah the son of Ahikam the son of Shaphan, whom the king of Babylon hath made governor over the cities of Judah, and dwell with him among the people: or go wheresoever it seemeth convenient unto thee to go. So the captain of the guard gave him victuals and a reward, and let him go.', '7~07725~, [8 9] 11~07725~ 14~01436~ 16~01121~ 18~0296~ 20~01121~ 22~08227~, 25~04428~ 27~0894~ 30~06485~ 33~05892~ 35~03063~, 37~03427~ 40~08432~ 42~05971~: 44~03212~ 48~05869~ 49~03477~ 52~03212~. 55~07227~ 58~02876~ 59~05414~ 61~0737~ 64~04864~, 68~07971~.'),
  (7336, 9, 5, 10, 'Therefore they sent the ark of God to Ekron. And it came to pass, as the ark of God came to Ekron, that the Ekronites cried out, saying, They have brought about the ark of the God of Israel to us, to slay us and our people.', '2~07971~ 4~0727~ 6~0430~ 8~06138~. 16~0727~ 18~0430~ 19~0935~ 21~06138~, 24~06139~ 26~02199~, 27~0559~, 31~05437~ 33~0727~ 36~0430~ 38~03478~ 42~04191~ 46~05971~.'),
  (7499, 9, 13, 7, 'And some of the Hebrews went over Jordan to the land of Gad and Gilead. As for Saul, he was yet in Gilgal, and all the people followed him trembling.', '[1 2] 4~05680~ 6~05674~ 7~03383~ 10~0776~ 12~01410~ 14~01568~. 17~07586~, [19] 22~01537~, 26~05971~ 27~0310~ 29~02729~.'),
  (27234, 44, 9, 2, 'And desired of him letters to Damascus to the synagogues, that if he found any of this way, whether they were men or women, he might bring them bound unto Jerusalem.', '1~154~ 2~3844~ 3~846~ 4~1992~ 5~1519~ 6~1154~ 7~4314~ 9~4864~, 10~3704~ 11~1437~ 13~2147~ 14~5100~ 17~3598~, 18~5037~ 20~5607~ 21~435~ 22~2532~ 23~1135~, 27~71~ 28~1210~ 29~1519~ 30~2419~.'),
  (4778, 4, 33, 12, 'And they took their journey out of the wilderness of Sin, and encamped in Dophkah.', '4~05265~ 8~04057~ 10~05512~, 12~02583~ 14~01850~.'),
  (23801, 40, 19, 29, 'And every one that hath forsaken houses, or brethren, or sisters, or father, or mother, or wife, or children, or lands, for my name''s sake, shall receive an hundredfold, and shall inherit everlasting life.', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 2~3739~ 5~863~ 6~3614~, 7~2228~ 8~80~, 9~2228~ 10~79~, 11~2228~ 12~3962~, 13~2228~ 14~3384~, 15~2228~ 16~1135~, 17~2228~ 18~5043~, 19~2228~ 20~68~, 22~3450~ 23~3686~ 24~1752~, 26~2983~ 28~1542~, 29~2532~ 31~2816~ 32~166~ 33~2222~.'),
  (10440, 13, 5, 4, 'The sons of Joel; Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son,', '1~01121~ 3~03100~; 4~08098~ 6~01121~, 7~01463~ 9~01121~, 10~08096~ 12~01121~,'),
  (15064, 19, 74, 7, 'They have cast fire into thy sanctuary, they have defiled by casting down the dwelling place of thy name to the ground.', '2~07971~ 3~0784~ 6~04720~, 9~02490~ [10 12] 15~04908~ 18~08034~ 21~0776~.'),
  (5065, 5, 5, 6, 'I am the LORD thy God, which brought thee out of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage.', '&para; [1] 3~03068~ 5~0430~, 9~03318~ 12~0776~ 14~04714~, 17~01004~ 19~05650~.'),
  (28268, 45, 12, 7, 'Or ministry, let us wait on our ministering: or he that teacheth, on teaching;', '0~1535~ 1~1248~, [2 4] 5~1722~ [6] 7~1248~: 8~1535~ 11~1321~, 12~1722~ 13~1319~;'),
  (8356, 10, 13, 32, 'And Jonadab, the son of Shimeah David''s brother, answered and said, Let not my lord suppose that they have slain all the young men the king''s sons; for Amnon only is dead: for by the appointment of Absalom this hath been determined from the day that he forced his sister Tamar.', '1~03122~, 3~01121~ 5~08093~ 6~01732~ 7~0251~, 8~06030~ 10~0559~, 14~0113~ 15~0559~ [16] 19~04191~ 23~05288~ 25~04428~ 26~01121~; 28~0550~ 31~04191~: 35~06310~ 37~053~ 41~07760~ 44~03117~ 47~06031~ 49~0269~ 50~08559~.'),
  (7817, 9, 22, 23, 'Abide thou with me, fear not: for he that seeketh my life seeketh thy life: but with me thou shalt be in safeguard.', '0~03427~ 4~03372~ 9~01245~ 11~05315~ 12~01245~ 14~05315~: [19 20] 22~04931~.'),
  (17219, 20, 28, 14, 'Happy is the man that feareth alway: but he that hardeneth his heart shall fall into mischief.', '&para; 0~0835~ [1] 3~0120~ 5~06342~ 6~08548~: 10~07185~ 12~03820~ 14~05307~ 16~07451~.'),
  (26164, 43, 3, 29, 'He that hath the bride is the bridegroom: but the friend of the bridegroom, which standeth and heareth him, rejoiceth greatly because of the bridegroom''s voice: this my joy therefore is fulfilled.', '2~2192~ 4~3565~ 5~2076~ 7~3566~: 8~1161~ 10~5384~ 13~3566~, 14~3588~ 15~2476~ 16~2532~ 17~191~ 18~846~, 19~5463~ 20~5479~ 21~1223~ 24~3566~ 25~5456~: 26~3778~ 27~1699~ 28~5479~ 29~3767~ 31~4137~.'),
  (31018, 66, 18, 9, 'And the kings of the earth, who have committed fornication and lived deliciously with her, shall bewail her, and lament for her, when they shall see the smoke of her burning,', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~935~ 5~1093~, 6~3588~ 9~4203~ 10~2532~ 12~4763~ 13~3326~ 14~846~, 16~2799~ 17~846~, 18~2532~ 19~2875~ 20~1909~ 21~846~, 22~3752~ 25~991~ 27~2586~ 29~846~ 30~4451~,'),
  (24089, 40, 26, 25, 'Then Judas, which betrayed him, answered and said, Master, is it I? He said unto him, Thou hast said.', '0~1161~ 1~2455~, 2~3588~ 3~3860~ 4~846~, 5~611~ 7~2036~, 8~4461~, 9~1510~ 10~3385~ 11~1473~? 13~3004~ 15~846~, 16~4771~ 18~2036~.'),
  (10328, 13, 2, 14, 'Nethaneel the fourth, Raddai the fifth,', '0~05417~ 2~07243~, 3~07288~ 5~02549~,'),
  (4363, 4, 21, 18, 'The princes digged the well, the nobles of the people digged it, by the direction of the lawgiver, with their staves. And from the wilderness they went to Mattanah:', '1~08269~ 2~02658~ 4~0875~, 6~05081~ 9~05971~ 10~03738~ [13 15] 17~02710~, 20~04938~. 24~04057~ [25 26] 28~04980~:'),
  (21311, 26, 33, 22, 'Now the hand of the LORD was upon me in the evening, afore he that was escaped came; and had opened my mouth, until he came to me in the morning; and my mouth was opened, and I was no more dumb.', '2~03027~ 5~03068~ 11~06153~, 12~06440~ 16~06412~ 17~0935~; 20~06605~ 22~06310~, 25~0935~ 30~01242~; 33~06310~ 35~06605~, 41~0481~.'),
  (17915, 23, 12, 6, 'Cry out and shout, thou inhabitant of Zion: for great is the Holy One of Israel in the midst of thee.', '1~06670~ 3~07442~, 5~03427~ 7~06726~: 9~01419~ [10] 13~06918~ 15~03478~ 18~07130~'),
  (178, 1, 7, 18, 'And the waters prevailed, and were increased greatly upon the earth; and the ark went upon the face of the waters.', '2~04325~ 3~01396~, 6~07235~ 7~03966~ 10~0776~; 13~08392~ 14~03212~ 17~06440~ 20~04325~.'),
  (17224, 20, 28, 19, 'He that tilleth his land shall have plenty of bread: but he that followeth after vain persons shall have poverty enough.', '&para; 2~05647~ 4~0127~ 7~07646~ 9~03899~: 13~07291~ 15~07386~ [16] 20~07389~.'),
  (21600, 26, 43, 19, 'And thou shalt give to the priests the Levites that be of the seed of Zadok, which approach unto me, to minister unto me, saith the Lord GOD, a young bullock for a sin offering.', '3~05414~ 6~03548~ 8~03881~ 13~02233~ 15~06659~, 17~07138~ 21~08334~ 24~05002~ 26~0136~ 27~03069~, 29~01241~ 30~01121~* 31~06499~ 35~02403~.'),
  (26590, 43, 11, 52, 'And not for that nation only, but that also he should gather together in one the children of God that were scattered abroad.', '0~2532~ 1~3756~ 3~5228~ 4~1484~ 5~3440~, 6~235~ 7~2443~ 8~2532~ 12~4863~ 13~1519~ 14~1520~ 16~5043~ 18~2316~ 22~1287~.'),
  (19377, 24, 17, 11, 'As the partridge sitteth on eggs, and hatcheth them not; so he that getteth riches, and not by right, shall leave them in the midst of his days, and at his end shall be a fool.', '[0] 2~07124~ 3~01716~ [4 5] 7~03205~ [8] [10] 13~06213~ 14~06239~, 18~04941~, 20~05800~ 24~02677~ 27~03117~, 31~0319~ 35~05036~.'),
  (19870, 24, 36, 19, 'Then said the princes unto Baruch, Go, hide thee, thou and Jeremiah; and let no man know where ye be.', '1~0559~ 3~08269~ 5~01263~, 6~03212~, 7~05641~ 11~03414~; 15~0376~ 16~03045~ 17~0375~'),
  (16386, 19, 148, 6, 'He hath also stablished them for ever and ever: he hath made a decree which shall not pass.', '3~05975~ 6~05703~ 8~05769~: 11~05414~ 13~02706~ 17~05674~.'),
  (21629, 26, 44, 21, 'Neither shall any priest drink wine, when they enter into the inner court.', '3~03548~ 4~08354~ 5~03196~, 8~0935~ 11~06442~ 12~02691~.'),
  (21380, 26, 36, 12, 'Yea, I will cause men to walk upon you, even my people Israel; and they shall possess thee, and thou shalt be their inheritance, and thou shalt no more henceforth bereave them of men.', '4~0120~ 6~03212~ [9] 11~05971~ 12~03478~; 16~03423~ 23~05159~, 28~03254~ 30~07921~ [32 33]'),
  (17697, 23, 2, 3, 'And many people shall go and say, Come ye, and let us go up to the mountain of the LORD, to the house of the God of Jacob; and he will teach us of his ways, and we will walk in his paths: for out of Zion shall go forth the law, and the word of the LORD from Jerusalem.', '1~07227~ 2~05971~ 4~01980~ 6~0559~, 7~03212~ 13~05927~ 16~02022~ 19~03068~, 22~01004~ 25~0430~ 27~03290~; 31~03384~ 35~01870~, 39~03212~ 42~0734~: 46~06726~ 49~03318~ 51~08451~, 54~01697~ 57~03068~ 59~03389~.'),
  (978, 1, 33, 13, 'And he said unto him, My lord knoweth that the children are tender, and the flocks and herds with young are with me: and if men should overdrive them one day, all the flock will die.', '2~0559~ 6~0113~ 7~03045~ 10~03206~ [11] 12~07390~, 15~06629~ 17~01241~ 19~05763~ [20] 27~01849~ 29~0259~ 30~03117~, 33~06629~ 35~04191~.'),
  (28108, 45, 7, 1, 'Know ye not, brethren, (for I speak to them that know the law,) how that the law hath dominion over a man as long as he liveth?', '&para; 0~2228~ 3~50~, 4~80~, 5~1063~* 8~2980~ 12~1097~ 14~3551~,) 16~3754~ 18~3551~ 21~2961~ 23~444~ 26~5550~ 27~1909~* 28~3745~ 29~2198~?'),
  (30446, 60, 3, 6, 'Even as Sara obeyed Abraham, calling him lord: whose daughters ye are, as long as ye do well, and are not afraid with any amazement.', '1~5613~ 2~4564~ 3~5219~ 4~11~, 5~2564~ 6~846~ 7~2962~: 8~3739~ 9~5043~ 11~1096~, 17~15~, 18~2532~ 19~5399~ 20~3361~ 21~5399~ 23~3367~ 24~4423~.'),
  (9869, 12, 12, 11, 'And they gave the money, being told, into the hands of them that did the work, that had the oversight of the house of the LORD: and they laid it out to the carpenters and builders, that wrought upon the house of the LORD,', '2~05414~ 4~03701~, 6~08505~, 9~03027~ 13~06213~ 15~04399~, 19~06485~ 22~01004~ 25~03068~: 30~03318~ 33~06086~ 34~02796~ 35~01129~, 37~06213~ 40~01004~ 43~03068~,'),
  (8266, 10, 10, 19, 'And when all the kings that were servants to Hadarezer saw that they were smitten before Israel, they made peace with Israel, and served them. So the Syrians feared to help the children of Ammon any more.', '4~04428~ [5 6] 7~05650~ 9~01928~ 10~07200~ 14~05062~ 15~06440~ 16~03478~, 19~07999~ 21~03478~, 23~05647~ 27~0758~ 28~03372~ 30~03467~ 32~01121~ 34~05983~'),
  (23231, 40, 4, 12, 'Now when Jesus had heard that John was cast into prison, he departed into Galilee;', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~2424~ 4~191~ 5~3754~ 6~2491~ 10~3860~, 12~402~ 13~1519~ 14~1056~;'),
  (6425, 6, 21, 37, 'Kedemoth with her suburbs, and Mephaath with her suburbs; four cities.', '0~06932~ 5~04158~ 9~0702~ 10~05892~.'),
  (8907, 11, 6, 3, 'And the porch before the temple of the house, twenty cubits was the length thereof, according to the breadth of the house; and ten cubits was the breadth thereof before the house.', '2~0197~ 3~06440~ 5~01964~ 8~01004~, 9~06242~ 10~0520~ [11] 13~0753~ 18~07341~ 21~01004~; [22] 23~06235~ 24~0520~ [25] 27~07341~ 31~01004~.'),
  (11994, 14, 35, 19, 'In the eighteenth year of the reign of Josiah was this passover kept.', '2~06240~ 3~08083~* 4~08141~ 7~04438~ 9~02977~ 12~06453~ 13~06213~.'),
  (4239, 4, 16, 40, 'To be a memorial unto the children of Israel, that no stranger, which is not of the seed of Aaron, come near to offer incense before the LORD; that he be not as Korah, and as his company: as the LORD said to him by the hand of Moses.', '[0 1] 3~02146~ 6~01121~ 8~03478~, 9~04616~ 10~0834~ 11~02114~ 12~0376~,* [14] 18~02233~ 20~0175~, 22~07126~ 24~06999~ 25~07004~ 26~06440~ 28~03068~; 34~07141~, 38~05712~: 41~03068~ 42~01696~ 47~03027~ 49~04872~.'),
  (6873, 7, 11, 37, 'And she said unto her father, Let this thing be done for me: let me alone two months, that I may go up and down upon the mountains, and bewail my virginity, I and my fellows.', '2~0559~ 5~01~, 8~01697~ 10~06213~ 15~07503~ 16~08147~ 17~02320~, 22~03212~ 24~03381~ 27~02022~, 29~01058~ 31~01331~, 35~07464~ 36~07474~.*'),
  (5418, 5, 19, 6, 'Lest the avenger of the blood pursue the slayer, while his heart is hot, and overtake him, because the way is long, and slay him; whereas he was not worthy of death, inasmuch as he hated him not in time past.', '2~01350~ 5~01818~ 6~07291~ 8~07523~ 9~0310~,* 10~03588~ 12~03824~ 14~03179~, 16~05381~ 20~01870~ 22~07235~, 24~05221~ 25~05315~; [28] 30~04941~ 32~04194~, 34~03588~ 36~08130~ 40~08543~ 41~08032~.'),
  (28281, 45, 12, 20, 'Therefore if thine enemy hunger, feed him; if he thirst, give him drink: for in so doing thou shalt heap coals of fire on his head.', '0~3767~ 1~1437~ 2~4675~ 3~2190~ 4~3983~, 5~5595~ 6~846~; 7~1437~ 9~1372~, 10~4222~ 11~846~ 12~4222~: 13~1063~ 15~5124~ 16~4160~ 19~4987~ 20~440~ 22~4442~ 23~1909~ 24~846~ 25~2776~.'),
  (2642, 2, 38, 4, 'And he made for the altar a brazen grate of network under the compass thereof beneath unto the midst of it.', '2~06213~ 5~04196~ 7~05178~ 8~04345~ 10~04639~ 11~07568~ 13~03749~ 15~04295~ 18~02677~'),
  (27229, 44, 8, 37, 'And Philip said, If thou believest with all thine heart, thou mayest. And he answered and said, I believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God.', '0~1161~ 1~5376~ 2~2036~, 3~1487~ 5~4100~ 6~1537~ 8~3650~ 9~2588~, 11~1832~. 12~1161~ 14~611~ 16~2036~, 18~4100~ 20~2424~ 21~5547~ 22~1511~ 24~5207~ 26~2316~.'),
  (29711, 53, 3, 17, 'The salutation of Paul with mine own hand, which is the token in every epistle: so I write.', '1~783~ 3~3972~ 6~1699~ 7~5495~, 8~3739~ 9~2076~ 11~4592~ 12~1722~ 13~3956~ 14~1992~: 15~3779~ 17~1125~.'),
  (11828, 14, 29, 28, 'And all the congregation worshipped, and the singers sang, and the trumpeters sounded: and all this continued until the burnt offering was finished.', '3~06951~ 4~07812~, 7~07892~ 8~07891~, 11~02689~ 12~02690~ [13] [15 16] 20~05930~ 22~03615~.'),
  (5387, 5, 17, 17, 'Neither shall he multiply wives to himself, that his heart turn not away: neither shall he greatly multiply to himself silver and gold.', '3~07235~ 4~0802~ 9~03824~ 10~05493~ 16~03966~ 17~07235~ 20~03701~ 22~02091~.'),
  (5455, 5, 21, 2, 'Then thy elders and thy judges shall come forth, and they shall measure unto the cities which are round about him that is slain:', '2~02205~ 5~08199~ 8~03318~, 12~04058~ 15~05892~ [17] 19~05439~ 23~02491~:'),
  (7631, 9, 17, 6, 'And he had greaves of brass upon his legs, and a target of brass between his shoulders.', '[1 2] 3~04697~ 5~05178~ 8~07272~, 11~03591~ 13~05178~ 16~03802~.'),
  (252, 1, 10, 17, 'And the Hivite, and the Arkite, and the Sinite,', '2~02340~, 5~06208~, 8~05513~,'),
  (17644, 22, 7, 8, 'I said, I will go up to the palm tree, I will take hold of the boughs thereof: now also thy breasts shall be as clusters of the vine, and the smell of thy nose like apples;', '1~0559~, 5~05927~ 9~08558~, 13~0270~ 16~05577~ 21~07699~ 25~0811~ 28~01612~, 31~07381~ 34~0639~ 36~08598~;'),
  (22328, 29, 2, 8, 'Neither shall one thrust another; they shall walk every one in his path: and when they fall upon the sword, they shall not be wounded.', '2~0376~ 3~01766~ 4~0251~; 7~03212~ 9~01397~ 12~04546~: [14] 16~05307~ 19~07973~, 24~01214~.'),
  (5291, 5, 13, 13, 'Certain men, the children of Belial, are gone out from among you, and have withdrawn the inhabitants of their city, saying, Let us go and serve other gods, which ye have not known;', '[0] 1~0582~, 3~01121~ 5~01100~, 8~03318~ 10~07130~ 14~05080~ 16~03427~ 19~05892~, 20~0559~, 23~03212~ 25~05647~ 26~0312~ 27~0430~, 32~03045~;'),
  (13173, 18, 13, 11, 'Shall not his excellency make you afraid? and his dread fall upon you?', '3~07613~ 6~01204~? 9~06343~ 10~05307~'),
  (17717, 23, 3, 1, 'For, behold, the Lord, the LORD of hosts, doth take away from Jerusalem and from Judah the stay and the staff, the whole stay of bread, and the whole stay of water.', '&para; 3~0113~, 5~03068~ 7~06635~, 10~05493~ 12~03389~ 15~03063~ 17~04937~ 20~04938~, 23~04937~ 25~03899~, 28~03605~ 29~04937~ 31~04325~,');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (13326, 18, 19, 20, 'My bone cleaveth to my skin and to my flesh, and I am escaped with the skin of my teeth.', '1~06106~ 2~01692~ 5~05785~ 9~01320~, 13~04422~ 16~05785~ 19~08127~.'),
  (5646, 5, 28, 29, 'And thou shalt grope at noonday, as the blind gropeth in darkness, and thou shalt not prosper in thy ways: and thou shalt be only oppressed and spoiled evermore, and no man shall save thee.', '3~04959~ 5~06672~, 8~05787~ 9~04959~ 11~0653~, 16~06743~ 19~01870~: 25~06231~ 27~01497~ 28~03117~, 33~03467~ [34]'),
  (6566, 7, 2, 14, 'And the anger of the LORD was hot against Israel, and he delivered them into the hands of spoilers that spoiled them, and he sold them into the hands of their enemies round about, so that they could not any longer stand before their enemies.', '2~0639~ 5~03068~ 7~02734~ 9~03478~, 12~05414~ 16~03027~ 18~08154~ 20~08155~ 24~04376~ 28~03027~ 31~0341~ 33~05439~, 37~03201~ 40~05750~ 41~05975~ 42~06440~ 44~0341~.'),
  (19550, 24, 25, 7, 'Yet ye have not hearkened unto me, saith the LORD; that ye might provoke me to anger with the works of your hands to your own hurt.', '4~08085~ 7~05002~ 9~03068~; 16~03707~ 19~04639~ 22~03027~ 26~07451~.'),
  (8223, 10, 8, 7, 'And David took the shields of gold that were on the servants of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem.', '1~01732~ 2~03947~ 4~07982~ 6~02091~ 11~05650~ 13~01909~, 15~0935~ 18~03389~.'),
  (16529, 20, 5, 3, 'For the lips of a strange woman drop as an honeycomb, and her mouth is smoother than oil:', '2~08193~ 6~02114~ 7~05197~ [8] 10~05317~, 13~02441~ [14] 15~02509~ 17~08081~:'),
  (20798, 26, 16, 27, 'Behold, therefore I have stretched out my hand over thee, and have diminished thine ordinary food, and delivered thee unto the will of them that hate thee, the daughters of the Philistines, which are ashamed of thy lewd way.', '5~05186~ 7~03027~ 12~01639~ 14~02706~ [15] 17~05414~ 21~05315~ 25~08130~ 28~01323~ 31~06430~, 34~03637~ 37~02154~ 38~01870~.'),
  (677, 1, 25, 15, 'Hadar, and Tema, Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah:', '0~02316~, 2~08485~, 3~03195~, 4~05305~, 6~06929~:'),
  (2976, 3, 9, 18, 'He slew also the bullock and the ram for a sacrifice of peace offerings, which was for the people: and Aaron''s sons presented unto him the blood, which he sprinkled upon the altar round about,', '1~07819~ 4~07794~ 7~0352~ [8] 10~02077~ 13~08002~, [15] 18~05971~: 20~0175~ 21~01121~ 22~04672~ 26~01818~, 29~02236~ 32~04196~ 34~05439~,'),
  (5215, 5, 11, 1, 'Therefore thou shalt love the LORD thy God, and keep his charge, and his statutes, and his judgments, and his commandments, alway.', '&para; 3~0157~ 5~03068~ 7~0430~, 9~08104~ 11~04931~, 14~02708~, 17~04941~, 20~04687~, 21~03117~.'),
  (26712, 43, 14, 29, 'And now I have told you before it come to pass, that, when it is come to pass, ye might believe.', '0~2532~ 1~3568~ 4~2046~ 5~5213~ 6~4250~ 10~1096~, 11~2443~, 12~3752~ 17~1096~, 20~4100~.'),
  (20137, 24, 49, 1, 'Concerning the Ammonites, thus saith the LORD; Hath Israel no sons? hath he no heir? why then doth their king inherit Gad, and his people dwell in his cities?', '&para; 2~05983~ 3~01121~,* 5~0559~ 7~03068~; 9~03478~ 11~01121~? 15~03423~? [17] 20~04428~ 21~03423~ 22~01410~, 25~05971~ 26~03427~ 29~05892~?'),
  (4925, 5, 1, 27, 'And ye murmured in your tents, and said, Because the LORD hated us, he hath brought us forth out of the land of Egypt, to deliver us into the hand of the Amorites, to destroy us.', '2~07279~ 5~0168~, 7~0559~, 10~03068~ 11~08135~ 17~03318~ 21~0776~ 23~04714~, 25~05414~ 29~03027~ 32~0567~, 34~08045~'),
  (11300, 14, 6, 10, 'The LORD therefore hath performed his word that he hath spoken: for I am risen up in the room of David my father, and am set on the throne of Israel, as the LORD promised, and have built the house for the name of the LORD God of Israel.', '1~03068~ 4~06965~ 6~01697~ 10~01696~: 15~06965~ 20~01732~ 22~01~, 25~03427~ 28~03678~ 30~03478~, 33~03068~ 34~01696~, 37~01129~ 39~01004~ 42~08034~ 45~03068~ 46~0430~ 48~03478~.'),
  (4866, 4, 35, 15, 'These six cities shall be a refuge, both for the children of Israel, and for the stranger, and for the sojourner among them: that every one that killeth any person unawares may flee thither.', '1~08337~ 2~05892~ 6~04733~, [7] 10~01121~ 12~03478~, 16~01616~, 20~08453~ 21~08432~ 27~05221~ 29~05315~ 30~07684~ 32~05127~'),
  (20453, 25, 5, 2, 'Our inheritance is turned to strangers, our houses to aliens.', '1~05159~ 3~02015~ 5~02114~, 7~01004~ 9~05237~.'),
  (6154, 6, 12, 18, 'The king of Aphek, one; the king of Lasharon, one;', '1~04428~ 3~0663~, 4~0259~; 6~04428~ 8~08289~, 9~0259~;'),
  (7205, 8, 4, 8, 'Therefore the kinsman said unto Boaz, Buy it for thee. So he drew off his shoe.', '2~01350~ 3~0559~ 5~01162~, 6~07069~ [7] 13~08025~ 15~05275~.'),
  (16517, 20, 4, 18, 'But the path of the just is as the shining light, that shineth more and more unto the perfect day.', '2~0734~ 5~06662~ [6] 9~05051~ 10~0216~, 12~0215~ 13~01980~ 18~03559~ 19~03117~.'),
  (937, 1, 32, 5, 'And I have oxen, and asses, flocks, and menservants, and womenservants: and I have sent to tell my lord, that I may find grace in thy sight.', '3~07794~, 5~02543~, 6~06629~, 8~05650~, 10~08198~: 14~07971~ 16~05046~ 18~0113~, 22~04672~ 23~02580~ 26~05869~.'),
  (26414, 43, 8, 18, 'I am one that bear witness of myself, and the Father that sent me beareth witness of me.', '0~1473~ 1~1510~ 5~3140~ 6~4012~ 7~1683~, 8~2532~ 10~3962~ 12~3992~ 13~3165~ 15~3140~ 16~4012~ 17~1700~.'),
  (10129, 12, 21, 2, 'And he did that which was evil in the sight of the LORD, after the abominations of the heathen, whom the LORD cast out before the children of Israel.', '2~06213~ [3 5] 6~07451~ 9~05869~ 12~03068~, 15~08441~ 18~01471~, 21~03068~ 23~03423~ 24~06440~ 26~01121~ 28~03478~.'),
  (24999, 42, 2, 14, 'Glory to God in the highest, and on earth peace, good will toward men.', '0~1391~ 2~2316~ 3~1722~ 5~5310~, 6~2532~ 7~1909~ 8~1093~ 9~1515~, 11~2107~ 12~1722~ 13~444~.'),
  (26061, 43, 1, 3, 'All things were made by him; and without him was not any thing made that was made.', '1~3956~ 3~1096~ 4~1223~ 5~846~; 6~2532~ 7~5565~ 8~846~ 9~1096~ 10~3761~ 12~1520~ 13~1096~ 14~3739~ 16~1096~.'),
  (23785, 40, 19, 13, 'Then were there brought unto him little children, that he should put his hands on them, and pray: and the disciples rebuked them.', '&para; 0~5119~ 3~4374~ 5~846~ 7~3813~, 8~2443~ 11~2007~ [12] 13~5495~ 14~2007~ 15~846~, 16~2532~ 17~4336~: 18~1161~ 20~3101~ 21~2008~ 22~846~.'),
  (7772, 9, 20, 35, 'And it came to pass in the morning, that Jonathan went out into the field at the time appointed with David, and a little lad with him.', '&para; 7~01242~, 9~03083~ 11~03318~ 14~07704~ 18~04150~ 20~01732~, 23~06996~ 24~05288~'),
  (30420, 60, 2, 5, 'Ye also, as lively stones, are built up a spiritual house, an holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices, acceptable to God by Jesus Christ.', '0~846~ 1~2532~, 2~5613~ 3~2198~ 4~3037~, 7~3618~ 9~4152~ 10~3624~, 12~40~ 13~2406~, 16~399~ 17~4152~ 18~2378~, 19~2144~ 21~2316~ 22~1223~ 23~2424~ 24~5547~.'),
  (4161, 4, 15, 3, 'And will make an offering by fire unto the LORD, a burnt offering, or a sacrifice in performing a vow, or in a freewill offering, or in your solemn feasts, to make a sweet savour unto the LORD, of the herd, or of the flock:', '2~06213~ 6~0801~ 9~03068~, 12~05930~, 15~02077~ 17~06381~ 19~05088~, 24~05071~, 29~04150~, 31~06213~ 33~05207~ 34~07381~ 37~03068~, 40~01241~, 44~06629~:'),
  (23238, 40, 4, 19, 'And he saith unto them, Follow me, and I will make you fishers of men.', '0~2532~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 5~1205~ 6~3694~* 7~3450~, 8~2532~ 11~4160~ 12~5209~ 13~231~ 15~444~.'),
  (14345, 19, 31, 5, 'Into thine hand I commit my spirit: thou hast redeemed me, O LORD God of truth.', '2~03027~ 4~06485~ 6~07307~: 9~06299~ 12~03068~ 13~0410~ 15~0571~.'),
  (29396, 50, 1, 19, 'For I know that this shall turn to my salvation through your prayer, and the supply of the Spirit of Jesus Christ,', '0~1063~ 2~1492~ 3~3754~ 4~5124~ 6~576~ 7~1519~ 8~3427~ 9~4991~ 10~1223~ 11~5216~ 12~1162~, 13~2532~ 15~2024~ 18~4151~ 20~2424~ 21~5547~,'),
  (20343, 25, 2, 2, 'The Lord hath swallowed up all the habitations of Jacob, and hath not pitied: he hath thrown down in his wrath the strong holds of the daughter of Judah; he hath brought them down to the ground: he hath polluted the kingdom and the princes thereof.', '1~0136~ 4~01104~ 7~04999~ 9~03290~, 13~02550~: 17~02040~ 20~05678~ 23~04013~ 26~01323~ 28~03063~; [32] 33~05060~ 36~0776~: 39~02490~ 41~04467~ 44~08269~'),
  (10427, 13, 4, 34, 'And Meshobab, and Jamlech, and Joshah, the son of Amaziah,', '1~04877~, 3~03230~, 5~03144~ 7~01121~ 9~0558~,'),
  (26611, 43, 12, 16, 'These things understood not his disciples at the first: but when Jesus was glorified, then remembered they that these things were written of him, and that they had done these things unto him.', '0~1161~ 1~5023~ 2~1097~ 3~3756~ 4~846~ 5~3101~ 8~4412~: 9~235~ 10~3753~ 11~2424~ 13~1392~, 14~5119~ 16~3415~ 17~3754~ 19~5023~ 20~2258~ 21~1125~ 22~1909~ 23~846~, 24~2532~ [25] 28~4160~ 30~5023~ 32~846~.'),
  (14804, 19, 59, 5, 'Thou therefore, O LORD God of hosts, the God of Israel, awake to visit all the heathen: be not merciful to any wicked transgressors. Selah.', '3~03068~ 4~0430~ 6~06635~, 8~0430~ 10~03478~, 11~06974~ 13~06485~ 16~01471~: 19~02603~ 22~0205~ 23~0898~. 24~05542~.'),
  (21839, 27, 3, 23, 'And these three men, Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, fell down bound into the midst of the burning fiery furnace.', '1~0479~ 2~08532~ 3~01400~, 4~07715~, 5~04336~, 7~05665~, 9~05308~ 10~03729~ 13~01459~ 16~03345~ 17~05135~ 18~0861~.'),
  (16023, 19, 119, 116, 'Uphold me according unto thy word, that I may live: and let me not be ashamed of my hope.', '&para; 0~05564~ 5~0565~, 9~02421~: 15~0954~ 18~07664~.'),
  (11310, 14, 6, 20, 'That thine eyes may be open upon this house day and night, upon the place whereof thou hast said that thou wouldest put thy name there; to hearken unto the prayer which thy servant prayeth toward this place.', '2~05869~ 5~06605~ 8~01004~ 9~03119~ 11~03915~, 14~04725~ 18~0559~ 22~07760~ 24~08034~ 27~08085~ 30~08605~ 33~05650~ 34~06419~ 37~04725~.'),
  (19434, 24, 20, 3, 'And it came to pass on the morrow, that Pashur brought forth Jeremiah out of the stocks. Then said Jeremiah unto him, The LORD hath not called thy name Pashur, but Magormissabib.', '7~04283~, 9~06583~ 11~03318~ 12~03414~ 16~04115~. 18~0559~ 19~03414~ 23~03068~ 26~07121~ 28~08034~ 29~06583~, 31~04036~.'),
  (21579, 26, 42, 18, 'He measured the south side, five hundred reeds, with the measuring reed.', '1~04058~ 3~01864~ 4~07307~, 5~02568~ 6~03967~ 7~07070~, 10~04060~ 11~07070~.'),
  (6084, 6, 10, 14, 'And there was no day like that before it or after it, that the LORD hearkened unto the voice of a man: for the LORD fought for Israel.', '4~03117~ 7~06440~ 10~0310~ 14~03068~ 15~08085~ 18~06963~ 21~0376~: 24~03068~ 25~03898~ 27~03478~.'),
  (10635, 13, 9, 12, 'And Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pashur, the son of Malchijah, and Maasiai the son of Adiel, the son of Jahzerah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Meshillemith, the son of Immer;', '1~05718~ 3~01121~ 5~03395~, 7~01121~ 9~06583~, 11~01121~ 13~04441~, 15~04640~ 17~01121~ 19~05717~, 21~01121~ 23~03170~, 25~01121~ 27~04918~, 29~01121~ 31~04921~, 33~01121~ 35~0564~;'),
  (15241, 19, 81, 15, 'The haters of the LORD should have submitted themselves unto him: but their time should have endured for ever.', '1~08130~ 4~03068~ 7~03584~ 13~06256~ 18~05769~.'),
  (25202, 42, 6, 44, 'For every tree is known by his own fruit. For of thorns men do not gather figs, nor of a bramble bush gather they grapes.', '0~1063~ 1~1538~ 2~1186~ 4~1097~ 5~1537~ 7~2398~ 8~2590~. 9~1063~ 10~1537~ 11~173~ 14~3756~ 15~4816~ 16~4810~, 17~3761~ 18~1537~ 21~942~ 23~5166~ 24~4718~.'),
  (2059, 2, 20, 3, 'Thou shalt have no other gods before me.', '4~0312~ 5~0430~ 7~06440~.'),
  (23560, 40, 13, 11, 'He answered and said unto them, Because it is given unto you to know the mysteries of the kingdom of heaven, but to them it is not given.', '1~611~ 2~1161~ 3~2036~ 5~846~, 6~3754~ 9~1325~ 11~5213~ 13~1097~ 15~3466~ 18~932~ 20~3772~, 21~1161~ 23~1565~ 25~1325~ 26~3756~ 27~1325~.'),
  (17146, 20, 25, 24, 'It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop, than with a brawling woman and in a wide house.', '&para; [0 1] 2~02896~ 4~03427~ 7~06438~ 10~01406~, 14~04079~ 15~04066~* 16~0802~ 20~02267~ 21~01004~.'),
  (1634, 2, 4, 28, 'And Moses told Aaron all the words of the LORD who had sent him, and all the signs which he had commanded him.', '1~04872~ 2~05046~ 3~0175~ 6~01697~ 9~03068~ 12~07971~ 17~0226~ 21~06680~'),
  (26506, 43, 10, 10, 'The thief cometh not, but for to steal, and to kill, and to destroy: I am come that they might have life, and that they might have it more abundantly.', '1~2812~ 2~2064~ 3~3756~, 4~1508~ 6~2443~ 7~2813~, 8~2532~ 10~2380~, 11~2532~ 13~622~: 14~1473~ 16~2064~ 17~2443~ 20~2192~ 21~2222~, 22~2532~ 26~2192~ [27] 29~4053~.'),
  (30890, 66, 11, 2, 'But the court which is without the temple leave out, and measure it not; for it is given unto the Gentiles: and the holy city shall they tread under foot forty and two months.', '0~2532~ 2~833~ 3~3588~ 5~2081~ 6~1855~ 7~3485~ 8~1544~ 9~1854~, 10~2532~ 11~3354~ 12~846~ 13~3361~; 14~3754~ 17~1325~ 20~1484~: 21~2532~ 23~40~ 24~4172~ 29~3961~ 30~5062~ [31] 32~1417~ 33~3376~.'),
  (11288, 14, 5, 12, 'Also the Levites which were the singers, all of them of Asaph, of Heman, of Jeduthun, with their sons and their brethren, being arrayed in white linen, having cymbals and psalteries and harps, stood at the east end of the altar, and with them an hundred and twenty priests sounding with trumpets:)', '2~03881~ [3 4] 6~07891~, 11~0623~, 13~01968~, 15~03038~, 18~01121~ 21~0251~, [22] 23~03847~ 26~0948~, 28~04700~ 30~05035~ 32~03658~, 33~05975~ 37~04217~ 40~04196~, 45~03967~ 47~06242~ 48~03548~ 49~02690~ 51~02689~:)'),
  (13722, 18, 34, 30, 'That the hypocrite reign not, lest the people be ensnared.', '2~02611~ 3~0120~* 4~04427~ 8~05971~ 10~04170~.'),
  (22971, 38, 6, 15, 'And they that are far off shall come and build in the temple of the LORD, and ye shall know that the LORD of hosts hath sent me unto you. And this shall come to pass, if ye will diligently obey the voice of the LORD your God.', '[2 3] 5~07350~ 7~0935~ 9~01129~ 12~01964~ 15~03068~, 19~03045~ 22~03068~ 24~06635~ 26~07971~ [31] 39~08085~ 40~08085~ 42~06963~ 45~03068~ 47~0430~.'),
  (6537, 7, 1, 21, 'And the children of Benjamin did not drive out the Jebusites that inhabited Jerusalem; but the Jebusites dwell with the children of Benjamin in Jerusalem unto this day.', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~01144~ 8~03423~ 10~02983~ 12~03427~ 13~03389~; 16~02983~ 17~03427~ 20~01121~ 22~01144~ 24~03389~ 27~03117~.'),
  (20564, 26, 5, 9, 'And I will do in thee that which I have not done, and whereunto I will not do any more the like, because of all thine abominations.', '3~06213~ 11~06213~, 17~06213~ 22~03282~ 26~08441~.'),
  (30152, 58, 10, 3, 'But in those sacrifices there is a remembrance again made of sins every year.', '0~235~ 1~1722~ 2~846~ [3 5] 8~364~ [9] 11~266~ 12~2596~ 13~1763~.'),
  (26620, 43, 12, 25, 'He that loveth his life shall lose it; and he that hateth his life in this world shall keep it unto life eternal.', '2~5368~ 3~846~ 4~5590~ 6~622~ 7~846~; 8~2532~ 11~3404~ 12~846~ 13~5590~ 14~1722~ 15~5129~ 16~2889~ 18~5442~ 19~846~ 20~1519~ 21~2222~ 22~166~.'),
  (7680, 9, 17, 55, 'And when Saul saw David go forth against the Philistine, he said unto Abner, the captain of the host, Abner, whose son is this youth? And Abner said, As thy soul liveth, O king, I cannot tell.', '2~07586~ 3~07200~ 4~01732~ 6~03318~ 7~07125~ 9~06430~, 11~0559~ 13~074~, 15~08269~ 18~06635~, 19~074~, 21~01121~ [22] 24~05288~? 26~074~ 27~0559~, [28] 30~05315~ 31~02416~, 33~04428~, 35~0518~ 36~03045~.'),
  (15406, 19, 91, 2, 'I will say of the LORD, He is my refuge and my fortress: my God; in him will I trust.', '2~0559~ 5~03068~, [6 7] 9~04268~ 12~04686~: 14~0430~; 19~0982~.'),
  (30042, 58, 4, 12, 'For the word of God is quick, and powerful, and sharper than any twoedged sword, piercing even to the dividing asunder of soul and spirit, and of the joints and marrow, and is a discerner of the thoughts and intents of the heart.', '0~1063~ 2~3056~ 4~2316~ [5] 6~2198~, 7~2532~ 8~1756~, 9~2532~ 10~5114~ 11~5228~ 12~3956~ 13~1366~ 14~3162~, 15~1338~ 17~891~ 20~3311~ 22~5590~ 23~2532~ 24~5037~* 25~4151~, 26~2532~ 27~5037~ 29~719~ 30~2532~ 31~3452~, 32~2532~ [33] 35~2924~ 38~1761~ 39~2532~ 40~1771~ 43~2588~.'),
  (21760, 27, 1, 14, 'So he consented to them in this matter, and proved them ten days.', '2~08085~ 7~01697~, 9~05254~ 11~06235~ 12~03117~.'),
  (21003, 26, 22, 18, 'Son of man, the house of Israel is to me become dross: all they are brass, and tin, and iron, and lead, in the midst of the furnace; they are even the dross of silver.', '0~01121~ 2~0120~, 4~01004~ 6~03478~ 11~05509~: [14] 15~05178~, 17~0913~, 19~01270~, 21~05777~, 24~08432~ 27~03564~; [30] 32~05509~ 34~03701~.'),
  (9929, 12, 14, 25, 'He restored the coast of Israel from the entering of Hamath unto the sea of the plain, according to the word of the LORD God of Israel, which he spake by the hand of his servant Jonah, the son of Amittai, the prophet, which was of Gathhepher.', '1~07725~ 3~01366~ 5~03478~ 8~0935~ 10~02574~ 13~03220~ 16~06160~, 20~01697~ 23~03068~ 24~0430~ 26~03478~, 29~01696~ 32~03027~ 35~05650~ 36~03124~, 38~01121~ 40~0573~, 42~05030~, [44] 46~01662~.'),
  (16277, 19, 140, 5, 'The proud have hid a snare for me, and cords; they have spread a net by the wayside; they have set gins for me. Selah.', '1~01343~ 3~02934~ 5~06341~ 9~02256~; 12~06566~ 14~07568~ 17~04570~ 18~03027~;* 21~07896~ 22~04170~ 25~05542~.'),
  (6339, 6, 19, 11, 'And their border went up toward the sea, and Maralah, and reached to Dabbasheth, and reached to the river that is before Jokneam;', '2~01366~ 4~05927~ 7~03220~, 9~04831~, 11~06293~ 13~01708~, 15~06293~ 18~05158~ [20] 21~06440~ 22~03362~;'),
  (24234, 41, 1, 9, 'And it came to pass in those days, that Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee, and was baptized of John in Jordan.', '&para; 0~2532~ 4~1096~ 5~1722~ 6~1565~ 7~2250~, 9~2424~ 10~2064~ 11~575~ 12~3478~ 14~1056~, 15~2532~ 17~907~ 18~5259~ 19~2491~ 20~1519~ 21~2446~.'),
  (27900, 44, 27, 29, 'Then fearing lest we should have fallen upon rocks, they cast four anchors out of the stern, and wished for the day.', '0~5037~ 1~5399~ 2~4458~ 3~3381~ 6~1601~ 7~1519~ 8~5138~ 9~5117~,* 11~4496~ 12~5064~ 13~45~ 15~1537~ 17~4403~, 19~2172~ 20~1096~* 23~2250~.'),
  (16115, 19, 124, 4, 'Then the waters had overwhelmed us, the stream had gone over our soul:', '0~0233~ 2~04325~ 4~07857~ 7~05158~ 10~05674~ 12~05315~:'),
  (17667, 23, 1, 4, 'Ah sinful nation, a people laden with iniquity, a seed of evildoers, children that are corrupters: they have forsaken the LORD, they have provoked the Holy One of Israel unto anger, they are gone away backward.', '0~01945~ 1~02398~ 2~01471~, 4~05971~ 5~03515~ 7~05771~, 9~02233~ 11~07489~, 12~01121~ 15~07843~: 18~05800~ 19~0853~* 21~03068~, 24~05006~ 25~0853~* 28~06918~ 30~03478~ 32~05006~, 36~02114~ 37~0268~.'),
  (18471, 23, 41, 11, 'Behold, all they that were incensed against thee shall be ashamed and confounded: they shall be as nothing; and they that strive with thee shall perish.', '5~02734~ 10~0954~ 12~03637~: 19~0582~ 21~07379~ 25~06~.'),
  (27954, 45, 1, 8, 'First, I thank my God through Jesus Christ for you all, that your faith is spoken of throughout the whole world.', '&para; 0~3303~ 1~4412~,* 3~2168~ 4~3450~ 5~2316~ 6~1223~ 7~2424~ 8~5547~ 9~5228~ 10~5216~ 11~3956~, 12~3754~ 13~5216~ 14~4102~ 16~2605~ 18~1722~ 20~3650~ 21~2889~.'),
  (1211, 1, 41, 11, 'And we dreamed a dream in one night, I and he; we dreamed each man according to the interpretation of his dream.', '2~02492~ 4~02472~ 6~0259~ 7~03915~, 12~02492~ 14~0376~ 18~06623~ 21~02472~.'),
  (6232, 6, 15, 23, 'And Kedesh, and Hazor, and Ithnan,', '1~06943~, 3~02674~, 5~03497~,'),
  (13941, 18, 42, 10, 'And the LORD turned the captivity of Job, when he prayed for his friends: also the LORD gave Job twice as much as he had before.', '&para; 2~03068~ 3~07725~ 5~07622~ 6~07622~* 8~0347~, 11~06419~ 14~07453~: 17~03068~ 18~03254~ 19~0347~ 22~04932~'),
  (9217, 11, 13, 25, 'And, behold, men passed by, and saw the carcase cast in the way, and the lion standing by the carcase: and they came and told it in the city where the old prophet dwelt.', '2~0582~ 4~05674~, 6~07200~ 8~05038~ 9~07993~ 12~01870~, 15~0738~ 16~05975~ 17~0681~ 19~05038~: 22~0935~ 24~01696~ [25] 28~05892~ 31~02205~ 32~05030~ 33~03427~.'),
  (1105, 1, 37, 17, 'And the man said, They are departed hence; for I heard them say, Let us go to Dothan. And Joseph went after his brethren, and found them in Dothan.', '2~0376~ 3~0559~, 6~05265~ 7~02088~; 10~08085~ 12~0559~, 15~03212~ 17~01886~. 19~03130~ 20~03212~ 21~0310~ 23~0251~, 25~04672~ 28~01886~.'),
  (21452, 26, 38, 18, 'And it shall come to pass at the same time when Gog shall come against the land of Israel, saith the Lord GOD, that my fury shall come up in my face.', '9~03117~ 10~03117~ 11~01463~ 13~0935~ 16~0127~ 18~03478~, 19~05002~ 21~0136~ 22~03069~, [23] 25~02534~ 28~05927~ 31~0639~.'),
  (13149, 18, 12, 12, 'With the ancient is wisdom; and in length of days understanding.', '&para; 2~03453~ [3] 4~02451~; 7~0753~ 9~03117~ 10~08394~.'),
  (714, 1, 26, 18, 'And Isaac digged again the wells of water, which they had digged in the days of Abraham his father; for the Philistines had stopped them after the death of Abraham: and he called their names after the names by which his father had called them.', '1~03327~ 2~02658~ 3~07725~ 5~0875~ 7~04325~, 11~02658~ 14~03117~ 16~085~ 18~01~; 21~06430~ 23~05640~ 25~0310~ 27~04194~ 29~085~: 32~07121~ 34~08034~ 37~08034~ 39~0834~ 41~01~ 43~07121~'),
  (1003, 1, 34, 18, 'And their words pleased Hamor, and Shechem Hamor''s son.', '&para; 2~01697~ 3~03190~ 4~05869~* 5~02544~, 7~07927~ 8~02544~ 9~01121~.'),
  (13182, 18, 13, 20, 'Only do not two things unto me: then will I not hide myself from thee.', '1~06213~ 3~08147~ [4] 11~05641~ 14~06440~.'),
  (11162, 13, 28, 11, 'Then David gave to Solomon his son the pattern of the porch, and of the houses thereof, and of the treasuries thereof, and of the upper chambers thereof, and of the inner parlours thereof, and of the place of the mercy seat,', '&para; 1~01732~ 2~05414~ 4~08010~ 6~01121~ 8~08403~ 11~0197~, 15~01004~ 20~01597~ 26~05944~ 31~06442~ 32~02315~ 37~01004~ 41~03727~,'),
  (9393, 11, 18, 44, 'And it came to pass at the seventh time, that he said, Behold, there ariseth a little cloud out of the sea, like a man''s hand. And he said, Go up, say unto Ahab, Prepare thy chariot, and get thee down, that the rain stop thee not.', '8~07637~, 11~0559~, 14~05927~ 16~06996~ 17~05645~ 21~03220~, 24~0376~ 25~03709~. 28~0559~, 30~05927~, 31~0559~ 33~0256~, 34~0631~ [35 36] 40~03381~, 43~01653~ 44~06113~'),
  (26877, 43, 19, 37, 'And again another scripture saith, They shall look on him whom they pierced.', '0~2532~ 1~3825~ 2~2087~ 3~1124~ 4~3004~, 7~3700~ 8~1519~ 10~3739~ 12~1574~.'),
  (20280, 24, 51, 59, 'The word which Jeremiah the prophet commanded Seraiah the son of Neriah, the son of Maaseiah, when he went with Zedekiah the king of Judah into Babylon in the fourth year of his reign. And this Seraiah was a quiet prince.', '&para; 1~01697~ 3~03414~ 5~05030~ 6~06680~ 7~08304~ 9~01121~ 11~05374~, 13~01121~ 15~04271~, 18~03212~ 20~06667~ 22~04428~ 24~03063~ 26~0894~ 29~07243~ 30~08141~ 33~04427~. [35] 36~08304~ [37] 39~04496~ 40~08269~.'),
  (2180, 2, 23, 31, 'And I will set thy bounds from the Red sea even unto the sea of the Philistines, and from the desert unto the river: for I will deliver the inhabitants of the land into your hand; and thou shalt drive them out before thee.', '3~07896~ 5~01366~ 8~05488~ 9~03220~ 13~03220~ 16~06430~, 20~04057~ 23~05104~: 27~05414~ 29~03427~ 32~0776~ 35~03027~; 41~01644~ 42~06440~'),
  (21402, 26, 36, 34, 'And the desolate land shall be tilled, whereas it lay desolate in the sight of all that passed by.', '2~08074~ 3~0776~ 6~05647~, 10~08077~ 13~05869~ 18~05674~.'),
  (27471, 44, 15, 13, 'And after they had held their peace, James answered, saying, Men and brethren, hearken unto me:', '0~1161~ 1~3326~ 4~4601~ 5~846~ 6~4601~, 7~2385~ 8~611~, 9~3004~, 10~435~ [11] 12~80~, 13~191~ 15~3450~:'),
  (16424, 20, 1, 15, 'My son, walk not thou in the way with them; refrain thy foot from their path:', '1~01121~, 2~03212~ 7~01870~ 10~04513~ 12~07272~ 15~05410~:'),
  (9076, 11, 9, 17, 'And Solomon built Gezer, and Bethhoron the nether,', '1~08010~ 2~01129~ 3~01507~, 5~01032~ 7~08481~,'),
  (23264, 40, 5, 20, 'For I say unto you, That except your righteousness shall exceed the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees, ye shall in no case enter into the kingdom of heaven.', '0~1063~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3754~ 6~3362~ 7~5216~ 8~1343~ 10~4052~ 11~4119~* [12 13] 16~1122~ 17~2532~ 18~5330~, 23~3364~ 24~1525~ 25~1519~ 27~932~ 29~3772~.'),
  (24635, 41, 10, 36, 'And he said unto them, What would ye that I should do for you?', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~5101~ 6~2309~ 9~3165~ 11~4160~ 13~5213~?'),
  (7183, 8, 3, 4, 'And it shall be, when he lieth down, that thou shalt mark the place where he shall lie, and thou shalt go in, and uncover his feet, and lay thee down; and he will tell thee what thou shalt do.', '7~07901~, 11~03045~ 13~04725~ 17~07901~, 22~0935~, 24~01540~ 26~04772~, 30~07901~; 34~05046~ 39~06213~.'),
  (21774, 27, 2, 7, 'They answered again and said, Let the king tell his servants the dream, and we will shew the interpretation of it.', '1~06032~ 2~08579~ 4~0560~, 7~04430~ 8~0560~ 10~05649~ 12~02493~, 16~02324~ 18~06591~'),
  (13332, 18, 19, 26, 'And though after my skin worms destroy this body, yet in my flesh shall I see God:', '[1] 2~0310~ 4~05785~ [5] 6~05362~ [8] 12~01320~ 15~02372~ 16~0433~:'),
  (18850, 23, 60, 20, 'Thy sun shall no more go down; neither shall thy moon withdraw itself: for the LORD shall be thine everlasting light, and the days of thy mourning shall be ended.', '1~08121~ 6~0935~; 10~03391~ 11~0622~ 15~03068~ 19~05769~ 20~0216~, 23~03117~ 26~060~ 29~07999~.'),
  (6214, 6, 15, 5, 'And the east border was the salt sea, even unto the end of Jordan. And their border in the north quarter was from the bay of the sea at the uttermost part of Jordan:', '2~06924~ 3~01366~ [4] 6~04417~ 7~03220~, [8] 11~07097~ 13~03383~. [15] 16~01366~ 19~06828~ 20~06285~ [21] 24~03956~ 27~03220~ 31~07097~ 33~03383~:'),
  (28759, 46, 15, 25, 'For he must reign, till he hath put all enemies under his feet.', '0~1063~ 1~846~ 2~1163~ 3~936~, 4~3757~ 5~891~ 7~5087~ 8~302~* 9~3956~ 10~2190~ 11~5259~ 12~846~ 13~4228~.'),
  (12719, 17, 1, 8, 'And the drinking was according to the law; none did compel: for so the king had appointed to all the officers of his house, that they should do according to every man''s pleasure.', '2~08360~ [3] 7~01881~; 10~0597~: 14~04428~ 16~03245~ 20~07227~ 23~01004~, 27~06213~ 31~0376~ 32~07522~.'),
  (3651, 4, 1, 42, 'Of the children of Naphtali, throughout their generations, after their families, by the house of their fathers, according to the number of the names, from twenty years old and upward, all that were able to go forth to war;', '2~01121~ 4~05321~, 7~08435~, 10~04940~, 13~01004~ 16~01~, 20~04557~ 23~08034~, 25~06242~ 26~08141~ 27~01121~ 29~04605~, 36~03318~ 38~06635~;');
