VALUES
  (4792, 4, 33, 26, 'And they removed from Makheloth, and encamped at Tahath.', '2~05265~ 4~04722~, 6~02583~ 8~08480~.'),
  (19643, 24, 28, 16, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD; Behold, I will cast thee from off the face of the earth: this year thou shalt die, because thou hast taught rebellion against the LORD.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~; 8~07971~ 13~06440~ 16~0127~: 18~08141~ 21~04191~, 25~01696~ 26~05627~ 29~03068~.'),
  (12836, 17, 8, 10, 'And he wrote in the king Ahasuerus'' name, and sealed it with the king''s ring, and sent letters by posts on horseback, and riders on mules, camels, and young dromedaries:', '2~03789~ 5~04428~ 6~0325~ 7~08034~, 9~02856~ [10] 13~04428~ 14~02885~, 16~07971~ 17~05612~ 18~03027~ 19~07323~ 21~05483~, [22] 23~07392~ 25~07409~, 26~0327~, [27] 28~01121~ 29~07424~:'),
  (19584, 24, 26, 3, 'If so be they will hearken, and turn every man from his evil way, that I may repent me of the evil, which I purpose to do unto them because of the evil of their doings.', '5~08085~, 7~07725~ 9~0376~ 12~07451~ 13~01870~, 17~05162~ 21~07451~, 24~02803~ 26~06213~ 29~06440~ 32~07455~ 35~04611~.'),
  (26883, 43, 20, 1, 'The first day of the week cometh Mary Magdalene early, when it was yet dark, unto the sepulchre, and seeth the stone taken away from the sepulchre.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~3391~ [3] 6~4521~ 7~2064~ 8~3137~ 9~3094~ 10~4404~, 13~5607~ 14~2089~ 15~4653~, 16~1519~ 18~3419~, 19~2532~ 20~991~ 22~3037~ 24~142~ 25~1537~ 27~3419~.'),
  (13306, 18, 18, 21, 'Surely such are the dwellings of the wicked, and this is the place of him that knoweth not God.', '[2] 4~04908~ 7~05767~, [10] 12~04725~ [13 15] 16~03045~ 18~0410~.'),
  (4132, 4, 14, 19, 'Pardon, I beseech thee, the iniquity of this people according unto the greatness of thy mercy, and as thou hast forgiven this people, from Egypt even until now.', '0~05545~, 5~05771~ 8~05971~ 12~01433~ 15~02617~, 20~05375~ 22~05971~, 24~04714~ 27~02008~.'),
  (23214, 40, 3, 12, 'Whose fan is in his hand, and he will thoroughly purge his floor, and gather his wheat into the garner; but he will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire.', '0~3739~ 1~4425~ [2] 3~1722~ 4~846~ 5~5495~, 6~2532~ 10~1245~ 11~846~ 12~257~, 13~2532~ 14~4863~ 15~846~ 16~4621~ 17~1519~ 19~596~; 20~1161~ 24~2618~ 26~892~ 28~762~ 29~4442~.'),
  (6110, 6, 10, 40, 'So Joshua smote all the country of the hills, and of the south, and of the vale, and of the springs, and all their kings: he left none remaining, but utterly destroyed all that breathed, as the LORD God of Israel commanded.', '1~03091~ 2~05221~ 5~0776~ 8~02022~, 12~05045~, 16~08219~, 20~0794~, 24~04428~: 26~07604~ 28~08300~, 31~02763~ 34~05397~, 37~03068~ 38~0430~ 40~03478~ 41~06680~.'),
  (17684, 23, 1, 21, 'How is the faithful city become an harlot! it was full of judgment; righteousness lodged in it; but now murderers.', '&para; 3~0539~ 4~07151~ 7~02181~! 10~04392~ 12~04941~; 13~06664~ 14~03885~ 19~07523~.'),
  (9521, 11, 22, 33, 'And it came to pass, when the captains of the chariots perceived that it was not the king of Israel, that they turned back from pursuing him.', '7~08269~ 10~07393~ 11~07200~ [14] 17~04428~ 19~03478~, 23~07725~ 25~0310~'),
  (16611, 20, 7, 27, 'Her house is the way to hell, going down to the chambers of death.', '1~01004~ [2] 4~01870~ 6~07585~, 8~03381~ 11~02315~ 13~04194~.'),
  (30974, 66, 16, 4, 'And the third angel poured out his vial upon the rivers and fountains of waters; and they became blood.', '0~2532~ 2~5154~ 3~32~ 5~1632~ 6~846~ 7~5357~ 8~1519~ 10~4215~ 11~1519~ 12~2532~* 13~4077~ 15~5204~; 16~2532~ 18~1096~ 19~129~.'),
  (27772, 44, 23, 22, 'So the chief captain then let the young man depart, and charged him, See thou tell no man that thou hast shewed these things to me.', '0~3767~ 1~3303~ 3~5506~ [4] 5~630~ 8~3494~ 9~630~, 11~3853~ [12 14] 15~1583~ 17~3367~ 18~3754~ 21~1718~ 23~5023~ 24~4314~ 25~3165~.'),
  (3515, 3, 25, 41, 'And then shall he depart from thee, both he and his children with him, and shall return unto his own family, and unto the possession of his fathers shall he return.', '[1] 4~03318~ [7] 11~01121~ 16~07725~ 20~04940~, 24~0272~ 27~01~ 30~07725~.'),
  (14779, 19, 57, 2, 'I will cry unto God most high; unto God that performeth all things for me.', '2~07121~ 4~0430~ 6~05945~; 8~0410~ 10~01584~ [11 12]'),
  (27480, 44, 15, 22, 'Then pleased it the apostles and elders, with the whole church, to send chosen men of their own company to Antioch with Paul and Barnabas; namely, Judas surnamed Barsabas, and Silas, chief men among the brethren:', '&para; 0~5119~ 2~1380~ 4~652~ 5~2532~ 6~4245~, 7~4862~ 9~3650~ 10~1577~, 12~3992~ 13~1586~ 14~435~ 15~1537~ 18~846~ 19~1519~ 20~490~ 21~4862~ 22~3972~ 23~2532~ 24~921~; [25] 26~2455~ 27~1941~ 28~923~, 29~2532~ 30~4609~, 31~2233~ 32~435~ 33~1722~ 35~80~:'),
  (946, 1, 32, 14, 'Two hundred she goats, and twenty he goats, two hundred ewes, and twenty rams,', '1~03967~ 3~05795~, 5~06242~ 7~08495~, 9~03967~ 10~07353~, 12~06242~ 13~0352~,'),
  (9524, 11, 22, 36, 'And there went a proclamation throughout the host about the going down of the sun, saying, Every man to his city, and every man to his own country.', '2~05674~ 4~07440~ 7~04264~ 11~0935~ 14~08121~, 15~0559~, 17~0376~ 20~05892~, 23~0376~ 27~0776~.'),
  (15891, 19, 118, 13, 'Thou hast thrust sore at me that I might fall: but the LORD helped me.', '2~01760~ 3~01760~ 9~05307~: 12~03068~ 13~05826~'),
  (24980, 42, 1, 75, 'In holiness and righteousness before him, all the days of our life.', '0~1722~ 1~3742~ 2~2532~ 3~1343~ 4~1799~ 5~846~, 6~3956~ 8~2250~ 10~2257~ 11~2222~.'),
  (13166, 18, 13, 4, 'But ye are forgers of lies, ye are all physicians of no value.', '0~0199~ [2] 3~02950~ 5~08267~, [7] 9~07495~ 12~0457~.'),
  (7545, 9, 14, 30, 'How much more, if haply the people had eaten freely to day of the spoil of their enemies which they found? for had there not been now a much greater slaughter among the Philistines?', '2~0637~, 4~03863~ 6~05971~ 8~0398~ 9~0398~ 11~03117~ 14~07998~ 17~0341~ 20~04672~? 29~07235~ 30~04347~ 33~06430~?'),
  (14408, 19, 34, 11, 'Come, ye children, hearken unto me: I will teach you the fear of the LORD.', '&para; 0~03212~, 2~01121~, 3~08085~ 8~03925~ 11~03374~ 14~03068~.'),
  (28053, 45, 4, 15, 'Because the law worketh wrath: for where no law is, there is no transgression.', '0~1063~ 2~3551~ 3~2716~ 4~3709~: 5~1063~ 6~3757~ 7~3756~ 8~3551~ 9~2076~, [10 11] 12~3761~ 13~3847~.'),
  (16772, 20, 13, 16, 'Every prudent man dealeth with knowledge: but a fool layeth open his folly.', '&para; 1~06175~ [2] 3~06213~ 5~01847~: 8~03684~ 10~06566~ [11] 12~0200~.'),
  (29790, 54, 5, 11, 'But the younger widows refuse: for when they have begun to wax wanton against Christ, they will marry;', '0~1161~ 2~3501~ 3~5503~ 4~3868~: 5~1063~ 6~3752~ 13~2691~ 14~5547~, 16~2309~ 17~1060~;'),
  (880, 1, 31, 3, 'And the LORD said unto Jacob, Return unto the land of thy fathers, and to thy kindred; and I will be with thee.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~03290~, 6~07725~ 9~0776~ 12~01~, 16~04138~;'),
  (6838, 7, 11, 2, 'And Gilead''s wife bare him sons; and his wife''s sons grew up, and they thrust out Jephthah, and said unto him, Thou shalt not inherit in our father''s house; for thou art the son of a strange woman.', '1~01568~ 2~0802~ 3~03205~ 5~01121~; 8~0802~ 9~01121~ 11~01431~, 15~01644~ 16~03316~, 18~0559~ 24~05157~ 27~01~ 28~01004~; [31] 33~01121~ 36~0312~ 37~0802~.'),
  (9644, 12, 4, 33, 'He went in therefore, and shut the door upon them twain, and prayed unto the LORD.', '2~0935~ 5~05462~ 7~01817~ 10~08147~, 12~06419~ 15~03068~.'),
  (7576, 9, 15, 9, 'But Saul and the people spared Agag, and the best of the sheep, and of the oxen, and of the fatlings, and the lambs, and all that was good, and would not utterly destroy them: but every thing that was vile and refuse, that they destroyed utterly.', '1~07586~ 4~05971~ 5~02550~ 6~090~, 9~04315~ 12~06629~, 16~01241~, 20~04932~, 23~03733~, [26 27] 28~02896~, 30~014~ 33~02763~ 37~04399~ [38 39] 40~05240~ 42~04549~, 46~02763~.'),
  (22641, 33, 4, 12, 'But they know not the thoughts of the LORD, neither understand they his counsel: for he shall gather them as the sheaves into the floor.', '2~03045~ 5~04284~ 8~03068~, 10~0995~ 13~06098~: 17~06908~ 21~05995~ 24~01637~.'),
  (15978, 19, 119, 71, 'It is good for me that I have been afflicted; that I might learn thy statutes.', '&para; [0 1] 2~02896~ 9~06031~; 13~03925~ 15~02706~.'),
  (30618, 62, 3, 23, 'And this is his commandment, That we should believe on the name of his Son Jesus Christ, and love one another, as he gave us commandment.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~3778~ 2~2076~ 3~846~ 4~1785~, 5~2443~ 8~4100~ 11~3686~ 13~846~ 14~5207~ 15~2424~ 16~5547~, 17~2532~ 18~25~ 20~240~, 21~2531~ 23~1325~ 24~2254~ 25~1785~.'),
  (7470, 9, 12, 3, 'Behold, here I am: witness against me before the LORD, and before his anointed: whose ox have I taken? or whose ass have I taken? or whom have I defrauded? whom have I oppressed? or of whose hand have I received any bribe to blind mine eyes therewith? and I will restore it you.', '[3] 4~06030~ 9~03068~, 13~04899~: 15~07794~ 18~03947~? 21~02543~ 24~03947~? 29~06231~? 33~07533~? 37~03027~ [41] 42~03724~ 44~05956~ 46~05869~ 51~07725~'),
  (17786, 23, 6, 8, 'Also I heard the voice of the Lord, saying, Whom shall I send, and who will go for us? Then said I, Here am I; send me.', '2~08085~ 4~06963~ 7~0136~, 8~0559~, 12~07971~, 16~03212~ 20~0559~ [23] 25~07971~'),
  (14527, 19, 39, 6, 'Surely every man walketh in a vain shew: surely they are disquieted in vain: he heapeth up riches, and knoweth not who shall gather them.', '2~0376~ 3~01980~ 7~06754~: 11~01993~ 13~01892~: 16~06651~ [17] 19~03045~ 23~0622~'),
  (11943, 14, 34, 1, 'Josiah was eight years old when he began to reign, and he reigned in Jerusalem one and thirty years.', '&para; 0~02977~ [1] 2~08083~ 3~08141~ 4~01121~ 9~04427~, 12~04427~ 14~03389~ 15~0259~ 17~07970~ 18~08141~.'),
  (2237, 2, 25, 37, 'And thou shalt make the seven lamps thereof: and they shall light the lamps thereof, that they may give light over against it.', '3~06213~ 5~07651~ 6~05216~ 11~05927~ 13~05216~ 19~0215~ 21~05676~ 22~06440~.'),
  (10117, 12, 20, 11, 'And Isaiah the prophet cried unto the LORD: and he brought the shadow ten degrees backward, by which it had gone down in the dial of Ahaz.', '1~03470~ 3~05030~ 4~07121~ 7~03068~: 10~07725~ 12~06738~ 13~06235~ 14~04609~ 15~0322~, 16~04609~ 21~03381~ 24~04609~ 26~0271~.'),
  (28296, 45, 13, 14, 'But put ye on the Lord Jesus Christ, and make not provision for the flesh, to fulfil the lusts thereof.', '0~235~ 3~1746~ 5~2962~ 6~2424~ 7~5547~, 8~2532~ 9~4160~ 10~3361~ 11~4307~ 12~1519~ 14~4561~, [16] 18~1939~ [19]'),
  (14529, 19, 39, 8, 'Deliver me from all my transgressions: make me not the reproach of the foolish.', '0~05337~ 5~06588~: 6~07760~ 10~02781~ 13~05036~.'),
  (6896, 7, 13, 5, 'For, lo, thou shalt conceive, and bear a son; and no razor shall come on his head: for the child shall be a Nazarite unto God from the womb: and he shall begin to deliver Israel out of the hand of the Philistines.', '4~02030~, 6~03205~ 8~01121~; 11~04177~ 13~05927~ 16~07218~: 19~05288~ 23~05139~ 25~0430~ 28~0990~: 32~02490~ 34~03467~ 35~03478~ 39~03027~ 42~06430~.'),
  (5857, 5, 34, 12, 'And in all that mighty hand, and in all the great terror which Moses shewed in the sight of all Israel.', '4~02389~ 5~03027~, 10~01419~ 11~04172~ 13~04872~ 14~06213~ 17~05869~ 20~03478~.'),
  (7685, 9, 18, 2, 'And Saul took him that day, and would let him go no more home to his father''s house.', '1~07586~ 2~03947~ 5~03117~, 8~05414~ 13~07725~ 16~01~ 17~01004~.'),
  (25679, 42, 17, 14, 'And when he saw them, he said unto them, Go shew yourselves unto the priests. And it came to pass, that, as they went, they were cleansed.', '0~2532~ 3~1492~ [4] 6~2036~ 8~846~, 9~4198~ 10~1925~ 11~1438~ 14~2409~. 15~2532~ 19~1096~, 22~846~ 23~5217~ 24~1722~,* 27~2511~.'),
  (20388, 25, 3, 25, 'The LORD is good unto them that wait for him, to the soul that seeketh him.', '1~03068~ [2] 3~02896~ 7~06960~ 12~05315~ [13] 14~01875~'),
  (27376, 44, 12, 23, 'And immediately the angel of the Lord smote him, because he gave not God the glory: and he was eaten of worms, and gave up the ghost.', '0~1161~ 1~3916~ 3~32~ 6~2962~ 7~3960~ 8~846~, 9~3739~ 10~473~ 11~1325~ 12~3756~ 13~2316~ 15~1391~: 16~2532~ 18~1096~ 21~4662~, 26~1634~.'),
  (21506, 26, 40, 20, 'And the gate of the outward court that looked toward the north, he measured the length thereof, and the breadth thereof.', '2~08179~ 5~02435~ 6~02691~ 8~06440~ 9~01870~ 11~06828~, 13~04058~ 15~0753~ 19~07341~'),
  (5582, 5, 26, 10, 'And now, behold, I have brought the firstfruits of the land, which thou, O LORD, hast given me. And thou shalt set it before the LORD thy God, and worship before the LORD thy God:', '5~0935~ 7~07225~ 8~06529~ 10~0127~, 14~03068~, 16~05414~ 21~03240~ 23~06440~ 25~03068~ 27~0430~, 29~07812~ 30~06440~ 32~03068~ 34~0430~:'),
  (6233, 6, 15, 24, 'Ziph, and Telem, and Bealoth,', '0~02128~, 2~02928~, 4~01175~,'),
  (4181, 4, 15, 23, 'Even all that the LORD hath commanded you by the hand of Moses, from the day that the LORD commanded Moses, and henceforward among your generations;', '[0] 4~03068~ 6~06680~ 10~03027~ 12~04872~, 15~03117~ 18~03068~ 19~06680~ [20] 22~01973~ 25~01755~;'),
  (18173, 23, 27, 13, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that the great trumpet shall be blown, and they shall come which were ready to perish in the land of Assyria, and the outcasts in the land of Egypt, and shall worship the LORD in the holy mount at Jerusalem.', '8~03117~, [9] 11~01419~ 12~07782~ 15~08628~, 19~0935~ 24~06~ 27~0776~ 29~0804~, 32~05080~ 35~0776~ 37~04714~, 40~07812~ 42~03068~ 45~06944~ 46~02022~ 48~03389~.'),
  (9684, 12, 6, 2, 'Let us go, we pray thee, unto Jordan, and take thence every man a beam, and let us make us a place there, where we may dwell. And he answered, Go ye.', '2~03212~, 7~03383~, 9~03947~ 12~0376~ 13~0259~ 14~06982~, 18~06213~ 21~04725~ 26~03427~. 29~0559~, 30~03212~'),
  (893, 1, 31, 16, 'For all the riches which God hath taken from our father, that is ours, and our children''s: now then, whatsoever God hath said unto thee, do.', '3~06239~ 5~0430~ 7~05337~ 10~01~, [12] 16~01121~: 20~0430~ 22~0559~ 25~06213~.'),
  (3810, 4, 5, 13, 'And a man lie with her carnally, and it be hid from the eyes of her husband, and be kept close, and she be defiled, and there be no witness against her, neither she be taken with the manner;', '2~0376~ 3~07901~ 6~02233~ 7~07902~,* 11~05956~ 14~05869~ 17~0376~, 21~05641~, 25~02930~, [27 28] 30~05707~ 36~08610~ [37 39]'),
  (21886, 27, 5, 3, 'Then they brought the golden vessels that were taken out of the temple of the house of God which was at Jerusalem; and the king, and his princes, his wives, and his concubines, drank in them.', '0~0116~ 2~0858~ 4~01722~ 5~03984~ 8~05312~ 10~04481~ 12~01965~ 15~01005~ 17~0426~ [19] 21~03390~; 24~04430~, 27~07261~, 29~07695~, 32~03904~, 33~08355~'),
  (8982, 11, 7, 40, 'And Hiram made the lavers, and the shovels, and the basins. So Hiram made an end of doing all the work that he made king Solomon for the house of the LORD:', '1~02438~ 2~06213~ 4~03595~, 7~03257~, 10~04219~. 12~02438~ 13~03615~ 17~06213~ 20~04399~ 23~06213~ 24~04428~ 25~08010~ 28~01004~ 31~03068~:'),
  (21400, 26, 36, 32, 'Not for your sakes do I this, saith the Lord GOD, be it known unto you: be ashamed and confounded for your own ways, O house of Israel.', '4~06213~ [6] 7~05002~ 9~0136~ 10~03069~, 13~03045~ 17~0954~ 19~03637~ 23~01870~, 25~01004~ 27~03478~.'),
  (14309, 19, 28, 1, 'A Psalm of David. Unto thee will I cry, O LORD my rock; be not silent to me: lest, if thou be silent to me, I become like them that go down into the pit.', '&para; [0 1] 3] 3~01732~ 8~07121~, 10~03068~ 12~06697~; 15~02814~ [19] 22~02790~ 26~04911~ 31~03381~ 34~0953~.'),
  (26961, 44, 1, 22, 'Beginning from the baptism of John, unto that same day that he was taken up from us, must one be ordained to be a witness with us of his resurrection.', '0~756~ 1~575~ 3~908~ 5~2491~, 6~2193~ 9~2250~ 10~3739~ 14~353~ 15~575~ 16~2257~, 17~1163~ 18~1520~ 20~1096~ 24~3144~ 25~4862~ 26~2254~ 28~846~ 29~386~.'),
  (4926, 5, 1, 28, 'Whither shall we go up? our brethren have discouraged our heart, saying, The people is greater and taller than we; the cities are great and walled up to heaven; and moreover we have seen the sons of the Anakims there.', '4~05927~? 6~0251~ 8~04549~ 10~03824~, 11~0559~, 13~05971~ [14] 15~01419~ 17~07311~ 21~05892~ [22] 23~01419~ 26~01219~ 28~08064~; 33~07200~ 35~01121~ 38~06062~'),
  (613, 1, 24, 18, 'And she said, Drink, my lord: and she hasted, and let down her pitcher upon her hand, and gave him drink.', '2~0559~, 3~08354~, 5~0113~: 8~04116~, 11~03381~ 13~03537~ 16~03027~, 20~08248~.'),
  (17134, 20, 25, 12, 'As an earring of gold, and an ornament of fine gold, so is a wise reprover upon an obedient ear.', '[0] 2~05141~ 4~02091~, 7~02481~ 10~03800~, [11 12] 14~02450~ 15~03198~ 18~08085~ 19~0241~.'),
  (20715, 26, 12, 26, 'Again the word of the LORD came to me, saying,', '2~01697~ 5~03068~ 9~0559~,'),
  (11417, 14, 10, 13, 'And the king answered them roughly; and king Rehoboam forsook the counsel of the old men,', '2~04428~ 3~06030~ 5~07186~; 7~04428~ 8~07346~ 9~05800~ 11~06098~ 15~02205~,'),
  (14754, 19, 55, 13, 'But it was thou, a man mine equal, my guide, and mine acquaintance.', '[1 2] 5~0582~ 7~06187~, 9~0441~, 12~03045~.'),
  (3371, 3, 21, 21, 'No man that hath a blemish of the seed of Aaron the priest shall come nigh to offer the offerings of the LORD made by fire: he hath a blemish; he shall not come nigh to offer the bread of his God.', '1~0376~ 5~03971~ 8~02233~ 10~0175~ 12~03548~ 15~05066~ 17~07126~ 19~0801~ 22~03068~ 25~0801~: 29~03971~; 34~05066~ 36~07126~ 38~03899~ 41~0430~.'),
  (17199, 20, 27, 21, 'As the fining pot for silver, and the furnace for gold; so is a man to his praise.', '&para; [0] 3~04715~ 5~03701~, 8~03564~ 10~02091~; [12] 14~0376~ 15~06310~ 17~04110~.'),
  (21229, 26, 30, 16, 'And I will set fire in Egypt: Sin shall have great pain, and No shall be rent asunder, and Noph shall have distresses daily.', '3~05414~ 4~0784~ 6~04714~: 7~05512~ 10~02342~ 11~02342~, 13~04996~ 17~01234~, 19~05297~ [20 21] 22~06862~ 23~03119~.'),
  (18997, 24, 2, 23, 'How canst thou say, I am not polluted, I have not gone after Baalim? see thy way in the valley, know what thou hast done: thou art a swift dromedary traversing her ways;', '3~0559~, 7~02930~, 11~01980~ 12~0310~ 13~01168~? 14~07200~ 16~01870~ 19~01516~, 20~03045~ 24~06213~: [25 26] 28~07031~ 29~01072~ 30~08308~ 32~01870~;'),
  (3715, 4, 3, 18, 'And these are the names of the sons of Gershon by their families; Libni, and Shimei.', '[2] 4~08034~ 7~01121~ 9~01648~ 12~04940~; 13~03845~, 15~08096~.'),
  (30711, 65, 1, 23, 'And others save with fear, pulling them out of the fire; hating even the garment spotted by the flesh.', '0~1161~ 1~3739~ 2~4982~ 3~1722~ 4~5401~, 5~726~ [6] 8~1537~ 10~4442~; 11~3404~ 12~2532~ 14~5509~ 15~4695~ 16~575~ 18~4561~.'),
  (10455, 13, 5, 19, 'And they made war with the Hagarites, with Jetur, and Nephish, and Nodab.', '2~06213~ 3~04421~ 6~01905~, 8~03195~, 10~05305~, 12~05114~.'),
  (25771, 42, 19, 26, 'For I say unto you, That unto every one which hath shall be given; and from him that hath not, even that he hath shall be taken away from him.', '0~1063~ 2~3004~ 4~5213~, 5~3754~ 8~3956~ 9~3588~ 10~2192~ 13~1325~; 14~1161~ 15~575~ 18~2192~ 19~3361~, 20~2532~ 21~3739~ 23~2192~ 27~142~ 28~575~ 29~846~.'),
  (18821, 23, 59, 12, 'For our transgressions are multiplied before thee, and our sins testify against us: for our transgressions are with us; and as for our iniquities, we know them;', '2~06588~ 4~07231~ 9~02403~ 10~06030~ 15~06588~ [16] [20 21] 23~05771~, 25~03045~'),
  (3477, 3, 25, 3, 'Six years thou shalt sow thy field, and six years thou shalt prune thy vineyard, and gather in the fruit thereof;', '0~08337~ 1~08141~ 4~02232~ 6~07704~, 8~08337~ 9~08141~ 12~02168~ 14~03754~, 16~0622~ 19~08393~'),
  (19794, 24, 33, 10, 'Thus saith the LORD; Again there shall be heard in this place, which ye say shall be desolate without man and without beast, even in the cities of Judah, and in the streets of Jerusalem, that are desolate, without man, and without inhabitant, and without beast,', '&para; 1~0559~ 3~03068~; 8~08085~ 11~04725~, 14~0559~ [15 16] 17~02720~ 19~0120~ 22~0929~, [23] 26~05892~ 28~03063~, 32~02351~ 34~03389~, 37~08074~, 39~0120~, 42~03427~, 45~0929~,'),
  (30884, 66, 10, 7, 'But in the days of the voice of the seventh angel, when he shall begin to sound, the mystery of God should be finished, as he hath declared to his servants the prophets.', '0~235~ 1~1722~ 3~2250~ 6~5456~ 9~1442~ 10~32~, 11~3752~ 14~3195~ 16~4537~ 17~2532~,* 19~3466~ 21~2316~ 24~5055~, 25~5613~ 28~2097~ 30~1438~ 31~1401~ 33~4396~.'),
  (23526, 40, 12, 27, 'And if I by Beelzebub cast out devils, by whom do your children cast them out? therefore they shall be your judges.', '0~2532~ 1~1487~ 2~1473~ 3~1722~ 4~954~ 6~1544~ 7~1140~, 8~1722~ 9~5101~ 11~5216~ 12~5207~ [14] 15~1544~? 16~1223~ 17~5124~* 18~846~ 20~2071~ 21~5216~ 22~2923~.'),
  (30368, 59, 4, 15, 'For that ye ought to say, If the Lord will, we shall live, and do this, or that.', '1~473~ 2~5209~ [3] 5~3004~, 6~1437~ 8~2962~ 9~2309~ 10~2532~,* 13~2198~ 14~2532~ 15~4160~ 16~5124~, 17~2228~ 18~1565~.'),
  (13898, 18, 41, 1, 'Canst thou draw out leviathan with an hook? or his tongue with a cord which thou lettest down?', '&para; 3~04900~ 4~03882~ 7~02443~? 10~03956~ 13~02256~ [14] 17~08257~?'),
  (11758, 14, 26, 17, 'And Azariah the priest went in after him, and with him fourscore priests of the LORD, that were valiant men:', '1~05838~ 3~03548~ 5~0935~ 6~0310~ 11~08084~ 12~03548~ 15~03068~, [16 17] 18~02428~ 19~01121~:'),
  (17143, 20, 25, 21, 'If thine enemy be hungry, give him bread to eat; and if he be thirsty, give him water to drink:', '&para; 2~08130~ 4~07457~, 7~03899~ 9~0398~; 14~06771~, 17~04325~ 19~08248~:'),
  (27225, 44, 8, 33, 'In his humiliation his judgment was taken away: and who shall declare his generation? for his life is taken from the earth.', '0~1722~ 1~846~ 2~5014~ 3~846~ 4~2920~ 7~142~: 8~1161~ 9~5101~ 11~1334~ 12~846~ 13~1074~? 14~3754~ 15~846~ 16~2222~ 18~142~ 19~575~ 21~1093~.'),
  (29400, 50, 1, 23, 'For I am in a strait betwixt two, having a desire to depart, and to be with Christ; which is far better:', '0~1063~ 5~4912~ 6~1537~ 7~1417~, 8~2192~ 10~1939~ 11~1519~ 12~360~, 13~2532~ 15~1511~ 16~4862~ 17~5547~; 20~3123~ 21~4183~* 22~2908~:'),
  (13835, 18, 38, 33, 'Knowest thou the ordinances of heaven? canst thou set the dominion thereof in the earth?', '0~03045~ 3~02708~ 5~08064~? 8~07760~ 10~04896~ 14~0776~?'),
  (23082, 38, 14, 5, 'And ye shall flee to the valley of the mountains; for the valley of the mountains shall reach unto Azal: yea, ye shall flee, like as ye fled from before the earthquake in the days of Uzziah king of Judah: and the LORD my God shall come, and all the saints with thee.', '3~05127~ [4] 6~01516~ 9~02022~; 12~01516~ 15~02022~ 17~05060~ 19~0682~: 23~05127~, 27~05127~ 29~06440~ 31~07494~ 34~03117~ 36~05818~ 37~04428~ 39~03063~: 42~03068~ 44~0430~ 46~0935~, [47] 50~06918~'),
  (8018, 9, 31, 2, 'And the Philistines followed hard upon Saul and upon his sons; and the Philistines slew Jonathan, and Abinadab, and Melchishua, Saul''s sons.', '2~06430~ 4~01692~ 6~07586~ 10~01121~; 13~06430~ 14~05221~ 15~03083~, 17~041~, 19~04444~, 20~07586~ 21~01121~.'),
  (25172, 42, 6, 14, 'Simon, (whom he also named Peter,) and Andrew his brother, James and John, Philip and Bartholomew,', '0~4613~, 1~3739~* 4~2532~ 5~3687~ 6~4074~,) 7~2532~ 8~406~ 9~846~ 10~80~, 11~2385~ 12~2532~ 13~2491~, 14~5376~ 15~2532~ 16~918~,'),
  (20580, 26, 6, 8, 'Yet will I leave a remnant, that ye may have some that shall escape the sword among the nations, when ye shall be scattered through the countries.', '&para; 5~03498~, [10] 13~06412~ 15~02719~ 18~01471~, 23~02219~ 26~0776~.'),
  (29295, 49, 4, 7, 'But unto every one of us is given grace according to the measure of the gift of Christ.', '0~1161~ 2~1538~ 3~1520~ 5~2257~ 7~1325~ 8~5485~ 10~2596~ 12~3358~ 15~1431~ 17~5547~.'),
  (11003, 13, 23, 12, 'The sons of Kohath; Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel, four.', '1~01121~ 3~06955~; 4~06019~, 5~03324~, 6~02275~, 8~05816~, 9~0702~.'),
  (28000, 45, 2, 22, 'Thou that sayest a man should not commit adultery, dost thou commit adultery? thou that abhorrest idols, dost thou commit sacrilege?', '2~3004~ 5~3431~ 6~3361~ 8~3431~, 12~3431~? 15~948~ 16~1497~, 20~2416~?'),
  (12192, 15, 7, 10, 'For Ezra had prepared his heart to seek the law of the LORD, and to do it, and to teach in Israel statutes and judgments.', '1~05830~ 3~03559~ 5~03824~ 7~01875~ 9~08451~ 12~03068~, 15~06213~ [16] 19~03925~ 21~03478~ 22~02706~ 24~04941~.'),
  (14213, 19, 21, 13, 'Be thou exalted, LORD, in thine own strength: so will we sing and praise thy power.', '2~07311~, 3~03068~, 7~05797~: [8] 11~07891~ 13~02167~ 15~01369~.'),
  (18311, 23, 33, 23, 'Thy tacklings are loosed; they could not well strengthen their mast, they could not spread the sail: then is the prey of a great spoil divided; the lame take the prey.', '1~02256~ 3~05203~; 7~03653~ 8~02388~ 10~08650~, 14~06566~ 16~05251~: 20~05706~ 23~04766~ 24~07998~ 25~02505~; 27~06455~ 28~0962~ 30~0957~.'),
  (22752, 35, 1, 12, 'Art thou not from everlasting, O LORD my God, mine Holy One? we shall not die. O LORD, thou hast ordained them for judgment; and, O mighty God, thou hast established them for correction.', '&para; [0] 4~06924~, 6~03068~ 8~0430~, 11~06918~? 15~04191~. 17~03068~, 20~07760~ 23~04941~; 27~06697~, 30~03245~ 33~03198~.'),
  (19595, 24, 26, 14, 'As for me, behold, I am in your hand: do with me as seemeth good and meet unto you.', '[5] 8~03027~: 9~06213~ 13~05869~ 14~02896~ 16~03477~'),
  (3318, 3, 19, 32, 'Thou shalt rise up before the hoary head, and honour the face of the old man, and fear thy God: I am the LORD.', '3~06965~ 4~06440~ 7~07872~, 9~01921~ 11~06440~ 15~02205~, 17~03372~ 19~0430~: [21] 23~03068~.');
