VALUES
  (3725, 4, 3, 28, 'In the number of all the males, from a month old and upward, were eight thousand and six hundred, keeping the charge of the sanctuary.', '2~04557~ 6~02145~, 9~02320~ 10~01121~ 12~04605~, [13] 14~08083~ 15~0505~ 17~08337~ 18~03967~, 19~08104~ 21~04931~ 24~06944~.'),
  (21814, 27, 2, 47, 'The king answered unto Daniel, and said, Of a truth it is, that your God is a God of gods, and a Lord of kings, and a revealer of secrets, seeing thou couldest reveal this secret.', '1~04430~ 2~06032~ 4~01841~, 6~0560~, 7~04481~ 9~07187~ [10 11] 12~01768~ 14~0426~ [15] 17~0426~ 19~0426~, 22~04756~ 24~04430~, 27~01541~ 29~07328~, 32~03202~ 33~01541~ 34~01836~ 35~07328~.'),
  (20582, 26, 6, 10, 'And they shall know that I am the LORD, and that I have not said in vain that I would do this evil unto them.', '3~03045~ [6] 8~03068~, [9 10] 14~01696~ 16~02600~ 20~06213~ 22~07451~'),
  (25982, 42, 23, 33, 'And when they were come to the place, which is called Calvary, there they crucified him, and the malefactors, one on the right hand, and the other on the left.', '0~2532~ 1~3753~ 4~565~ 5~1909~ 7~5117~, 8~3588~ 10~2564~ 11~2898~, 12~1563~ 14~4717~ 15~846~, 16~2532~ 18~2557~, 19~3303~ 20~3739~* 21~1537~ 24~1188~, 25~1161~ 27~3739~ 28~1537~ 30~710~.'),
  (21876, 27, 4, 30, 'The king spake, and said, Is not this great Babylon, that I have built for the house of the kingdom by the might of my power, and for the honour of my majesty?', '1~04430~ 2~06032~, 4~0560~, 6~03809~ 7~01668~ 8~01932~* 9~07229~ 10~0895~, 12~0576~ 14~01124~ 17~01005~ 20~04437~ 23~08632~ 26~02632~, 30~03367~ 33~01923~?'),
  (26730, 43, 15, 16, 'Ye have not chosen me, but I have chosen you, and ordained you, that ye should go and bring forth fruit, and that your fruit should remain: that whatsoever ye shall ask of the Father in my name, he may give it you.', '0~5210~ 1~1586~ 2~3756~ 3~1586~ 4~3165~, 5~235~ 6~1473~ 8~1586~ 9~5209~, 10~2532~ 11~5087~ 12~5209~, 13~2443~ 14~5210~ 16~5217~ 17~2532~ 19~5342~ 20~2590~, 21~2532~ [22] 23~5216~ 24~2590~ 26~3306~: 27~2443~ 28~3748~ 29~3739~* 30~302~ 32~154~ 35~3962~ 36~1722~ 37~3450~ 38~3686~, 42~1325~ 43~5213~.'),
  (11734, 14, 25, 21, 'So Joash the king of Israel went up; and they saw one another in the face, both he and Amaziah king of Judah, at Bethshemesh, which belongeth to Judah.', '1~03101~ 3~04428~ 5~03478~ 7~05927~; 12~07200~ 15~06440~, [16] 19~0558~ 20~04428~ 22~03063~, 24~01053~, [26] 28~03063~.'),
  (30041, 58, 4, 11, 'Let us labour therefore to enter into that rest, lest any man fall after the same example of unbelief.', '&para; 2~4704~ 3~3767~ 5~1525~ 6~1519~ 7~1565~ 8~2663~, 9~3363~ 11~5100~ 12~4098~ 13~1722~ 15~846~ 16~5262~ 18~543~.'),
  (18405, 23, 38, 6, 'And I will deliver thee and this city out of the hand of the king of Assyria: and I will defend this city.', '3~05337~ 7~05892~ 11~03709~ 14~04428~ 16~0804~: 20~01598~ 22~05892~.'),
  (25295, 42, 8, 38, 'Now the man out of whom the devils were departed besought him that he might be with him: but Jesus sent him away, saying,', '0~1161~ 2~435~ 4~575~ 5~3739~ 7~1140~ 9~1831~ 10~1189~ 11~846~ 15~1511~ 16~4862~ 17~846~: 18~1161~ 19~2424~ 20~630~ 21~846~ 22~630~, 23~3004~,'),
  (5519, 5, 23, 13, 'And thou shalt have a paddle upon thy weapon; and it shall be, when thou wilt ease thyself abroad, thou shalt dig therewith, and shalt turn back and cover that which cometh from thee:', '5~03489~ 8~0240~; 16~03427~ 18~02351~, 21~02658~ 26~07725~ 28~03680~ 31~06627~'),
  (17058, 20, 23, 5, 'Wilt thou set thine eyes upon that which is not? for riches certainly make themselves wings; they fly away as an eagle toward heaven.', '2~05774~ 4~05869~ [11] 12~06213~ 13~06213~ 15~03671~; 18~05774~ 21~05404~ 23~08064~.'),
  (2066, 2, 20, 10, 'But the seventh day is the sabbath of the LORD thy God: in it thou shalt not do any work, thou, nor thy son, nor thy daughter, thy manservant, nor thy maidservant, nor thy cattle, nor thy stranger that is within thy gates:', '2~07637~ 3~03117~ [4] 6~07676~ 9~03068~ 11~0430~: [12 13] 17~06213~ 19~04399~, 23~01121~, 26~01323~, 28~05650~, 31~0519~, 34~0929~, 37~01616~ [39] 42~08179~:'),
  (28890, 47, 4, 15, 'For all things are for your sakes, that the abundant grace might through the thanksgiving of many redound to the glory of God.', '0~1063~ 2~3956~ [3] 4~1223~ 5~5209~ 6~1223~, 7~2443~ 9~4121~ 10~5485~ 11~4052~ 12~1223~ 14~2169~ 16~4119~ 17~4052~ 18~1519~ 20~1391~ 22~2316~.'),
  (30838, 66, 7, 12, 'Saying, Amen: Blessing, and glory, and wisdom, and thanksgiving, and honour, and power, and might, be unto our God for ever and ever. Amen.', '0~3004~, 1~281~: 2~2129~, 3~2532~ 4~1391~, 5~2532~ 6~4678~, 7~2532~ 8~2169~, 9~2532~ 10~5092~, 11~2532~ 12~1411~, 13~2532~ 14~2479~, [15] 17~2257~ 18~2316~ 19~1519~ 20~165~ 22~165~. 23~281~.'),
  (18805, 23, 58, 10, 'And if thou draw out thy soul to the hungry, and satisfy the afflicted soul; then shall thy light rise in obscurity, and thy darkness be as the noon day:', '[1] 4~06329~ 6~05315~ 9~07457~, 11~07646~ 13~06031~ 14~05315~; 18~0216~ 19~02224~ 21~02822~, 24~0653~ [25] 28~06672~:'),
  (20915, 26, 20, 11, 'And I gave them my statutes, and shewed them my judgments, which if a man do, he shall even live in them.', '2~05414~ 5~02708~, 7~03045~ 10~04941~, [12] 14~0120~ 15~06213~, 19~02425~'),
  (8920, 11, 6, 16, 'And he built twenty cubits on the sides of the house, both the floor and the walls with boards of cedar: he even built them for it within, even for the oracle, even for the most holy place.', '2~01129~ 3~06242~ 4~0520~ 7~03411~ 10~01004~, 11~04480~ 13~07172~ 16~07023~ 18~06763~ 20~0730~: 23~01129~ [24] 27~01004~, [28] 31~01687~, [32] 35~06944~ 36~06944~ [37]'),
  (18409, 23, 38, 10, 'I said in the cutting off of my days, I shall go to the gates of the grave: I am deprived of the residue of my years.', '1~0559~ 5~01824~ 8~03117~, 11~03212~ 14~08179~ 17~07585~: 20~06485~ 23~03499~ 26~08141~.'),
  (30523, 61, 2, 7, 'And delivered just Lot, vexed with the filthy conversation of the wicked:', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~4506~ 2~1342~ 3~3091~, 4~2669~ 5~5259~ 7~766~ 8~391~ 11~113~:'),
  (3292, 3, 19, 6, 'It shall be eaten the same day ye offer it, and on the morrow: and if ought remain until the third day, it shall be burnt in the fire.', '3~0398~ 6~03117~ 8~02077~ 13~04283~: 17~03498~ 20~07992~ 21~03117~, 25~08313~ 28~0784~.'),
  (18565, 23, 44, 23, 'Sing, O ye heavens; for the LORD hath done it: shout, ye lower parts of the earth: break forth into singing, ye mountains, O forest, and every tree therein: for the LORD hath redeemed Jacob, and glorified himself in Israel.', '0~07442~, 3~08064~; 6~03068~ 8~06213~ [9] 10~07321~, 13~08482~ 16~0776~: 18~06476~ 20~07440~, 22~02022~, 24~03293~, 27~06086~ 31~03068~ 33~01350~ 34~03290~, 36~06286~ 39~03478~.'),
  (14792, 19, 58, 4, 'Their poison is like the poison of a serpent: they are like the deaf adder that stoppeth her ear;', '1~02534~ [2] 3~01823~ 5~02534~ 8~05175~: [9 10] 13~02795~ 14~06620~ [15] 16~0331~ 18~0241~;'),
  (2388, 2, 30, 1, 'And thou shalt make an altar to burn incense upon: of shittim wood shalt thou make it.', '&para; 3~06213~ 5~04196~ 7~04729~ 8~07004~ [10] 11~07848~ 12~06086~ 15~06213~'),
  (19154, 24, 7, 26, 'Yet they hearkened not unto me, nor inclined their ear, but hardened their neck: they did worse than their fathers.', '2~08085~ 7~05186~ 9~0241~, 11~07185~ 13~06203~: 16~07489~ 19~01~.'),
  (9335, 11, 17, 10, 'So he arose and went to Zarephath. And when he came to the gate of the city, behold, the widow woman was there gathering of sticks: and he called to her, and said, Fetch me, I pray thee, a little water in a vessel, that I may drink.', '2~06965~ 4~03212~ 6~06886~. 10~0935~ 13~06607~ 16~05892~, 19~0490~ 20~0802~ [21] 23~07197~ 25~06086~: 28~07121~ 32~0559~, 33~03947~ 39~04592~ 40~04325~ 43~03627~, 47~08354~.'),
  (13148, 18, 12, 11, 'Doth not the ear try words? and the mouth taste his meat?', '3~0241~ 4~0974~ 5~04405~? 8~02441~ 9~02938~ 11~0400~?'),
  (12500, 16, 7, 71, 'And some of the chief of the fathers gave to the treasure of the work twenty thousand drams of gold, and two thousand and two hundred pound of silver.', '[1] 4~07218~ 7~01~ 8~05414~ 11~0214~ 14~04399~ 15~08147~ 16~07239~ 17~01871~ 19~02091~, 22~0505~ 25~03967~ 26~04488~ 28~03701~.'),
  (17703, 23, 2, 9, 'And the mean man boweth down, and the great man humbleth himself: therefore forgive them not.', '3~0120~ 5~07817~, 9~0376~ 10~08213~ 13~05375~'),
  (1181, 1, 40, 4, 'And the captain of the guard charged Joseph with them, and he served them: and they continued a season in ward.', '2~08269~ 5~02876~ 6~06485~ 7~03130~ 12~08334~ 18~03117~ 20~04929~.'),
  (2615, 2, 37, 6, 'And he made the mercy seat of pure gold: two cubits and a half was the length thereof, and one cubit and a half the breadth thereof.', '2~06213~ 5~03727~ [6] 7~02889~ 8~02091~: 10~0520~ 13~02677~ [14] 16~0753~ 20~0520~ 23~02677~ 25~07341~'),
  (15932, 19, 119, 25, 'DALETH. My soul cleaveth unto the dust: quicken thou me according to thy word.', '&para; 2~05315~ 3~01692~ 6~06083~: 7~02421~ 13~01697~.'),
  (11045, 13, 24, 22, 'Of the Izharites; Shelomoth: of the sons of Shelomoth; Jahath.', '2~03325~; 3~08013~: 6~01121~ 8~08013~; 9~03189~.'),
  (9909, 12, 14, 5, 'And it came to pass, as soon as the kingdom was confirmed in his hand, that he slew his servants which had slain the king his father.', '9~04467~ 11~02388~ 14~03027~, 17~05221~ 19~05650~ 22~05221~ 24~04428~ 26~01~.'),
  (8721, 10, 24, 21, 'And Araunah said, Wherefore is my lord the king come to his servant? And David said, To buy the threshingfloor of thee, to build an altar unto the LORD, that the plague may be stayed from the people.', '1~0728~ 2~0559~, 6~0113~ 8~04428~ 9~0935~ 12~05650~? 14~01732~ 15~0559~, 17~07069~ 19~01637~ 23~01129~ 25~04196~ 28~03068~, 31~04046~ 34~06113~ 37~05971~.'),
  (25854, 42, 21, 14, 'Settle it therefore in your hearts, not to meditate before what ye shall answer:', '0~5087~ [1] 2~3767~ 3~1519~ 4~5216~ 5~2588~, 6~3361~ 9~4304~ 13~626~:'),
  (1258, 1, 42, 1, 'Now when Jacob saw that there was corn in Egypt, Jacob said unto his sons, Why do ye look one upon another?', '&para; 2~03290~ 3~07200~ 6~03426~ 7~07668~ 9~04714~, 10~03290~ 11~0559~ 14~01121~, 18~07200~'),
  (11529, 14, 16, 11, 'And, behold, the acts of Asa, first and last, lo, they are written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel.', '3~01697~ 5~0609~, 6~07223~ 8~0314~, [11] 12~03789~ 15~05612~ 18~04428~ 20~03063~ 22~03478~.'),
  (20080, 24, 46, 26, 'And I will deliver them into the hand of those that seek their lives, and into the hand of Nebuchadrezzar king of Babylon, and into the hand of his servants: and afterward it shall be inhabited, as in the days of old, saith the LORD.', '3~05414~ 7~03027~ 11~01245~ 13~05315~, 17~03027~ 19~05019~ 20~04428~ 22~0894~, 26~03027~ 29~05650~: 31~0310~ 35~07931~, 39~03117~ 41~06924~, 42~05002~ 44~03068~.'),
  (7853, 9, 24, 7, 'So David stayed his servants with these words, and suffered them not to rise against Saul. But Saul rose up out of the cave, and went on his way.', '1~01732~ 2~08156~ 4~0582~ 7~01697~, 9~05414~ 13~06965~ 15~07586~. 17~07586~ 19~06965~ 23~04631~, 25~03212~ [27] 28~01870~.'),
  (11601, 14, 20, 5, 'And Jehoshaphat stood in the congregation of Judah and Jerusalem, in the house of the LORD, before the new court,', '1~03092~ 2~05975~ 5~06951~ 7~03063~ 9~03389~, 12~01004~ 15~03068~, 16~06440~ 18~02319~ 19~02691~,'),
  (12239, 15, 8, 29, 'Watch ye, and keep them, until ye weigh them before the chief of the priests and the Levites, and chief of the fathers of Israel, at Jerusalem, in the chambers of the house of the LORD.', '0~08245~ 3~08104~ [4] 7~08254~ [8] 9~06440~ 11~08269~ 14~03548~ 17~03881~, 19~08269~ 22~01~ 24~03478~, 26~03389~, 29~03957~ 32~01004~ 35~03068~.'),
  (17431, 21, 6, 5, 'Moreover he hath not seen the sun, nor known any thing: this hath more rest than the other.', '4~07200~ 6~08121~, 8~03045~ [9 10] 11~02088~ 14~05183~ 15~02088~'),
  (15910, 19, 119, 3, 'They also do no iniquity: they walk in his ways.', '2~06466~ 4~05766~: 6~01980~ 9~01870~.'),
  (30140, 58, 9, 19, 'For when Moses had spoken every precept to all the people according to the law, he took the blood of calves and of goats, with water, and scarlet wool, and hyssop, and sprinkled both the book, and all the people,', '0~1063~ 1~5259~ 2~3475~ 4~2980~ 5~3956~ 6~1785~ 8~3956~ 10~2992~ 11~2596~ 14~3551~, 16~2983~ 18~129~ 20~3448~ 21~2532~ 23~5131~, 24~3326~ 25~5204~, 26~2532~ 27~2847~ 28~2053~, 29~2532~ 30~5301~, 32~4472~ 33~5037~ 35~846~ 36~975~,* 37~2532~ 38~3956~ 40~2992~,'),
  (26118, 43, 2, 8, 'And he saith unto them, Draw out now, and bear unto the governor of the feast. And they bare it.', '0~2532~ 2~3004~ 4~846~, 6~501~ 7~3568~, 8~2532~ 9~5342~ 15~755~. 16~2532~ 18~5342~ [19]'),
  (7288, 9, 3, 5, 'And he ran unto Eli, and said, Here am I; for thou calledst me. And he said, I called not; lie down again. And he went and lay down.', '2~07323~ 4~05941~, 6~0559~, [8] 9~02009~; 12~07121~ 16~0559~, 18~07121~ 21~07901~ 22~07725~. 25~03212~ 28~07901~.'),
  (16428, 20, 1, 19, 'So are the ways of every one that is greedy of gain; which taketh away the life of the owners thereof.', '[1] 3~0734~ 9~01214~ 11~01215~; [12] 14~03947~ 16~05315~ 19~01167~'),
  (13099, 18, 10, 4, 'Hast thou eyes of flesh? or seest thou as man seeth?', '2~05869~ 4~01320~? 6~07200~ 9~0582~ 10~07200~?'),
  (21463, 26, 39, 6, 'And I will send a fire on Magog, and among them that dwell carelessly in the isles: and they shall know that I am the LORD.', '3~07971~ 5~0784~ 7~04031~, 12~03427~ 13~0983~ 16~0339~: 20~03045~ [23] 25~03068~.'),
  (1628, 2, 4, 22, 'And thou shalt say unto Pharaoh, Thus saith the LORD, Israel is my son, even my firstborn:', '3~0559~ 5~06547~, 7~0559~ 9~03068~, 10~03478~ [11] 13~01121~, [14] 16~01060~:'),
  (25198, 42, 6, 40, 'The disciple is not above his master: but every one that is perfect shall be as his master.', '1~3101~ 2~2076~ 3~3756~ 4~5228~ 5~846~ 6~1320~: 7~1161~ 9~3956~ 12~2675~ 14~2071~ 15~5613~ 16~846~ 17~1320~.'),
  (21111, 26, 26, 2, 'Son of man, because that Tyrus hath said against Jerusalem, Aha, she is broken that was the gates of the people: she is turned unto me: I shall be replenished, now she is laid waste:', '0~01121~ 2~0120~, 5~06865~ 7~0559~ 9~03389~, 10~01889~, 13~07665~ [14 15] 17~01817~ 20~05971~: 23~05437~ 29~04390~, [30] 34~02717~:'),
  (14037, 19, 9, 7, 'But the LORD shall endure for ever: he hath prepared his throne for judgment.', '2~03068~ 4~03427~ 6~05769~: 9~03559~ 11~03678~ 13~04941~.'),
  (18125, 23, 24, 21, 'And it shall come to pass in that day, that the LORD shall punish the host of the high ones that are on high, and the kings of the earth upon the earth.', '8~03117~, [9] 11~03068~ 13~06485~ 15~06635~ 19~04791~ [20 21] 23~04791~, 26~04428~ 29~0127~ 32~0127~.'),
  (26367, 43, 7, 24, 'Judge not according to the appearance, but judge righteous judgment.', '0~2919~ 1~3361~ 3~2596~ 5~3799~, 6~235~ 7~2919~ 8~1342~ 9~2920~.'),
  (8847, 11, 3, 23, 'Then said the king, The one saith, This is my son that liveth, and thy son is the dead: and the other saith, Nay; but thy son is the dead, and my son is the living.', '1~0559~ 3~04428~, 5~02063~ 6~0559~, [8] 10~01121~ 12~02416~, 15~01121~ [16] 18~04191~: 21~02063~ 22~0559~, 26~01121~ [27] 29~04191~, 32~01121~ [33] 35~02416~.'),
  (17870, 23, 10, 11, 'Shall I not, as I have done unto Samaria and her idols, so do to Jerusalem and her idols?', '6~06213~ 8~08111~ 11~0457~, 13~06213~ 15~03389~ 18~06091~?'),
  (22336, 29, 2, 16, 'Gather the people, sanctify the congregation, assemble the elders, gather the children, and those that suck the breasts: let the bridegroom go forth of his chamber, and the bride out of her closet.', '0~0622~ 2~05971~, 3~06942~ 5~06951~, 6~06908~ 8~02205~, 9~0622~ 11~05768~, 15~03243~ 17~07699~: 20~02860~ 22~03318~ 25~02315~, 28~03618~ 32~02646~.'),
  (24505, 41, 7, 31, 'And again, departing from the coasts of Tyre and Sidon, he came unto the sea of Galilee, through the midst of the coasts of Decapolis.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~3825~, 2~1831~ 3~1537~ 5~3725~ 7~5184~ 8~2532~ 9~4605~, 11~2064~ 12~4314~ 14~2281~ 16~1056~, 17~303~ 19~3319~ 22~3725~ 24~1179~.'),
  (17469, 21, 8, 2, 'I counsel thee to keep the king''s commandment, and that in regard of the oath of God.', '[1 2] 4~08104~ 6~04428~ 7~06310~, [9] 11~01700~ 14~07621~ 16~0430~.'),
  (16679, 20, 10, 14, 'Wise men lay up knowledge: but the mouth of the foolish is near destruction.', '&para; 0~02450~ [1] 3~06845~ 4~01847~: 7~06310~ 10~0191~ [11] 12~07138~ 13~04288~.'),
  (30148, 58, 9, 27, 'And as it is appointed unto men once to die, but after this the judgment:', '0~2532~ 1~3745~ 2~2596~ 4~606~ 6~444~ 7~530~ 9~599~, 10~1161~ 11~3326~ 12~5124~ 14~2920~:'),
  (25669, 42, 17, 4, 'And if he trespass against thee seven times in a day, and seven times in a day turn again to thee, saying, I repent; thou shalt forgive him.', '0~2532~ 1~1437~ 3~264~ 4~1519~ 5~4571~ 7~2034~ 10~2250~, 11~2532~ 13~2034~ 16~2250~ 18~1994~ 19~1909~ 20~4571~, 21~3004~, 23~3340~; 26~863~ 27~846~.'),
  (12457, 16, 7, 28, 'The men of Bethazmaveth, forty and two.', '1~0582~ 3~01041~, 4~0705~ 6~08147~.'),
  (10891, 13, 17, 20, 'O LORD, there is none like thee, neither is there any God beside thee, according to all that we have heard with our ears.', '1~03068~, [2 3] [8 10] 11~0430~ 12~02108~ 20~08085~ 23~0241~.'),
  (3519, 3, 25, 45, 'Moreover of the children of the strangers that do sojourn among you, of them shall ye buy, and of their families that are with you, which they begat in your land: and they shall be your possession.', '3~01121~ 6~08453~ 9~01481~ 16~07069~, 20~04940~ [22] 27~03205~ 30~0776~: 36~0272~.'),
  (15647, 19, 105, 32, 'He gave them hail for rain, and flaming fire in their land.', '1~05414~ 3~01259~ 5~01653~, [6] 7~03852~ 8~0784~ 11~0776~.'),
  (24537, 41, 8, 26, 'And he sent him away to his house, saying, Neither go into the town, nor tell it to any in the town.', '0~2532~ 2~649~ 3~846~ 4~649~ 5~1519~ 6~846~ 7~3624~, 8~3004~, 9~3366~ 10~1525~ 11~1519~ 13~2968~, 14~3366~ 15~2036~ [16] 18~5100~ 19~1722~ 21~2968~.'),
  (30891, 66, 11, 3, 'And I will give power unto my two witnesses, and they shall prophesy a thousand two hundred and threescore days, clothed in sackcloth.', '&para; 0~2532~ 3~1325~ [4] 6~3450~ 7~1417~ 8~3144~, 9~2532~ 12~4395~ 14~5507~ 16~1250~ [17] 18~1835~ 19~2250~, 21~4016~ 22~4526~.'),
  (7732, 9, 19, 19, 'And it was told Saul, saying, Behold, David is at Naioth in Ramah.', '3~05046~ 4~07586~, 5~0559~, 7~01732~ [8] 10~05121~ 12~07414~.'),
  (4040, 4, 11, 11, 'And Moses said unto the LORD, Wherefore hast thou afflicted thy servant? and wherefore have I not found favour in thy sight, that thou layest the burden of all this people upon me?', '1~04872~ 2~0559~ 5~03068~, 9~07489~ 11~05650~? 17~04672~ 18~02580~ 21~05869~, 24~07760~ 26~04853~ 30~05971~'),
  (8470, 10, 17, 14, 'And Absalom and all the men of Israel said, The counsel of Hushai the Archite is better than the counsel of Ahithophel. For the LORD had appointed to defeat the good counsel of Ahithophel, to the intent that the LORD might bring evil upon Absalom.', '1~053~ 5~0376~ 7~03478~ 8~0559~, 10~06098~ 12~02365~ 14~0757~ [15] 16~02896~ 19~06098~ 21~0302~. 24~03068~ 26~06680~ 28~06565~ 30~02896~ 31~06098~ 33~0302~, 36~05668~ 39~03068~ 41~0935~ 42~07451~ 44~053~.'),
  (25149, 42, 5, 30, 'But their scribes and Pharisees murmured against his disciples, saying, Why do ye eat and drink with publicans and sinners?', '0~2532~ 1~846~ 2~1122~ 3~2532~ 4~5330~ 5~1111~ 6~4314~ 7~846~ 8~3101~, 9~3004~, 10~1302~ 13~2068~ 14~2532~ 15~4095~ 16~3326~ 17~5057~ 18~2532~ 19~268~?'),
  (13403, 18, 22, 5, 'Is not thy wickedness great? and thine iniquities infinite?', '&para; [0] 3~07451~ 4~07227~? 7~05771~ 8~07093~?'),
  (1241, 1, 41, 41, 'And Pharaoh said unto Joseph, See, I have set thee over all the land of Egypt.', '1~06547~ 2~0559~ 4~03130~, 5~07200~, 8~05414~ 13~0776~ 15~04714~.'),
  (7523, 9, 14, 8, 'Then said Jonathan, Behold, we will pass over unto these men, and we will discover ourselves unto them.', '1~0559~ 2~03083~, 7~05674~ [9] 10~0582~, 14~01540~'),
  (17359, 21, 2, 17, 'Therefore I hated life; because the work that is wrought under the sun is grievous unto me: for all is vanity and vexation of spirit.', '&para; 2~08130~ 3~02416~; 6~04639~ 9~06213~ 12~08121~ [13] 14~07451~ [19] 20~01892~ 22~07469~ 24~07307~.'),
  (29437, 50, 2, 30, 'Because for the work of Christ he was nigh unto death, not regarding his life, to supply your lack of service toward me.', '0~3754~ 1~1223~ 3~2041~ 5~5547~ 8~1448~ 9~3360~ 10~2288~, 12~3851~ 14~5590~, 15~2443~ 16~378~ 17~5216~ 18~5303~ 20~3009~ 21~4314~ 22~3165~.'),
  (12940, 18, 4, 1, 'Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said,', '&para; 1~0464~ 3~08489~ 4~06030~ 6~0559~,'),
  (8650, 10, 22, 40, 'For thou hast girded me with strength to battle: them that rose up against me hast thou subdued under me.', '3~0247~ 6~02428~ 8~04421~: 12~06965~ 17~03766~'),
  (13786, 18, 37, 8, 'Then the beasts go into dens, and remain in their places.', '2~02416~ 3~0935~ 4~01119~ 5~0695~, 7~07931~ 10~04585~.'),
  (1675, 2, 6, 15, 'And the sons of Simeon; Jemuel, and Jamin, and Ohad, and Jachin, and Zohar, and Shaul the son of a Canaanitish woman: these are the families of Simeon.', '2~01121~ 4~08095~; 5~03223~, 7~03226~, 9~0161~, 11~03199~, 13~06714~, 15~07586~ 17~01121~ 21~03669~: [23] 25~04940~ 27~08095~.'),
  (4328, 4, 20, 12, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses and Aaron, Because ye believed me not, to sanctify me in the eyes of the children of Israel, therefore ye shall not bring this congregation into the land which I have given them.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~ 7~0175~, 10~0539~ 14~06942~ 18~05869~ 21~01121~ 23~03478~, 28~0935~ 30~06951~ 33~0776~ 37~05414~'),
  (23395, 40, 9, 6, 'But that ye may know that the Son of man hath power on earth to forgive sins, (then saith he to the sick of the palsy,) Arise, take up thy bed, and go unto thine house.', '0~1161~ 1~2443~ 4~1492~ 5~3754~ 7~5207~ 9~444~ 10~2192~ 11~1849~ 12~1909~ 13~1093~ 15~863~ 16~266~, 17~5119~* 20~3004~ 26~3885~,) 27~1453~, 29~142~ 30~4675~ 31~2825~, 32~2532~ 33~5217~ 34~1519~ 35~4675~ 36~3624~.'),
  (2310, 2, 28, 12, 'And thou shalt put the two stones upon the shoulders of the ephod for stones of memorial unto the children of Israel: and Aaron shall bear their names before the LORD upon his two shoulders for a memorial.', '3~07760~ 5~08147~ 6~068~ 9~03802~ 12~0646~ [13] 14~068~ 16~02146~ 19~01121~ 21~03478~: 23~0175~ 25~05375~ 27~08034~ 28~06440~ 30~03068~ 33~08147~ 34~03802~ 37~02146~.'),
  (7064, 7, 20, 3, '(Now the children of Benjamin heard that the children of Israel were gone up to Mizpeh.) Then said the children of Israel, Tell us, how was this wickedness?', '2~01121~ 4~01144~ 5~08085~ 8~01121~ 10~03478~ 13~05927~ 15~04709~) 17~0559~ 19~01121~ 21~03478~, 22~01696~ [23] 25~01961~ 27~07451~?'),
  (12972, 18, 5, 12, 'He disappointeth the devices of the crafty, so that their hands cannot perform their enterprise.', '1~06565~ 3~04284~ 6~06175~, 10~03027~ 12~06213~ [13] 14~08454~.'),
  (15738, 19, 107, 30, 'Then are they glad because they be quiet; so he bringeth them unto their desired haven.', '3~08055~ 7~08367~; 10~05148~ 14~02656~ 15~04231~.'),
  (851, 1, 30, 17, 'And God hearkened unto Leah, and she conceived, and bare Jacob the fifth son.', '1~0430~ 2~08085~ 4~03812~, 7~02029~, 9~03205~ 10~03290~ 12~02549~ 13~01121~.'),
  (29248, 49, 2, 3, 'Among whom also we all had our conversation in times past in the lusts of our flesh, fulfilling the desires of the flesh and of the mind; and were by nature the children of wrath, even as others.', '0~1722~ 1~3739~ 2~2532~ 3~2249~ 4~3956~ 7~390~ 10~4218~ 11~1722~ 13~1939~ 15~2257~ 16~4561~, 17~4160~ 19~2307~ 22~4561~ 23~2532~ 26~1271~; 27~2532~ 28~2258~ 30~5449~ 32~5043~ 34~3709~, 35~2532~ 36~5613~ 37~3062~.'),
  (14110, 19, 16, 9, 'Therefore my heart is glad, and my glory rejoiceth: my flesh also shall rest in hope.', '2~03820~ 4~08055~, 7~03519~ 8~01523~: 10~01320~ 13~07931~ 15~0983~.'),
  (18442, 23, 40, 13, 'Who hath directed the Spirit of the LORD, or being his counsellor hath taught him?', '2~08505~ 4~07307~ 7~03068~, [9] 11~06098~ 12~0376~ 13~03045~'),
  (30901, 66, 11, 13, 'And the same hour was there a great earthquake, and the tenth part of the city fell, and in the earthquake were slain of men seven thousand: and the remnant were affrighted, and gave glory to the God of heaven.', '0~2532~ 2~1565~ 3~1722~* 4~5610~ 6~1096~ 8~3173~ 9~4578~, 10~2532~ 13~1182~ 16~4172~ 17~4098~, 18~2532~ 19~1722~ 21~4578~ 23~615~ 24~3686~* 26~444~ 27~2033~ 28~5505~: 29~2532~ 31~3062~ 32~1096~ 33~1719~, 34~2532~ 35~1325~ 36~1391~ 39~2316~ 41~3772~.'),
  (29386, 50, 1, 9, 'And this I pray, that your love may abound yet more and more in knowledge and in all judgment;', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~5124~ 3~4336~, 4~2443~ 5~5216~ 6~26~ 8~4052~ 9~2089~ 10~3123~ 11~2532~ 12~3123~ 13~1722~ 14~1922~ 15~2532~ [16] 17~3956~ 18~144~;'),
  (1614, 2, 4, 8, 'And it shall come to pass, if they will not believe thee, neither hearken to the voice of the first sign, that they will believe the voice of the latter sign.', '10~0539~ 13~08085~ 16~06963~ 19~07223~ 20~0226~, 24~0539~ 26~06963~ 29~0314~ 30~0226~.'),
  (22479, 30, 7, 6, 'The LORD repented for this: This also shall not be, saith the Lord GOD.', '1~03068~ 2~05162~ 10~0559~ 12~0136~ 13~03069~.'),
  (8659, 10, 22, 49, 'And that bringeth me forth from mine enemies: thou also hast lifted me up on high above them that rose up against me: thou hast delivered me from the violent man.', '4~03318~ 7~0341~: 15~07311~ 20~06965~ 25~05337~ 29~02555~ 30~0376~.'),
  (158, 1, 6, 20, 'Of fowls after their kind, and of cattle after their kind, of every creeping thing of the earth after his kind, two of every sort shall come unto thee, to keep them alive.', '1~05775~ 4~04327~, 7~0929~ 10~04327~, 14~07431~ 17~0127~ 20~04327~, 21~08147~ [24] 26~0935~ [31] 32~02421~.'),
  (30413, 60, 1, 23, 'Being born again, not of corruptible seed, but of incorruptible, by the word of God, which liveth and abideth for ever.', '2~313~, 3~3756~ 4~1537~ 5~5349~ 6~4701~, 7~235~ 9~862~, 10~1223~ 12~3056~ 14~2316~, 16~2198~ 17~2532~ 18~3306~ 19~1519~ 20~165~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (19723, 24, 31, 23, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts, the God of Israel; As yet they shall use this speech in the land of Judah and in the cities thereof, when I shall bring again their captivity; The LORD bless thee, O habitation of justice, and mountain of holiness.', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~, 7~0430~ 9~03478~; 14~0559~ 16~01697~ 19~0776~ 21~03063~ 25~05892~ 31~07725~ 33~07622~; 35~03068~ 36~01288~ 39~05116~ 41~06664~, [42] 43~02022~ 45~06944~.'),
  (23260, 40, 5, 16, 'Let your light so shine before men, that they may see your good works, and glorify your Father which is in heaven.', '1~5216~ 2~5457~ 3~3779~ 4~2989~ 5~1715~ 6~444~, 7~3704~ 10~1492~ 11~5216~ 12~2570~ 13~2041~, 14~2532~ 15~1392~ 16~5216~ 17~3962~ 18~3588~ 20~1722~ 21~3772~.'),
  (20025, 24, 44, 6, 'Wherefore my fury and mine anger was poured forth, and was kindled in the cities of Judah and in the streets of Jerusalem; and they are wasted and desolate, as at this day.', '2~02534~ 5~0639~ 8~05413~, 11~01197~ 14~05892~ 16~03063~ 20~02351~ 22~03389~; 26~02723~ [27] 28~08077~, 32~03117~.'),
  (18024, 23, 19, 11, 'Surely the princes of Zoan are fools, the counsel of the wise counsellors of Pharaoh is become brutish: how say ye unto Pharaoh, I am the son of the wise, the son of ancient kings?', '2~08269~ 4~06814~ [5] 6~0191~, 8~06098~ 11~02450~ 12~03289~ 14~06547~ 17~01197~: 19~0559~ 22~06547~, [24] 26~01121~ 29~02450~, 31~01121~ 33~06924~ 34~04428~?'),
  (7614, 9, 16, 12, 'And he sent, and brought him in. Now he was ruddy, and withal of a beautiful countenance, and goodly to look to. And the LORD said, Arise, anoint him: for this is he.', '2~07971~, 6~0935~. [9] 10~0132~, [11] 12~05973~ 15~03303~ 16~05869~, 18~02896~ 21~07210~. 24~03068~ 25~0559~, 26~06965~, 27~04886~ [31]'),
  (14058, 19, 10, 8, 'He sitteth in the lurking places of the villages: in the secret places doth he murder the innocent: his eyes are privily set against the poor.', '1~03427~ 5~03993~ 8~02691~: 12~04565~ 15~02026~ 17~05355~: 19~05869~ 22~06845~ 25~02489~.'),
  (22875, 37, 2, 11, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; Ask now the priests concerning the law, saying,', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~; 6~07592~ 9~03548~ [10] 12~08451~, 13~0559~,'),
  (1189, 1, 40, 12, 'And Joseph said unto him, This is the interpretation of it: The three branches are three days:', '1~03130~ 2~0559~ [6] 8~06623~ 12~07969~ 13~08299~ [14] 15~07969~ 16~03117~:'),
  (18574, 23, 45, 4, 'For Jacob my servant''s sake, and Israel mine elect, I have even called thee by thy name: I have surnamed thee, though thou hast not known me.', '1~03290~ 3~05650~ 6~03478~ 8~0972~, 12~07121~ 16~08034~: 19~03655~ 25~03045~'),
  (26360, 43, 7, 17, 'If any man will do his will, he shall know of the doctrine, whether it be of God, or whether I speak of myself.', '0~1437~ 2~5100~ 3~2309~ 4~4160~ 5~846~ 6~2307~, 9~1097~ 10~4012~ 12~1322~, 13~4220~ 15~2076~ 16~1537~ 17~2316~, 18~2228~ [19] 20~1473~ 21~2980~ 22~575~ 23~1683~.'),
  (26089, 43, 1, 30, 'This is he of whom I said, After me cometh a man which is preferred before me: for he was before me.', '0~3778~ 2~2076~ 3~4012~ 4~3739~ 5~1473~ 6~2036~, 7~3694~ 8~3450~ 9~2064~ 11~435~ 12~3739~ 14~1096~ 15~1715~ 16~3450~: 17~3754~ 19~2258~ 20~4413~ 21~3450~.'),
  (16761, 20, 13, 5, 'A righteous man hateth lying: but a wicked man is loathsome, and cometh to shame.', '&para; 1~06662~ [2] 3~08130~ 4~08267~ 5~01697~:* 8~07563~ [9] 11~0887~, 15~02659~.'),
  (28421, 46, 2, 11, 'For what man knoweth the things of a man, save the spirit of man which is in him? even so the things of God knoweth no man, but the Spirit of God.', '0~1063~ 1~5101~ 2~444~ 3~1492~ 5~3588~ 8~444~, 9~1508~ 11~4151~ 13~444~ 14~3588~ 16~1722~ 17~846~? 18~2532~ 19~3779~ 21~3588~ 23~2316~ 24~1492~ 26~3762~, 27~1508~ 29~4151~ 31~2316~.'),
  (30822, 66, 6, 13, 'And the stars of heaven fell unto the earth, even as a fig tree casteth her untimely figs, when she is shaken of a mighty wind.', '0~2532~ 2~792~ 4~3772~ 5~4098~ 6~1519~ 8~1093~, 10~5613~ 13~4808~ 14~906~ 15~846~ 17~3653~, 21~4579~ 22~5259~ 24~3173~ 25~417~.'),
  (13040, 18, 8, 2, 'How long wilt thou speak these things? and how long shall the words of thy mouth be like a strong wind?', '0~0575~ 1~05704~ 4~04448~ [6] [8 10] 12~0561~ 15~06310~ [16 17] 19~03524~ 20~07307~?'),
  (8755, 11, 1, 30, 'Even as I sware unto thee by the LORD God of Israel, saying, Assuredly Solomon thy son shall reign after me, and he shall sit upon my throne in my stead; even so will I certainly do this day.', '3~07650~ 8~03068~ 9~0430~ 11~03478~, 12~0559~, 14~08010~ 16~01121~ 18~04427~ 19~0310~ 24~03427~ 27~03678~ 36~06213~ 38~03117~.'),
  (12039, 15, 2, 3, 'The children of Parosh, two thousand an hundred seventy and two.', '1~01121~ 3~06551~, 5~0505~ 7~03967~ 8~07657~ 10~08147~.'),
  (2370, 2, 29, 29, 'And the holy garments of Aaron shall be his sons'' after him, to be anointed therein, and to be consecrated in them.', '2~06944~ 3~0899~ 5~0175~ 9~01121~ 10~0310~ 14~04888~ 19~04390~ 20~03027~*'),
  (30030, 58, 3, 19, 'So we see that they could not enter in because of unbelief.', '0~2532~ 2~991~ 3~3754~ 5~1410~ 6~3756~ 8~1525~ 9~1223~ 11~570~.'),
  (24665, 41, 11, 14, 'And Jesus answered and said unto it, No man eat fruit of thee hereafter for ever. And his disciples heard it.', '0~2532~ 1~2424~ 2~611~ 4~2036~ 6~846~, 8~3367~ 9~5315~ 10~2590~ 11~1537~ 12~4675~ 13~3371~ 14~1519~ 15~165~. 16~2532~ 17~846~ 18~3101~ 19~191~ [20]'),
  (4403, 4, 22, 23, 'And the ass saw the angel of the LORD standing in the way, and his sword drawn in his hand: and the ass turned aside out of the way, and went into the field: and Balaam smote the ass, to turn her into the way.', '2~0860~ 3~07200~ 5~04397~ 8~03068~ 9~05324~ 12~01870~, 15~02719~ 16~08025~ 19~03027~: 22~0860~ 24~05186~ 28~01870~, 30~03212~ 33~07704~: 35~01109~ 36~05221~ 38~0860~, 40~05186~ 44~01870~.'),
  (15668, 19, 106, 8, 'Nevertheless he saved them for his name''s sake, that he might make his mighty power to be known.', '2~03467~ 6~08034~ 14~01369~ 17~03045~.'),
  (9200, 11, 13, 8, 'And the man of God said unto the king, If thou wilt give me half thine house, I will not go in with thee, neither will I eat bread nor drink water in this place:', '2~0376~ 4~0430~ 5~0559~ 8~04428~, 12~05414~ 14~02677~ 16~01004~, 21~0935~ 27~0398~ 28~03899~ 30~08354~ 31~04325~ 34~04725~:'),
  (2087, 2, 21, 5, 'And if the servant shall plainly say, I love my master, my wife, and my children; I will not go out free:', '3~05650~ 5~0559~ 6~0559~, 8~0157~ 10~0113~, 12~0802~, 15~01121~; 20~03318~ 21~02670~:'),
  (26041, 42, 24, 36, 'And as they thus spake, Jesus himself stood in the midst of them, and saith unto them, Peace be unto you.', '&para; 0~1161~ 2~846~ 3~5023~ 4~2980~, 5~2424~ 6~846~ 7~2476~ 8~1722~ 10~3319~ 12~846~, 13~2532~ 14~3004~ 16~846~, 17~1515~ [18] 20~5213~.'),
  (30855, 66, 8, 12, 'And the fourth angel sounded, and the third part of the sun was smitten, and the third part of the moon, and the third part of the stars; so as the third part of them was darkened, and the day shone not for a third part of it, and the night likewise.', '0~2532~ 2~5067~ 3~32~ 4~4537~, 5~2532~ 8~5154~ 11~2246~ 13~4141~, 14~2532~ 17~5154~ 20~4582~, 21~2532~ 24~5154~ 27~792~; 29~2443~ 32~5154~ 34~846~ 36~4654~, 37~2532~ 39~2250~ 40~5316~ 41~3361~ 45~5154~ 47~846~, 48~2532~ 50~3571~ 51~3668~.'),
  (18642, 23, 48, 19, 'Thy seed also had been as the sand, and the offspring of thy bowels like the gravel thereof; his name should not have been cut off nor destroyed from before me.', '1~02233~ 7~02344~, 10~06631~ 13~04578~ 16~04579~ 19~08034~ 25~03772~ 27~08045~ 29~06440~'),
  (28823, 47, 1, 7, 'And our hope of you is stedfast, knowing, that as ye are partakers of the sufferings, so shall ye be also of the consolation.', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~2257~ 2~1680~ 3~5228~ 4~5216~ [5] 6~949~, 7~1492~, 8~3754~ 9~5618~ 11~2075~ 12~2844~ 15~3804~, 16~3779~ [17 19] 20~2532~ 23~3874~.'),
  (2957, 3, 8, 35, 'Therefore shall ye abide at the door of the tabernacle of the congregation day and night seven days, and keep the charge of the LORD, that ye die not: for so I am commanded.', '3~03427~ [4] 6~06607~ 9~0168~ 12~04150~ 13~03119~ 15~03915~ 16~07651~ 17~03117~, 19~08104~ 21~04931~ 24~03068~, 27~04191~ 33~06680~.'),
  (4997, 5, 3, 16, 'And unto the Reubenites and unto the Gadites I gave from Gilead even unto the river Arnon half the valley, and the border even unto the river Jabbok, which is the border of the children of Ammon;', '3~07206~ 7~01425~ 9~05414~ 11~01568~ 15~05158~ 16~0769~ 17~08432~ 19~05158~, 22~01366~ 26~05158~ 27~02999~, [28 29] 31~01366~ 34~01121~ 36~05983~;'),
  (29372, 49, 6, 19, 'And for me, that utterance may be given unto me, that I may open my mouth boldly, to make known the mystery of the gospel,', '&para; 0~2532~ 1~5228~ 2~1700~, 3~2443~ 4~3056~ 7~1325~ 9~3427~, 13~457~ 14~1722~* 15~3450~ 16~4750~ 17~3954~ 18~1722~,* 21~1107~ 23~3466~ 26~2098~,'),
  (29982, 58, 1, 3, 'Who being the brightness of his glory, and the express image of his person, and upholding all things by the word of his power, when he had by himself purged our sins, sat down on the right hand of the Majesty on high;', '0~3739~ 1~5607~ 3~541~ [5] 6~1391~, 7~2532~ 10~5481~ 12~846~ 13~5287~, 14~5037~ 15~5342~ 17~3956~ 20~4487~ 22~846~ 23~1411~, 26~4160~ 27~2512~* 28~1223~ 29~1438~ 30~4160~ 31~2512~* 32~2257~ 33~266~, 35~2523~ 36~1722~ 39~1188~ 42~3172~ 43~1722~ 44~5308~;'),
  (13956, 19, 2, 2, 'The kings of the earth set themselves, and the rulers take counsel together, against the LORD, and against his anointed, saying,', '1~04428~ 4~0776~ 5~03320~ 9~07336~ 11~03245~ 12~03162~, 15~03068~, 19~04899~, [20]'),
  (8734, 11, 1, 9, 'And Adonijah slew sheep and oxen and fat cattle by the stone of Zoheleth, which is by Enrogel, and called all his brethren the king''s sons, and all the men of Judah the king''s servants:', '1~0138~ 2~02076~ 3~06629~ 5~01241~ 8~04806~ 11~068~ 13~02120~, [15] 16~0681~ 17~05883~, 19~07121~ 22~0251~ 24~04428~ 25~01121~, 29~0582~ 31~03063~ 33~04428~ 34~05650~:'),
  (23823, 40, 20, 21, 'And he said unto her, What wilt thou? She saith unto him, Grant that these my two sons may sit, the one on thy right hand, and the other on the left, in thy kingdom.', '0~1161~ 2~2036~ 4~846~, 5~5101~ 7~2309~? 9~3004~ 11~846~, 12~2036~ 13~2443~ 14~3778~ 15~3450~ 16~1417~ 17~5207~ 19~2523~, 21~1520~ 22~1537~ 23~4675~ 25~1188~, 26~2532~ 28~1520~ 29~1537~ 31~2176~, 32~1722~ 33~4675~ 34~932~.'),
  (21298, 26, 33, 9, 'Nevertheless, if thou warn the wicked of his way to turn from it; if he do not turn from his way, he shall die in his iniquity; but thou hast delivered thy soul.', '3~02094~ 5~07563~ 8~01870~ 10~07725~ 17~07725~ 20~01870~, 23~04191~ 26~05771~; 30~05337~ 32~05315~.'),
  (17147, 20, 25, 25, 'As cold waters to a thirsty soul, so is good news from a far country.', '&para; [0] 1~07119~ 2~04325~ 5~05889~ 6~05315~, [8] 9~02896~ 10~08052~ 13~04801~ 14~0776~.'),
  (2379, 2, 29, 38, 'Now this is that which thou shalt offer upon the altar; two lambs of the first year day by day continually.', '&para; [2 3] 7~06213~ 10~04196~; 11~08147~ 12~03532~ 15~01121~ 16~08141~ 17~03117~ 19~03117~ 20~08548~.'),
  (11969, 14, 34, 27, 'Because thine heart was tender, and thou didst humble thyself before God, when thou heardest his words against this place, and against the inhabitants thereof, and humbledst thyself before me, and didst rend thy clothes, and weep before me; I have even heard thee also, saith the LORD.', '2~03824~ 4~07401~, 8~03665~ 10~06440~ 11~0430~, 14~08085~ 16~01697~ 19~04725~, 23~03427~ 26~03665~ 28~06440~ 32~07167~ 34~0899~, 36~01058~ 37~06440~ 42~08085~ [43] 45~05002~ 47~03068~.'),
  (20527, 26, 3, 16, 'And it came to pass at the end of seven days, that the word of the LORD came unto me, saying,', '&para; 7~07097~ 9~07651~ 10~03117~, 13~01697~ 16~03068~ 20~0559~,'),
  (13723, 18, 34, 31, 'Surely it is meet to be said unto God, I have borne chastisement, I will not offend any more:', '&para; 6~0559~ 8~0410~, 11~05375~ [12] 16~02254~ [17 18]'),
  (19655, 24, 29, 11, 'For I know the thoughts that I think toward you, saith the LORD, thoughts of peace, and not of evil, to give you an expected end.', '2~03045~ 4~04284~ 7~02803~ 10~05002~ 12~03068~, 13~04284~ 15~07965~, 19~07451~, 21~05414~ 24~08615~ 25~0319~.'),
  (8200, 10, 7, 13, 'He shall build an house for my name, and I will stablish the throne of his kingdom for ever.', '2~01129~ 4~01004~ 7~08034~, 11~03559~ 13~03678~ 16~04467~ 17~05704~ 18~05769~.'),
  (25871, 42, 21, 31, 'So likewise ye, when ye see these things come to pass, know ye that the kingdom of God is nigh at hand.', '0~3779~ 1~2532~ 2~5210~, 3~3752~ 5~1492~ 7~5023~ 10~1096~, 12~1097~ 13~3754~ 15~932~ 17~2316~ 18~2076~ 21~1451~.'),
  (14497, 19, 37, 38, 'But the transgressors shall be destroyed together: the end of the wicked shall be cut off.', '2~06586~ 5~08045~ 6~03162~: 8~0319~ 11~07563~ 15~03772~.'),
  (19900, 24, 37, 17, 'Then Zedekiah the king sent, and took him out: and the king asked him secretly in his house, and said, Is there any word from the LORD? And Jeremiah said, There is: for, said he, thou shalt be delivered into the hand of the king of Babylon.', '1~06667~ 3~04428~ 4~07971~, 8~03947~: 11~04428~ 12~07592~ 14~05643~ 17~01004~, 19~0559~, [22] 23~01697~ 26~03068~? 28~03414~ 29~0559~, 31~03426~: 33~0559~ 38~05414~ 41~03027~ 44~04428~ 46~0894~.'),
  (24513, 41, 8, 2, 'I have compassion on the multitude, because they have now been with me three days, and have nothing to eat:', '2~4697~ 3~1909~ 5~3793~, 6~3754~ 8~4357~ 9~2235~ 10~4357~ 12~3427~ 13~5140~ 14~2250~, 15~2532~ 16~2192~ 17~5101~ 18~3756~ 19~5315~:'),
  (19781, 24, 32, 41, 'Yea, I will rejoice over them to do them good, and I will plant them in this land assuredly with my whole heart and with my whole soul.', '3~07797~ 9~02895~, 13~05193~ 17~0776~ 18~0571~ 22~03820~ 27~05315~.'),
  (25327, 42, 9, 14, 'For they were about five thousand men. And he said to his disciples, Make them sit down by fifties in a company.', '0~1063~ 2~2258~ 3~5616~ 5~4000~ 6~435~. 7~1161~ 9~2036~ 10~4314~ 11~846~ 12~3101~, 13~2625~ 14~846~ 16~2625~ 17~303~ 18~4004~ 21~2828~.'),
  (13964, 19, 2, 10, 'Be wise now therefore, O ye kings: be instructed, ye judges of the earth.', '&para; 1~07919~ 6~04428~: 8~03256~, 10~08199~ 13~0776~.'),
  (17092, 20, 24, 4, 'And by knowledge shall the chambers be filled with all precious and pleasant riches.', '2~01847~ 5~02315~ 7~04390~ 10~03368~ 12~05273~ 13~01952~.'),
  (5916, 6, 3, 17, 'And the priests that bare the ark of the covenant of the LORD stood firm on dry ground in the midst of Jordan, and all the Israelites passed over on dry ground, until all the people were passed clean over Jordan.', '2~03548~ 4~05375~ 6~0727~ 9~01285~ 12~03068~ 13~05975~ 14~03559~ 17~02724~ 20~08432~ 22~03383~, 26~03478~ 28~05674~ 31~02724~, 35~01471~ 37~05674~ 38~08552~ 39~05674~ 40~03383~.'),
  (14926, 19, 68, 17, 'The chariots of God are twenty thousand, even thousands of angels: the Lord is among them, as in Sinai, in the holy place.', '1~07393~ 3~0430~ [4] 6~07239~, [7] 8~0505~ 10~08136~: 12~0136~ [13] [16 17] 18~05514~, 21~06944~ [22]'),
  (19045, 24, 4, 9, 'And it shall come to pass at that day, saith the LORD, that the heart of the king shall perish, and the heart of the princes; and the priests shall be astonished, and the prophets shall wonder.', '8~03117~, 9~05002~ 11~03068~, [12] 14~03820~ 17~04428~ 19~06~, 22~03820~ 25~08269~; 28~03548~ 31~08074~, 34~05030~ 36~08539~.'),
  (25445, 42, 11, 28, 'But he said, Yea rather, blessed are they that hear the word of God, and keep it.', '0~1161~ 1~846~ 2~2036~, 4~3304~, 5~3107~ [6] 9~191~ 11~3056~ 13~2316~, 14~2532~ 15~5442~ 16~846~.'),
  (31099, 66, 22, 3, 'And there shall be no more curse: but the throne of God and of the Lamb shall be in it; and his servants shall serve him:', '0~2532~ 3~2071~ 4~3756~ 5~3956~ 6~2089~* 7~2652~: 8~2532~ 10~2362~ 12~2316~ 13~2532~ 16~721~ 18~2071~ 19~1722~ 20~846~; 21~2532~ 22~846~ 23~1401~ 25~3000~ 26~846~:'),
  (14642, 19, 47, 8, 'God reigneth over the heathen: God sitteth upon the throne of his holiness.', '0~0430~ 1~04427~ 4~01471~: 5~0430~ 6~03427~ 9~03678~ 12~06944~.'),
  (11622, 14, 20, 26, 'And on the fourth day they assembled themselves in the valley of Berachah; for there they blessed the LORD: therefore the name of the same place was called, The valley of Berachah, unto this day.', '3~07243~ 4~03117~ 6~06950~ 10~06010~ 12~01294~; 16~01288~ 18~03068~: 21~08034~ 25~04725~ 27~07121~, 29~06010~ 31~01294~, 34~03117~.'),
  (25214, 42, 7, 7, 'Wherefore neither thought I myself worthy to come unto thee: but say in a word, and my servant shall be healed.', '0~1352~ 1~3761~ 3~515~ 4~1683~ 5~515~ 7~2064~ 8~4314~ 9~4571~: 10~235~ 11~2036~ 14~3056~, 15~2532~ 16~3450~ 17~3816~ 20~2390~.'),
  (18717, 23, 52, 12, 'For ye shall not go out with haste, nor go by flight: for the LORD will go before you; and the God of Israel will be your rereward.', '5~03318~ 7~02649~, 9~03212~ 11~04499~: 14~03068~ 16~01980~ 17~06440~ 21~0430~ 23~03478~ [24 25] 27~0622~.'),
  (30703, 65, 1, 15, 'To execute judgment upon all, and to convince all that are ungodly among them of all their ungodly deeds which they have ungodly committed, and of all their hard speeches which ungodly sinners have spoken against him.', '&para; 1~4160~ 2~2920~ 3~2596~ 4~3956~, 5~2532~ 7~1827~ 8~3956~ 11~765~ 13~846~ 14~4012~ 15~3956~ 16~846~ 17~763~ 18~2041~ 19~3739~ 23~764~, 24~2532~ 25~4012~ 26~3956~ 28~4642~ [29] 30~3739~ 31~765~ 32~268~ 34~2980~ 35~2596~ 36~846~.'),
  (16752, 20, 12, 24, 'The hand of the diligent shall bear rule: but the slothful shall be under tribute.', '&para; 1~03027~ 4~02742~ 7~04910~: 10~07423~ 14~04522~.'),
  (13179, 18, 13, 17, 'Hear diligently my speech, and my declaration with your ears.', '0~08085~ 1~08085~ 3~04405~, 6~0262~ 9~0241~.'),
  (2168, 2, 23, 19, 'The first of the firstfruits of thy land thou shalt bring into the house of the LORD thy God. Thou shalt not seethe a kid in his mother''s milk.', '1~07225~ 4~01061~ 7~0127~ 10~0935~ 13~01004~ 16~03068~ 18~0430~. 22~01310~ 24~01423~ 27~0517~ 28~02461~.'),
  (25420, 42, 11, 3, 'Give us day by day our daily bread.', '0~1325~ 1~2254~ 2~2596~ 4~2250~ 5~2257~ 6~1967~ 7~740~.'),
  (1323, 1, 43, 28, 'And they answered, Thy servant our father is in good health, he is yet alive. And they bowed down their heads, and made obeisance.', '2~0559~, 4~05650~ 6~01~ [7] 10~07965~, [12] 14~02416~. 20~06915~, 23~07812~.'),
  (609, 1, 24, 14, 'And let it come to pass, that the damsel to whom I shall say, Let down thy pitcher, I pray thee, that I may drink; and she shall say, Drink, and I will give thy camels drink also: let the same be she that thou hast appointed for thy servant Isaac; and thereby shall I know that thou hast shewed kindness unto my master.', '8~05291~ 13~0559~, 15~05186~ 17~03537~, 24~08354~; 28~0559~, 29~08354~, 33~08248~ 35~01581~ 36~08248~ [38 41] [43] 46~03198~ 49~05650~ 50~03327~; 55~03045~ 59~06213~ 60~02617~ 63~0113~.'),
  (14672, 19, 49, 15, 'But God will redeem my soul from the power of the grave: for he shall receive me. Selah.', '&para; 1~0430~ 3~06299~ 5~05315~ 8~03027~ 11~07585~: 15~03947~ 17~05542~.'),
  (5584, 5, 26, 12, 'When thou hast made an end of tithing all the tithes of thine increase the third year, which is the year of tithing, and hast given it unto the Levite, the stranger, the fatherless, and the widow, that they may eat within thy gates, and be filled;', '&para; 5~03615~ 7~06237~ 10~04643~ 13~08393~ 15~07992~ 16~08141~, [17 18] 20~08141~ 22~04643~, 25~05414~ [26] 29~03881~, 31~01616~, 33~03490~, 36~0490~, 40~0398~ 43~08179~, 46~07646~;'),
  (3015, 3, 11, 13, 'And these are they which ye shall have in abomination among the fowls; they shall not be eaten, they are an abomination: the eagle, and the ossifrage, and the osprey,', '[2 4] 9~08262~ 10~04480~ 12~05775~; 17~0398~, [19] 21~08263~: 23~05404~, 26~06538~, 29~05822~,'),
  (2179, 2, 23, 30, 'By little and little I will drive them out from before thee, until thou be increased, and inherit the land.', '1~04592~ 3~04592~ 8~01644~ 10~06440~ 15~06509~, 17~05157~ 19~0776~.'),
  (29890, 55, 4, 4, 'And they shall turn away their ears from the truth, and shall be turned unto fables.', '0~2532~ 4~654~ 5~3303~* [6] 7~189~ 8~575~ 10~225~, 11~1161~ 14~1624~ 15~1909~ 16~3454~.'),
  (16041, 19, 119, 134, 'Deliver me from the oppression of man: so will I keep thy precepts.', '&para; 0~06299~ 4~06233~ 6~0120~: 10~08104~ 12~06490~.'),
  (13565, 18, 29, 24, 'If I laughed on them, they believed it not; and the light of my countenance they cast not down.', '[0] 2~07832~ 6~0539~ [7] 11~0216~ 14~06440~ 18~05307~.'),
  (30820, 66, 6, 11, 'And white robes were given unto every one of them; and it was said unto them, that they should rest yet for a little season, until their fellowservants also and their brethren, that should be killed as they were, should be fulfilled.', '0~2532~ 1~3022~ 2~4749~ 4~1325~ 9~1538~; 10~2532~ 13~4483~ 15~846~, 16~2443~ 19~373~ 20~2089~ 23~3398~ 24~5550~, 25~2193~ 26~846~ 27~4889~ 28~2532~ 29~2532~ 30~846~ 31~80~, 33~3195~ 35~615~ 36~2532~ 37~5613~* 38~846~ [39] 40~3739~ 42~4137~.'),
  (10363, 13, 2, 49, 'She bare also Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the father of Machbenah, and the father of Gibea: and the daughter of Caleb was Achsa.', '1~03205~ 3~08174~ 5~01~ 7~04089~, 8~07724~ 10~01~ 12~04343~, 15~01~ 17~01388~: 20~01323~ 22~03612~ [23] 24~05915~.'),
  (9195, 11, 13, 3, 'And he gave a sign the same day, saying, This is the sign which the LORD hath spoken; Behold, the altar shall be rent, and the ashes that are upon it shall be poured out.', '2~05414~ 4~04159~ 7~03117~, 8~0559~, [10] 12~04159~ 15~03068~ 17~01696~; 20~04196~ 23~07167~, 26~01880~ [28] 34~08210~.'),
  (29169, 48, 4, 22, 'For it is written, that Abraham had two sons, the one by a bondmaid, the other by a freewoman.', '0~1063~ 3~1125~, 4~3754~ 5~11~ 6~2192~ 7~1417~ 8~5207~, 10~1520~ 11~1537~ 13~3814~ 14~2532~,* 16~1520~ 17~1537~ 19~1658~.'),
  (10908, 13, 18, 10, 'He sent Hadoram his son to king David, to inquire of his welfare, and to congratulate him, because he had fought against Hadarezer, and smitten him; (for Hadarezer had war with Tou;) and with him all manner of vessels of gold and silver and brass.', '1~07971~ 2~01913~ 4~01121~ 6~04428~ 7~01732~, 9~07592~ 12~07965~, 15~01288~ 20~03898~ 22~01928~, 24~05221~ 27~01928~ 29~04421~ 30~0376~ 31~08583~;) [33 34] 38~03627~ 40~02091~ 42~03701~ 44~05178~.'),
  (15499, 19, 97, 12, 'Rejoice in the LORD, ye righteous; and give thanks at the remembrance of his holiness.', '0~08055~ 3~03068~, 5~06662~; 8~03034~ 11~02143~ 14~06944~.'),
  (27272, 44, 9, 40, 'But Peter put them all forth, and kneeled down, and prayed; and turning him to the body said, Tabitha, arise. And she opened her eyes: and when she saw Peter, she sat up.', '0~1161~ 1~4074~ 2~1544~ 4~3956~ 5~1854~, 8~5087~ 9~1119~,* 11~4336~; 12~2532~ 13~1994~ [14] 15~4314~ 17~4983~ 18~2036~, 19~5000~, 20~450~. 21~1161~ 23~455~ 24~846~ 25~3788~: 26~2532~ 29~1492~ 30~4074~, 33~339~.'),
  (22361, 29, 3, 9, 'Proclaim ye this among the Gentiles; Prepare war, wake up the mighty men, let all the men of war draw near; let them come up:', '&para; 0~07121~ 5~01471~; 6~06942~ 7~04421~, 9~05782~ 12~01368~, 16~0582~ 18~04421~ 20~05066~; 24~05927~:'),
  (25458, 42, 11, 40, 'Ye fools, did not he that made that which is without make that which is within also?', '[0] 1~878~, 2~4160~ 3~3756~ 6~4160~ 8~3588~ 10~1855~ 11~4160~ 13~3588~ 15~2081~ 16~2532~?'),
  (15394, 19, 90, 7, 'For we are consumed by thine anger, and by thy wrath are we troubled.', '&para; 3~03615~ 6~0639~, 10~02534~ 13~0926~.'),
  (12450, 16, 7, 21, 'The children of Ater of Hezekiah, ninety and eight.', '1~01121~ 3~0333~ 5~02396~, 6~08673~ 8~08083~.'),
  (6518, 7, 1, 2, 'And the LORD said, Judah shall go up: behold, I have delivered the land into his hand.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~, 4~03063~ 7~05927~: 11~05414~ 13~0776~ 16~03027~.'),
  (17652, 22, 8, 3, 'His left hand should be under my head, and his right hand should embrace me.', '2~08040~ [3 4] 7~07218~, 11~03225~ 13~02263~'),
  (29259, 49, 2, 14, 'For he is our peace, who hath made both one, and hath broken down the middle wall of partition between us;', '&para; 0~1063~ 1~846~ 2~2076~ 3~2257~ 4~1515~, 5~3588~ 7~4160~ 8~297~ 9~1520~, 10~2532~ 13~3089~ 16~3320~ 18~5418~ [19 20]'),
  (22333, 29, 2, 13, 'And rend your heart, and not your garments, and turn unto the LORD your God: for he is gracious and merciful, slow to anger, and of great kindness, and repenteth him of the evil.', '1~07167~ 3~03824~, 7~0899~, 9~07725~ 12~03068~ 14~0430~: [17] 18~02587~ 20~07349~, 21~0750~ 23~0639~, 26~07227~ 27~02617~, 29~05162~ 33~07451~.'),
  (15186, 19, 78, 64, 'Their priests fell by the sword; and their widows made no lamentation.', '1~03548~ 2~05307~ 5~02719~; 8~0490~ 11~01058~.'),
  (7803, 9, 22, 9, 'Then answered Doeg the Edomite, which was set over the servants of Saul, and said, I saw the son of Jesse coming to Nob, to Ahimelech the son of Ahitub.', '1~06030~ 2~01673~ 4~0130~, 7~05324~ 10~05650~ 12~07586~, 14~0559~, 16~07200~ 18~01121~ 20~03448~ 21~0935~ 23~05011~, 25~0288~ 27~01121~ 29~0285~.'),
  (12871, 17, 9, 28, 'And that these days should be remembered and kept throughout every generation, every family, every province, and every city; and that these days of Purim should not fail from among the Jews, nor the memorial of them perish from their seed.', '[1] 3~03117~ [4 5] 6~02142~ 8~06213~ 9~01755~ 11~01755~, 13~04940~, 15~04082~, 18~05892~; [20] 22~03117~ 24~06332~ 27~05674~ 29~08432~ 31~03064~, 34~02143~ 37~05486~ 40~02233~.'),
  (15266, 19, 83, 16, 'Fill their faces with shame; that they may seek thy name, O LORD.', '0~04390~ 2~06440~ 4~07036~; 8~01245~ 10~08034~, 12~03068~.'),
  (3930, 4, 7, 75, 'One young bullock, one ram, one lamb of the first year, for a burnt offering:', '0~0259~ 1~01241~ 2~06499~, 3~0259~ 4~0352~, 5~0259~ 6~03532~ 9~01121~ 10~08141~, 14~05930~:'),
  (28657, 46, 12, 7, 'But the manifestation of the Spirit is given to every man to profit withal.', '0~1161~ 2~5321~ 5~4151~ 7~1325~ 10~1538~ 11~4314~ 13~4851~.'),
  (8580, 10, 20, 18, 'Then she spake, saying, They were wont to speak in old time, saying, They shall surely ask counsel at Abel: and so they ended the matter.', '2~0559~, 3~0559~, 6~01696~ 8~01696~ 11~07223~, 12~0559~, 15~07592~ 16~07592~ [17] 19~059~: 23~08552~ [24 25]'),
  (13718, 18, 34, 26, 'He striketh them as wicked men in the open sight of others;', '1~05606~ 3~08478~ 5~07563~ 8~04725~ 9~07200~'),
  (16487, 20, 3, 23, 'Then shalt thou walk in thy way safely, and thy foot shall not stumble.', '3~03212~ 6~01870~ 7~0983~, 10~07272~ 13~05062~.'),
  (12219, 15, 8, 9, 'Of the sons of Joab; Obadiah the son of Jehiel, and with him two hundred and eighteen males.', '2~01121~ 4~03097~; 5~05662~ 7~01121~ 9~03171~, 14~03967~ 16~06240~ 17~08083~* 18~02145~.'),
  (11936, 14, 33, 19, 'His prayer also, and how God was entreated of him, and all his sins, and his trespass, and the places wherein he built high places, and set up groves and graven images, before he was humbled: behold, they are written among the sayings of the seers.', '1~08605~ [4 5] 7~06279~ 13~02403~, 16~04604~, 19~04725~ 22~01129~ 24~01116~, 27~05975~ 28~0842~ 31~06456~, 32~06440~ 35~03665~: [38] 39~03789~ 42~01697~ 45~02374~ 46~02335~.*');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (28825, 47, 1, 9, 'But we had the sentence of death in ourselves, that we should not trust in ourselves, but in God which raiseth the dead:', '0~846~ 1~235~ 2~2192~ 4~610~ 6~2288~ 7~1722~ 8~1438~, 9~3363~ 11~3982~ 12~3363~ 13~3982~ 14~1909~ 15~5600~ 16~1438~,* 17~235~ 18~1909~ 19~2316~ 20~3588~ 21~1453~ 23~3498~:'),
  (20938, 26, 20, 34, 'And I will bring you out from the people, and will gather you out of the countries wherein ye are scattered, with a mighty hand, and with a stretched out arm, and with fury poured out.', '5~03318~ 8~05971~, 11~06908~ 16~0776~ 20~06327~, 23~02389~ 24~03027~, 29~05186~ 30~02220~, 33~02534~ 35~08210~.'),
  (2302, 2, 28, 4, 'And these are the garments which they shall make; a breastplate, and an ephod, and a robe, and a broidered coat, a mitre, and a girdle: and they shall make holy garments for Aaron thy brother, and his sons, that he may minister unto me in the priest''s office.', '[2] 4~0899~ 8~06213~; 10~02833~, 13~0646~, 16~04598~, 19~08665~ 20~03801~, 22~04701~, 25~073~: 29~06213~ 30~06944~ 31~0899~ 33~0175~ 35~0251~, 38~01121~, 48~03547~.'),
  (29513, 51, 2, 3, 'In whom are hid all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge.', '0~1722~ 1~3739~ 2~1526~ 3~614~ 4~3956~ 6~2344~ 8~4678~ 9~2532~ 10~1108~.'),
  (8529, 10, 19, 10, 'And Absalom, whom we anointed over us, is dead in battle. Now therefore why speak ye not a word of bringing the king back?', '1~053~, 4~04886~ 8~04191~ 10~04421~. 14~02790~ 20~07725~ 22~04428~ 23~07725~?'),
  (14101, 19, 15, 5, 'He that putteth not out his money to usury, nor taketh reward against the innocent. He that doeth these things shall never be moved.', '[0 1] 4~05414~ 6~03701~ 8~05392~, 10~03947~ 11~07810~ 14~05355~. 17~06213~ [19] 21~05769~ 23~04131~.'),
  (23796, 40, 19, 24, 'And again I say unto you, It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle, than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God.', '0~1161~ 1~3825~ 3~3004~ 5~5213~, 7~2076~ 8~2123~ 11~2574~ 13~1330~ 14~1223~ 16~5169~ 19~4476~, 20~2228~ 24~4145~ 26~1525~ 27~1519~ 29~932~ 31~2316~.'),
  (2802, 3, 4, 2, 'Speak unto the children of Israel, saying, If a soul shall sin through ignorance against any of the commandments of the LORD concerning things which ought not to be done, and shall do against any of them:', '0~01696~ 3~01121~ 5~03478~, 6~0559~, 9~05315~ 11~02398~ 13~07684~ 18~04687~ 21~03068~ [22 23] 29~06213~, 32~06213~ 34~0259~ 36~02007~:'),
  (25726, 42, 18, 24, 'And when Jesus saw that he was very sorrowful, he said, How hardly shall they that have riches enter into the kingdom of God!', '0~1161~ 2~2424~ 3~1492~ 5~846~ 6~1096~ 8~4036~, 10~2036~, 11~4459~ 12~1423~ 14~1525~ 16~2192~ 17~5536~ 18~1525~ 19~1519~ 21~932~ 23~2316~!'),
  (30981, 66, 16, 11, 'And blasphemed the God of heaven because of their pains and their sores, and repented not of their deeds.', '0~2532~ 1~987~ 3~2316~ 5~3772~ 7~1537~ 8~846~ 9~4192~ 10~1537~ 11~2532~* 12~846~ 13~1668~, 14~2532~ 15~3340~ 16~3756~ 17~1537~ 18~846~ 19~2041~.'),
  (20155, 24, 49, 19, 'Behold, he shall come up like a lion from the swelling of Jordan against the habitation of the strong: but I will suddenly make him run away from her: and who is a chosen man, that I may appoint over her? for who is like me? and who will appoint me the time? and who is that shepherd that will stand before me?', '4~05927~ 7~0738~ 10~01347~ 12~03383~ 15~05116~ 18~0386~: 22~07280~ 26~07323~ [31] 33~0977~ [34 35] 38~06485~ [43] 52~03259~? [55] 57~07462~ 60~05975~ 61~06440~'),
  (27780, 44, 23, 30, 'And when it was told me how that the Jews laid wait for the man, I sent straightway to thee, and gave commandment to his accusers also to say before thee what they had against him. Farewell.', '0~1161~ 4~3377~ 5~3427~ 7~5259~ 9~2453~ 11~3195~ 12~1917~* 13~1510~* 14~1519~ 16~435~, 18~3992~ 19~1824~ 20~4314~ 21~4571~, 24~3853~ 27~2725~ 28~2532~ 30~3004~ 31~1909~ 32~4675~ [34 35] 36~4314~ 37~846~. 38~4517~.'),
  (2563, 2, 35, 27, 'And the rulers brought onyx stones, and stones to be set, for the ephod, and for the breastplate;', '2~05387~ 3~0935~ 4~07718~ 5~068~, 7~068~ 10~04394~, 13~0646~, 17~02833~;'),
  (13054, 18, 8, 16, 'He is green before the sun, and his branch shooteth forth in his garden.', '[1] 2~07373~ 3~06440~ 5~08121~, 8~03127~ 10~03318~ 13~01593~.'),
  (24791, 41, 14, 26, 'And when they had sung an hymn, they went out into the mount of Olives.', '0~2532~ 6~5214~, 9~1831~ 10~1519~ 12~3735~ 14~1636~.'),
  (6367, 6, 19, 39, 'This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Naphtali according to their families, the cities and their villages.', '[1] 3~05159~ 6~04294~ 9~01121~ 11~05321~ 15~04940~, 17~05892~ 20~02691~.'),
  (706, 1, 26, 10, 'And Abimelech said, What is this thou hast done unto us? one of the people might lightly have lien with thy wife, and thou shouldest have brought guiltiness upon us.', '1~040~ 2~0559~, [4] 8~06213~ 11~0259~ 14~05971~ 16~04592~ 18~07901~ 21~0802~, 26~0935~ 27~0817~'),
  (5828, 5, 33, 12, 'And of Benjamin he said, The beloved of the LORD shall dwell in safety by him; and the LORD shall cover him all the day long, and he shall dwell between his shoulders.', '&para; [0] 2~01144~ 4~0559~, 6~03039~ 9~03068~ 11~07931~ 13~0983~ [16 18] 20~02653~ 24~03117~ 29~07931~ 32~03802~.'),
  (30353, 59, 3, 18, 'And the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace of them that make peace.', '0~1161~ 2~2590~ 4~1343~ 6~4687~ 7~1722~ 8~1515~ 12~4160~ 13~1515~.'),
  (18745, 23, 54, 13, 'And all thy children shall be taught of the LORD; and great shall be the peace of thy children.', '3~01121~ [4 5] 6~03928~ 9~03068~; 11~07227~ [12 13] 15~07965~ 18~01121~.'),
  (14899, 19, 66, 17, 'I cried unto him with my mouth, and he was extolled with my tongue.', '1~07121~ 6~06310~, 10~07311~ 11~08478~ 13~03956~.'),
  (27902, 44, 27, 31, 'Paul said to the centurion and to the soldiers, Except these abide in the ship, ye cannot be saved.', '0~3972~ 1~2036~ 4~1543~ 5~2532~ 8~4757~, 9~3362~ 10~3778~ 11~3306~ 12~1722~ 14~4143~, 15~5210~ 16~1410~ 17~3756~* 19~4982~.'),
  (25046, 42, 3, 9, 'And now also the ax is laid unto the root of the trees: every tree therefore which bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down, and cast into the fire.', '0~1161~ 1~2235~ 2~2532~ 4~513~ 6~2749~ 7~4314~ 9~4491~ 12~1186~: 13~3956~ 14~1186~ 15~3767~ 17~4160~ 18~3361~ 19~4160~ 20~2570~ 21~2590~ 24~1581~, 25~2532~ 26~906~ 27~1519~ 29~4442~.'),
  (6601, 7, 3, 26, 'And Ehud escaped while they tarried, and passed beyond the quarries, and escaped unto Seirath.', '1~0164~ 2~04422~ 5~04102~, 8~05674~ 10~06456~, 12~04422~ 14~08167~.'),
  (1576, 2, 2, 17, 'And the shepherds came and drove them away: but Moses stood up and helped them, and watered their flock.', '2~07462~ 3~0935~ 7~01644~: 9~04872~ 11~06965~ 13~03467~ 16~08248~ 18~06629~.'),
  (11382, 14, 9, 10, 'And the servants also of Huram, and the servants of Solomon, which brought gold from Ophir, brought algum trees and precious stones.', '2~05650~ 5~02361~, 8~05650~ 10~08010~, 12~0935~ 13~02091~ 15~0211~, 16~0935~ 17~0418~ 18~06086~ 20~03368~ 21~068~.'),
  (2072, 2, 20, 16, 'Thou shalt not bear false witness against thy neighbour.', '3~06030~ 4~08267~ 5~05707~ 8~07453~.'),
  (14986, 19, 71, 1, 'In thee, O LORD, do I put my trust: let me never be put to confusion.', '&para; 3~03068~, 8~02620~: 11~05769~ 12~0408~ 15~0954~.'),
  (21682, 26, 46, 18, 'Moreover the prince shall not take of the people''s inheritance by oppression, to thrust them out of their possession; but he shall give his sons inheritance out of his own possession: that my people be not scattered every man from his possession.', '2~05387~ 5~03947~ 8~05971~ 9~05159~ 11~03238~, 13~03238~ 18~0272~; [19] 24~01121~ 25~05157~ 30~0272~: 33~05971~ 36~06327~ 38~0376~ 41~0272~.'),
  (18751, 23, 55, 2, 'Wherefore do ye spend money for that which is not bread? and your labour for that which satisfieth not? hearken diligently unto me, and eat ye that which is good, and let your soul delight itself in fatness.', '3~08254~ 4~03701~ [6 8] 10~03899~? 13~03018~ [15 16] 17~07654~ 18~03808~? 19~08085~ 20~08085~ 24~0398~ [26 28] 29~02896~, 33~05315~ 34~06026~ 37~01880~.'),
  (857, 1, 30, 23, 'And she conceived, and bare a son; and said, God hath taken away my reproach:', '2~02029~, 4~03205~ 6~01121~; 8~0559~, 9~0430~ 12~0622~ 14~02781~:'),
  (26657, 43, 13, 12, 'So after he had washed their feet, and had taken his garments, and was set down again, he said unto them, Know ye what I have done to you?', '0~3767~ 1~3753~ 4~3538~ 5~846~ 6~4228~, 7~2532~ 9~2983~ 10~846~ 11~2440~, 15~377~ 16~3825~, 18~2036~ 20~846~, 22~1097~ 23~5101~ 26~4160~ 28~5213~?'),
  (21740, 26, 48, 29, 'This is the land which ye shall divide by lot unto the tribes of Israel for inheritance, and these are their portions, saith the Lord GOD.', '[1] 3~0776~ 7~05307~ 12~07626~ 14~03478~ 16~05159~, [19] 21~04256~, 22~05002~ 24~0136~ 25~03069~.'),
  (15256, 19, 83, 6, 'The tabernacles of Edom, and the Ishmaelites; of Moab, and the Hagarenes;', '1~0168~ 3~0123~, 6~03459~; 8~04124~, 11~01905~;'),
  (12771, 17, 3, 15, 'The posts went out, being hastened by the king''s commandment, and the decree was given in Shushan the palace. And the king and Haman sat down to drink; but the city Shushan was perplexed.', '1~07323~ 3~03318~, 5~01765~ 8~04428~ 9~01697~, 12~01881~ 14~05414~ 16~07800~ 18~01002~. 21~04428~ 23~02001~ 25~03427~ 27~08354~; 30~05892~ 31~07800~ 33~0943~.'),
  (28276, 45, 12, 15, 'Rejoice with them that do rejoice, and weep with them that weep.', '0~5463~ 1~3326~ 5~5463~, 6~2532~ 7~2799~ 8~3326~ 11~2799~.'),
  (23661, 40, 15, 18, 'But those things which proceed out of the mouth come forth from the heart; and they defile the man.', '0~1161~ 3~3588~ 4~1607~ 6~1537~ 8~4750~ 10~1831~ 11~1537~ 13~2588~; 15~2548~ 16~2840~ 18~444~.'),
  (16423, 20, 1, 14, 'Cast in thy lot among us; let us all have one purse:', '0~05307~ 3~01486~ 4~08432~ 10~0259~ 11~03599~:'),
  (24660, 41, 11, 9, 'And they that went before, and they that followed, cried, saying, Hosanna; Blessed is he that cometh in the name of the Lord:', '0~2532~ 4~4254~, 5~2532~ 8~190~, 9~2896~, 10~3004~, 11~5614~; 12~2127~ [13] 16~2064~ 17~1722~ 19~3686~ 22~2962~:'),
  (14200, 19, 20, 9, 'Save, LORD: let the king hear us when we call.', '0~03467~, 1~03068~: 4~04428~ 5~06030~ 7~03117~ 9~07121~.'),
  (21687, 26, 46, 23, 'And there was a row of building round about in them, round about them four, and it was made with boiling places under the rows round about.', '[1 2] 4~02905~ [5 6] 8~05439~ 12~05439~ 14~0702~, [16 17] 18~06213~ 21~04018~ 24~02918~ 26~05439~.'),
  (12477, 16, 7, 48, 'The children of Lebana, the children of Hagaba, the children of Shalmai,', '1~01121~ 3~03838~, 5~01121~ 7~02286~, 9~01121~ 11~08014~,'),
  (23577, 40, 13, 28, 'He said unto them, An enemy hath done this. The servants said unto him, Wilt thou then that we go and gather them up?', '0~1161~ 1~5346~ 3~846~, 5~444~ 6~2190~ 7~4160~ 8~5124~ 9~1161~.* 11~1401~ 12~2036~ 14~846~, 16~2309~ 17~3767~ 20~565~ 22~4816~ 23~846~ 24~4816~?'),
  (29082, 48, 1, 9, 'As we said before, so say I now again, If any man preach any other gospel unto you than that ye have received, let him be accursed.', '0~5613~ 3~4280~, 4~2532~ 6~3004~ 7~737~ 8~3825~, 10~1536~ [11] 12~2097~ 14~3844~ 15~2097~ 17~5209~ 18~3844~ 19~3739~ 22~3880~, 25~2077~ 26~331~.'),
  (9966, 12, 15, 33, 'Five and twenty years old was he when he began to reign, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. And his mother''s name was Jerusha, the daughter of Zadok.', '0~02568~ 2~06242~ 3~08141~ 4~01121~ 11~04427~, 14~04427~ 15~06240~ 16~08337~* 17~08141~ 19~03389~. 22~0517~ 23~08034~ [24] 25~03388~, 27~01323~ 29~06659~.'),
  (4841, 4, 34, 19, 'And the names of the men are these: Of the tribe of Judah, Caleb the son of Jephunneh.', '2~08034~ 5~0582~ [6] 10~04294~ 12~03063~, 13~03612~ 15~01121~ 17~03312~.'),
  (6410, 6, 21, 22, 'And Kibzaim with her suburbs, and Bethhoron with her suburbs; four cities.', '1~06911~ 4~04054~, 6~01032~ 9~04054~; 10~0702~ 11~05892~.'),
  (28512, 46, 7, 9, 'But if they cannot contain, let them marry: for it is better to marry than to burn.', '0~1161~ 1~1487~ 2~1467~ 3~3756~ 4~1467~, 7~1060~: 8~1063~ 10~2076~ 11~2909~ 13~1060~ 14~2228~ 16~4448~.'),
  (24945, 42, 1, 41, 'And it came to pass, that, when Elisabeth heard the salutation of Mary, the babe leaped in her womb; and Elisabeth was filled with the Holy Ghost:', '0~2532~ 4~1096~, 6~5613~ 7~1665~ 8~191~ 10~783~ 12~3137~, 14~1025~ 15~4640~ 16~1722~ 17~846~ 18~2836~; 19~2532~ 20~1665~ 22~4130~ 25~40~ 26~4151~:'),
  (20121, 24, 48, 32, 'O vine of Sibmah, I will weep for thee with the weeping of Jazer: thy plants are gone over the sea, they reach even to the sea of Jazer: the spoiler is fallen upon thy summer fruits and upon thy vintage.', '1~01612~ 3~07643~, 6~01058~ 11~01065~ 13~03270~: 15~05189~ 18~05674~ 20~03220~, 22~05060~ [23] 26~03220~ 28~03270~: 30~07703~ 32~05307~ 36~07019~ 40~01210~.'),
  (29085, 48, 1, 12, 'For I neither received it of man, neither was I taught it, but by the revelation of Jesus Christ.', '0~1063~ 1~1473~ 2~3761~ 3~3880~ 4~846~ 5~3844~ 6~444~, 7~3777~ 10~1321~ [11] 12~235~ 13~1223~ 15~602~ 17~2424~ 18~5547~.'),
  (13511, 18, 27, 21, 'The east wind carrieth him away, and he departeth: and as a storm hurleth him out of his place.', '1~06921~ 5~05375~, 8~03212~: 13~08175~ 18~04725~.'),
  (5282, 5, 13, 4, 'Ye shall walk after the LORD your God, and fear him, and keep his commandments, and obey his voice, and ye shall serve him, and cleave unto him.', '2~03212~ 3~0310~ 5~03068~ 7~0430~, 9~03372~ 12~08104~ 14~04687~, 16~08085~ 18~06963~, 22~05647~ 25~01692~'),
  (27195, 44, 8, 3, 'As for Saul, he made havock of the church, entering into every house, and haling men and women committed them to prison.', '0~1161~ 2~4569~, 5~3075~ 8~1577~, 10~1531~ 11~2596~ 12~3624~, 14~4951~ 15~5037~* 16~435~ 17~2532~ 18~1135~ 19~3860~ [20] 21~1519~ 22~5438~.'),
  (20147, 24, 49, 11, 'Leave thy fatherless children, I will preserve them alive; and let thy widows trust in me.', '0~05800~ 3~03490~, [7] 8~02421~; 12~0490~ 13~0982~'),
  (24896, 41, 16, 12, 'After that he appeared in another form unto two of them, as they walked, and went into the country.', '0~3326~ 1~1161~* 2~5023~ 4~5319~ 5~1722~ 6~2087~ 7~3444~ 9~1417~ 10~1537~ 11~846~, 14~4043~, 16~4198~ 17~1519~ 19~68~.'),
  (28822, 47, 1, 6, 'And whether we be afflicted, it is for your consolation and salvation, which is effectual in the enduring of the same sufferings which we also suffer: or whether we be comforted, it is for your consolation and salvation.', '0~1161~ 1~1535~ 4~2346~, [5 6] 7~5228~ 8~5216~ 9~3874~ 10~2532~ 11~4991~, 12~3588~ 14~1754~ 15~1722~ 17~5281~ 20~846~ 21~3804~ 22~3739~ 23~2249~ 24~2532~ 25~3958~: 27~1535~ 30~3870~, [31 32] 33~5228~ 34~5216~ 35~3874~ 36~2532~ 37~4991~.'),
  (7927, 9, 26, 15, 'And David said to Abner, Art not thou a valiant man? and who is like to thee in Israel? wherefore then hast thou not kept thy lord the king? for there came one of the people in to destroy the king thy lord.', '1~01732~ 2~0559~ 4~074~, [5] [9] 10~0376~? [13] 18~03478~? 24~08104~ 26~0113~ 28~04428~? 31~0935~ 32~0259~ 35~05971~ 38~07843~ 40~04428~ 42~0113~.'),
  (19310, 24, 14, 8, 'O the hope of Israel, the saviour thereof in time of trouble, why shouldest thou be as a stranger in the land, and as a wayfaring man that turneth aside to tarry for a night?', '2~04723~ 4~03478~, 6~03467~ 9~06256~ 11~06869~, 18~01616~ 21~0776~, 26~0732~ [27] 29~05186~ 34~03885~?'),
  (24365, 41, 4, 32, 'But when it is sown, it groweth up, and becometh greater than all herbs, and shooteth out great branches; so that the fowls of the air may lodge under the shadow of it.', '0~2532~ 1~3752~ 4~4687~, 7~305~, 8~2532~ 9~1096~ 11~3187~ 12~3956~ 13~3001~, 14~2532~ 16~4160~ 17~3173~ 18~2798~; 20~5620~ 22~4071~ 25~3772~ 26~1410~ 27~2681~ 28~5259~ 30~4639~ 32~846~.'),
  (28287, 45, 13, 5, 'Wherefore ye must needs be subject, not only for wrath, but also for conscience sake.', '0~1352~ [1] 3~318~ 5~5293~, 6~3756~ 7~3440~ 8~1223~ 9~3709~, 10~235~ 11~2532~ 13~4893~ 14~1223~.'),
  (24278, 41, 2, 8, 'And immediately when Jesus perceived in his spirit that they so reasoned within themselves, he said unto them, Why reason ye these things in your hearts?', '0~2532~ 1~2112~ 3~2424~ 4~1921~ 6~846~ 7~4151~ 8~3754~ 10~3779~ 11~1260~ 12~1722~ 13~1438~, 15~2036~ 17~846~, 18~5101~ 20~1260~ 22~5023~ 23~1722~ 24~5216~ 25~2588~?'),
  (24449, 41, 6, 32, 'And they departed into a desert place by ship privately.', '0~2532~ 2~565~ 3~1519~ 5~2048~ 6~5117~ 8~4143~ 9~2398~ 10~2596~.*'),
  (10403, 13, 4, 10, 'And Jabez called on the God of Israel, saying, Oh that thou wouldest bless me indeed, and enlarge my coast, and that thine hand might be with me, and that thou wouldest keep me from evil, that it may not grieve me! And God granted him that which he requested.', '1~03258~ 2~07121~ 5~0430~ 7~03478~, 8~0559~, 10~0518~ 13~01288~ 15~01288~, 17~07235~ 19~01366~, 23~03027~ 32~06213~ [33] 35~07451~, 40~06087~ 43~0430~ 44~0935~ 49~07592~.'),
  (4037, 4, 11, 8, 'And the people went about, and gathered it, and ground it in mills, or beat it in a mortar, and baked it in pans, and made cakes of it: and the taste of it was as the taste of fresh oil.', '[0] 2~05971~ 4~07751~, 6~03950~ [7] 9~02912~ [10] 12~07347~, 14~01743~ [15] 18~04085~, 20~01310~ [21] 23~06517~, 25~06213~ 26~05692~ 31~02940~ 37~02940~ 39~03955~ 40~08081~.'),
  (17781, 23, 6, 3, 'And one cried unto another, and said, Holy, holy, holy, is the LORD of hosts: the whole earth is full of his glory.', '2~07121~ 6~0559~, 7~06918~, 8~06918~, 9~06918~, [10] 12~03068~ 14~06635~: 17~0776~ [18] 19~04393~ 22~03519~.'),
  (14493, 19, 37, 34, 'Wait on the LORD, and keep his way, and he shall exalt thee to inherit the land: when the wicked are cut off, thou shalt see it.', '&para; 0~06960~ 3~03068~, 5~08104~ 7~01870~, 11~07311~ 14~03423~ 16~0776~: 19~07563~ 22~03772~, 25~07200~ [26]'),
  (11514, 14, 15, 15, 'And all Judah rejoiced at the oath: for they had sworn with all their heart, and sought him with their whole desire; and he was found of them: and the LORD gave them rest round about.', '2~03063~ 3~08055~ 6~07621~: 10~07650~ 14~03824~, 16~01245~ 21~07522~; 25~04672~ 30~03068~ 33~05117~ 35~05439~.'),
  (19258, 24, 11, 23, 'And there shall be no remnant of them: for I will bring evil upon the men of Anathoth, even the year of their visitation.', '5~07611~ 11~0935~ 12~07451~ 15~0582~ 17~06068~, [18] 20~08141~ 23~06486~.'),
  (26101, 43, 1, 42, 'And he brought him to Jesus. And when Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone.', '0~2532~ 2~71~ 3~846~ 4~4314~ 5~2424~. 6~1161~ 8~2424~ 9~1689~ 10~846~, 12~2036~, 13~4771~ 14~1488~ 15~4613~ 17~5207~ 19~2495~: 20~4771~ 23~2564~ 24~2786~, 25~3739~ 28~2059~, 30~4074~.'),
  (4971, 5, 2, 27, 'Let me pass through thy land: I will go along by the high way, I will neither turn unto the right hand nor to the left.', '2~05674~ 5~0776~: 8~03212~ 13~01870~ 14~01870~,* 18~05493~ 22~03225~ 26~08040~.'),
  (16192, 19, 135, 8, 'Who smote the firstborn of Egypt, both of man and beast.', '1~05221~ 3~01060~ 5~04714~, 8~0120~ 10~0929~.'),
  (6224, 6, 15, 15, 'And he went up thence to the inhabitants of Debir: and the name of Debir before was Kirjathsepher.', '3~05927~ 7~03427~ 9~01688~: 12~08034~ 14~01688~ 15~06440~ [16] 17~07158~.'),
  (12521, 16, 9, 1, 'Now in the twenty and fourth day of this month the children of Israel were assembled with fasting, and with sackclothes, and earth upon them.', '&para; 3~06242~ 5~0702~ 6~03117~ 9~02320~ 11~01121~ 13~03478~ 15~0622~ 17~06685~, 20~08242~, 22~0127~'),
  (26647, 43, 13, 2, 'And supper being ended, the devil having now put into the heart of Judas Iscariot, Simon''s son, to betray him;', '0~2532~ 1~1173~ 3~1096~, 5~1228~ 7~2235~ 8~906~ 9~1519~ 11~2588~ 13~2455~ 14~2469~, 15~4613~ [16] 17~2443~ 18~3860~ 19~846~;'),
  (18741, 23, 54, 9, 'For this is as the waters of Noah unto me: for as I have sworn that the waters of Noah should no more go over the earth; so have I sworn that I would not be wroth with thee, nor rebuke thee.', '[2 3] 5~04325~ 7~05146~ [11] 14~07650~ 17~04325~ 19~05146~ 24~05674~ 26~0776~; 30~07650~ 36~07107~ 40~01605~'),
  (10495, 13, 6, 33, 'And these are they that waited with their children. Of the sons of the Kohathites: Heman a singer, the son of Joel, the son of Shemuel,', '[2] 5~05975~ 8~01121~. 11~01121~ 14~06956~: 15~01968~ 17~07891~, 19~01121~ 21~03100~, 23~01121~ 25~08050~,'),
  (15116, 19, 77, 14, 'Thou art the God that doest wonders: thou hast declared thy strength among the people.', '[1] 3~0410~ 5~06213~ 6~06382~: 9~03045~ 11~05797~ 14~05971~.'),
  (26840, 43, 18, 40, 'Then cried they all again, saying, Not this man, but Barabbas. Now Barabbas was a robber.', '0~3767~ 2~2905~ 3~3956~ 4~3825~, 5~3004~, 6~3361~ 8~5126~, 9~235~ 10~912~. 11~1161~ 12~912~ 13~2258~ 15~3027~.'),
  (5293, 5, 13, 15, 'Thou shalt surely smite the inhabitants of that city with the edge of the sword, destroying it utterly, and all that is therein, and the cattle thereof, with the edge of the sword.', '2~05221~ 3~05221~ 5~03427~ 8~05892~ 11~06310~ 14~02719~, 17~02763~, [21] 25~0929~ 29~06310~ 32~02719~.'),
  (19205, 24, 9, 21, 'For death is come up into our windows, and is entered into our palaces, to cut off the children from without, and the young men from the streets.', '1~04194~ 4~05927~ 7~02474~, [8] 10~0935~ 13~0759~, 16~03772~ 18~05768~ 20~02351~, [21] 24~0970~ 27~07339~.'),
  (16718, 20, 11, 21, 'Though hand join in hand, the wicked shall not be unpunished: but the seed of the righteous shall be delivered.', '&para; [0] 1~03027~ [2] 4~03027~, 6~07451~ 10~05352~: 13~02233~ 16~06662~ 19~04422~.'),
  (1706, 2, 7, 16, 'And thou shalt say unto him, The LORD God of the Hebrews hath sent me unto thee, saying, Let my people go, that they may serve me in the wilderness: and, behold, hitherto thou wouldest not hear.', '3~0559~ 7~03068~ 8~0430~ 11~05680~ 13~07971~ 17~0559~, 20~05971~ 21~07971~, 25~05647~ 29~04057~: 32~03541~ 36~08085~.'),
  (11038, 13, 24, 15, 'The seventeenth to Hezir, the eighteenth to Aphses,', '1~06240~ 2~07651~ 3~02387~, 5~06240~ 6~08083~ 7~06483~,'),
  (30550, 61, 3, 12, 'Looking for and hasting unto the coming of the day of God, wherein the heavens being on fire shall be dissolved, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat?', '1~4328~ 2~2532~ 3~4692~ 6~3952~ 9~2250~ 11~2316~, 12~3739~ 13~1223~ 14~3772~ 17~4448~ 20~3089~, 21~2532~ 23~4747~ 25~5080~ 28~2741~?'),
  (12824, 17, 7, 8, 'Then the king returned out of the palace garden into the place of the banquet of wine; and Haman was fallen upon the bed whereon Esther was. Then said the king, Will he force the queen also before me in the house? As the word went out of the king''s mouth, they covered Haman''s face.', '2~04428~ 3~07725~ 7~01055~ 8~01594~ 11~01004~ 14~04960~ 16~03196~; 18~02001~ 20~05307~ 23~04296~ 25~0635~ [26] 28~0559~ 30~04428~, 33~03533~ 35~04436~ 41~01004~? 44~01697~ 46~03318~ 49~04428~ 50~06310~, 52~02645~ 53~02001~ 54~06440~.'),
  (30242, 58, 12, 14, 'Follow peace with all men, and holiness, without which no man shall see the Lord:', '0~1377~ 1~1515~ 2~3326~ 3~3956~ [4] 5~2532~ 6~38~, 7~5565~ 8~3739~ 10~3762~ 12~3700~ 14~2962~:'),
  (9768, 12, 9, 4, 'So the young man, even the young man the prophet, went to Ramothgilead.', '3~05288~, [4] 7~05288~ 9~05030~, 10~03212~ 12~01568~ 13~07433~.*'),
  (9037, 11, 8, 44, 'If thy people go out to battle against their enemy, whithersoever thou shalt send them, and shall pray unto the LORD toward the city which thou hast chosen, and toward the house that I have built for thy name:', '2~05971~ 4~03318~ 6~04421~ 9~0341~, 10~01870~ 13~07971~ 17~06419~ 20~03068~ 21~01870~ 23~05892~ 27~0977~, [29] 31~01004~ 35~01129~ 38~08034~:'),
  (18535, 23, 43, 21, 'This people have I formed for myself; they shall shew forth my praise.', '0~02098~ 1~05971~ 4~03335~ 10~05608~ 12~08416~.'),
  (15202, 19, 79, 8, 'O remember not against us former iniquities: let thy tender mercies speedily prevent us: for we are brought very low.', '1~02142~ 5~07223~ 6~05771~: 10~07356~ 11~04118~ 12~06923~ 17~01809~ 18~03966~ 19~01809~.'),
  (24059, 40, 25, 41, 'Then shall he say also unto them on the left hand, Depart from me, ye cursed, into everlasting fire, prepared for the devil and his angels:', '0~5119~ 3~2046~ 4~2532~ 7~1537~ 10~2176~, 11~4198~ 12~575~ 13~1700~, 15~2672~, 16~1519~ 17~166~ 18~4442~, 19~2090~ 22~1228~ 23~2532~ 24~846~ 25~32~:'),
  (19182, 24, 8, 20, 'The harvest is past, the summer is ended, and we are not saved.', '1~07105~ 3~05674~, 5~07019~ 7~03615~, 12~03467~.'),
  (29415, 50, 2, 8, 'And being found in fashion as a man, he humbled himself, and became obedient unto death, even the death of the cross.', '0~2532~ 2~2147~ 4~4976~ 5~5613~ 7~444~, 9~5013~ 10~1438~, 12~1096~ 13~5255~ 14~3360~ 15~2288~, 16~1161~ 18~2288~ 21~4716~.'),
  (10387, 13, 3, 18, 'Malchiram also, and Pedaiah, and Shenazar, Jecamiah, Hoshama, and Nedabiah.', '0~04443~ 3~06305~, 5~08137~, 6~03359~, 7~01953~, 9~05072~.'),
  (523, 1, 21, 6, 'And Sarah said, God hath made me to laugh, so that all that hear will laugh with me.', '1~08283~ 2~0559~, 3~0430~ 5~06213~ 8~06712~, [9 10] 13~08085~ 15~06711~'),
  (1002, 1, 34, 17, 'But if ye will not hearken unto us, to be circumcised; then will we take our daughter, and we will be gone.', '5~08085~ 10~04135~; 14~03947~ 16~01323~, 21~01980~.'),
  (12888, 18, 1, 10, 'Hast not thou made an hedge about him, and about his house, and about all that he hath on every side? thou hast blessed the work of his hands, and his substance is increased in the land.', '5~07753~ 9~01157~ 11~01004~, 20~05439~? 23~01288~ 25~04639~ 28~03027~, 31~04735~ 33~06555~ 36~0776~.'),
  (5606, 5, 27, 15, 'Cursed be the man that maketh any graven or molten image, an abomination unto the LORD, the work of the hands of the craftsman, and putteth it in a secret place. And all the people shall answer and say, Amen.', '0~0779~ [1] 3~0376~ 5~06213~ [6] 7~06459~ 10~04541~, 12~08441~ 15~03068~, 17~04639~ 20~03027~ 23~02796~, 25~07760~ [26] [28] 29~05643~ [30] 34~05971~ 36~06030~ 38~0559~, 39~0543~.'),
  (302, 1, 12, 1, 'Now the LORD had said unto Abram, Get thee out of thy country, and from thy kindred, and from thy father''s house, unto a land that I will shew thee:', '&para; 2~03068~ 4~0559~ 6~087~, 9~03212~ 12~0776~, 16~04138~, 20~01~ 21~01004~, 24~0776~ 28~07200~');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (27267, 44, 9, 35, 'And all that dwelt at Lydda and Saron saw him, and turned to the Lord.', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 3~2730~ 5~3069~ 6~2532~ 7~4565~ 8~1492~ 9~846~, 10~3748~ 11~1994~ 12~1909~ 14~2962~.'),
  (27020, 44, 3, 8, 'And he leaping up stood, and walked, and entered with them into the temple, walking, and leaping, and praising God.', '0~2532~ 3~1814~ 4~2476~, 5~2532~ 6~4043~, 7~2532~ 8~1525~ 9~4862~ 10~846~ 11~1519~ 13~2411~, 14~4043~, 15~2532~ 16~242~, 17~2532~ 18~134~ 19~2316~.'),
  (11570, 14, 18, 19, 'And the LORD said, Who shall entice Ahab king of Israel, that he may go up and fall at Ramothgilead? And one spake saying after this manner, and another saying after that manner.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~, 6~06601~ 7~0256~ 8~04428~ 10~03478~, 15~05927~ 17~05307~ 19~01568~ 20~07433?~* 23~0559~ 24~0559~ 27~03602~, 30~0559~ 33~03602~.'),
  (28478, 46, 5, 8, 'Therefore let us keep the feast, not with old leaven, neither with the leaven of malice and wickedness; but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.', '0~5620~ 5~1858~, 6~3361~ 7~1722~ 8~3820~ 9~2219~, 10~3366~ 11~1722~ 13~2219~ 15~2549~ 16~2532~ 17~4189~; 18~235~ 19~1722~ 21~106~ [22] 24~1505~ 25~2532~ 26~225~.'),
  (28673, 46, 12, 23, 'And those members of the body, which we think to be less honourable, upon these we bestow more abundant honour; and our uncomely parts have more abundant comeliness.', '0~2532~ 1~3739~ [2] 5~4983~, 8~1380~ 10~1511~ 12~820~, 14~5125~ 16~4060~ 18~4055~ 19~5092~; 20~2532~ 21~2257~ 22~809~ [23] 24~2192~ 26~4055~ 27~2157~.'),
  (7345, 9, 6, 7, 'Now therefore make a new cart, and take two milch kine, on which there hath come no yoke, and tie the kine to the cart, and bring their calves home from them:', '2~06213~ 3~0259~ 4~02319~ 5~05699~, 7~03947~ 8~08147~ 9~05763~ 10~06510~, 15~05927~ 17~05923~, 19~0631~ 21~06510~ 24~05699~, 26~07725~ 28~01121~ 29~01004~ 31~0310~:'),
  (25309, 42, 8, 52, 'And all wept, and bewailed her: but he said, Weep not; she is not dead, but sleepeth.', '0~1161~ 1~3956~ 2~2799~, 3~2532~ 4~2875~ 5~846~: 6~1161~ 8~2036~, 9~2799~ 10~3361~; 12~599~ 13~3756~ 14~599~, 15~235~ 16~2518~.'),
  (1688, 2, 6, 28, 'And it came to pass on the day when the LORD spake unto Moses in the land of Egypt,', '7~03117~ [8] 10~03068~ 11~01696~ 13~04872~ 16~0776~ 18~04714~,'),
  (6607, 7, 4, 1, 'And the children of Israel again did evil in the sight of the LORD, when Ehud was dead.', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~03254~ 6~06213~ 7~07451~ 10~05869~ 13~03068~, 15~0164~ 17~04191~.'),
  (22959, 38, 6, 3, 'And in the third chariot white horses; and in the fourth chariot grisled and bay horses.', '3~07992~ 4~04818~ 5~03836~ 6~05483~; 10~07243~ 11~04818~ 12~01261~ 14~0554~ 15~05483~.'),
  (13331, 18, 19, 25, 'For I know that my redeemer liveth, and that he shall stand at the latter day upon the earth:', '2~03045~ [3] 5~01350~ 6~02416~, [8] 11~06965~ 14~0314~ [15] 18~06083~:'),
  (23954, 40, 23, 26, 'Thou blind Pharisee, cleanse first that which is within the cup and platter, that the outside of them may be clean also.', '[0] 1~5185~ 2~5330~, 3~2511~ 4~4412~ [6 7] 8~1787~ 10~4221~ 11~2532~ 12~3953~, 13~2443~ 15~1622~ 17~846~ 19~1096~ 20~2513~ 21~2532~.'),
  (18577, 23, 45, 7, 'I form the light, and create darkness: I make peace, and create evil: I the LORD do all these things.', '1~03335~ 3~0216~, 5~01254~ 6~02822~: 8~06213~ 9~07965~, 11~01254~ 12~07451~: 15~03068~ 16~06213~ [19]'),
  (20458, 25, 5, 7, 'Our fathers have sinned, and are not; and we have borne their iniquities.', '1~01~ 3~02398~, [4 5] 6~0369~; 10~05445~ 12~05771~.'),
  (11815, 14, 29, 15, 'And they gathered their brethren, and sanctified themselves, and came, according to the commandment of the king, by the words of the LORD, to cleanse the house of the LORD.', '2~0622~ 4~0251~, 6~06942~ 9~0935~, 13~04687~ 16~04428~, 19~01697~ 22~03068~, 24~02891~ 26~01004~ 29~03068~.'),
  (6354, 6, 19, 26, 'And Alammelech, and Amad, and Misheal; and reacheth to Carmel westward, and to Shihorlibnath;', '1~0487~, 3~06008~, 5~04861~; 7~06293~ 9~03760~ 10~03220~, 13~07884~;'),
  (2332, 2, 28, 34, 'A golden bell and a pomegranate, a golden bell and a pomegranate, upon the hem of the robe round about.', '1~02091~ 2~06472~ 5~07416~, 7~02091~ 8~06472~ 11~07416~, 14~07757~ 17~04598~ 19~05439~.'),
  (11931, 14, 33, 14, 'Now after this he built a wall without the city of David, on the west side of Gihon, in the valley, even to the entering in at the fish gate, and compassed about Ophel, and raised it up a very great height, and put captains of war in all the fenced cities of Judah.', '2~0310~ 4~01129~ 6~02346~ 7~02435~ 9~05892~ 11~01732~, 15~04628~ 17~01521~, 20~05158~, 25~0935~ 28~01709~ 29~08179~, 31~05437~ 33~06077~, 37~01361~ 41~03966~, 43~07760~ 44~08269~ 46~02428~ 50~01219~ 51~05892~ 53~03063~.'),
  (28820, 47, 1, 4, 'Who comforteth us in all our tribulation, that we may be able to comfort them which are in any trouble, by the comfort wherewith we ourselves are comforted of God.', '0~3588~ 1~3870~ 2~2248~ 3~1909~ 4~3956~ 5~2257~ 6~2347~, 7~1519~ 8~2248~ 11~1410~ 13~3870~ 17~1722~ 18~3956~ 19~2347~, 20~1223~ 22~3874~ 23~3739~ 24~3870~ 25~846~ 27~3870~ 28~5259~ 29~2316~.'),
  (19463, 24, 21, 14, 'But I will punish you according to the fruit of your doings, saith the LORD: and I will kindle a fire in the forest thereof, and it shall devour all things round about it.', '3~06485~ 8~06529~ 11~04611~, 12~05002~ 14~03068~: 18~03341~ 20~0784~ 23~03293~ 28~0398~ 32~05439~'),
  (9432, 11, 20, 16, 'And they went out at noon. But Benhadad was drinking himself drunk in the pavilions, he and the kings, the thirty and two kings that helped him.', '3~03318~ 5~06672~. 7~01130~ [8] 9~08354~ 11~07910~ 14~05521~, 18~04428~, 20~07970~ 22~08147~ 23~04428~ 25~05826~'),
  (26639, 43, 12, 44, 'Jesus cried and said, He that believeth on me, believeth not on me, but on him that sent me.', '&para; 0~1161~ 1~2424~ 2~2896~ 3~2532~ 4~2036~, 7~4100~ 8~1519~ 9~1691~, 10~4100~ 11~3756~ 12~1519~ 13~1691~, 14~235~ 15~1519~ 18~3992~ 19~3165~.'),
  (7160, 8, 2, 4, 'And, behold, Boaz came from Bethlehem, and said unto the reapers, The LORD be with you. And they answered him, The LORD bless thee.', '&para; 2~01162~ 3~0935~ 5~01035~, 7~0559~ 10~07114~, 12~03068~ [13] 18~0559~ 21~03068~ 22~01288~'),
  (8579, 10, 20, 17, 'And when he was come near unto her, the woman said, Art thou Joab? And he answered, I am he. Then she said unto him, Hear the words of thine handmaid. And he answered, I do hear.', '5~07126~ 9~0802~ 10~0559~, [11] 13~03097~? 16~0559~, [18 19] 22~0559~ 25~08085~ 27~01697~ 30~0519~. 33~0559~, 36~08085~.'),
  (14096, 19, 14, 7, 'Oh that the salvation of Israel were come out of Zion! when the LORD bringeth back the captivity of his people, Jacob shall rejoice, and Israel shall be glad.', '1~05414~ 3~03444~ 5~03478~ [6 7] 10~06726~! 13~03068~ 15~07725~ 17~07622~ 20~05971~, 21~03290~ 23~01523~, [24] 25~03478~ 28~08055~.'),
  (29, 1, 1, 29, 'And God said, Behold, I have given you every herb bearing seed, which is upon the face of all the earth, and every tree, in the which is the fruit of a tree yielding seed; to you it shall be for meat.', '&para; 1~0430~ 2~0559~, 3~02009~, 6~05414~ 9~06212~ 10~02232~ 11~02233~, [13] 16~06440~ 20~0776~, 23~06086~, [27] 29~06529~ 32~06086~ 33~02232~ 34~02233~; 39~01961~ 41~0402~.'),
  (5315, 5, 14, 19, 'And every creeping thing that flieth is unclean unto you: they shall not be eaten.', '3~08318~ 5~05775~ [6] 7~02931~ 14~0398~.'),
  (10314, 13, 1, 54, 'Duke Magdiel, duke Iram. These are the dukes of Edom.', '0~0441~ 1~04025~, 2~0441~ 3~05902~. [5] 7~0441~ 9~0123~.'),
  (25922, 42, 22, 44, 'And being in an agony he prayed more earnestly: and his sweat was as it were great drops of blood falling down to the ground.', '0~2532~ 1~1096~ 2~1722~ 4~74~ 6~4336~ 8~1617~: 9~1161~ 10~846~ 11~2402~ 12~1096~ 15~5616~ 17~2361~ 19~129~ 21~2597~ 22~1909~ 24~1093~.'),
  (4468, 4, 24, 17, 'I shall see him, but not now: I shall behold him, but not nigh: there shall come a Star out of Jacob, and a Sceptre shall rise out of Israel, and shall smite the corners of Moab, and destroy all the children of Sheth.', '2~07200~ 9~07789~ 13~07138~: 16~01869~ 18~03556~ 21~03290~, 24~07626~ 26~06965~ 29~03478~, 32~04272~ 34~06285~ 36~04124~, 38~06979~ 41~01121~ 43~08352~ 44~08351~.*'),
  (22637, 33, 4, 8, 'And thou, O tower of the flock, the strong hold of the daughter of Zion, unto thee shall it come, even the first dominion; the kingdom shall come to the daughter of Jerusalem.', '&para; 3~04026~ 6~05739~ 7~04029~,* 10~06076~ 13~01323~ 15~06726~, 20~0857~, 23~07223~ 24~04475~; 26~04467~ 28~0935~ 31~01323~ 33~03389~.'),
  (16615, 20, 8, 4, 'Unto you, O men, I call; and my voice is to the sons of man.', '3~0376~, 5~07121~; 8~06963~ [9] 12~01121~ 14~0120~.'),
  (30978, 66, 16, 8, 'And the fourth angel poured out his vial upon the sun; and power was given unto him to scorch men with fire.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~5067~ 3~32~ 5~1632~ 6~846~ 7~5357~ 8~1909~ 10~2246~; 11~2532~ 14~1325~ 16~846~ 18~2739~ 19~444~ 20~1722~ 21~4442~.'),
  (26046, 42, 24, 41, 'And while they yet believed not for joy, and wondered, he said unto them, Have ye here any meat?', '0~1161~ 2~846~ 3~2089~ 5~569~ 6~575~ 7~5479~, 8~2532~ 9~2296~, 11~2036~ 13~846~, 15~2192~ 16~1759~ 17~5100~ 18~1034~?'),
  (24423, 41, 6, 6, 'And he marvelled because of their unbelief. And he went round about the villages, teaching.', '0~2532~ 2~2296~ 3~1223~ 5~846~ 6~570~. 7~2532~ 9~4013~ 11~2945~ 13~2968~, 14~1321~.'),
  (1131, 1, 38, 7, 'And Er, Judah''s firstborn, was wicked in the sight of the LORD; and the LORD slew him.', '1~06147~, 2~03063~ 3~01060~, 5~07451~ 8~05869~ 11~03068~; 14~03068~ 15~04191~'),
  (7029, 7, 18, 29, 'And they called the name of the city Dan, after the name of Dan their father, who was born unto Israel: howbeit the name of the city was Laish at the first.', '2~07121~ 4~08034~ 7~05892~ 8~01835~, 11~08034~ 13~01835~ 15~01~, 18~03205~ 20~03478~: 21~0199~ 23~08034~ 26~05892~ [27] 28~03919~ 31~07223~.'),
  (16773, 20, 13, 17, 'A wicked messenger falleth into mischief: but a faithful ambassador is health.', '&para; 1~07563~ 2~04397~ 3~05307~ 5~07451~: 8~0529~ 9~06735~ [10] 11~04832~.'),
  (29791, 54, 5, 12, 'Having damnation, because they have cast off their first faith.', '0~2192~ 1~2917~, 2~3754~ 6~114~ 8~4413~ 9~4102~.'),
  (17631, 22, 6, 8, 'There are threescore queens, and fourscore concubines, and virgins without number.', '2~08346~ 3~04436~, 5~08084~ 6~06370~, 8~05959~ 10~04557~.'),
  (24567, 41, 9, 18, 'And wheresoever he taketh him, he teareth him: and he foameth, and gnasheth with his teeth, and pineth away: and I spake to thy disciples that they should cast him out; and they could not.', '0~2532~ 1~302~ 2~3699~ 3~2638~ 4~846~, 6~4486~ 7~846~: 8~2532~ 10~875~, 11~2532~ 12~5149~ 14~846~ 15~3599~, 16~2532~ 18~3583~: 19~2532~ 21~2036~ 23~4675~ 24~3101~ 25~2443~ 28~1544~ 29~846~ 30~1544~; 31~2532~ 33~2480~ 34~3756~.'),
  (28034, 45, 3, 27, 'Where is boasting then? It is excluded. By what law? of works? Nay: but by the law of faith.', '0~4226~ [1] 2~2746~ 3~3767~? 6~1576~. 7~1223~ 8~4169~ 9~3551~? 11~2041~? 12~3780~: 13~235~ 14~1223~ 16~3551~ 18~4102~.'),
  (18071, 23, 22, 10, 'And ye have numbered the houses of Jerusalem, and the houses have ye broken down to fortify the wall.', '3~05608~ 5~01004~ 7~03389~, 10~01004~ 14~05422~ 16~01219~ 18~02346~.'),
  (30982, 66, 16, 12, 'And the sixth angel poured out his vial upon the great river Euphrates; and the water thereof was dried up, that the way of the kings of the east might be prepared.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~1623~ 3~32~ 5~1632~ 6~846~ 7~5357~ 8~1909~ 10~3173~ 11~4215~ 12~2166~; 13~2532~ 15~5204~ 16~846~ 19~3583~, 20~2443~ 22~3598~ 25~935~ 26~575~ 28~2246~ 29~395~ 31~2090~.'),
  (24052, 40, 25, 34, 'Then shall the King say unto them on his right hand, Come, ye blessed of my Father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world:', '0~5119~ 3~935~ 4~2046~ 7~1537~ 8~846~ 10~1188~, 11~1205~, 13~2127~ 15~3450~ 16~3962~, 17~2816~ 19~932~ 20~2090~ 22~5213~ 23~575~ 25~2602~ 28~2889~:'),
  (28203, 45, 9, 32, 'Wherefore? Because they sought it not by faith, but as it were by the works of the law. For they stumbled at that stumblingstone;', '0~1302~? 1~3754~ [2 4] 5~3756~ 6~1537~ 7~4102~, 8~235~ 9~5613~ 12~1537~ 14~2041~ 17~3551~. 18~1063~ 20~4350~ 23~4348~ 24~3037~;*'),
  (9980, 12, 16, 9, 'And the king of Assyria hearkened unto him: for the king of Assyria went up against Damascus, and took it, and carried the people of it captive to Kir, and slew Rezin.', '2~04428~ 4~0804~ 5~08085~ 10~04428~ 12~0804~ 14~05927~ 16~01834~, 18~08610~ [22 24] 26~01540~ 28~07024~, 30~04191~ 31~07526~.'),
  (17603, 22, 4, 12, 'A garden enclosed is my sister, my spouse; a spring shut up, a fountain sealed.', '1~01588~ 2~05274~ [3] 5~0269~, [6] 7~03618~; 9~01530~ 11~05274~, 13~04599~ 14~02856~.'),
  (1607, 2, 4, 1, 'And Moses answered and said, But, behold, they will not believe me, nor hearken unto my voice: for they will say, The LORD hath not appeared unto thee.', '&para; 1~04872~ 2~06030~ 4~0559~, 10~0539~ 13~08085~ 16~06963~: 20~0559~, 22~03068~ 25~07200~'),
  (25644, 42, 16, 11, 'If therefore ye have not been faithful in the unrighteous mammon, who will commit to your trust the true riches?', '0~1487~ 1~3767~ 3~1096~ 4~3756~ 5~1096~ 6~4103~ 7~1722~ 9~94~ 10~3126~, 11~5101~ 13~4100~ 15~5213~ 16~4100~ 18~228~ [19]'),
  (29127, 48, 3, 9, 'So then they which be of faith are blessed with faithful Abraham.', '1~5620~ 5~1537~ 6~4102~ 8~2127~ 9~4862~ 10~4103~ 11~11~.'),
  (13992, 19, 5, 10, 'Destroy thou them, O God; let them fall by their own counsels; cast them out in the multitude of their transgressions; for they have rebelled against thee.', '0~0816~ 4~0430~; 7~05307~ 11~04156~; 14~05080~ 17~07230~ 20~06588~; 24~04784~'),
  (21909, 27, 5, 26, 'This is the interpretation of the thing: MENE; God hath numbered thy kingdom, and finished it.', '0~01836~ [1] 3~06591~ 6~04406~: 7~04484~; 8~0426~ 10~04483~ 12~04437~, 14~08000~'),
  (11213, 14, 1, 11, 'And God said to Solomon, Because this was in thine heart, and thou hast not asked riches, wealth, or honour, nor the life of thine enemies, neither yet hast asked long life; but hast asked wisdom and knowledge for thyself, that thou mayest judge my people, over whom I have made thee king:', '1~0430~ 2~0559~ 4~08010~, 10~03824~, 15~07592~ 16~06239~, 17~05233~, 19~03519~, 22~05315~ 25~08130~, 29~07592~ 30~07227~ 31~03117~; 34~07592~ 35~02451~ 37~04093~ 43~08199~ 45~05971~, 52~04427~:'),
  (10499, 13, 6, 37, 'The son of Tahath, the son of Assir, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah,', '1~01121~ 3~08480~, 5~01121~ 7~0617~, 9~01121~ 11~043~, 13~01121~ 15~07141~,'),
  (24852, 41, 15, 15, 'And so Pilate, willing to content the people, released Barabbas unto them, and delivered Jesus, when he had scourged him, to be crucified.', '&para; 0~1161~ [1] 2~4091~, 3~1014~ 5~4160~ 6~2425~* 8~3793~, 9~630~ 10~912~ 12~846~, 13~2532~ 14~3860~ 15~2424~, 19~5417~ [20] 21~2443~ 23~4717~.'),
  (12674, 16, 12, 41, 'And the priests; Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Michaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah, and Hananiah, with trumpets;', '2~03548~; 3~0471~, 4~04641~, 5~04509~, 6~04320~, 7~0454~, 8~02148~, [9] 10~02608~, 12~02689~;'),
  (22870, 37, 2, 6, 'For thus saith the LORD of hosts; Yet once, it is a little while, and I will shake the heavens, and the earth, and the sea, and the dry land;', '2~0559~ 4~03068~ 6~06635~; 8~0259~, [10] 13~04592~, 17~07493~ 19~08064~, 22~0776~, 25~03220~, 28~02724~ [29]'),
  (23511, 40, 12, 12, 'How much then is a man better than a sheep? Wherefore it is lawful to do well on the sabbath days.', '1~4214~ 2~3767~ 5~444~ 7~1308~ 9~4263~? 10~5620~ 13~1832~ 15~4160~ 16~2573~ 20~4521~.'),
  (30786, 66, 4, 2, 'And immediately I was in the spirit; and, behold, a throne was set in heaven, and one sat on the throne.', '0~2532~ 1~2112~ 3~1096~ 4~1722~ 6~4151~: 7~2532~, 8~2400~, 10~2362~ 12~2749~ 13~1722~ 14~3772~, 15~2532~ [16] 17~2521~ 18~1909~ 20~2362~.'),
  (30553, 61, 3, 15, 'And account that the longsuffering of our Lord is salvation; even as our beloved brother Paul also according to the wisdom given unto him hath written unto you;', '0~2532~ 1~2233~ [2] 4~3115~ 6~2257~ 7~2962~ [8] 9~4991~; 11~2531~ 12~2257~ 13~27~ 14~80~ 15~3972~ 16~2532~ 18~2596~ 20~4678~ 21~1325~ 23~846~ 25~1125~ 27~5213~;'),
  (23947, 40, 23, 19, 'Ye fools and blind: for whether is greater, the gift, or the altar that sanctifieth the gift?', '[0] 1~3474~ 2~2532~ 3~5185~: 4~1063~ 5~5101~ [6] 7~3187~, 9~1435~, 10~2228~ 12~2379~ 14~37~ 16~1435~?'),
  (3702, 4, 3, 5, 'And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,', '2~03068~ 3~01696~ 5~04872~, 6~0559~,'),
  (18506, 23, 42, 17, 'They shall be turned back, they shall be greatly ashamed, that trust in graven images, that say to the molten images, Ye are our gods.', '3~05472~ 4~0268~, 8~01322~ 9~0954~, 11~0982~ 14~06459~, 16~0559~ 20~04541~, [22] 24~0430~.'),
  (8120, 10, 3, 32, 'And they buried Abner in Hebron: and the king lifted up his voice, and wept at the grave of Abner; and all the people wept.', '2~06912~ 3~074~ 5~02275~: 8~04428~ 10~05375~ 12~06963~, 14~01058~ 17~06913~ 19~074~; 23~05971~ 24~01058~.'),
  (20741, 26, 14, 1, 'Then came certain of the elders of Israel unto me, and sat before me.', '&para; 1~0935~ 2~0582~ 5~02205~ 7~03478~ 11~03427~ 12~06440~'),
  (2782, 3, 2, 15, 'And thou shalt put oil upon it, and lay frankincense thereon: it is a meat offering.', '3~05414~ 4~08081~ 8~07760~ 9~03828~ [12] 15~04503~.'),
  (28214, 45, 10, 10, 'For with the heart man believeth unto righteousness; and with the mouth confession is made unto salvation.', '0~1063~ 3~2588~ 5~4100~ 6~1519~ 7~1343~; 8~1161~ 11~4750~ 14~3670~ 15~1519~ 16~4991~.'),
  (18416, 23, 38, 17, 'Behold, for peace I had great bitterness: but thou hast in love to my soul delivered it from the pit of corruption: for thou hast cast all my sins behind thy back.', '2~07965~ 6~04843~ 7~04751~:* 12~02836~ 15~05315~ [16 17] 20~07845~ 22~01097~: 26~07993~ 29~02399~ 30~0310~ 32~01460~.'),
  (10848, 13, 16, 20, 'And when they went from nation to nation, and from one kingdom to another people;', '[1] 3~01980~ 5~01471~ 7~01471~, [10] 11~04467~ 13~0312~ 14~05971~;'),
  (7070, 7, 20, 9, 'But now this shall be the thing which we will do to Gibeah; we will go up by lot against it;', '[3 4] 6~01697~ 10~06213~ 12~01390~; [13 16] 18~01486~'),
  (23432, 40, 10, 5, 'These twelve Jesus sent forth, and commanded them, saying, Go not into the way of the Gentiles, and into any city of the Samaritans enter ye not:', '&para; 0~5128~ 1~1427~ 2~2424~ 4~649~, 6~3853~ 7~846~, 8~3004~, 9~565~ 10~3361~ 11~1519~ 13~3598~ 16~1484~, 17~2532~ 18~1519~ [19] 20~4172~ 23~4541~ 25~1525~ 26~3361~:'),
  (9162, 11, 12, 3, 'That they sent and called him. And Jeroboam and all the congregation of Israel came, and spake unto Rehoboam, saying,', '2~07971~ 4~07121~ 7~03379~ 11~06951~ 13~03478~ 14~0935~, 16~01696~ 18~07346~, 19~0559~,'),
  (10711, 13, 11, 30, 'Maharai the Netophathite, Heled the son of Baanah the Netophathite,', '0~04121~ 2~05200~, 3~02466~ 5~01121~ 7~01196~ 9~05200~,'),
  (18419, 23, 38, 20, 'The LORD was ready to save me: therefore we will sing my songs to the stringed instruments all the days of our life in the house of the LORD.', '1~03068~ [2 3] 5~03467~ 12~05058~ 16~05059~ 19~03117~ 22~02416~ 25~01004~ 28~03068~.'),
  (7127, 7, 21, 18, 'Howbeit we may not give them wives of our daughters: for the children of Israel have sworn, saying, Cursed be he that giveth a wife to Benjamin.', '2~03201~ 4~05414~ 6~0802~ 9~01323~: 12~01121~ 14~03478~ 16~07650~, 17~0559~, 18~0779~ [19] 22~05414~ 24~0802~ 26~01144~.'),
  (18545, 23, 44, 3, 'For I will pour water upon him that is thirsty, and floods upon the dry ground: I will pour my spirit upon thy seed, and my blessing upon thine offspring:', '3~03332~ 4~04325~ 9~06771~, 11~05140~ 15~03004~: 18~03332~ 20~07307~ 23~02233~, 26~01293~ 29~06631~:'),
  (2690, 2, 39, 21, 'And they did bind the breastplate by his rings unto the rings of the ephod with a lace of blue, that it might be above the curious girdle of the ephod, and that the breastplate might not be loosed from the ephod; as the LORD commanded Moses.', '3~07405~ 5~02833~ 8~02885~ 11~02885~ 14~0646~ 17~06616~ 19~08504~, 27~02805~ 30~0646~, 34~02833~ 38~02118~ 41~0646~; 44~03068~ 45~06680~ 46~04872~.'),
  (27527, 44, 16, 28, 'But Paul cried with a loud voice, saying, Do thyself no harm: for we are all here.', '0~1161~ 1~3972~ 2~5455~ 5~3173~ 6~5456~, 7~3004~, 8~4238~ 9~4572~ 10~3367~ 11~2556~: 12~1063~ 14~2070~ 15~537~ 16~1759~.'),
  (9544, 12, 1, 3, 'But the angel of the LORD said to Elijah the Tishbite, Arise, go up to meet the messengers of the king of Samaria, and say unto them, Is it not because there is not a God in Israel, that ye go to inquire of Baalzebub the god of Ekron?', '2~04397~ 5~03068~ 6~01696~ 8~0452~ 10~08664~, 11~06965~, 13~05927~ 15~07125~ 17~04397~ 20~04428~ 22~08111~, 24~01696~ [27 28] [31 32] 35~0430~ 37~03478~, [38] 40~01980~ 42~01875~ 44~01176~ 46~0430~ 48~06138~?'),
  (2513, 2, 34, 12, 'Take heed to thyself, lest thou make a covenant with the inhabitants of the land whither thou goest, lest it be for a snare in the midst of thee:', '1~08104~ 6~03772~ 8~01285~ 11~03427~ 14~0776~ 17~0935~, 23~04170~ 26~07130~'),
  (4615, 4, 29, 1, 'And in the seventh month, on the first day of the month, ye shall have an holy convocation; ye shall do no servile work: it is a day of blowing the trumpets unto you.', '&para; 3~07637~ 4~02320~, 7~0259~ [8] 11~02320~, 16~06944~ 17~04744~; 20~06213~ 22~05656~ 23~04399~: 27~03117~ 29~08643~'),
  (25691, 42, 17, 26, 'And as it was in the days of Noe, so shall it be also in the days of the Son of man.', '0~2532~ 1~2531~ 3~1096~ 4~1722~ 6~2250~ 8~3575~, 9~3779~ 12~2071~ 13~2532~ 14~1722~ 16~2250~ 19~5207~ 21~444~.'),
  (18242, 23, 30, 16, 'But ye said, No; for we will flee upon horses; therefore shall ye flee: and, We will ride upon the swift; therefore shall they that pursue you be swift.', '2~0559~, 7~05127~ 9~05483~; 13~05127~: 17~07392~ 20~07031~; 25~07291~ 28~07043~.'),
  (17013, 20, 21, 20, 'There is treasure to be desired and oil in the dwelling of the wise; but a foolish man spendeth it up.', '&para; [0 1] 2~0214~ 5~02530~ 7~08081~ 10~05116~ 13~02450~; 16~03684~ 17~0120~ 20~01104~.'),
  (25344, 42, 9, 31, 'Who appeared in glory, and spake of his decease which he should accomplish at Jerusalem.', '0~3739~ 1~3700~ 2~1722~ 3~1391~, 5~3004~ 7~846~ 8~1841~ 9~3739~ 11~3195~ 12~4137~ 13~1722~ 14~2419~.'),
  (12126, 15, 4, 7, 'And in the days of Artaxerxes wrote Bishlam, Mithredath, Tabeel, and the rest of their companions, unto Artaxerxes king of Persia; and the writing of the letter was written in the Syrian tongue, and interpreted in the Syrian tongue.', '3~03117~ 5~0783~ 6~03789~ 7~01312~, 8~04990~, 9~02870~, 12~07605~ 15~03674~, 17~0783~ 18~04428~ 20~06539~; 23~03791~ 26~05406~ [27] 28~03789~ 32~0762~, 34~08638~ 38~0762~.'),
  (1926, 2, 15, 1, 'Then sang Moses and the children of Israel this song unto the LORD, and spake, saying, I will sing unto the LORD, for he hath triumphed gloriously: the horse and his rider hath he thrown into the sea.', '&para; 1~07891~ 2~04872~ 5~01121~ 7~03478~ 9~07892~ 12~03068~, 14~0559~, 15~0559~, 18~07891~ 21~03068~, 25~01342~ 26~01342~: 28~05483~ 31~07392~ 34~07411~ 37~03220~.'),
  (20008, 24, 43, 2, 'Then spake Azariah the son of Hoshaiah, and Johanan the son of Kareah, and all the proud men, saying unto Jeremiah, Thou speakest falsely: the LORD our God hath not sent thee to say, Go not into Egypt to sojourn there:', '1~0559~ 2~05838~ 4~01121~ 6~01955~, 8~03110~ 10~01121~ 12~07143~, 16~02086~ 17~0582~, 18~0559~ 20~03414~, 22~01696~ 23~08267~: 25~03068~ 27~0430~ 30~07971~ 33~0559~, 34~0935~ 37~04714~ 39~01481~'),
  (20345, 25, 2, 4, 'He hath bent his bow like an enemy: he stood with his right hand as an adversary, and slew all that were pleasant to the eye in the tabernacle of the daughter of Zion: he poured out his fury like fire.', '2~01869~ 4~07198~ 7~0341~: 9~05324~ 13~03225~ 16~06862~, 18~02026~ [20 21] 22~04261~ 25~05869~ 28~0168~ 31~01323~ 33~06726~: 36~08210~ 38~02534~ 40~0784~.'),
  (18854, 23, 61, 2, 'To proclaim the acceptable year of the LORD, and the day of vengeance of our God; to comfort all that mourn;', '1~07121~ 3~07522~ 4~08141~ 7~03068~, 10~03117~ 12~05359~ 15~0430~; 17~05162~ 20~057~;'),
  (24753, 41, 13, 25, 'And the stars of heaven shall fall, and the powers that are in heaven shall be shaken.', '0~2532~ 2~792~ 4~3772~ 5~2071~ 6~1601~, 7~2532~ 9~1411~ 12~1722~ 13~3772~ 16~4531~.'),
  (27969, 45, 1, 23, 'And changed the glory of the uncorruptible God into an image made like to corruptible man, and to birds, and fourfooted beasts, and creeping things.', '0~2532~ 1~236~ 3~1391~ 6~862~ 7~2316~ 8~1722~ 10~1504~ 12~3667~ 14~5349~ 15~444~, 16~2532~ 18~4071~, 19~2532~ 21~5074~, 22~2532~ 24~2062~.'),
  (11699, 14, 24, 13, 'So the workmen wrought, and the work was perfected by them, and they set the house of God in his state, and strengthened it.', '2~06213~ 3~04399~* 4~06213~, 7~04399~ 8~05927~ 9~0724~ 11~03027~, 14~05975~ 16~01004~ 18~0430~ 21~04971~, 23~0553~'),
  (16350, 19, 145, 21, 'My mouth shall speak the praise of the LORD: and let all flesh bless his holy name for ever and ever.', '1~06310~ 3~01696~ 5~08416~ 8~03068~: 12~01320~ 13~01288~ 15~06944~ 16~08034~ 18~05769~ 20~05703~.'),
  (20437, 25, 4, 8, 'Their visage is blacker than a coal; they are not known in the streets: their skin cleaveth to their bones; it is withered, it is become like a stick.', '1~08389~ 3~02821~ 6~07815~; 10~05234~ 13~02351~: 15~05785~ 16~06821~ 19~06106~; 22~03001~, 28~06086~.'),
  (30718, 66, 1, 5, 'And from Jesus Christ, who is the faithful witness, and the first begotten of the dead, and the prince of the kings of the earth. Unto him that loved us, and washed us from our sins in his own blood,', '0~2532~ 1~575~ 2~2424~ 3~5547~, [4 5] 7~4103~ 8~3144~, [9] 12~4416~ 13~1537~ 15~3498~, 16~2532~ 18~758~ 21~935~ 24~1093~. 28~25~ 29~2248~, 30~2532~ 31~3068~ 32~2248~ 33~575~ 34~2257~ 35~266~ 36~1722~ 38~846~ 39~129~,'),
  (14713, 19, 51, 13, 'Then will I teach transgressors thy ways; and sinners shall be converted unto thee.', '[0] 3~03925~ 4~06586~ 6~01870~; 8~02400~ 11~07725~'),
  (3314, 3, 19, 28, 'Ye shall not make any cuttings in your flesh for the dead, nor print any marks upon you: I am the LORD.', '3~05414~ 4~03793~ 5~08296~ 8~01320~ 11~05315~, 13~05414~ 15~07085~ [19] 21~03068~.'),
  (27456, 44, 14, 26, 'And thence sailed to Antioch, from whence they had been recommended to the grace of God for the work which they fulfilled.', '1~2547~ 2~636~ 3~1519~ 4~490~, 6~3606~ 9~2258~ 10~3860~ 13~5485~ 15~2316~ 16~1519~ 18~2041~ 19~3739~ 21~4137~.');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (12047, 15, 2, 11, 'The children of Bebai, six hundred twenty and three.', '1~01121~ 3~0893~, 4~08337~ 5~03967~ 6~06242~ 8~07969~.'),
  (5202, 5, 10, 10, 'And I stayed in the mount, according to the first time, forty days and forty nights; and the LORD hearkened unto me at that time also, and the LORD would not destroy thee.', '2~05975~ 5~02022~, 9~07223~ 10~03117~, 11~0705~ 12~03117~ 14~0705~ 15~03915~; 18~03068~ 19~08085~ 24~06471~ [26] 28~03068~ 29~014~ 31~07843~'),
  (7546, 9, 14, 31, 'And they smote the Philistines that day from Michmash to Aijalon: and the people were very faint.', '2~05221~ 4~06430~ 6~03117~ 8~04363~ 10~0357~: 13~05971~ 15~03966~ 16~05774~.'),
  (14409, 19, 34, 12, 'What man is he that desireth life, and loveth many days, that he may see good?', '1~0376~ [2 4] 5~02655~ 6~02416~, [7] 8~0157~ [9] 10~03117~, 14~07200~ 15~02896~?'),
  (18039, 23, 20, 1, 'In the year that Tartan came unto Ashdod (when Sargon the king of Assyria sent him,) and fought against Ashdod, and took it;', '&para; 2~08141~ 4~08661~ 5~0935~ 7~0795~, 9~05623~ 11~04428~ 13~0804~ 14~07971~ 17~03898~ 19~0795~, 21~03920~'),
  (28713, 46, 14, 19, 'Yet in the church I had rather speak five words with my understanding, that by my voice I might teach others also, than ten thousand words in an unknown tongue.', '0~235~ 1~1722~ 3~1577~ 6~2309~ 7~2980~ 8~4002~ 9~3056~ 10~1223~ 11~3450~ 12~3563~, 13~2443~ [14 16] 19~2727~ 20~243~ 21~2532~, 22~2228~ 24~3463~ 25~3056~ 26~1722~ [28] 29~1100~.'),
  (10920, 13, 19, 5, 'Then there went certain, and told David how the men were served. And he sent to meet them: for the men were greatly ashamed. And the king said, Tarry at Jericho until your beards be grown, and then return.', '2~03212~ [3] 5~05046~ 6~01732~ 9~0582~ 14~07971~ 16~07125~ 20~0582~ 22~03966~ 23~03637~. 26~04428~ 27~0559~, 28~03427~ 30~03405~ 33~02206~ 35~06779~, [37] 38~07725~.'),
  (28141, 45, 8, 9, 'But ye are not in the flesh, but in the Spirit, if so be that the Spirit of God dwell in you. Now if any man have not the Spirit of Christ, he is none of his.', '0~1161~ 1~5210~ 2~2075~ 3~3756~ 4~1722~ 6~4561~, 7~235~ 8~1722~ 10~4151~, 13~1512~ 16~4151~ 18~2316~ 19~3611~ 20~1722~ 21~5213~. 22~1161~ 25~1536~ 26~2192~ 27~3756~ 29~4151~ 31~5547~, 32~3778~ 33~2076~ 34~3756~ 36~846~.'),
  (5971, 6, 6, 16, 'And it came to pass at the seventh time, when the priests blew with the trumpets, Joshua said unto the people, Shout; for the LORD hath given you the city.', '7~07637~ 8~06471~, 11~03548~ 12~08628~ 15~07782~, 16~03091~ 17~0559~ 20~05971~, 21~07321~; 24~03068~ 26~05414~ 29~05892~.'),
  (30807, 66, 5, 12, 'Saying with a loud voice, Worthy is the Lamb that was slain to receive power, and riches, and wisdom, and strength, and honour, and glory, and blessing.', '0~3004~ 3~3173~ 4~5456~, 5~514~ 6~2076~ 8~721~ 11~4969~ 13~2983~ 14~1411~, 15~2532~ 16~4149~, 17~2532~ 18~4678~, 19~2532~ 20~2479~, 21~2532~ 22~5092~, 23~2532~ 24~1391~, 25~2532~ 26~2129~.'),
  (13462, 18, 24, 17, 'For the morning is to them even as the shadow of death: if one know them, they are in the terrors of the shadow of death.', '2~01242~ [3] 7~03162~ 11~06757~: [13] 14~05234~ [15 18] 20~01091~ 25~06757~.'),
  (17389, 21, 3, 21, 'Who knoweth the spirit of man that goeth upward, and the spirit of the beast that goeth downward to the earth?', '1~03045~ 3~07307~ 5~0120~ 6~01121~ 7~05927~ 8~04605~, 11~07307~ 14~0929~ 16~03381~ 17~04295~ 20~0776~?'),
  (7935, 9, 26, 23, 'The LORD render to every man his righteousness and his faithfulness: for the LORD delivered thee into my hand to day, but I would not stretch forth mine hand against the LORD''S anointed.', '1~03068~ 2~07725~ 5~0376~ 7~06666~ 10~0530~: 13~03068~ 14~05414~ [17] 18~03027~ 20~03117~, 23~014~ 26~07971~ 28~03027~ 31~03068~ 32~04899~.'),
  (23536, 40, 12, 37, 'For by thy words thou shalt be justified, and by thy words thou shalt be condemned.', '0~1063~ 1~1537~ 2~4675~ 3~3056~ 7~1344~, 8~2532~ 9~1537~ 10~4675~ 11~3056~ 15~2613~.'),
  (29038, 47, 11, 33, 'And through a window in a basket was I let down by the wall, and escaped his hands.', '0~2532~ 1~1223~ 3~2376~ 4~1722~ 6~4553~ 10~5465~ 11~1223~ 13~5038~, 14~2532~ 15~1628~ 16~846~ 17~5495~.'),
  (14358, 19, 31, 18, 'Let the lying lips be put to silence; which speak grievous things proudly and contemptuously against the righteous.', '2~08267~ 3~08193~ 7~0481~; 9~01696~ 10~06277~ 12~01346~ 14~0937~ 17~06662~.'),
  (23942, 40, 23, 14, 'Woe unto you, scribes and Pharisees, hypocrites! for ye devour widows'' houses, and for a pretence make long prayer: therefore ye shall receive the greater damnation.', '0~3759~ 2~5213~, 3~1122~ 4~2532~ 5~5330~, 6~5273~! 7~3754~ 9~2719~ 10~5503~ 11~3614~, 12~2532~ 15~4392~ 16~4336~ 17~3117~ 18~4336~: 19~5124~ 20~1223~ 22~2983~ 24~4055~ 25~2917~.'),
  (11974, 14, 34, 32, 'And he caused all that were present in Jerusalem and Benjamin to stand to it. And the inhabitants of Jerusalem did according to the covenant of God, the God of their fathers.', '6~04672~ 8~03389~ 10~01144~ 12~05975~ [13 14] 17~03427~ 19~03389~ 20~06213~ 24~01285~ 26~0430~, 28~0430~ 31~01~.'),
  (28409, 46, 1, 30, 'But of him are ye in Christ Jesus, who of God is made unto us wisdom, and righteousness, and sanctification, and redemption:', '0~1161~ 1~1537~ 2~846~ 3~2075~ 4~5210~ 5~1722~ 6~5547~ 7~2424~, 8~3739~ 9~575~ 10~2316~ 12~1096~ 14~5037~ 15~2254~* 16~4678~, 18~1343~, 19~2532~ 20~38~, 21~2532~ 22~629~:'),
  (2493, 2, 33, 15, 'And he said unto him, If thy presence go not with me, carry us not up hence.', '2~0559~ 7~06440~ 8~01980~ [10 11] 15~05927~'),
  (23005, 38, 8, 20, 'Thus saith the LORD of hosts; It shall yet come to pass, that there shall come people, and the inhabitants of many cities:', '1~0559~ 3~03068~ 5~06635~; [6 7] [9 11] 15~0935~ 16~05971~, 19~03427~ 21~07227~ 22~05892~:'),
  (22284, 28, 13, 9, 'O Israel, thou hast destroyed thyself; but in me is thine help.', '&para; 1~03478~, 4~07843~ [9] 11~05828~.'),
  (26928, 43, 21, 14, 'This is now the third time that Jesus shewed himself to his disciples, after that he was risen from the dead.', '0~5124~ 1~5319~ 2~2235~ 5~5154~ 7~2424~ 9~5319~ 11~846~ 12~3101~, 17~1453~ 18~1537~ 20~3498~.'),
  (5831, 5, 33, 15, 'And for the chief things of the ancient mountains, and for the precious things of the lasting hills,', '4~07218~ 7~06924~ 8~02042~, 13~04022~ 16~05769~ 17~01389~,'),
  (6898, 7, 13, 7, 'But he said unto me, Behold, thou shalt conceive, and bear a son; and now drink no wine nor strong drink, neither eat any unclean thing: for the child shall be a Nazarite to God from the womb to the day of his death.', '2~0559~ 8~02030~, 10~03205~ 12~01121~; 15~07941~ 17~03196~ 20~08354~, 22~0398~ 24~02932~ [25] 28~05288~ 32~05139~ 34~0430~ 37~0990~ 40~03117~ 43~04194~.'),
  (13265, 18, 16, 18, 'O earth, cover not thou my blood, and let my cry have no place.', '1~0776~, 2~03680~ 6~01818~, 10~02201~ 13~04725~.'),
  (15657, 19, 105, 42, 'For he remembered his holy promise, and Abraham his servant.', '2~02142~ 4~06944~ 5~01697~, [6] 7~085~ 9~05650~.'),
  (4783, 4, 33, 17, 'And they departed from Kibrothhattaavah, and encamped at Hazeroth.', '2~05265~ 4~06914~, 6~02583~ 8~02698~.'),
  (21159, 26, 27, 29, 'And all that handle the oar, the mariners, and all the pilots of the sea, shall come down from their ships, they shall stand upon the land;', '3~08610~ 5~04880~, 7~04419~, [8] 11~02259~ 14~03220~, 17~03381~ 20~0591~, 23~05975~ 26~0776~;'),
  (9218, 11, 13, 26, 'And when the prophet that brought him back from the way heard thereof, he said, It is the man of God, who was disobedient unto the word of the LORD: therefore the LORD hath delivered him unto the lion, which hath torn him, and slain him, according to the word of the LORD, which he spake unto him.', '3~05030~ 7~07725~ 10~01870~ 11~08085~ [12] 14~0559~, [16] 18~0376~ 20~0430~, 23~04784~ 26~06310~ 29~03068~: 32~03068~ 34~05414~ 38~0738~, 41~07665~ 44~04191~ 49~01697~ 52~03068~, 55~01696~'),
  (31103, 66, 22, 7, 'Behold, I come quickly: blessed is he that keepeth the sayings of the prophecy of this book.', '0~2400~, 2~2064~ 3~5035~: 4~3107~ [5] 8~5083~ 10~3056~ 13~4394~ 15~5127~ 16~975~.'),
  (13531, 18, 28, 18, 'No mention shall be made of coral, or of pearls: for the price of wisdom is above rubies.', '1~02142~ 6~07215~, 9~01378~: 12~04901~ 14~02451~ [15] 17~06443~.'),
  (2874, 3, 6, 20, 'This is the offering of Aaron and of his sons, which they shall offer unto the LORD in the day when he is anointed; the tenth part of an ephah of fine flour for a meat offering perpetual, half of it in the morning, and half thereof at night.', '[1] 3~07133~ 5~0175~ 9~01121~, 13~07126~ 16~03068~ 19~03117~ 23~04886~; 26~06224~ 29~0374~ 32~05560~ 36~04503~ 37~08548~, 38~04276~ 43~01242~, 45~04276~ 48~06153~.'),
  (12919, 18, 3, 6, 'As for that night, let darkness seize upon it; let it not be joined unto the days of the year, let it not come into the number of the months.', '[1] 3~03915~, 5~0652~ 6~03947~ 13~02302~ 16~03117~ 19~08141~, 23~0935~ 26~04557~ 29~03391~.'),
  (4244, 4, 16, 45, 'Get you up from among this congregation, that I may consume them as in a moment. And they fell upon their faces.', '2~07426~ 4~08432~ 6~05712~, 10~03615~ 15~07281~. 18~05307~ 21~06440~.'),
  (26658, 43, 13, 13, 'Ye call me Master and Lord: and ye say well; for so I am.', '0~5210~ 1~5455~ 2~3165~ 3~1320~ 4~2532~ 5~2962~: 6~2532~ 8~3004~ 9~2573~; 10~1063~ [11] 13~1510~.'),
  (25994, 42, 23, 45, 'And the sun was darkened, and the veil of the temple was rent in the midst.', '0~2532~ 2~2246~ 4~4654~, 5~2532~ 7~2665~ 10~3485~ 12~4977~ 15~3319~.'),
  (20984, 26, 21, 31, 'And I will pour out mine indignation upon thee, I will blow against thee in the fire of my wrath, and deliver thee into the hand of brutish men, and skilful to destroy.', '4~08210~ 6~02195~ 11~06315~ 16~0784~ 19~05678~, 21~05414~ 25~03027~ 27~01197~ 28~0582~, [29] 30~02796~ 32~04889~.'),
  (7256, 9, 2, 9, 'He will keep the feet of his saints, and the wicked shall be silent in darkness; for by strength shall no man prevail.', '2~08104~ 4~07272~ 7~02623~, 10~07563~ 13~01826~ 15~02822~; 18~03581~ 21~0376~ 22~01396~.'),
  (23181, 40, 2, 2, 'Saying, Where is he that is born King of the Jews? for we have seen his star in the east, and are come to worship him.', '0~3004~, 1~4226~ 2~2076~ 6~5088~ 7~935~ 10~2453~? 11~1063~ 14~1492~ 15~846~ 16~792~ 17~1722~ 19~395~, 20~2532~ 22~2064~ 24~4352~ 25~846~.'),
  (24495, 41, 7, 21, 'For from within, out of the heart of men, proceed evil thoughts, adulteries, fornications, murders,', '0~1063~ 2~2081~, 4~1537~ 6~2588~ 8~444~, 9~1607~ 10~2556~ 11~1261~, 12~3430~, 13~4202~, 14~5408~,'),
  (2327, 2, 28, 29, 'And Aaron shall bear the names of the children of Israel in the breastplate of judgment upon his heart, when he goeth in unto the holy place, for a memorial before the LORD continually.', '1~0175~ 3~05375~ 5~08034~ 8~01121~ 10~03478~ 13~02833~ 15~04941~ 18~03820~, 21~0935~ 25~06944~ [26] 29~02146~ 30~06440~ 32~03068~ 33~08548~.'),
  (16150, 19, 130, 1, 'A Song of degrees. Out of the depths have I cried unto thee, O LORD.', '&para; [0 1~07892~ 3] 3~04609~ 7~04615~ 10~07121~ 14~03068~.'),
  (28567, 46, 9, 11, 'If we have sown unto you spiritual things, is it a great thing if we shall reap your carnal things?', '0~1487~ 1~2249~ 3~4687~ 5~5213~ 7~4152~, [8 9] 12~3173~ 13~1487~ 14~2249~ 16~2325~ 17~5216~ 19~4559~?'),
  (14342, 19, 31, 2, 'Bow down thine ear to me; deliver me speedily: be thou my strong rock, for an house of defence to save me.', '1~05186~ 3~0241~ 6~05337~ 8~04120~: 12~04581~ 13~06697~, 16~01004~ 18~04686~ 20~03467~'),
  (13625, 18, 31, 28, 'This also were an iniquity to be punished by the judge: for I should have denied the God that is above.', '[2] 4~05771~ [5 8] 10~06416~: 15~03584~ 17~0410~ [18 19] 20~04605~.'),
  (11116, 13, 26, 31, 'Among the Hebronites was Jerijah the chief, even among the Hebronites, according to the generations of his fathers. In the fortieth year of the reign of David they were sought for, and there were found among them mighty men of valour at Jazer of Gilead.', '2~02276~ [3] 4~03404~ 6~07218~, [7] 10~02276~, 14~08435~ 17~01~. 20~0705~ 21~08141~ 24~04438~ 26~01732~ 29~01875~ 34~04672~ 38~01368~ 40~02428~ 42~03270~ 44~01568~.'),
  (24663, 41, 11, 12, 'And on the morrow, when they were come from Bethany, he was hungry:', '&para; 0~2532~ 3~1887~, 5~846~ 7~1831~ 8~575~ 9~963~, 12~3983~:'),
  (16672, 20, 10, 7, 'The memory of the just is blessed: but the name of the wicked shall rot.', '&para; 1~02143~ 4~06662~ [5] 6~01293~: 9~08034~ 12~07563~ 14~07537~.'),
  (20488, 26, 1, 15, 'Now as I beheld the living creatures, behold one wheel upon the earth by the living creatures, with his four faces.', '&para; 3~07200~ 6~02416~, 8~0259~ 9~0212~ 12~0776~ 13~0681~ 16~02416~, 19~0702~ 20~06440~.'),
  (9227, 11, 14, 1, 'At that time Abijah the son of Jeroboam fell sick.', '&para; 2~06256~ 3~029~ 5~01121~ 7~03379~ 9~02470~.'),
  (1594, 2, 3, 10, 'Come now therefore, and I will send thee unto Pharaoh, that thou mayest bring forth my people the children of Israel out of Egypt.', '0~03212~ 6~07971~ 9~06547~, 14~03318~ 16~05971~ 18~01121~ 20~03478~ 23~04714~.'),
  (27476, 44, 15, 18, 'Known unto God are all his works from the beginning of the world.', '0~1110~ 2~2316~ 3~2076~ 4~3956~ 5~846~ 6~2041~ 7~575~ 12~165~.'),
  (7158, 8, 2, 2, 'And Ruth the Moabitess said unto Naomi, Let me now go to the field, and glean ears of corn after him in whose sight I shall find grace. And she said unto her, Go, my daughter.', '1~07327~ 3~04125~ 4~0559~ 6~05281~, 10~03212~ 13~07704~, 15~03950~ 18~07641~ 19~0310~ [20] 23~05869~ 26~04672~ 27~02580~. 30~0559~ 33~03212~, 35~01323~.'),
  (27304, 44, 10, 29, 'Therefore came I unto you without gainsaying, as soon as I was sent for: I ask therefore for what intent ye have sent for me?', '0~2532~ 1~1352~ 2~2064~ [3 4] 6~369~, 13~3343~: 15~4441~ 16~3767~ 18~5101~ 19~3056~ 23~3343~ 24~3165~?'),
  (14627, 19, 46, 4, 'There is a river, the streams whereof shall make glad the city of God, the holy place of the tabernacles of the most High.', '[0 1] 3~05104~, 5~06388~ 9~08055~ 11~05892~ 13~0430~, 15~06918~ [16] 19~04908~ 23~05945~.'),
  (2150, 2, 23, 1, 'Thou shalt not raise a false report: put not thine hand with the wicked to be an unrighteous witness.', '&para; 3~05375~ 5~07723~ 6~08088~: 7~07896~ 10~03027~ 13~07563~ 17~02555~ 18~05707~.'),
  (2627, 2, 37, 18, 'And six branches going out of the sides thereof; three branches of the candlestick out of the one side thereof, and three branches of the candlestick out of the other side thereof:', '1~08337~ 2~07070~ 4~03318~ 7~06654~ 9~07969~ 10~07070~ 13~04501~ 17~0259~ 18~06654~ 21~07969~ 22~07070~ 25~04501~ 29~08145~ 30~06654~'),
  (29315, 49, 4, 27, 'Neither give place to the devil.', '0~3383~ 1~1325~ 2~5117~ 5~1228~.'),
  (6587, 7, 3, 12, 'And the children of Israel did evil again in the sight of the LORD: and the LORD strengthened Eglon the king of Moab against Israel, because they had done evil in the sight of the LORD.', '&para; 2~01121~ 4~03478~ 5~06213~ 6~07451~ 7~03254~ 10~05869~ 13~03068~: 16~03068~ 17~02388~ 18~05700~ 20~04428~ 22~04124~ 24~03478~, 28~06213~ 29~07451~ 32~05869~ 35~03068~.'),
  (9374, 11, 18, 25, 'And Elijah said unto the prophets of Baal, Choose you one bullock for yourselves, and dress it first; for ye are many; and call on the name of your gods, but put no fire under.', '1~0452~ 2~0559~ 5~05030~ 7~01168~, 8~0977~ 10~0259~ 11~06499~ 15~06213~ [16] 17~07223~; [20] 21~07227~; 23~07121~ 26~08034~ 29~0430~, 31~07760~ 33~0784~ [34]'),
  (23988, 40, 24, 21, 'For then shall be great tribulation, such as was not since the beginning of the world to this time, no, nor ever shall be.', '0~1063~ 1~5119~ 3~2071~ 4~3173~ 5~2347~, 7~3634~ 8~1096~ 9~3756~ 10~575~ 12~746~ 15~2889~ 17~2193~ 18~3568~, 19~3761~, 21~3364~ 23~1096~.'),
  (28603, 46, 10, 20, 'But I say, that the things which the Gentiles sacrifice, they sacrifice to devils, and not to God: and I would not that ye should have fellowship with devils.', '0~235~ [2] 3~3754~ 6~3739~ 8~1484~ 9~2380~, 11~2380~ 13~1140~, 14~2532~ 15~3756~ 17~2316~: 18~1161~ 20~2309~ 21~3756~ 23~5209~ 25~1096~ 26~2844~ 28~1140~.'),
  (2731, 2, 40, 19, 'And he spread abroad the tent over the tabernacle, and put the covering of the tent above upon it; as the LORD commanded Moses.', '3~06566~ 5~0168~ 8~04908~, 10~07760~ 12~04372~ 15~0168~ 16~04605~ 21~03068~ 22~06680~ 23~04872~.'),
  (12248, 15, 9, 2, 'For they have taken of their daughters for themselves, and for their sons: so that the holy seed have mingled themselves with the people of those lands: yea, the hand of the princes and rulers hath been chief in this trespass.', '3~05375~ 6~01323~ 12~01121~: 16~06944~ 17~02233~ 19~06148~ 23~05971~ [25] 26~0776~: 29~03027~ 32~08269~ 34~05461~ 37~07223~ 40~04604~.'),
  (13105, 18, 10, 10, 'Hast thou not poured me out as milk, and curdled me like cheese?', '5~05413~ 7~02461~, 9~07087~ 12~01385~?'),
  (5766, 5, 32, 2, 'My doctrine shall drop as the rain, my speech shall distil as the dew, as the small rain upon the tender herb, and as the showers upon the grass:', '1~03948~ 3~06201~ 6~04306~, 8~0565~ 10~05140~ 13~02919~, 17~08164~ 21~01877~, 25~07241~ 28~06212~:'),
  (22101, 27, 12, 11, 'And from the time that the daily sacrifice shall be taken away, and the abomination that maketh desolate set up, there shall be a thousand two hundred and ninety days.', '3~06256~ [4] 6~08548~ [7] 11~05493~, 14~08251~ 17~08074~ 19~05414~, [20 22] 24~0505~ 26~03967~ 28~08673~ 29~03117~.'),
  (19562, 24, 25, 19, 'Pharaoh king of Egypt, and his servants, and his princes, and all his people;', '0~06547~ 1~04428~ 3~04714~, 6~05650~, 9~08269~, 13~05971~;'),
  (28827, 47, 1, 11, 'Ye also helping together by prayer for us, that for the gift bestowed upon us by the means of many persons thanks may be given by many on our behalf.', '0~5216~ 1~2532~ 3~4943~ 5~1162~ 6~5228~ 7~2257~, 8~2443~ 11~5486~ [12] 13~1519~ 14~2248~ 15~1537~ 19~4183~ 20~4383~ 23~2168~ 24~5228~ 25~1223~ 26~4183~ 29~2257~.'),
  (30777, 66, 3, 15, 'I know thy works, that thou art neither cold nor hot: I would thou wert cold or hot.', '1~1492~ 2~4675~ 3~2041~, 4~3754~ 6~1488~ 7~3777~ 8~5593~ 9~3777~ 10~2200~: 12~3785~ 14~1498~ 15~5593~ 16~2228~ 17~2200~.'),
  (10753, 13, 12, 25, 'Of the children of Simeon, mighty men of valour for the war, seven thousand and one hundred.', '2~01121~ 4~08095~, 6~01368~ 8~02428~ 11~06635~, 12~07651~ 13~0505~ 16~03967~.'),
  (24021, 40, 25, 3, 'They that were foolish took their lamps, and took no oil with them:', '0~3748~ [2] 3~3474~ 4~2983~ 5~1438~ 6~846~* 7~2985~, 9~2983~ 10~3756~ 11~1637~ 12~3326~ 13~1438~:'),
  (8824, 11, 2, 46, 'So the king commanded Benaiah the son of Jehoiada; which went out, and fell upon him, that he died. And the kingdom was established in the hand of Solomon.', '2~04428~ 3~06680~ 4~01141~ 6~01121~ 8~03077~; 11~03318~, 13~06293~ 18~04191~. 21~04467~ 23~03559~ 26~03027~ 28~08010~.'),
  (17357, 21, 2, 15, 'Then said I in my heart, As it happeneth to the fool, so it happeneth even to me; and why was I then more wise? Then I said in my heart, that this also is vanity.', '0~0227~ 1~0559~ 5~03820~, 8~04745~ 11~03684~, 14~07136~ 17~01571~; 23~03148~ 24~02449~? 27~01696~ 30~03820~, [34] 35~01892~.'),
  (18981, 24, 2, 7, 'And I brought you into a plentiful country, to eat the fruit thereof and the goodness thereof; but when ye entered, ye defiled my land, and made mine heritage an abomination.', '2~0935~ 6~03759~ 7~0776~, 9~0398~ 11~06529~ 15~02898~ 20~0935~, 22~02930~ 24~0776~, 26~07760~ 28~05159~ 30~08441~.'),
  (14186, 19, 19, 9, 'The fear of the LORD is clean, enduring for ever: the judgments of the LORD are true and righteous altogether.', '1~03374~ 4~03068~ [5] 6~02889~, 7~05975~ 9~05703~: 11~04941~ 14~03068~ [15] 16~0571~ [17] 18~06663~ 19~03162~.'),
  (26784, 43, 17, 10, 'And all mine are thine, and thine are mine; and I am glorified in them.', '0~2532~ 1~3956~ 2~1699~ 3~2076~ 4~4674~, 5~2532~ 6~4674~ 8~1699~; 9~2532~ 12~1392~ 13~1722~ 14~846~.'),
  (3973, 4, 9, 3, 'In the fourteenth day of this month, at even, ye shall keep it in his appointed season: according to all the rites of it, and according to all the ceremonies thereof, shall ye keep it.', '2~06240~ 3~0702~* 4~03117~ 7~02320~, 9~06153~, 12~06213~ 17~04150~: 22~02708~ 30~04941~ 34~06213~'),
  (20354, 25, 2, 13, 'What thing shall I take to witness for thee? what thing shall I liken to thee, O daughter of Jerusalem? what shall I equal to thee, that I may comfort thee, O virgin daughter of Zion? for thy breach is great like the sea: who can heal thee?', '6~05749~ 10~04100~ 13~01819~ 17~01323~ 19~03389~? 23~07737~ 29~05162~ 32~01330~ 33~01323~ 35~06726~? 38~07667~ [39] 40~01419~ 43~03220~: 46~07495~'),
  (7762, 9, 20, 25, 'And the king sat upon his seat, as at other times, even upon a seat by the wall: and Jonathan arose, and Abner sat by Saul''s side, and David''s place was empty.', '2~04428~ 3~03427~ 6~04186~, 10~06471~, [11] 14~04186~ 17~07023~: 19~03083~ 20~06965~, 22~074~ 23~03427~ 25~07586~ 26~06654~, 28~01732~ 29~04725~ 31~06485~.'),
  (8323, 10, 12, 30, 'And he took their king''s crown from off his head, the weight whereof was a talent of gold with the precious stones: and it was set on David''s head. And he brought forth the spoil of the city in great abundance.', '2~03947~ 4~04428~ 5~05850~ 9~07218~, 11~04948~ [13] 15~03603~ 17~02091~ 20~03368~ 21~068~: [25] 27~01732~ 28~07218~. 32~03318~ 34~07998~ 37~05892~ 39~03966~ 40~07235~.'),
  (27652, 44, 20, 10, 'And Paul went down, and fell on him, and embracing him said, Trouble not yourselves; for his life is in him.', '0~1161~ 1~3972~ 3~2597~, 6~1968~ 7~846~, 8~2532~ 9~4843~ [10] 11~2036~, 12~2350~ 13~3361~ 14~2350~; 15~1063~ 16~846~ 17~5590~ 18~2076~ 19~1722~ 20~846~.'),
  (5237, 5, 11, 23, 'Then will the LORD drive out all these nations from before you, and ye shall possess greater nations and mightier than yourselves.', '3~03068~ 5~03423~ 8~01471~ 10~06440~ 15~03423~ 16~01419~ 17~01471~ 19~06099~'),
  (24486, 41, 7, 12, 'And ye suffer him no more to do ought for his father or his mother;', '0~2532~ 2~863~ 3~846~ 5~3765~ 7~4160~ 8~3762~ 10~846~ 11~3962~ 12~2228~ 13~846~ 14~3384~;'),
  (10898, 13, 17, 27, 'Now therefore let it please thee to bless the house of thy servant, that it may be before thee for ever: for thou blessest, O LORD, and it shall be blessed for ever.', '4~02974~ 7~01288~ 9~01004~ 12~05650~, 17~06440~ 20~05769~: 23~01288~, 25~03068~, [27 29] 30~01288~ 32~05769~.'),
  (15488, 19, 97, 1, 'The LORD reigneth; let the earth rejoice; let the multitude of isles be glad thereof.', '&para; 1~03068~ 2~04427~; 5~0776~ 6~01523~; 9~07227~ 11~0339~ 13~08055~ [14]'),
  (5522, 5, 23, 16, 'He shall dwell with thee, even among you, in that place which he shall choose in one of thy gates, where it liketh him best: thou shalt not oppress him.', '2~03427~ [5] 6~07130~ 10~04725~ 14~0977~ 16~0259~ 19~08179~, 24~02896~: 28~03238~'),
  (9416, 11, 19, 21, 'And he returned back from him, and took a yoke of oxen, and slew them, and boiled their flesh with the instruments of the oxen, and gave unto the people, and they did eat. Then he arose, and went after Elijah, and ministered unto him.', '3~07725~ 5~0310~, 7~03947~ 9~06776~ 11~01241~, 13~02076~ 16~01310~ 18~01320~ 21~03627~ 24~01241~, 26~05414~ 29~05971~, 33~0398~. 36~06965~, 38~03212~ 39~0310~ 40~0452~, 42~08334~'),
  (8830, 11, 3, 6, 'And Solomon said, Thou hast shewed unto thy servant David my father great mercy, according as he walked before thee in truth, and in righteousness, and in uprightness of heart with thee; and thou hast kept for him this great kindness, that thou hast given him a son to sit on his throne, as it is this day.', '1~08010~ 2~0559~, 5~06213~ 8~05650~ 9~01732~ 11~01~ 12~01419~ 13~02617~, 17~01980~ 18~06440~ 21~0571~, 24~06666~, 27~03483~ 29~03824~ 35~08104~ 39~01419~ 40~02617~, 44~05414~ 47~01121~ 49~03427~ 52~03678~, [54 55] 57~03117~.'),
  (8206, 10, 7, 19, 'And this was yet a small thing in thy sight, O Lord GOD; but thou hast spoken also of thy servant''s house for a great while to come. And is this the manner of man, O Lord GOD?', '6~06994~ 9~05869~, 11~0136~ 12~03069~; 16~01696~ 20~05650~ 21~01004~ 27~07350~. [29] 32~08452~ 34~0120~, 36~0136~ 37~03069~?'),
  (17699, 23, 2, 5, 'O house of Jacob, come ye, and let us walk in the light of the LORD.', '1~01004~ 3~03290~, 4~03212~ 9~03212~ 12~0216~ 15~03068~.'),
  (26599, 43, 12, 4, 'Then saith one of his disciples, Judas Iscariot, Simon''s son, which should betray him,', '0~3767~ 1~3004~ 2~1520~ 3~1537~ 4~846~ 5~3101~, 6~2455~ 7~2469~, 8~4613~ [9] 10~3588~ 11~3195~ 12~3860~ 13~846~,'),
  (520, 1, 21, 3, 'And Abraham called the name of his son that was born unto him, whom Sarah bare to him, Isaac.', '1~085~ 2~07121~ 4~08034~ 7~01121~ 10~03205~ 14~08283~ 15~03205~ 18~03327~.'),
  (24321, 41, 3, 23, 'And he called them unto him, and said unto them in parables, How can Satan cast out Satan?', '0~2532~ 2~4341~ 3~846~ [4 5] 7~3004~ 9~846~ 10~1722~ 11~3850~, 12~4459~ 13~1410~ 14~4567~ 16~1544~ 17~4567~?'),
  (11595, 14, 19, 10, 'And what cause soever shall come to you of your brethren that dwell in their cities, between blood and blood, between law and commandment, statutes and judgments, ye shall even warn them that they trespass not against the LORD, and so wrath come upon you, and upon your brethren: this do, and ye shall not trespass.', '2~07379~ 5~0935~ 10~0251~ 12~03427~ 15~05892~, 17~01818~ 19~01818~, 21~08451~ 23~04687~, 24~02706~ 26~04941~, 30~02094~ 34~0816~ 38~03068~, [40] 41~07110~ 48~0251~: 49~03541~ 50~06213~, 55~0816~.'),
  (4833, 4, 34, 11, 'And the coast shall go down from Shepham to Riblah, on the east side of Ain; and the border shall descend, and shall reach unto the side of the sea of Chinnereth eastward:', '2~01366~ 5~03381~ 7~08221~ 9~07247~, 13~06924~ 15~05871~; 18~01366~ 20~03381~, 23~04229~ 26~03802~ 29~03220~ 31~03672~ 32~06924~:'),
  (22229, 28, 9, 12, 'Though they bring up their children, yet will I bereave them, that there shall not be a man left: yea, woe also to them when I depart from them!', '3~01431~ 5~01121~, 9~07921~ [11 13] [15] 17~0120~ [18] 20~0188~ 26~05493~'),
  (18384, 23, 37, 23, 'Whom hast thou reproached and blasphemed? and against whom hast thou exalted thy voice, and lifted up thine eyes on high? even against the Holy One of Israel.', '3~02778~ 5~01442~? 11~07311~ [12] 13~06963~, 16~05375~ 18~05869~ 20~04791~? [21] 25~06918~ 27~03478~.'),
  (773, 1, 27, 42, 'And these words of Esau her elder son were told to Rebekah: and she sent and called Jacob her younger son, and said unto him, Behold, thy brother Esau, as touching thee, doth comfort himself, purposing to kill thee.', '2~01697~ 4~06215~ 6~01419~ 7~01121~ 9~05046~ 11~07259~: 14~07971~ 16~07121~ 17~03290~ 19~06996~ 20~01121~, 22~0559~ 27~0251~ 28~06215~, 33~05162~ [35] 37~02026~');
INSERT INTO "KJVVerse" (id, bid, ch, ver, txt, coding)
VALUES
  (17706, 23, 2, 12, 'For the day of the LORD of hosts shall be upon every one that is proud and lofty, and upon every one that is lifted up; and he shall be brought low:', '2~03117~ 5~03068~ 7~06635~ [8 9] [12 14] 15~01343~ 17~07311~, [21 23] 25~05375~; 31~08213~:'),
  (22058, 27, 11, 13, 'For the king of the north shall return, and shall set forth a multitude greater than the former, and shall certainly come after certain years with a great army and with much riches.', '2~04428~ 5~06828~ 7~07725~, 11~05975~ 13~01995~ 14~07227~ 17~07223~, 20~0935~ 21~0935~ 22~07093~ 23~06256~ 24~08141~ 27~01419~ 28~02428~ 31~07227~ 32~07399~.'),
  (27035, 44, 3, 23, 'And it shall come to pass, that every soul, which will not hear that prophet, shall be destroyed from among the people.', '0~1161~ 5~2071~, [6] 7~3956~ 8~5590~, 9~302~ 10~3748~* 11~191~ 12~3361~ 13~191~ 14~1565~ 15~4396~, 18~1842~ 20~1537~ 22~2992~.'),
  (20154, 24, 49, 18, 'As in the overthrow of Sodom and Gomorrah and the neighbour cities thereof, saith the LORD, no man shall abide there, neither shall a son of man dwell in it.', '3~04114~ 5~05467~ 7~06017~ 10~07934~ [11] 13~0559~ 15~03068~, 17~0376~ 19~03427~ 24~01121~ 26~0120~ 27~01481~'),
  (20257, 24, 51, 36, 'Therefore thus saith the LORD; Behold, I will plead thy cause, and take vengeance for thee; and I will dry up her sea, and make her springs dry.', '2~0559~ 4~03068~; 8~07378~ 10~07379~, 13~05358~ 15~05360~; 20~02717~ 22~03220~, 26~04726~ 27~03001~.'),
  (16686, 20, 10, 21, 'The lips of the righteous feed many: but fools die for want of wisdom.', '1~08193~ 4~06662~ 5~07462~ 6~07227~: 8~0191~ 9~04191~ 11~02638~ 13~03820~.'),
  (22089, 27, 11, 44, 'But tidings out of the east and out of the north shall trouble him: therefore he shall go forth with great fury to destroy, and utterly to make away many.', '1~08052~ 5~04217~ 10~06828~ 12~0926~ 18~03318~ 20~01419~ 21~02534~ 23~08045~, 28~02763~ 29~07227~.'),
  (21834, 27, 3, 18, 'But if not, be it known unto thee, O king, that we will not serve thy gods, nor worship the golden image which thou hast set up.', '1~02006~ 2~03809~, 4~01934~ 5~03046~ 9~04430~, 12~0383~ 13~03809~ 14~06399~ 16~0426~, 17~03809~ 18~05457~ 20~01722~ 21~06755~ 26~06966~.'),
  (18168, 23, 27, 8, 'In measure, when it shooteth forth, thou wilt debate with it: he stayeth his rough wind in the day of the east wind.', '1~05432~, 5~07971~, 8~07378~ 12~01898~ 14~07186~ 15~07307~ 18~03117~ 22~06921~.'),
  (2052, 2, 19, 21, 'And the LORD said unto Moses, Go down, charge the people, lest they break through unto the LORD to gaze, and many of them perish.', '2~03068~ 3~0559~ 5~04872~, 7~03381~, 8~05749~ 10~05971~, 14~02040~ 17~03068~ 19~07200~, 21~07227~ 24~05307~.'),
  (28576, 46, 9, 20, 'And unto the Jews I became as a Jew, that I might gain the Jews; to them that are under the law, as under the law, that I might gain them that are under the law;', '0~2532~ 3~2453~ 5~1096~ 6~5613~ 8~2453~, 9~2443~ 12~2770~ 14~2453~; 19~5259~ 21~3551~, 22~5613~ 23~5259~ 25~3551~, 26~2443~ 29~2770~ 33~5259~ 35~3551~;'),
  (30879, 66, 10, 2, 'And he had in his hand a little book open: and he set his right foot upon the sea, and his left foot on the earth,', '0~2532~ 2~2192~ 3~1722~ 4~846~ 5~5495~ 8~974~ 9~455~: 10~2532~ 12~5087~ 13~846~ 14~1188~ 15~4228~ 16~1909~ 18~2281~, 19~1161~ [20] 21~2176~ [22] 23~1909~ 25~1093~,'),
  (10288, 13, 1, 28, 'The sons of Abraham; Isaac, and Ishmael.', '&para; 1~01121~ 3~085~; 4~03327~, 6~03458~.'),
  (8743, 11, 1, 18, 'And now, behold, Adonijah reigneth; and now, my lord the king, thou knowest it not:', '3~0138~ 4~04427~; 8~0113~ 10~04428~, 12~03045~ [13]'),
  (23687, 40, 16, 5, 'And when his disciples were come to the other side, they had forgotten to take bread.', '&para; 0~2532~ 2~846~ 3~3101~ 5~2064~ 6~1519~ 9~4008~, 12~1950~ 14~2983~ 15~740~.'),
  (6843, 7, 11, 7, 'And Jephthah said unto the elders of Gilead, Did not ye hate me, and expel me out of my father''s house? and why are ye come unto me now when ye are in distress?', '1~03316~ 2~0559~ 5~02205~ 7~01568~, 11~08130~ 14~01644~ 19~01~ 20~01004~? 25~0935~ 33~06887~?'),
  (9372, 11, 18, 23, 'Let them therefore give us two bullocks; and let them choose one bullock for themselves, and cut it in pieces, and lay it on wood, and put no fire under: and I will dress the other bullock, and lay it on wood, and put no fire under:', '3~05414~ 5~08147~ 6~06499~; 10~0977~ 11~0259~ 12~06499~ 19~05408~, 21~07760~ [22] 24~06086~, 26~07760~ 28~0784~ [29] 33~06213~ 35~0259~ 36~06499~, 38~05414~ [39] 41~06086~, 43~07760~ 45~0784~ [46]'),
  (12455, 16, 7, 26, 'The men of Bethlehem and Netophah, an hundred fourscore and eight.', '1~0582~ 3~01035~ 5~05199~, 7~03967~ 8~08084~ 10~08083~.'),
  (5184, 5, 9, 21, 'And I took your sin, the calf which ye had made, and burnt it with fire, and stamped it, and ground it very small, even until it was as small as dust: and I cast the dust thereof into the brook that descended out of the mount.', '2~03947~ 4~02403~, 6~05695~ 10~06213~, 12~08313~ 15~0784~, 17~03807~ [19] 20~02912~ [21] 23~03190~, [24] 29~01854~ 31~06083~: 34~07993~ 36~06083~ 40~05158~ 43~03381~ 46~02022~.'),
  (7304, 9, 3, 21, 'And the LORD appeared again in Shiloh: for the LORD revealed himself to Samuel in Shiloh by the word of the LORD.', '2~03068~ 3~07200~ 4~03254~ 6~07887~: 9~03068~ 10~01540~ 13~08050~ 15~07887~ 18~01697~ 21~03068~.'),
  (5868, 6, 1, 11, 'Pass through the host, and command the people, saying, Prepare you victuals; for within three days ye shall pass over this Jordan, to go in to possess the land, which the LORD your God giveth you to possess it.', '0~05674~ 1~07130~ 3~04264~, 5~06680~ 7~05971~, 8~0559~, 9~03559~ 11~06720~; 14~07969~ 15~03117~ 19~05674~ 21~03383~, 24~0935~ 26~03423~ 28~0776~, 31~03068~ 33~0430~ 34~05414~ 37~03423~'),
